HP:0002883.definition: Hyperventilation refers to an increased pulmonary ventilation rate that is faster than necessary for the exchange of gases. Hyperventilation can result from increased frequency of breathing, an increased tidal volume, or both, and leads to an excess intake of oxygen and the blowing off of carbon dioxide.

HP:0002884.name: Hepatoblastoma
HP:0002884.definition: A kind of neoplasm of the liver that originates from immature liver precursor cells and macroscopically is composed of tissue resembling fetal or mature liver cells or bile ducts.

HP:0002885.name: Medulloblastoma
HP:0002885.definition: A rapidly growing embryonic tumor arising in the posterior part of the cerebellar vermis and neuroepithelial roof of the fourth ventricle in children. More rarely, medulloblastoma arises in the cerebellum in adults.

HP:0002886.name: Vagal paraganglioma
HP:0002886.definition: A tumor that develops in the retrostyloid compartment of the parapharyngeal space, arising from an island of paraganglion tissue derived from the neural crest that is located on the vagus nerve.

HP:0002888.name: Ependymoma
HP:0002888.definition: The presence of an ependymoma of the central nervous system.

HP:0002890.name: Thyroid carcinoma
HP:0002890.definition: The presence of a carcinoma of the thyroid gland.

HP:0002891.name: Uterine leiomyosarcoma
HP:0002891.definition: The presence of a leiomyosarcoma of the uterus.

HP:0002893.name: Pituitary adenoma
HP:0002893.definition: A benign epithelial tumor derived from intrinsic cells of the adenohypophysis (anterior pituitary).

HP:0004267.name: Narrow small joints of the hand

HP:0004268.name: Osteoarthritis of the small joints of the hand

HP:0004269.name: Subluxation of the small joints of the hand
HP:0004269.definition: A partial dislocation of some or all of the small joints of the hand.

HP:0004276.name: Exostoses of hand bones
HP:0004276.definition: Abnormal formation of new bone on the surface of a bone of the hand.

HP:0004278.name: Synostosis involving bones of the hand
HP:0004278.definition: An abnormal union between bones or parts of bones of the hand.

HP:0004283.name: Narrow palm
HP:0004283.definition: For children from birth to 4 years of age, the palm width is more than 2 SD below the mean; for children from 4 to 16 years of age the palm width is below the 5th centile; or, the width of the palm appears disproportionately narrow for its length.

HP:0004290.name: Sclerosis of hand bones with transverse striations

HP:0004294.name: Subluxation of metacarpal phalangeal joints
HP:0004294.definition: A partial dislocation affecting some or all of the metacarpophalangeal joints.

HP:0004295.name: Abnormal gastric mucosa morphology
HP:0004295.definition: An abnormality of the gastric mucous membrane.

HP:0004297.name: Abnormality of the biliary system
HP:0004297.definition: An abnormality of the biliary system.

HP:0004298.name: Abnormality of the abdominal wall
HP:0004298.definition: The presence of any abnormality affecting the abdominal wall.

HP:0004299.name: Hernia of the abdominal wall
HP:0004299.definition: The presence of a hernia in the abdominal wall.

HP:0004303.name: Abnormal muscle fiber morphology
HP:0004303.definition: Any abnormality of the skeletal muscle cell. Muscle fibers are subdivided into two types. Type I fibers are fatigue-resistant and rich in oxidative enzymes (they stain light with the myosin ATPase reaction), and type II fibers are fast-contracting, fatigue-prone, and rich in glycolytic enzymes (these fibers stain darkly). Normal muscle tissue has a random distribution of type I and type II fibers.

HP:0004305.name: Involuntary movements
HP:0004305.definition: Involuntary contractions of muscle leading to involuntary movements of extremities, neck, trunk, or face.

HP:0004307.name: Abnormal anatomic location of the heart
HP:0004307.definition: Developmental defect characterized by an anomalous anatomic location of the heart.

HP:0004309.name: Ventricular preexcitation
HP:0004309.definition: An abnormality in which the cardiac ventricles depolarize too early as a result of an abnormality of cardiac conduction pathways such as an accessory pathway.

HP:0004313.name: Decreased circulating immunoglobulin concentration
HP:0004313.definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin in blood.

HP:0004315.name: Decreased circulating IgG concentration
HP:0004315.definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin G (IgG) in blood.

HP:0004320.name: Vaginal fistula
HP:0004320.definition: The presence of a fistula of the vagina.

HP:0004321.name: Bladder fistula
HP:0004321.definition: The presence of a fistula connecting the urinary bladder to another organ or the skin. The fistula can involve the bowel, the vagina, or rarely, the skin.

HP:0004322.name: Short stature
HP:0004322.definition: A height below that which is expected according to age and gender norms. Although there is no universally accepted definition of short stature, many refer to "short stature" as height more than 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender (or below the 3rd percentile for age and gender dependent norms).

HP:0004323.name: Abnormality of body weight
HP:0004323.definition: An abnormal increase or decrease of weight or an abnormal distribution of mass in the body.

HP:0004326.name: Cachexia
HP:0004326.definition: Severe weight loss, wasting of muscle, loss of appetite, and general debility related to a chronic disease.

HP:0004327.name: Abnormal vitreous humor morphology
HP:0004327.definition: Any structural anomaly of the vitreous body.

HP:0004328.name: Abnormal anterior eye segment morphology
HP:0004328.definition: An abnormality of the anterior segment of the eyeball (which comprises the structures in front of the vitreous humor: the cornea, iris, ciliary body, and lens).

HP:0004330.name: Increased skull ossification
HP:0004330.definition: An increase in the magnitude or amount of ossification of the skull.

HP:0004331.name: Decreased skull ossification
HP:0004331.definition: A reduction in the magnitude or amount of ossification of the skull.

HP:0004333.name: Bone-marrow foam cells
HP:0004333.definition: The presence of foam cells in the bone marrow, generally demonstrated by bone-marrow aspiration or biopsy. Foam cells have a vacuolated appearance due to the presence of complex lipid deposits, giving them a foamy or soap-suds appearance.

HP:0004334.name: Dermal atrophy
HP:0004334.definition: Partial or complete wasting (atrophy) of the skin.

HP:0004336.name: Myelin outfoldings
HP:0004336.definition: The presence of excessive redundant myelin in the peripheral nerve sheath.

HP:0004337.name: Abnormality of amino acid metabolism
HP:0004337.definition: Abnormality of an amino acid metabolic process.

HP:0004338.name: Abnormal circulating aromatic amino acid concentration
HP:0004338.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a aromatic amino acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0004339.name: Abnormal circulating sulfur amino acid concentration
HP:0004339.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a sulfur amino acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0004342.name: Abnormal galactosidase enyzme activity
HP:0004342.definition: Abnormality of galactoside metabolism. A galactoside is a glycoside (a sugar moiety bound to some other moiety) containing galactose.

HP:0004345.name: Ganglioside accumulation
HP:0004345.definition: Defects in the lysosomal glycosidases or specific co-activators, result in accumulation of the substrates, such as glycosphingolipids, including gangliosides in GM1 gangliosidosis (Tay-Sachs disease) and GM2 gangliosidosis (Sandhoff disease).

HP:0004347.name: Weakness of muscles of respiration
HP:0004347.definition: Reduced function of the muscles required to generate subatmospheric pressure in the thoracic cavity during breathing: the diaphragm, the external intercostal and the interchondral part of the internal intercostal muscles.

HP:0004348.name: Abnormality of bone mineral density
HP:0004348.definition: This term applies to all changes in bone mineral density which (depending on severity) can be seen on x-rays as a change in density and or structure of the bone. Changes may affect all bones of the organism, just certain bones or only parts of bones and include decreased mineralisation as may be seen in osteoporosis or increased mineralisation and or ossification as in osteopetrosis, exostoses or any kind of atopic calicfications of different origin and distribution. The overall amount of mineralization of the bone-organ can be measured as the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones, usually measured by densitometry of the lumbar spine or hip. The measurements are usually reported as g/cm3 or as a Z-score (the number of standard deviations above or below the mean for the patient's age and sex). Note that measurement with this method does not reflect local changes in other bones, and as such might not be correct with regard the hole bone-organ.

HP:0004349.name: Reduced bone mineral density
HP:0004349.definition: A reduction of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones.

HP:0004352.name: Abnormal circulating purine concentration
HP:0004352.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a purine in the blood circulation.

HP:0004353.name: Abnormal circulating pyrimidine concentration
HP:0004353.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a pyrimidine in the blood circulation.

HP:0004354.name: Abnormal circulating carboxylic acid concentration
HP:0004354.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0004357.name: Abnormal circulating leucine concentration
HP:0004357.definition: Any deviation from the normal circulation of leucine in the blood circulation.

HP:0004359.name: Abnormal circulating fatty-acid concentration
HP:0004359.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of a fatty acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0004360.name: Abnormality of acid-base homeostasis
HP:0004360.definition: An abnormality of the balance or maintenance of the balance of acids and bases in bodily fluids, resulting in an abnormal pH.

HP:0004361.name: Abnormal circulating leptin concentration
HP:0004361.definition: An abnormal concentration of leptin in the blood.

HP:0004362.name: Abnormal enteric ganglion morphology
HP:0004362.definition: An abnormality of the enteric nervous system, which comprises two types of ganglia, the myenteric (Auerbach's) and submucosal (Meissner's) plexuses. The enteric nervous system functions to control gut movement, fluid exchange between the gut and its lumen, and local blood flow.

HP:0004363.name: Abnormal circulating calcium concentration
HP:0004363.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of calcium in the blood circulation.

HP:0004364.name: Abnormal circulating nitrogen compound concentration
HP:0004364.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a nitrogen compound in the blood circulation.

HP:0004365.name: Abnormal circulating tryptophan concentration
HP:0004365.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of tryptophan in the blood circulation.

HP:0004368.name: Increased circulating purine concentration
HP:0004368.definition: Abnormally elevated concentration of a purine compound. Purine compounds are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.

HP:0004369.name: Decreased circulating purine concentration
HP:0004369.definition: Abnormally reduced concentration of a purine compound. Purine compounds are aromatic heterocyclic compounds containing a purine moiety, which is formed a pyrimidine-ring ring fused to an imidazole ring.

HP:0004372.name: Reduced consciousness
HP:0004372.definition: Abnormally diminished level of attention, responsiveness, or wakefulness.

HP:0004373.name: Focal dystonia
HP:0004373.definition: A type of dystonia that is localized to a specific part of the body.

HP:0004374.name: Hemiplegia/hemiparesis
HP:0004374.definition: Loss of strength in the arm, leg, and sometimes face on one side of the body. Hemiplegia refers to a severe or complete loss of strength, whereas hemiparesis refers to a relatively mild loss of strength.

HP:0004375.name: Neoplasm of the nervous system
HP:0004375.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the nervous system.

HP:0004376.name: Neuroblastic tumor
HP:0004376.definition: A family of tumors arising in the embryonal remnants of the sympathetic nervous system, which includes neuroblastoma, ganglioneuroblastoma, and ganglioneuroma.

HP:0004377.name: Hematological neoplasm
HP:0004377.definition: Neoplasms located in the blood and blood-forming tissue (the bone marrow and lymphatic tissue).

HP:0004379.name: Abnormality of alkaline phosphatase level
HP:0004379.definition: An abnormality of alkaline phosphatase level.

HP:0004380.name: Aortic valve calcification
HP:0004380.definition: Deposition of calcium salts in the aortic valve.

HP:0004381.name: Supravalvular aortic stenosis
HP:0004381.definition: A pathological narrowing in the region above the aortic valve associated with restricted left ventricular outflow.

HP:0004382.name: Mitral valve calcification
HP:0004382.definition: Abnormal calcification of the mitral valve.

HP:0004383.name: Hypoplastic left heart
HP:0004383.definition: Underdevelopment of the left side of the heart. May include atresia of the aortic or mitral orifice and hypoplasia of the ascending aorta.

HP:0004384.name: Type I truncus arteriosus
HP:0004384.definition: Truncus arteriosus (single great artery leaving the base of the heart, giving rise to the coronary, pulmonary, and systemic arteries) with a short pulmonary trunk arises from the truncus arteriosus, giving rise to both pulmonary arteries.

HP:0004386.name: Gastrointestinal inflammation
HP:0004386.definition: Inflammation of the alimentary part of the gastrointestinal system.

HP:0004387.name: Enterocolitis
HP:0004387.definition: An inflammation of the colon and small intestine. However, most conditions are either categorized as Enteritis (inflammation of the small intestine) or Colitis (inflammation of the large intestine).

HP:0004388.name: Microcolon
HP:0004388.definition: A colon of abnormally small caliber.

HP:0004389.name: Intestinal pseudo-obstruction
HP:0004389.definition: A functional rather than mechanical obstruction of the intestines, associated with manifestations that resemble those caused by an intestinal obstruction, including distension, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, constipation or diarrhea, in an individual in whom a mechanical blockage has been excluded.

HP:0004390.name: Hamartomatous polyposis
HP:0004390.definition: Polyp-like protrusions which are histologically hamartomas. These can occur throughout the gastrointestinal tract. Hamartomatous polyps are composed of the normal cellular elements of the gastrointestinal tract, but have a markedly distorted architecture.

HP:0004392.name: Prune belly
HP:0004392.definition: A kind of congenital defect of the anterior abdominal wall in which the intestines are evident through the thin, lax, and protruding abdominal wall in affected infants.

HP:0004395.name: Malnutrition
HP:0004395.definition: A deficiency in the intake of energy and nutrients.

HP:0004397.name: Ectopic anus
HP:0004397.definition: Abnormal displacement or malposition of the anus.

HP:0004398.name: Peptic ulcer
HP:0004398.definition: The term peptic ulcer refers to acid peptic injury of the digestive tract, resulting in mucosal break reaching the submucosa. Peptic ulcers are usually located in the stomach or proximal duodenum, but they can also be found in the esophagus or Meckel's diverticulum. Infection with Helicobacter pylori and the use of non steroidal antiinflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) or aspirin are the main risk factors of both gastric and duodenal peptic ulcers.

HP:0004401.name: Meconium ileus
HP:0004401.definition: Obstruction of the intestine due to abnormally thick meconium.

HP:0004408.name: Abnormality of the sense of smell
HP:0004408.definition: An anomaly in the ability to perceive and distinguish scents (odors).

HP:0004409.name: Hyposmia
HP:0004409.definition: A decreased sensitivity to odorants (that is, a decreased ability to perceive odors).

HP:0004411.name: Deviated nasal septum
HP:0004411.definition: Positioning of the nasal septum to the right or left in contrast to the normal midline position of the nasal septum.

HP:0004414.name: Abnormality of the pulmonary artery
HP:0004414.definition: An abnormality of the pulmonary artery.

HP:0004415.name: Pulmonary artery stenosis
HP:0004415.definition: An abnormal narrowing or constriction of the pulmonary artery, in the main pulmonary artery and/or in the left or right pulmonary artery branches.

HP:0004417.name: Intermittent claudication
HP:0004417.definition: Intermittent claudication is a symptom of peripheral arterial occlusive disease. After having walked over a distance which is individually characteristic, the patients experience pain or cramps in the calves, feet or thighs which typically subsides on standing still.

HP:0004418.name: Thrombophlebitis
HP:0004418.definition: Inflammation of a vein associated with venous thrombosis (blood clot formation within the vein).

HP:0004419.name: Recurrent thrombophlebitis
HP:0004419.definition: Repeated episodes of inflammation of a vein associated with venous thrombosis (blood clot formation within the vein).

HP:0004420.name: Arterial thrombosis
HP:0004420.definition: The formation of a blood clot inside an artery.

HP:0004421.name: Elevated systolic blood pressure
HP:0004421.definition: Abnormal increase in systolic blood pressure.

HP:0004422.name: Biparietal narrowing
HP:0004422.definition: A narrowing of the biparietal diameter (i.e., of the transverse distance between the protuberances of the two parietal bones of the skull).

HP:0004423.name: Cranium bifidum occultum
HP:0004423.definition: Cranium bifidum occultum, also known as Catlin mark, is a congenital midline skull defect presenting as an enlarged posterior fontanelle in the upper posterior angle of the parietal bone close to the intersection of the sagittal and lambdoid sutures. Cranium bifidum occultum occurs due to a defect in intramembranous ossification, a process through which skull bones (frontal, parietal, squamous temporal and occipital bones superior to the mendosal suture) ossify under a vascularized membrane toward the midline to cover the brain. Unlike cranium bifidum cysticum, cranium bifidum occultum does not have herniation of intracranial contents. As the skull grows, the midline cranium bifidum occultum defect is separated into bilateral enlarged parietal foramina (EPF) by a midline osseous bridge.

HP:0004426.name: Abnormal cheek morphology
HP:0004426.definition: An abnormality of the cheek- one of two bilateral soft tissue facial structures in the region of the face inferior to the eyes and between the nose and the ear. "Buccal" means relating to the cheek. The cheek is part of the midface

HP:0004428.name: Elfin facies
HP:0004428.definition: This is a description previously used to describe a facial form characterized by a short, upturned nose, wide mouth, widely spaced eyes, and full cheeks. Because of the imprecision in this definition it is preferable to describe these features precisely. This term is retained because it was often used in the past, but it should not be used for new annotations.

HP:0004429.name: Recurrent viral infections
HP:0004429.definition: Increased susceptibility to viral infections, as manifested by recurrent episodes of viral infection.

HP:0004430.name: Severe combined immunodeficiency
HP:0004430.definition: A type of primary immune deficiency that is characterized by a more severe defect in both the T- and B-lymphocyte systems.

HP:0004431.name: Reduced circulating complement concentration
HP:0004431.definition: An immunodeficiency defined by the absent or suboptimal functioning of one of the complement system proteins.

HP:0004432.name: Agammaglobulinemia
HP:0004432.definition: A lasting absence of total IgG and total IgA and total IgM in the blood circulation, whereby at most trace quantities can be measured.

HP:0004433.name: Secretory IgA deficiency
HP:0004433.definition: Deficiency of secretory IgA (polymers of 2-4 IgA monomers are linked by two additional chains) and is the primary antibody response at the mucosal level, where it forms immune complexes with pathogens and allergens.

HP:0004434.name: Decreased circulating complement C8 concentration
HP:0004434.definition: Concentration of the complement component C8 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0004437.name: Cranial hyperostosis
HP:0004437.definition: Excessive growth of the bones of cranium, i.e., of the skull.

HP:0004438.name: Hyperostosis frontalis interna
HP:0004438.definition: Bony overgrowth of the internal (endosteal) surface of the frontal bone.

HP:0004439.name: Craniofacial dysostosis
HP:0004439.definition: A characteristic appearance resulting from defective ossification of craniofacial bones.

HP:0004440.name: Coronal craniosynostosis
HP:0004440.definition: Premature closure of the coronal suture of skull.

HP:0004442.name: Sagittal craniosynostosis
HP:0004442.definition: A kind of craniosynostosis affecting the sagittal suture.

HP:0004443.name: Lambdoidal craniosynostosis
HP:0004443.definition: A kind of craniosynostosis affecting the lambdoidal suture.

HP:0004444.name: Spherocytosis
HP:0004444.definition: The presence of erythrocytes that are sphere-shaped.

HP:0004445.name: Elliptocytosis
HP:0004445.definition: The presence of elliptical, cigar-shaped erythrocytes on peripheral blood smear.

HP:0004446.name: Stomatocytosis
HP:0004446.definition: The presence of erythrocytes with a mouth-shaped (stoma) area of central pallor on peripheral blood smear.

HP:0004447.name: Poikilocytosis
HP:0004447.definition: The presence of abnormally shaped erythrocytes.

HP:0004448.name: Fulminant hepatic failure
HP:0004448.definition: Hepatic failure refers to the inability of the liver to perform its normal synthetic and metabolic functions, which can result in coagulopathy and alteration in the mental status of a previously healthy individual. Hepatic failure is defined as fulminant if there is onset of encephalopathy within 4 weeks of the onset of symptoms in a patient with a previously healthy liver.

HP:0004450.name: Preauricular skin furrow
HP:0004450.definition: A groove of the skin immediately in front of the ear.

HP:0004451.name: Postauricular skin tag
HP:0004451.definition: A rudimentary tag of ear tissue often containing a core of cartilage and located just in back of the auricle (outer part of the ear).

HP:0004452.name: Abnormality of the middle ear ossicles
HP:0004452.definition: An abnormality of the middle-ear ossicles (three small bones called malleus, incus, and stapes) that are contained within the middle ear and serve to transmit sounds from the air to the fluid-filled labyrinth (cochlea).

HP:0004453.name: Overfolding of the superior helices
HP:0004453.definition: A condition in which the superior portion of the helix is folded over to a greater degree than normal.

HP:0004458.name: Dilatated internal auditory canal
HP:0004458.definition: The presence of a dilated inner part of external acoustic meatus.

HP:0004459.name: Exostosis of the external auditory canal
HP:0004459.definition: A benign bony growth projecting outward from a bone surface within the external auditory canal.

HP:0004461.name: Congenital earlobe sinuses
HP:0004461.definition: Pits in the earlobes at the location where ears are typically pierced for earrings.

HP:0004463.name: Absent brainstem auditory responses
HP:0004463.definition: Lack of measurable response to stimulation of auditory evoked potentials.

HP:0004464.name: Postauricular pit
HP:0004464.definition: Benign congenital lesion of the postauricular soft tissue consisting of a blind-ending narrow tube or pit.

HP:0004466.name: Delayed brainstem auditory evoked response conduction time
HP:0004466.definition: An abnormal increase (delay) in the conduction time of the brainstem auditory-evoked response.

HP:0004467.name: Preauricular pit
HP:0004467.definition: Small indentation anterior to the insertion of the ear.

HP:0004468.name: Anomalous tracheal cartilage
HP:0004468.definition: An abnormality of the C-shaped rings of hyaline cartilage, normally 16 to 20 in number, that occupy the anterior two-thirds of the circumference of the trachea (the posterior portion of the ring is completed by fibrous and smooth muscle tissue).

HP:0004470.name: Atretic occipital cephalocele
HP:0004470.definition: A congenital defect in the occipital region of the skull, covered by skin of the scalp and containing meninges or remnants of glial or neural tissues.

HP:0004471.name: Aplasia cutis congenita over the scalp vertex
HP:0004471.definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the scalp vertex, often just lateral to the midline.

HP:0004474.name: Persistent open anterior fontanelle
HP:0004474.definition: The anterior fontanelle generally ossifies by around the 18th month of life. A persistent open anterior fontanelle is diagnosed if closure is delayed beyond this age.

HP:0004476.name: Aplasia cutis congenita over parietal area
HP:0004476.definition: A developmental defect resulting in the congenital absence of skin on the scalp in the parietal area.

HP:0004481.name: Progressive macrocephaly
HP:0004481.definition: The progressive development of an abnormally large skull.

HP:0004482.name: Relative macrocephaly
HP:0004482.definition: A relatively mild degree of macrocephaly in which the head circumference is not above two standard deviations from the mean, but appears dysproportionately large when other factors such as body stature are taken into account.

HP:0004484.name: Craniofacial asymmetry
HP:0004484.definition: Asymmetry of the bones of the skull and the face.

HP:0004485.name: Cessation of head growth
HP:0004485.definition: Stagnation of head growth seen as flattening of the head circumference curve.

HP:0004487.name: Acrobrachycephaly
HP:0004487.definition: An abnormality of head shape characterized by the presence of a short, wide head as well as a pointy or conical form of the top of the head owing to premature closure of the coronal and lambdoid sutures.

HP:0004488.name: Macrocephaly at birth
HP:0004488.definition: The presence of an abnormally large skull with onset at birth.

HP:0004491.name: Large posterior fontanelle
HP:0004491.definition: An enlargement of the posterior fontanelle relative to age-dependent norms.

HP:0004492.name: Widely patent fontanelles and sutures
HP:0004492.definition: An abnormally increased width of the cranial fontanelles and sutures.

HP:0004493.name: Craniofacial hyperostosis
HP:0004493.definition: Excessive growth of the craniofacial bones.

HP:0004499.name: Chronic rhinitis due to narrow nasal airway

HP:0004502.name: Bilateral choanal atresia
HP:0004502.definition: Bilateral absence (atresia) of the posterior nasal aperture (choana).

HP:0004510.name: Pancreatic islet-cell hyperplasia
HP:0004510.definition: Hyperplasia of the islets of Langerhans, i.e., of the regions of the pancreas that contain its endocrine cells.

HP:0004523.name: Long eyebrows
HP:0004523.definition: Increased length of the hairs of the eyebrows.

HP:0004524.name: Temporal hypotrichosis
HP:0004524.definition: Reduced or lacking hair growth in the temporal region (i.e., around the temples on the side of the skull).

HP:0004527.name: Large clumps of pigment irregularly distributed along hair shaft

HP:0004528.name: Generalized hypotrichosis
HP:0004528.definition: Reduced or lacking hair growth in a generalized distribution.

HP:0004532.name: Sacral hypertrichosis
HP:0004532.definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the sacral region.

HP:0004535.name: Anterior cervical hypertrichosis
HP:0004535.definition: Anterior cervical hypertrichosis (ACH) or 'hairy throat' refers to the presence of a tuft of terminal hair on the anterior neck, just above the laryngeal prominence.

HP:0004540.name: Congenital, generalized hypertrichosis
HP:0004540.definition: A confluent, generalized overgrowth of silvery blonde to gray lanugo hair at birth.

HP:0004558.name: Cervical platyspondyly
HP:0004558.definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates affecting the cervical spine.

HP:0004563.name: Increased spinal bone density
HP:0004563.definition: Increased bone density affecting the bones of the spine (vertebral column).

HP:0004566.name: Pear-shaped vertebrae
HP:0004566.definition: Bulbous appearance of the anterior vertebral bodies, such that the vertebral bodies have the greatest vertical height anteriorly as well as bulbous anterior superior-inferior contours.

HP:0004568.name: Beaking of vertebral bodies
HP:0004568.definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the vertebral bodies.

HP:0004570.name: Increased vertebral height
HP:0004570.definition: Increased top to bottom height of vertebral bodies.

HP:0004573.name: Anterior wedging of T11
HP:0004573.definition: An abnormality of the shape of the thoracic vertebra T11 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front).

HP:0004576.name: Sclerotic vertebral endplates
HP:0004576.definition: Sclerosis (increased density) affecting vertebral end plates.

HP:0004580.name: Anterior scalloping of vertebral bodies
HP:0004580.definition: An excessive concavity of the anterior surface of one or more vertebral bodies.

HP:0004586.name: Biconcave vertebral bodies
HP:0004586.definition: Exaggerated concavity of the anterior or posterior surface of the vertebral body, i.e., the upper and lower vertebral endplates are hollowed inward.

HP:0004590.name: Hypoplastic sacrum
HP:0004590.definition: A developmental defect characterized by undergrowth of the sacrum, which is a large, triangular bone at the base of the spine that forms by the fusing of the sacral vertebrae (S1-S5).

HP:0004592.name: Thoracic platyspondyly
HP:0004592.definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates affecting the thoracic spine.

HP:0004594.name: Hump-shaped mound of bone in central and posterior portions of vertebral endplate

HP:0004598.name: Supernumerary vertebral ossification centers
HP:0004598.definition: Three ossification sites are present in typical vertebral bodies (C3-L5): a single ossification center in the vertebral body, and one each in the two neural arches. This term applies if there are additional vertebral ossification centers present during the development and maturation of the spine.

HP:0004599.name: Absent or minimally ossified vertebral bodies

HP:0004601.name: Spina bifida occulta at L5
HP:0004601.definition: The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of the vertebra L5 with intact overlying skin.

HP:0004602.name: Cervical C2/C3 vertebral fusion
HP:0004602.definition: Fusion of cervical vertebrae at C2 and C3, caused by a failure in the normal segmentation or division of the cervical vertebrae during the early weeks of fetal development, leading to a short neck with a low hairline at the back of the head, and restricted mobility of the upper spine.

HP:0004605.name: Absent vertebral body mineralization
HP:0004605.definition: A lack of bone mineralization of the vertebral bodies.

HP:0004606.name: Unossified vertebral bodies
HP:0004606.definition: A lack of ossification of the vertebral bodies.

HP:0004607.name: Anterior beaking of lower thoracic vertebrae
HP:0004607.definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of the lower thoracic vertebral bodies.

HP:0004608.name: Anteriorly placed odontoid process
HP:0004608.definition: Anterior mislocalization of the dens of the axis.

HP:0004610.name: Lumbar spinal canal stenosis
HP:0004610.definition: An abnormal narrowing of the lumbar spinal canal.

HP:0004614.name: Spina bifida occulta at S1
HP:0004614.definition: The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of S1 with intact overlying skin.

HP:0004616.name: Cleft vertebral arch
HP:0004616.definition: A discontinuity of the vertebral arch, i.e., of the posterior part of a vertebra.

HP:0004617.name: Butterfly vertebral arch
HP:0004617.definition: Butterfly vertebrae have a cleft through the body of the vertebrae and a funnel shape at the ends.

HP:0004621.name: Enlarged vertebral pedicles
HP:0004621.definition: Increased size of the vertebral pedicle.

HP:0004622.name: Progressive intervertebral space narrowing
HP:0004622.definition: A progressive form of decreased height of the intervertebral disk.

HP:0004625.name: Biconvex vertebral bodies
HP:0004625.definition: Presence of abnormal convexity of the upper and lower end plates of the vertebrae, i.e., an exaggerated bulging out of the upper and lower vertebral end plates.

HP:0004630.name: Anterior beaking of thoracic vertebrae
HP:0004630.definition: Anterior tongue-like protrusions of thoracic vertebral bodies.

HP:0004631.name: Decreased cervical spine flexion due to contractures of posterior cervical muscles

HP:0004632.name: Cervical segmentation defect
HP:0004632.definition: An abnormality related to a defect of vertebral separation of cervical vertebrae during development.

HP:0004633.name: Lower thoracic kyphosis
HP:0004633.definition: Over curvature of the lower thoracic region, leading to a round back or if sever to a hump.

HP:0004635.name: Cervical C5/C6 vertebrae fusion
HP:0004635.definition: Fusion of the C5 and C6 cervical vertebrae.

HP:0004639.name: Elevated amniotic fluid alpha-fetoprotein
HP:0004639.definition: An elevation of alpha-feto protein measured in the amniotic fluid.

HP:0004660.name: Hypoplasia of facial musculature
HP:0004660.definition: Underdevelopment of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

HP:0004661.name: Frontalis muscle weakness
HP:0004661.definition: Reduced strength of the frontalis muscle (which is located on the forehead).

HP:0004664.name: Facial midline hemangioma
HP:0004664.definition: Hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, occurring in the midline region of the face.

HP:0004673.name: Decreased facial expression
HP:0004673.definition: A reduced degree of voluntary and involuntary facial movements involved in responded to others or expressing emotions.

HP:0004681.name: Deep longitudinal plantar crease
HP:0004681.definition: Narrow, paramedian longitudinal depressions in the plantar skin of the forefoot.

HP:0004684.name: Talipes valgus
HP:0004684.definition: Outward turning of the heel, resulting in clubfoot with the person walking on the inner part of the foot.

HP:0004686.name: Short third metatarsal
HP:0004686.definition: Underdevelopment of the Third metatarsal bone leading to a short (hypoplastic) third metatarsal bone.

HP:0004690.name: Thickened Achilles tendon
HP:0004690.definition: An abnormal thickening of the Achilles tendon.

HP:0004691.name: 2-3 toe syndactyly
HP:0004691.definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes two and three.

HP:0004692.name: 4-5 toe syndactyly
HP:0004692.definition: Syndactyly with fusion of toes four and five.

HP:0004695.name: Calcaneal epiphyseal stippling
HP:0004695.definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the calcaneus.

HP:0004699.name: Osteoporotic metatarsal
HP:0004699.definition: Decrease in mass and density of the metatarsal bones.

HP:0004712.name: Renal malrotation
HP:0004712.definition: An abnormality of the normal developmental rotation of the kidney leading to an abnormal orientation of the kidney.

HP:0004713.name: Reversible renal failure
HP:0004713.definition: Acute renal failure with resolution of manifestations.

HP:0004717.name: Axial malrotation of the kidney
HP:0004717.definition: An abnormality of the normal developmental rotation of the kidney leading to an abnormal axial orientation of the kidney.

HP:0004719.name: Hyperechogenic kidneys
HP:0004719.definition: An increase in amplitude of waves returned in ultrasonography of the kidney, which is generally displayed as increased brightness of the signal.

HP:0004722.name: Thickened glomerular basement membrane
HP:0004722.definition: Prominent glomerular basement membrane (GBM), reflecting an increase in thickness (subjective estimate) of the basal lamina of the glomerulus of the kidney.

HP:0004724.name: Calcium nephrolithiasis
HP:0004724.definition: The presence of calcium-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

HP:0004727.name: Impaired renal concentrating ability
HP:0004727.definition: A defect in the ability to concentrate the urine.

HP:0004729.name: Acute tubulointerstitial nephritis
HP:0004729.definition: Acute inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules.

HP:0004732.name: Impaired renal uric acid clearance
HP:0004732.definition: A reduction in the ability of the kidneys to remove uric acid from the serum.

HP:0004734.name: Renal cortical microcysts
HP:0004734.definition: Cysts of microscopic size confined to the cortex of the kidney.

HP:0004736.name: Crossed fused renal ectopia
HP:0004736.definition: A developmental anomaly in which the kidneys are fused and localized on the same side of the midline. This anomaly is thought to result from disruption of the normal embryologic migration of the kidneys.

HP:0004737.name: Global glomerulosclerosis
HP:0004737.definition: Obliteration of the glomerular capillary lumen by increased collagenous matrix, with or without hyalinosis or foam cells. Sclerosis involves 100% of the glomerular tuft. Relative to other patent glomeruli in the sample, glomerular size is preserved, or increased/decreased by no more than 50%.

HP:0004742.name: Abnormal renal collecting system morphology
HP:0004742.definition: An abnormality of the renal collecting system.

HP:0004743.name: Chronic tubulointerstitial nephritis
HP:0004743.definition: Chronic inflammation of the kidney affecting the interstitium of the kidneys surrounding the tubules.

HP:0004746.name: Glomerular subendothelial electron-dense deposits
HP:0004746.definition: Electron dense deposits at the glomerular basement membrane,

HP:0004749.name: Atrial flutter
HP:0004749.definition: A type of atrial arrhythmia characterized by atrial rates of between 240 and 400 beats per minute and some degree of atrioventricular node conduction block. Typically, the ventricular rate is half the atrial rate. In the EKG; atrial flutter waves are observed as sawtooth-like atrial activity. Pathophysiologically, atrial flutter is a form of atrial reentry in which there is a premature electrical impulse creates a self-propagating circuit.

HP:0004751.name: Paroxysmal ventricular tachycardia
HP:0004751.definition: Episodes of ventricular tachycardia that have a sudden onset and ending.

HP:0004752.name: Congenital atrioventricular dissociation
HP:0004752.definition: A form of atrioventricular (AV) dissociation (i.e., the atria and the ventricles are under the control of two separate pacemakers) with congenital onset.

HP:0004754.name: Permanent atrial fibrillation
HP:0004754.definition: Atrial fibrillation (AF) that cannot be successfully terminated by cardioversion, and longstanding (more than 1 year) AF, where cardioversion is not indicated or has not been attempted, is termed permanent.

HP:0004755.name: Supraventricular tachycardia
HP:0004755.definition: Supraventricular tachycardia (SVT) is an abnormally increased heart rate (over 100 beats per minute at rest) with origin above the level of the ventricles.

HP:0004756.name: Ventricular tachycardia
HP:0004756.definition: A tachycardia originating in the ventricles characterized by rapid heart rate (over 100 beats per minute) and broad QRS complexes (over 120 ms).

HP:0004757.name: Paroxysmal atrial fibrillation
HP:0004757.definition: Episodes of atrial fibrillation that typically last for several hours up to one day and terminate spontaneously.

HP:0004758.name: Effort-induced polymorphic ventricular tachycardia
HP:0004758.definition: Polymorphic ventricular arrhythmias of varying morphologythat do not exist under resting conditions but appear only upon physical exercise or catecholamine administration.

HP:0004759.name: obsolete Nodular calcific aortic valve disease

HP:0004762.name: Hypoplasia of right ventricle
HP:0004762.definition: Underdevelopment or reduced size of the heart right ventricle, often due to a reduced number of cells.

HP:0004763.name: Paroxysmal supraventricular tachycardia
HP:0004763.definition: An episodic form of supraventricular tachycardia with abrupt onset and termination.

HP:0004764.name: Myxomatous mitral valve degeneration
HP:0004764.definition: Myxomatous mitral valve is defined as the presence of excess leaflet tissue and leaflet thickening greater than 5 mm, resulting in a prolapse greater than 2 mm into the left atrium on parasternal long axis view.

HP:0004768.name: Sparse anterior scalp hair
HP:0004768.definition: Decreased number of head hairs per unit area on the anterior region of the scalp.

HP:0004780.name: Elbow hypertrichosis
HP:0004780.definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the elbow region.

HP:0004783.name: Duodenal polyposis
HP:0004783.definition: Presence of multiple polyps in the duodenum.

HP:0004784.name: Juvenile gastrointestinal polyposis
HP:0004784.definition: The presence of multiple juvenile polyps in the stomach and intestine. The term juvenile polyps refer to a special histopathology and not the age of onset as the polyp might be diagnosed at all ages. The juvenile polyp has a spherical appearance and is microscopically characterized by overgrowth of an oedematous lamina propria with inflammatory cells and cystic glands. Juvenile polyps are a specific type of hamartomatous polyps.

HP:0004785.name: Malrotation of colon
HP:0004785.definition: An anatomical anomaly that results from an abnormal rotation of the gut as it returns to the abdominal cavity during embryogenesis.

HP:0004787.name: Fulminant hepatitis
HP:0004787.definition: Acute hepatitis complicated by acute liver failure with hepatic encephalopathy occurring less than 8 weeks after the onset of jaundice.

HP:0004788.name: Intestinal lymphedema
HP:0004788.definition: Fluid retention and edema in the intestine caused by a compromised lymphatic system.

HP:0004791.name: Esophageal ulceration
HP:0004791.definition: Defect in the epithelium of the esophagus, essentially an open sore in the lining of the esophagus.

HP:0004792.name: Rectoperineal fistula
HP:0004792.definition: The presence of a fistula between the perineum and the rectum.

HP:0004794.name: Malrotation of small bowel
HP:0004794.definition: A deviation from the normal rotation of the midgut during embryologic development with mislocalization of the small bowel.

HP:0004795.name: Hamartomatous stomach polyps
HP:0004795.definition: Polyp-like protrusions which are histologically hamartomas located in the stomach.

HP:0004797.name: Multiple small bowel atresias
HP:0004797.definition: The presence of multiple areas of atresia affecting the small intestine.

HP:0004798.name: Recurrent infection of the gastrointestinal tract
HP:0004798.definition: Recurrent infection of the gastrointestinal tract.

HP:0004802.name: Episodic hemolytic anemia
HP:0004802.definition: A form of hemolytic anemia that occurs in repeated episodes.

HP:0004804.name: Congenital hemolytic anemia
HP:0004804.definition: A form of hemolytic anemia with congenital onset.

HP:0004808.name: Acute myeloid leukemia
HP:0004808.definition: A form of leukemia characterized by overproduction of an early myeloid cell.

HP:0004809.name: Neonatal alloimmune thrombocytopenia
HP:0004809.definition: Low platelet count associated with maternal platelet-specific alloantibodies.

HP:0004810.name: Congenital hypoplastic anemia
HP:0004810.definition: A type of hypoplastic anemia with congenital onset.

HP:0004812.name: B Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia
HP:0004812.definition: A type of ALL characterized by elevated levels of B-cell lymphoblasts in the bone marrow and the blood.

HP:0004813.name: Post-transfusion thrombocytopenia
HP:0004813.definition: Sudden onset of thrombocytopenia (reduced platelet count) within 5-10 days of the transfusion of blood products. The clinical presentation is post-transfusion purpura (PTP), wigth severe thrmbocytopenia, epistaxis, and hemorrhages.

HP:0004814.name: Fava bean-induced hemolytic anemia
HP:0004814.definition: A kind of hemolytic anemia that is induced by the ingestion of fava beans.

HP:0004817.name: Drug-sensitive hemolytic anemia
HP:0004817.definition: A form of hemolytic anemia that is triggered by ingestion of certain drugs.

HP:0004819.name: Normocytic hypoplastic anemia
HP:0004819.definition: A type of hypoplastic anemia in which the erythrocytes have a normal cell volume (the mean corpuscular volume is within normal limits).

HP:0004820.name: Acute myelomonocytic leukemia
HP:0004820.definition: An acute leukemia characterized by the proliferation of both neutrophil and monocyte precursors.

HP:0004821.name: Hypersegmentation of neutrophil nuclei
HP:0004821.definition: An excessive division of the lobes of the nucleus of a neutrophil.

HP:0004823.name: Anisopoikilocytosis
HP:0004823.definition: A type of poikilocytosis characterized by the presence in the blood of erythrocytes of varying sizes and abnormal shapes.

HP:0004825.name: Increased hemoglobin oxygen affinity
HP:0004825.definition: An abnormal increase in the binding affinity of hemoglobin for oxygen.

HP:0004826.name: Folate-unresponsive megaloblastic anemia
HP:0004826.definition: A type of megaloblastic anemia that does not improve upon administration of folate. Since vitamin B12 acts by promoting recycling of folate, administration of vitamin B12 also does not improve this type of anemia.

HP:0004828.name: Refractory anemia with ringed sideroblasts
HP:0004828.definition: A type of myelodysplastic syndrome characterized by less than 5% myeloblasts in the bone marrow, but with 15% or greater red cell precursors in the marrow being abnormal iron-stuffed cells called ringed sideroblasts.

HP:0004831.name: Recurrent thromboembolism
HP:0004831.definition: Repeated episodes of obstruction of blood flow due to an embolus, i.e., blood clot that has traveled from its point of origin within the blood stream.

HP:0004835.name: Microspherocytosis
HP:0004835.definition: The presence of erythrocytes that are sphere-shaped and reduced in size.

HP:0004836.name: Acute promyelocytic leukemia
HP:0004836.definition: A type of acute myeloid leukemia in which abnormal promyelocytes predominate.

HP:0004839.name: Pyropoikilocytosis
HP:0004839.definition: A form of severe hemolytic anemia characterized by erythrocyte morphology reminiscent of that seen in patients after a thermal burn.

HP:0004840.name: Hypochromic microcytic anemia
HP:0004840.definition: A type of anemia characterized by an abnormally low concentration of hemoglobin in the erythrocytes and lower than normal size of the erythrocytes.

HP:0004841.name: Reduced factor XII activity
HP:0004841.definition: Decreased activity of coagulation factor XII. Factor XII (fXII) is part of the intrinsic coagulation pathway and binds to exposed collagen at site of vessel wall injury, activated by high-MW kininogen and kallikrein, thereby initiating the coagulation cascade.

HP:0004844.name: Coombs-positive hemolytic anemia
HP:0004844.definition: A type of hemolytic anemia in which the Coombs test is positive.

HP:0004845.name: Acute monocytic leukemia
HP:0004845.definition: The accumulation of transformed primitive hematopoietic blast cells, which lose their ability of normal differentiation and proliferation.

HP:0004846.name: Prolonged bleeding after surgery
HP:0004846.definition: Bleeding that persists longer than the normal time following a surgical procedure.

HP:0004848.name: Ph-positive acute lymphoblastic leukemia
HP:0004848.definition: A subset of acute lymphoblastic leukemia that results from a reciprocal translocation between the ABL-1 oncogene and a breakpoint cluster region (BCR), resulting in a fusion gene, BCR-ABL, that encodes an oncogenic protein with constitutively active tyrosine kinase activity.

HP:0004850.name: Recurrent deep vein thrombosis
HP:0004850.definition: Repeated episodes of the formation of a blot clot in a deep vein.

HP:0004851.name: Folate-responsive megaloblastic anemia
HP:0004851.definition: A type of megaloblastic anemia (i.e., anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal) that improves upon the administration of folate.

HP:0004852.name: Reduced leukocyte alkaline phosphatase
HP:0004852.definition: Decreased alkaline phosphatase measured within leukocytes.

HP:0004854.name: Intermittent thrombocytopenia
HP:0004854.definition: Reduced platelet count that occurs sporadically, i.e., it comes and goes.

HP:0004855.name: Reduced protein S activity
HP:0004855.definition: An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of vitamin K-dependent protein S. Protein S is a cofactor of protein C.

HP:0004856.name: Normochromic microcytic anemia
HP:0004856.definition: A type of anemia characterized by an normal concentration of hemoglobin in the erythrocytes and lower than normal size of the erythrocytes.

HP:0004857.name: Hyperchromic macrocytic anemia
HP:0004857.definition: A type of anemia characterized by abnormally large erythrocytes with abnormally high amounts of hemoglobin.

HP:0004859.name: Amegakaryocytic thrombocytopenia
HP:0004859.definition: Thrombocytopenia related to lack of or severe reduction in the count of megakaryocytes.

HP:0004860.name: Thiamine-responsive megaloblastic anemia
HP:0004860.definition: A type of megaloblastic anemia (i.e., anemia characterized by the presence of erythroblasts that are larger than normal) that improves upon the administration of thiamine.

HP:0004864.name: Elevated bone marrow ring sideroblast count
HP:0004864.definition: Count of ring sideroblasts in the bone marrow above the upper limit of normal. Ring sideroblasts are nucleated erythroblasts with a pathologic accumulation of iron granules in the mitochondrial matrix. They can be detected by Prussian blue staining as blue perinuclear aggregates in bone marrow aspirate erythroblasts.

HP:0004866.name: Impaired ADP-induced platelet aggregation
HP:0004866.definition: Abnormal platelet response to ADP as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of ADP.

HP:0004870.name: Chronic hemolytic anemia
HP:0004870.definition: An chronic form of hemolytic anemia.

HP:0004871.name: Perineal fistula
HP:0004871.definition: The presence of a fistula between the bowel and the perineum.

HP:0004872.name: Incisional hernia
HP:0004872.definition: An abdominal hernia that occurs at a site of weakness in the abdominal wall resulting from an incompletely-healed surgical wound.

HP:0004876.name: Spontaneous neonatal pneumothorax
HP:0004876.definition: Pneumothorax occurring neonatally without traumatic injury to the chest or lung.

HP:0004878.name: Intercostal muscle weakness
HP:0004878.definition: Lack of strength of the intercostal muscles, i.e., of the muscle groups running along the ribs that create and move the chest wall.

HP:0004880.name: Respiratory infections in early life
HP:0004880.definition: Increased susceptibility to respiratory infections in early life, as manifested by recurrent episodes of respiratory infections.

HP:0004887.name: Respiratory failure requiring assisted ventilation
HP:0004887.definition: A state of respiratory distress that requires a life saving intervention in the form of gaining airway access and instituting positive pressure ventilation.

HP:0004889.name: Intermittent episodes of respiratory insufficiency due to muscle weakness

HP:0004890.name: Elevated pulmonary artery pressure
HP:0004890.definition: An abnormally elevated blood pressure in the circulation of the pulmonary artery.

HP:0004891.name: Recurrent infections due to aspiration
HP:0004891.definition: Increased susceptibility to infections due to aspiration, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infections due to aspiration.

HP:0004897.name: Stress/infection-induced lactic acidosis
HP:0004897.definition: A form of lactic acidemia that occurs in relation to stress or infection.

HP:0004898.name: Persistent lactic acidosis
HP:0004898.definition: A continuous form of lactic acidemia.

HP:0004900.name: Severe lactic acidosis
HP:0004900.definition: A severe form of lactic acidemia.

HP:0004901.name: Exercise-induced lactic acidemia
HP:0004901.definition: A form of lactic acidemia that occurs following exercise or exertion.

HP:0004902.name: Congenital lactic acidosis
HP:0004902.definition: A form of lactic acidemia with congenital onset.

HP:0004904.name: Maturity-onset diabetes of the young
HP:0004904.definition: The term Maturity-onset diabetes of the young (MODY) was initially used for patients diagnosed with fasting hyperglycemia that could be treated without insulin for more than two years, where the initial diagnosis was made at a young age (under 25 years). Thus, MODY combines characteristics of type 1 diabetes (young age at diagnosis) and type 2 diabetes (less insulin dependence than type 1 diabetes). The term MODY is now most often used to refer to a group of monogenic diseases with these characteristics. Here, the term is used to describe hyperglycemia diagnosed at a young age with no or minor insulin dependency, no evidence of insulin resistance, and lack of evidence of autoimmune destruction of the beta cells.

HP:0004905.name: Reduced circulating vitamin A concentration
HP:0004905.definition: Concentration of vitamin A below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0004911.name: Episodic metabolic acidosis
HP:0004911.definition: Repeated transient episodes of metabolic acidosis, that is, of the buildup of acid or depletion of base due to accumulation of metabolic acids.

HP:0004913.name: Intermittent lactic acidemia
HP:0004913.definition: An intermittent (discontinuous) form of lactic acidemia.

HP:0004914.name: Recurrent infantile hypoglycemia
HP:0004914.definition: Recurrent episodes of decreased concentration of glucose in the blood occurring during the infantile period.

HP:0004918.name: Hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis
HP:0004918.definition: A form of metabolic acidosis with increased serum chloride levels.

HP:0004921.name: Abnormal magnesium concentration
HP:0004921.definition: An abnormality of magnesium ion homeostasis.

HP:0004923.name: Hyperphenylalaninemia
HP:0004923.definition: An increased concentration of L-phenylalanine in the blood.

HP:0004924.name: Abnormal oral glucose tolerance
HP:0004924.definition: An abnormal resistance to glucose, i.e., a reduction in the ability to maintain glucose levels in the blood stream within normal limits following oral administration of glucose.

HP:0004925.name: Chronic lactic acidosis
HP:0004925.definition: A chronic form of lactic acidemia.

HP:0004926.name: Orthostatic hypotension due to autonomic dysfunction

HP:0004927.name: Pulmonary artery dilatation
HP:0004927.definition: An abnormal widening of the diameter of the pulmonary artery.

HP:0004931.name: Arteriosclerosis of small cerebral arteries
HP:0004931.definition: Arteriosclerosis (increased thickness, increased stiffness, loss of elasticity) of the small arteries of the brain.

HP:0004933.name: Ascending aortic dissection
HP:0004933.definition: A separation of the layers within the wall of the ascending aorta. Tears in the intimal layer result in the propagation of dissection (proximally or distally) secondary to blood entering the intima-media space.

HP:0004935.name: Pulmonary artery atresia
HP:0004935.definition: A congenital anomaly with a narrowing or complete absence of the opening between the right ventricle and the pulmonary artery.

HP:0004936.name: Venous thrombosis
HP:0004936.definition: Formation of a blood clot (thrombus) inside a vein, causing the obstruction of blood flow.

HP:0004937.name: Pulmonary artery aneurysm
HP:0004937.definition: An aneurysm (severe localized balloon-like outward bulging) in the pulmonary artery.

HP:0004938.name: Tortuous cerebral arteries
HP:0004938.definition: Excessive bending, twisting, and winding of a cerebral artery.

HP:0004940.name: Generalized arterial calcification
HP:0004940.definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts, affecting arteries distributed throughout the body.

HP:0004941.name: Extrahepatic portal hypertension
HP:0004941.definition: Increased pressure in the pre-hepatic portal vein.

HP:0004942.name: Aortic aneurysm
HP:0004942.definition: Aortic dilatation refers to a dimension that is greater than the 95th percentile for the normal person age, sex and body size. In contrast, an aneurysm is defined as a localized dilation of the aorta that is more than 150 percent of predicted (ratio of observed to expected diameter 1.5 or more). Aneurysm should be distinguished from ectasia, which represents a diffuse dilation of the aorta less than 50 percent of normal aorta diameter.

HP:0004943.name: Accelerated atherosclerosis
HP:0004943.definition: Atherosclerosis which occurs in a person with certain risk factors (e.g., SLE, diabetes, smoking, hypertension, hypercholesterolaemia, family history of early heart disease) at an earlier age than would occur in another person without those risk factors.

HP:0004944.name: Dilatation of the cerebral artery
HP:0004944.definition: The presence of a localized dilatation or ballooning of a cerebral artery.

HP:0004945.name: Extracranial internal carotid artery dissection
HP:0004945.definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the extracranial portion of the internal carotid artery wall.

HP:0004947.name: Arteriovenous fistula
HP:0004947.definition: An abnormal connection between an artery and vein.

HP:0004948.name: Vascular tortuosity
HP:0004948.definition: Abnormal twisting of arteries or veins.

HP:0004950.name: Peripheral arterial stenosis
HP:0004950.definition: Narrowing of peripheral arteries with reduction of blood flow to the limbs. This feature may be quantified as an ankle-brachial index of less than 0.9, and may be manifested clinically as claudication.

HP:0004952.name: Pulmonary arteriovenous fistulas
HP:0004952.definition: A rare vascular anomaly with a direct communication between pulmonary artery and pulmonary vein without an intervening capillary bed.

HP:0004954.name: obsolete Dilatation of the descending aorta

HP:0004955.name: Generalized arterial tortuosity
HP:0004955.definition: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of arteries affecting most or all arteries.

HP:0004959.name: Descending thoracic aorta aneurysm
HP:0004959.definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the descending thoracic aorta.

HP:0004960.name: Absent pulmonary artery
HP:0004960.definition: A congenital defect with aplasia (absence) of one of the right or left pulmonary artery.

HP:0004961.name: Pulmonary artery sling
HP:0004961.definition: An anomalous origin of the left pulmonary artery, such that it arises from the posterior aspect of the right pulmonary artery and passes between the trachea and esophagus to reach the left hilum.

HP:0004962.name: Thoracic aorta calcification
HP:0004962.definition: An accumulation of calcium and phosphate in arteries with mineral deposits in the intimal or medial layer of the vessel wall in the thoracic aorta.

HP:0004963.name: Calcification of the aorta
HP:0004963.definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the aorta.

HP:0004964.name: Pulmonary arterial medial hypertrophy
HP:0004964.definition: Increase in mass of the tunica media of the arteries in the pulmonary circulation.

HP:0004966.name: Medial calcification of large arteries
HP:0004966.definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of large (conduit) arteries.

HP:0004968.name: Recurrent cerebral hemorrhage
HP:0004968.definition: Recurrent bleeding into the parenchyma of the brain.

HP:0004969.name: Peripheral pulmonary artery stenosis
HP:0004969.definition: Stenosis of a peripheral branch of the pulmonary artery.

HP:0004970.name: Ascending tubular aorta aneurysm
HP:0004970.definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the tubular part of the ascending aorta.

HP:0004972.name: Elevated mean arterial pressure
HP:0004972.definition: An abnormal increase in the average blood pressure in an individual during a single cardiac cycle.

HP:0004974.name: Coarctation of abdominal aorta
HP:0004974.definition: Coarctation of the aorta is a narrowing or constriction of a segment of the abdominal aorta.

HP:0004975.name: Erlenmeyer flask deformity of the femurs

HP:0004977.name: Bilateral radial aplasia
HP:0004977.definition: Missing radius bone on both sides associated with congenital failure of development.

HP:0004979.name: Metaphyseal sclerosis
HP:0004979.definition: Abnormally increased density of metaphyseal bone.

HP:0004980.name: Metaphyseal rarefaction
HP:0004980.definition: Reduction in density of metaphyseal bony tissue.

HP:0004987.name: Mesomelic leg shortening
HP:0004987.definition: Shortening of the middle parts of the leg in relation to the upper and terminal segments.

HP:0004991.name: Rhizomelic arm shortening
HP:0004991.definition: Disproportionate shortening of the proximal segment of the arm (i.e. the humerus).

HP:0004993.name: Slender long bones with narrow diaphyses
HP:0004993.definition: Reduced diameter of a long bone with a more pronounced reduction of the diameter of the diaphysis of the long bones.

HP:0004997.name: Multicentric ossification of proximal humeral epiphyses

HP:0005003.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the capital femoral epiphysis
HP:0005003.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

HP:0005004.name: Flattened proximal radial epiphyses
HP:0005004.definition: An abnormally flat form of the proximal epiphysis of the radius.

HP:0005005.name: Femoral bowing present at birth, straightening with time
HP:0005005.definition: Congenital onset bending or abnormal curvature of the femur that normalizes with age.

HP:0005009.name: Dumbbell-shaped humerus
HP:0005009.definition: The humerus is shortened and displays flaring (widening) of the metaphyses.

HP:0005010.name: Osteomyelitis leading to amputation due to slow healing fractures

HP:0005011.name: Mesomelic arm shortening
HP:0005011.definition: Shortening of the middle parts of the arm in relation to the upper and terminal segments.

HP:0005013.name: Dysplastic distal radial epiphyses
HP:0005013.definition: Abnormally developed (dysplastic) distal epiphysis of the radius.

HP:0005019.name: Diaphyseal undertubulation
HP:0005019.definition: Tubulation refers to the size and shape of tubular bones. In children and adolescents, the modeling process regulates normal bone growth. Final shaft (tube) diameter depends on appositional bone growth and the equilibrium between periosteal and endosteal bone resorption and formation. Undertubulation refers to a broad, widened form of the shafts (diaphyses) of long bones.

HP:0005025.name: Hypoplastic distal humeri
HP:0005025.definition: Underdevelopment of the distal portion of the humerus.

HP:0005033.name: Distal ulnar hypoplasia
HP:0005033.definition: Underdevelopment of the distal portion of the ulna.

HP:0005035.name: Shortening of all phalanges of the toes
HP:0005035.definition: Developmental hypoplasia (shortening) of all phalanges of the foot.

HP:0005036.name: Unilateral ulnar hypoplasia
HP:0005036.definition: Underdevelopment of the ulna on only one side.

HP:0005037.name: Proximal radio-ulnar synostosis
HP:0005037.definition: An abnormal osseous union (fusion) between the proximal portions of the radius and the ulna.

HP:0005039.name: Multiple long-bone exostoses
HP:0005039.definition: Multiple exostoses originating in long bones.

HP:0005041.name: Irregular capital femoral epiphysis
HP:0005041.definition: Irregular surface of the normally relatively smooth capital femoral epiphysis.

HP:0005043.name: Proximal humeral metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0005043.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the metaphysis at the proximal end of the humerus (at the shoulder).

HP:0005045.name: Diaphyseal cortical sclerosis
HP:0005045.definition: An elevation in bone density of the cortex of one or more diaphyses. Sclerosis is normally detected on a radiograph as an area of increased opacity.

HP:0005050.name: Anterolateral radial head dislocation
HP:0005050.definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an anterolateral direction.

HP:0005054.name: Metaphyseal spurs
HP:0005054.definition: Bony outgrowths that extend laterally from the margin of the metaphysis.

HP:0005066.name: Cone-shaped epiphyses fused within their metaphyses

HP:0005067.name: Proximal fibular overgrowth
HP:0005067.definition: Overgrowth of the proximal part of the fibula.

HP:0005070.name: Proximal radial head dislocation
HP:0005070.definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an proximal direction.

HP:0005072.name: Wrist hypermobility
HP:0005072.definition: The ability of the wrist joints to move beyond their normal range of motion.

HP:0005084.name: Anterior radial head dislocation
HP:0005084.definition: A dislocation of the head of the radius from its socket in the elbow joint in an anterior direction.

HP:0005085.name: Limited knee flexion/extension
HP:0005085.definition: A limited ability of the knee joint to perform extension and flexion.

HP:0005089.name: Abnormal metaphyseal trabeculation
HP:0005089.definition: An abnormality of the pattern of trabecula (small interconnecting rods of bone) in a metaphyseal region of bone.

HP:0005090.name: Lateral femoral bowing
HP:0005090.definition: A lateral bending or abnormal curvature of the femur.

HP:0005092.name: Streaky metaphyseal sclerosis
HP:0005092.definition: The presence of streaks (bands) of abnormally increased density of metaphyseal bone.

HP:0005093.name: Absent proximal radial epiphyses
HP:0005093.definition: Absence of the proximal radial epiphysis.

HP:0005096.name: Distal femoral bowing
HP:0005096.definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of the distal portion of the femur.

HP:0005100.name: Premature birth following premature rupture of fetal membranes

HP:0005101.name: High-frequency hearing impairment
HP:0005101.definition: A type of hearing impairment affecting primarily the higher frequencies of sound (3,000 to 6,000 Hz).

HP:0005102.name: Cochlear degeneration
HP:0005102.definition: Deterioration or loss of the tissues of the cochlea.

HP:0005103.name: Calcification of the auricular cartilage
HP:0005103.definition: Ossification affecting the external ear cartilage.

HP:0005106.name: Abnormality of the vertebral endplates
HP:0005106.definition: Any abnormality of the vertebral end plates, which are the top and bottom portions of the vertebral bodies that interface with the vertebral disks.

HP:0005107.name: Abnormal sacrum morphology
HP:0005107.definition: An abnormality of the sacral bone.

HP:0005108.name: Abnormal intervertebral disk morphology
HP:0005108.definition: Any structural abnormality of the intervertebral disk.

HP:0005109.name: Abnormality of the Achilles tendon
HP:0005109.definition: An abnormality of the Achilles tendon.

HP:0005110.name: Atrial fibrillation
HP:0005110.definition: An atrial arrhythmia characterized by disorganized atrial activity without discrete P waves on the surface EKG, but instead by an undulating baseline or more sharply circumscribed atrial deflections of varying amplitude an frequency ranging from 350 to 600 per minute.

HP:0005111.name: obsolete Dilatation of the ascending aorta

HP:0005112.name: Abdominal aortic aneurysm
HP:0005112.definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the abdominal aorta.

HP:0005113.name: Aortic arch aneurysm
HP:0005113.definition: An abnormal localized widening (dilatation) of the aortic arch.

HP:0005114.name: obsolete Abnormalities of the peripheral arteries

HP:0005115.name: Supraventricular arrhythmia
HP:0005115.definition: A type of arrhythmia that originates above the ventricles, whereby the electrical impulse propagates down the normal His Purkinje system similar to normal sinus rhythm.

HP:0005116.name: Arterial tortuosity
HP:0005116.definition: Abnormal tortuous (i.e., twisted) form of arteries.

HP:0005117.name: Elevated diastolic blood pressure
HP:0005117.definition: Abnormal increase in diastolic blood pressure.

HP:0005120.name: Abnormal cardiac atrium morphology
HP:0005120.definition: Any structural abnormality of a cardiac atrium.

HP:0005121.name: Posterior scalloping of vertebral bodies
HP:0005121.definition: An excessive concavity of the posterior surface of one or more vertebral bodies.

HP:0005132.name: Pericardial constriction
HP:0005132.definition: Compression of the heart caused by rigid, thickened, or fused pericardial membranes.

HP:0005133.name: Right ventricular dilatation
HP:0005133.definition: Enlargement of the chamber of the right ventricle, which can be defined echocardiographically as a right ventricular to left ventricular ratio greater than 1:1.

HP:0005134.name: Absence of the pulmonary valve
HP:0005134.definition: Refers to the specific combination of defects with a severely dysplastic pulmonary valve and massively dilated branch pulmonary arteries.

HP:0005135.name: Abnormal T-wave
HP:0005135.definition: An abnormality of the T wave on the electrocardiogram, which mainly represents the repolarization of the ventricles.

HP:0005136.name: Mitral annular calcification
HP:0005136.definition: Mitral annular calcification (MAC) results from progressive calcium deposition along and beneath the mitral valve annulus.

HP:0005143.name: Anomalous origin of right pulmonary artery from ascending aorta
HP:0005143.definition: The right pulmonary artery originates from the ascending aorta in the presence of a pulmonary valve and main pulmonary artery.

HP:0005144.name: Ventricular septal hypertrophy
HP:0005144.definition: The dividing wall between left and right sides of the heart, thickens and bulges into the left ventricle.

HP:0005145.name: Coronary artery stenosis
HP:0005145.definition: Abnormal narrowing of the coronary artery.

HP:0005146.name: Cardiac valve calcification
HP:0005146.definition: Abnormal calcification of a cardiac valve.

HP:0005148.name: Pulmonary valve defects
HP:0005148.definition: Any defect in the valve connecting the heart and the pulmonary artery.

HP:0005150.name: Abnormal atrioventricular conduction
HP:0005150.definition: An impairment of the electrical continuity between the atria and ventricles.

HP:0005151.name: Preductal coarctation of the aorta
HP:0005151.definition: Narrowing or constriction of the aorta localized proximal to the ductus arteriosus, i.e., to the preductal region of aortic arch.

HP:0005152.name: Histiocytoid cardiomyopathy
HP:0005152.definition: A type of cardiomyopathy characterized pathologically by hamartomatous lesions of cardiac Purkinje cells.

HP:0005155.name: Ventricular escape rhythm
HP:0005155.definition: A ventricular escape rhythm occurs whenever higher-lever pacemakers in AV junction or sinus node fail to control ventricular activation. Escape rate is usually 20-40 bpm, often associated with broad QRS complexes (at least 120 ms).

HP:0005157.name: Concentric hypertrophic cardiomyopathy
HP:0005157.definition: Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with an symmetrical and concentric pattern of hypertrophy.

HP:0005160.name: Total anomalous pulmonary venous return
HP:0005160.definition: Total anomalous pulmonary venous return refers to a congenital malformation in which all four pulmonary veins do not connect normally to the left atrium, but instead drain abnormally to the right atrium.

HP:0005162.name: Abnormal left ventricular function
HP:0005162.definition: Inability of the left ventricle to perform its normal physiologic function. Failure is either due to an inability to contract the left ventricle or the inability to relax completely and fill with blood during diastole.

HP:0005164.name: Dysplastic pulmonary valve
HP:0005164.definition: A congenital malformation of the pulmonary valve characterized by leaflet deformation.

HP:0005165.name: Shortened PR interval
HP:0005165.definition: Reduced time for the PR interval (beginning of the P wave to the beginning of the QRS complex). In adults, normal values are 120 to 200 ms long.

HP:0005168.name: Elevated right atrial pressure
HP:0005168.definition: An abnormal increase in magnitude of the pressure in the right atrium.

HP:0005170.name: Complete heart block with broad QRS complexes
HP:0005170.definition: A type of third degree heart block in which the escape rhythm arises at a relatively low part of the conduction system (below the atrioventricular node), which produces a wide QRS complex.

HP:0005172.name: Left posterior fascicular block
HP:0005172.definition: Conduction block in the posterior division of the left bundle branch of the bundle of His.

HP:0005174.name: Membranous subvalvular aortic stenosis
HP:0005174.definition: Subvalvular stenosis is caused by a diaphragm-like membrane. The stenosis is clinically manifested like any other form of aortic stenosis but is often associated with some aortic insufficiency.

HP:0005176.name: Dysplastic aortic valve
HP:0005176.definition: A congenital malformation of the aortic valve characterized by leaflet deformation.

HP:0005177.name: Premature arteriosclerosis
HP:0005177.definition: Arteriosclerosis occurring at an age that is younger than usual.

HP:0005178.name: Complete heart block with narrow QRS complexes
HP:0005178.definition: A type of third degree heart block in which the escape rhythm arises at the atrioventricular node, which produces a narrow QRS complex.

HP:0005180.name: Tricuspid regurgitation
HP:0005180.definition: Failure of the tricuspid valve to close sufficiently upon contraction of the right ventricle, causing blood to regurgitate (flow backward) into the right atrium.

HP:0005181.name: Premature coronary artery atherosclerosis
HP:0005181.definition: Reduction of the diameter of the coronary arteries as the result of an accumulation of atheromatous plaques within the walls of the coronary arteries before age of 45.

HP:0005182.name: Bicuspid pulmonary valve
HP:0005182.definition: The presence of a bicuspid pulmonary valve.

HP:0005183.name: Pericardial lymphangiectasia
HP:0005183.definition: An abnormal dilatation of lymph vessels in the pericardium.

HP:0005184.name: Prolonged QTc interval
HP:0005184.definition: A longer than normal interval (corrected for heart rate) between the Q and T waves in the heart's cycle. Prolonged QTc can cause premature action potentials during late phase depolarizations thereby leading to ventricular arrhythmias and ventricular fibrillations.

HP:0005185.name: Global systolic dysfunction
HP:0005185.definition: A reduced ejection fraction and an enlarged left ventricle chamber, the latter by an increased resistance to filling with increased filling pressures. Systolic dysfunction is clinically associated with left ventricular failure in the presence of marked cardiomegaly.

HP:0005186.name: Synovial lining hyperplasia
HP:0005186.definition: Synovial hyperplasia involves proliferation of mesenchymal stromal/stem cells and leads to synovial thickening, which can be observed radiographically.

HP:0005194.name: Flattened metatarsal heads
HP:0005194.definition: Abnormally flat shape of the heads of the metatarsal bones.

HP:0005197.name: Generalized morning stiffness
HP:0005197.definition: A sensation of stiffness in the joints that occurs following waking up in the morning.

HP:0005198.name: Stiff interphalangeal joints
HP:0005198.definition: Interphalangeal joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in the interphalangeal joints when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity.

HP:0005199.name: Aplasia of the abdominal wall musculature

HP:0005202.name: Helicobacter pylori infection
HP:0005202.definition: A recurrent infection of the GI tract with helicobacter pylori, a gram-negative, microaerophilic bacterium usually found in the stomach.

HP:0005203.name: Spontaneous esophageal perforation
HP:0005203.definition: The occurrence of the full-thickness tear (perforation) of the wall of the esophagus.

HP:0005206.name: Pancreatic pseudocyst
HP:0005206.definition: Cyst-like space not lined by epithelium and contained within the pancreas. Pancreatic pseudocysts are often associated with pancreatitis.

HP:0005208.name: Secretory diarrhea
HP:0005208.definition: Watery voluminous diarrhea resulting from an imbalance between ion and water secretion and absorption.

HP:0005209.name: Intrahepatic bile duct cysts
HP:0005209.definition: The presence of cyst of the intrahepatic bile duct.

HP:0005212.name: Anal mucosal leukoplakia
HP:0005212.definition: Leukoplakia is a precancerous dermatosis of mucous membranes analogous Leukoplakia is basically a chronic inflammatory hypertrophy in which anaplasia and malignant dyskeratosis may develop and subsequently advance to an invasive squamous cell cancer. The clinical diagnosis of primary anal leukoplakia is indicated by single or multiple slightly raised,irregular, marginated, grayish-white keratinized' patches in the anal canal. Tissue biopsy is necessary for confirmation.

HP:0005213.name: Pancreatic calcification
HP:0005213.definition: The presence of abnormal calcium deposition lesions in the pancreas.

HP:0005214.name: Intestinal obstruction
HP:0005214.definition: Blockage or impairment of the normal flow of the contents of the intestine towards the anal canal.

HP:0005215.name: Frequent Giardia lamblia infestation
HP:0005215.definition: Increased susceptibility to Giardia lamblia infection of the intestine, as manifested by a medical history of multiple episodes of Giardia lamblia intestinal infection.

HP:0005216.name: Impaired mastication
HP:0005216.definition: An abnormal reduction in the ability to masticate (chew), i.e., in the ability to crush and ground food in preparation for swallowing.

HP:0005217.name: Abdominal organ duplication
HP:0005217.definition: A congenital malformation characterized by the development of an additional organ or organ-like structure, i.e., an extra copy of the organ normally located in the abdomen.

HP:0005218.name: Anoperineal fistula
HP:0005218.definition: The presence of a fistula (abnormal tunnel) between the anal canal and the perineum.

HP:0005219.name: Absence of intrinsic factor
HP:0005219.definition: Absence of gastric intrinsic factor, which is normally produced by the parietal cells of the stomach, and is required for the absorption of vitamin B12.

HP:0005222.name: Bowel diverticulosis
HP:0005222.definition: The presence of multiple diverticula of the intestine.

HP:0005224.name: Rectal abscess
HP:0005224.definition: A collection of pus in the area of the rectum.

HP:0005225.name: Intestinal edema
HP:0005225.definition: Accumulation of cell free, noninflammatony fluid within the wall of the intestinal tract producing uniform thickening of the mucosal folds.

HP:0005227.name: Adenomatous colonic polyposis
