It is a useful feature for clinical diagnosis because it appears to be very rare in syndromes other than Pallister-Hall-Syndrome and is also rare as an isolated malformation.

HP:0010565.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the Epiglottis
HP:0010565.definition: This term applies if the Epiglottis is absent or hypoplastic.

HP:0010566.name: Hamartoma
HP:0010566.definition: A disordered proliferation of mature tissues that is native to the site of origin, e.g., exostoses, nevi and soft tissue hamartomas. Although most hamartomas are benign, some histologic subtypes, e.g., neuromuscular hamartoma, may proliferate aggressively such as mesenchymal cystic hamartoma, Sclerosing epithelial hamartoma, Sclerosing metanephric hamartoma.

HP:0010567.name: Y-shaped metatarsals
HP:0010567.definition: Y-shaped metatarsals are the result of a partial fusion of two metatarsal bones, with the two arms of the Y pointing in the distal direction. Y-shaped metatarsals may be seen in combination with polydactyly.

HP:0010568.name: Hamartoma of the eye
HP:0010568.definition: A hamartoma (disordered proliferation of mature tissues) which can originate from any tissue of the eye.

HP:0010569.name: Elevated circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
HP:0010569.definition: Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0010570.name: Low maternal circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
HP:0010570.definition: An abnormally low concentration of serum alpha-fetoprotein as compared to normal values for gestational-age.

HP:0010571.name: Elevated circulating phytanic acid concentration
HP:0010571.definition: An abnormal elevation of phytanic acid.

HP:0010574.name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the femoral head
HP:0010574.definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the femur.

HP:0010575.name: Dysplasia of the femoral head
HP:0010575.definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the femoral head.

HP:0010576.name: Intracranial cystic lesion
HP:0010576.definition: A cystic lesion originating within the brain.

HP:0010579.name: Cone-shaped epiphysis
HP:0010579.definition: Cone-shaped epiphyses (also known as coned epiphyses) are epiphyses that invaginate into cupped metaphyses. That is, the epiphysis has a cone-shaped distal extension resulting from increased growth of the central portion of the epiphysis relative to its periphery.

HP:0010582.name: Irregular epiphyses
HP:0010582.definition: An alteration of the normally smooth contour of the epiphysis leading to an irregular appearance.

HP:0010583.name: Ivory epiphyses
HP:0010583.definition: Sclerosis of the epiphyses, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

HP:0010585.name: Small epiphyses
HP:0010585.definition: Reduction in the size or volume of epiphyses.

HP:0010587.name: Triangular epiphysis
HP:0010587.definition: Longitudinal epiphyseal bracket or bracket epiphysis is an uncommon disorder of growth. Alternatively known as a delta phalanx, it is due to an anomalous secondary ossification center that extends longitudinally along the diaphysis. Although rare, longitudinal epiphyseal bracket most commonly manifests in the hands as clinodactyly and in the feet as hallux varus.

HP:0010588.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion
HP:0010588.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at each end of a long bone, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0010590.name: Abnormality of the distal femoral epiphysis
HP:0010590.definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the femur.

HP:0010591.name: Abnormality of the proximal tibial epiphysis
HP:0010591.definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the tibia.

HP:0010592.name: Abnormality of the distal tibial epiphysis

HP:0010594.name: Abnormality of the proximal fibular epiphysis
HP:0010594.definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the fibula.

HP:0010595.name: Abnormality of the distal fibular epiphysis
HP:0010595.definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the fibula.

HP:0010596.name: Abnormality of the proximal radial epiphysis
HP:0010596.definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the radius.

HP:0010597.name: Abnormality of the distal radial epiphysis
HP:0010597.definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the radius.

HP:0010598.name: Abnormality of the proximal humeral epiphysis
HP:0010598.definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the humerus.

HP:0010599.name: Abnormality of the distal humeral epiphysis
HP:0010599.definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the humerus.

HP:0010600.name: Abnormal distal ulnar epiphysis morphology
HP:0010600.definition: Any abnormality of the distal epiphysis of the ulna.

HP:0010601.name: Abnormal proximal ulnar epiphysis morphology
HP:0010601.definition: Any abnormality of the proximal epiphysis of the ulna.

HP:0010602.name: Type 2 muscle fiber predominance
HP:0010602.definition: An abnormal predominance of type II muscle fibers (in general, this feature can only be observed on muscle biopsy).

HP:0010603.name: Odontogenic keratocysts of the jaw
HP:0010603.definition: A benign uni- or multicystic, intraosseous tumor of odontogenic origin, with a characteristic lining of parakeratinized stratified squamous epithelium and potential for aggressive, infiltrative behavior.

HP:0010605.name: Chalazion
HP:0010605.definition: A chronic epithelioid cell granulomatous inflammation of the meibomian gland caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland. A chalazion or meibomian cyst appears as a painless tuberous swelling in the upper lid without loss of eyelashes.

HP:0010606.name: Hordeolum
HP:0010606.definition: An acute purulent infection of the sebaceous glands of Zeis at the base of the eyelashes, of the apocrine sweat glands of Moll or the meibomian sebacious glands often caused by staphylococcus infections. Hordeola can either occur as Hordeola externa affecting the sebaceous glands of Zeis or the apocrine sweat glands of Moll or as Hordeola interna affecting the meibomian sebacious glands. In contrast to chalazia, hordeola are extremely painful and can cause extreme local swelling.

HP:0010607.name: Hordeolum externum
HP:0010607.definition: Hordeola externa are acute purulent infections affecting the sebaceous glands of Zeis or the apocrine sweat glands of Moll, often caused by staphylococcus infections. In contrast to chalazia, hordeola are extremely painfull and can cause extreme local swelling.

HP:0010608.name: Hordeolum internum
HP:0010608.definition: Hordeola interna are acute purulent infections affecting the meibomian sebacious glands, often caused by staphylococcus infections. In contrast to chalazia (chronic epithelioid cell granulomatous inflammation of the meibomian gland caused by inflammation of a blocked meibomian gland), hordeola are extremely painfull and can cause extreme local swelling.

HP:0010609.name: Skin tags
HP:0010609.definition: Cutaneous skin tags also known as acrochorda or fibroepithelial polyps are small benign tumors that may either form secondarily over time primarily in areas where the skin forms creases, such as the neck, armpit or groin or may also be present at birth, in which case they usually occur in the periauricular region.

HP:0010612.name: Plantar pits
HP:0010612.definition: The presence of multiple pits (small, pinpoint-large indentations on the surface of the skin) located on the skin of sole of foot.

HP:0010614.name: Fibroma
HP:0010614.definition: Benign tumors that are composed of fibrous or connective tissue. They can grow in all organs, arising from mesenchyme tissue. The term "fibroblastic" or "fibromatous" is used to describe tumors of the fibrous connective tissue. When the term fibroma is used without modifier, it is usually considered benign, with the term fibrosarcoma reserved for malignant tumors.

HP:0010615.name: Angiofibromas
HP:0010615.definition: Angiofibroma consist of many often dilated vessels.

HP:0010616.name: Lung fibroma
HP:0010616.definition: The presence of a lung fibroma, a benign neoplasm that can present as a mass causing airway obstruction, cough, and hemoptysis, or present without symptoms as a solitary pulmonary nodule.

HP:0010618.name: Ovarian fibroma
HP:0010618.definition: The presence of a fibroma of the ovary.

HP:0010619.name: Fibroadenoma of the breast
HP:0010619.definition: A benign biphasic tumor of the breast with epithelial and stromal components.

HP:0010620.name: Malar prominence
HP:0010620.definition: Prominence of the malar process of the maxilla and infraorbital area appreciated in profile and from in front of the face.

HP:0010621.name: Cutaneous syndactyly of toes
HP:0010621.definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between adjacent foot digits that involves at least half of the proximodistal length of one of the two involved digits; or, a soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between two digits of the foot that does not meet the prior objective criteria.

HP:0010622.name: Neoplasm of the skeletal system
HP:0010622.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the skeleton.

HP:0010624.name: Aplastic/hypoplastic toenail
HP:0010624.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the toenail.

HP:0010625.name: Anterior pituitary dysgenesis
HP:0010625.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the anterior pituitary gland, also known as the adenohypophysis.

HP:0010626.name: Anterior pituitary agenesis
HP:0010626.definition: Absence of the anterior pituitary gland resulting from a developmental defect.

HP:0010627.name: Anterior pituitary hypoplasia
HP:0010627.definition: Underdevelopment of the anterior pituitary gland.

HP:0010628.name: Facial palsy
HP:0010628.definition: Facial nerve palsy is a dysfunction of cranial nerve VII (the facial nerve) that results in inability to control facial muscles on the affected side with weakness of the muscles of facial expression and eye closure. This can either be present in unilateral or bilateral form.

HP:0010629.name: Abnormal morphology of the cortex of the humerus
HP:0010629.definition: Any abnormality affecting the cortex of the humerus.

HP:0010630.name: Abnormal metatarsal epiphysis morphology
HP:0010630.definition: Any abnormality of a metatarsal bone epiphysis.

HP:0010631.name: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the feet
HP:0010631.definition: Any abnormality of the epiphyses of the feet.

HP:0010632.name: Total anosmia
HP:0010632.definition: Inability to detect any qualitative olfactory sensation.

HP:0010633.name: Partial anosmia
HP:0010633.definition: Inability to perceive certain odorants (implies that the sense of smell is maintained for other classes of odorants).

HP:0010634.name: Total hyposmia
HP:0010634.definition: Reduced ability to detect any qualitative olfactory sensation.

HP:0010635.name: Partial hyposmia
HP:0010635.definition: Reduced ability to perceive certain odorants (implies that the sense of smell is maintained for other classes of odorants).

HP:0010636.name: Schizencephaly
HP:0010636.definition: The presence of a cleft in the cerebral cortex unilaterally or bilaterally, usually located in the frontal area.

HP:0010637.name: Conjunctival amyloidosis
HP:0010637.definition: A form of amyloidosis that affects the conjunctiva.

HP:0010638.name: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of hepatic origin
HP:0010638.definition: An abnormally increased level of liver isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

HP:0010639.name: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of bone origin
HP:0010639.definition: An abnormally increased level of bone isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

HP:0010640.name: Abnormal nasal cavity morphology
HP:0010640.definition: Abnormality of the nasal cavity (the cavity includes and starts at the nares and reaches all the way through to the and includes the choanae, the posterior nasal apertures).

HP:0010641.name: Abnormality of the midnasal cavity
HP:0010641.definition: Abnormality of the midnasal cavity which includes the cavity between the nares and the choanae.

HP:0010643.name: Midnasal atresia
HP:0010643.definition: Absence or abnormal closure of the midnasal cavity.

HP:0010644.name: Midnasal stenosis
HP:0010644.definition: Abnormal narrowing (stenosis) of the midnasal cavity, i.e., of the middle nasal meatus, which in neonates can cause respiratory distress.

HP:0010645.name: Aplasia of the distal phalanges of the toes
HP:0010645.definition: Absence of the distal phalanges of the toes.

HP:0010646.name: Cervical spine instability
HP:0010646.definition: An abnormal lack of stability of the cervical spine.

HP:0010647.name: Abnormal elasticity of skin
HP:0010647.definition: Any abnormal increase or reduction in skin elasticity.

HP:0010648.name: Dermal translucency
HP:0010648.definition: An abnormally increased ability of the skin to permit light to pass through (translucency) such that subcutaneous structures such as veins display an increased degree of visibility.

HP:0010649.name: Flat nasal alae
HP:0010649.definition: An abnormal degree of flatness of the Ala of nose, which can be defined as a reduced nasal elevation index (lateral depth of the nose from the tip of the nose to the insertion of the nasal ala in the cheek x 100 divided by the side-to-side breadth of the nasal alae).

HP:0010650.name: Hypoplasia of the premaxilla
HP:0010650.definition: An abnormality of the premaxilla (the embryonic structure that forms the anterior part of the maxilla) causing it to appear relatively small in size compared to the other parts of the maxilla or other facial structures.

HP:0010651.name: Abnormal meningeal morphology
HP:0010651.definition: An abnormality of the Meninges, including any abnormality of the Dura mater, the Arachnoid mater, and the Pia mater.

HP:0010652.name: Abnormal dura mater morphology
HP:0010652.definition: An abnormality of the Dura mater.

HP:0010653.name: Abnormality of the falx cerebri
HP:0010653.definition: An abnormality of the Falx cerebri.

HP:0010654.name: Aplasia of the falx cerebri
HP:0010654.definition: A developmental defect characterized by aplasia of the Falx cerebri.

HP:0010655.name: Epiphyseal stippling
HP:0010655.definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in one or more epiphyses.

HP:0010656.name: Abnormal epiphyseal ossification
HP:0010656.definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of an epiphysis.

HP:0010657.name: Patchy reduction of bone mineral density
HP:0010657.definition: Patchy (irregular) reduction in bone density. This can take on many forms depending on severity and distribution as can be seen on x-rays.

HP:0010658.name: Patchy changes of bone mineral density
HP:0010658.definition: Patchy (irregular) changes in bone mineral density. These changes can either be patchy reduction or increase of mineral density as seen on x-rays. Depending on the pathomechanism and the underlying disease, these changes can either appear solely as reduction or increase or as a combination of both (patches of bone showing an increased density while others are affected by reduction of mineral density).

HP:0010659.name: Patchy variation in bone mineral density
HP:0010659.definition: Patchy (irregular) changes in bone mineral density with patches of bone showing an increased density side to side with patches that are affected by reduction of mineral density. This is sometimes referred to as a moth-eaten appearance on x-rays.

HP:0010660.name: Abnormal hand bone ossification
HP:0010660.definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any bone of the skeleton of hand.

HP:0010661.name: Absence of the third cerebral ventricle
HP:0010661.definition: A developmental defect characterized by the absence of the third ventricle.

HP:0010662.name: Abnormal diencephalon morphology
HP:0010662.definition: An abnormality of the Diencephalon, which together with the cerebrum (telencephalon) makes up the forebrain.

HP:0010664.name: Fusion of the left and right thalami
HP:0010664.definition: A developmental defect characterized by fusion of the left and right halves of the thalamus.

HP:0010665.name: Bilateral coxa valga
HP:0010665.definition: The presence of bilateral coxa valga.

HP:0010666.name: Hypoplasia of the anterior nasal spine
HP:0010666.definition: Underdevelopment of the anterior nasal spine of maxilla.

HP:0010667.name: Aplasia of the maxilla
HP:0010667.definition: A congenital defect characterized by absence of the Maxilla.

HP:0010668.name: Abnormal zygomatic bone morphology
HP:0010668.definition: An abnormality of the zygomatic bone.

HP:0010669.name: Hypoplasia of the zygomatic bone
HP:0010669.definition: Underdevelopment of the zygomatic bone. That is, a reduction in size of the zygomatic bone, including the zygomatic process of the temporal bone of the skull, which forms part of the zygomatic arch.

HP:0010672.name: Abnormality of the third metatarsal bone
HP:0010672.definition: An abnormality of the third metatarsal bone.

HP:0010674.name: Abnormal curvature of the vertebral column
HP:0010674.definition: The presence of an abnormal curvature of the vertebral column.

HP:0010675.name: Abnormal foot bone ossification
HP:0010675.definition: An abnormality of the formation and mineralization of any bone of the skeleton of foot.

HP:0003259.name: Elevated circulating creatinine concentration
HP:0003259.definition: An increased amount of creatinine in the blood.

HP:0003260.name: Hydroxyprolinemia
HP:0003260.definition: An increased concentration of hydroxyproline in the blood.

HP:0003261.name: Increased circulating IgA concentration
HP:0003261.definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin A in blood.

HP:0003262.name: Anti-smooth muscle antibody positivity
HP:0003262.definition: The presence in serum of antibodies against smooth muscle.

HP:0003265.name: Neonatal hyperbilirubinemia
HP:0003265.definition: A type of hyperbilirubinemia with neonatal onset.

HP:0003267.name: Reduced orotidine 5-prime phosphate decarboxylase level
HP:0003267.definition: An abnormal decrease in orotidine 5'-phosphate decarboxylase level.

HP:0003268.name: Argininuria
HP:0003268.definition: A increased concentration of arginine in the urine.

HP:0003271.name: Visceromegaly
HP:0003271.definition: Abnormal increased size of the viscera of the abdomen.

HP:0003272.name: Abnormal hip bone morphology
HP:0003272.definition: An abnormality of the hip bone.

HP:0003273.name: Hip contracture
HP:0003273.definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the hip joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

HP:0003275.name: Narrow pelvis bone
HP:0003275.definition: Reduced side to side width of the pelvis.

HP:0003276.name: Pelvic bone exostoses
HP:0003276.definition: A benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface of the pelvis. Exostoses are capped by cartilage, and arise from a bone that develops from cartilage.

HP:0003278.name: Square pelvis bone
HP:0003278.definition: An abnormally squared appearance of the bony pelvis, a normally rounded or basin-shaped structure.

HP:0003279.name: Coxa magna
HP:0003279.definition: Widening of the femoral head and neck.

HP:0003281.name: Increased circulating ferritin concentration
HP:0003281.definition: Increased concentration of ferritin in the blood circulation.

HP:0003282.name: Decreased circulating alkaline phosphatase activity
HP:0003282.definition: Concentration or activity of alkaline phosphatase outside the upper or lower limtis of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0003286.name: Cystathioninemia
HP:0003286.definition: An increased concentration of cystathionine in the blood.

HP:0003292.name: Decreased serum leptin
HP:0003292.definition: A decreased concentration of leptin in the blood.

HP:0003295.name: obsolete Impaired FSH and LH secretion

HP:0003296.name: Hyperthreoninuria
HP:0003296.definition: An increased concentration of threonine in the urine.

HP:0003297.name: Hyperlysinuria
HP:0003297.definition: An increased concentration of lysine in the urine.

HP:0003298.name: Spina bifida occulta
HP:0003298.definition: The closed form of spina bifida with incomplete closure of a vertebral body with intact overlying skin.

HP:0003300.name: Ovoid vertebral bodies
HP:0003300.definition: When viewed in lateral radiographs, vertebral bodies have a roughly rectangular configuration. This term applies if the vertebral body appears rounded or oval.

HP:0003301.name: Irregular vertebral endplates
HP:0003301.definition: An irregular surface of the vertebral end plates, which are normally relatively smooth.

HP:0003302.name: Spondylolisthesis
HP:0003302.definition: Complete bilateral fractures of the pars interarticularis resulting in the anterior slippage of the vertebra.

HP:0003304.name: Spondylolysis
HP:0003304.definition: Spondylolysis is an osseous defect of the pars interarticularis, thought to be a developmental or acquired stress fracture secondary to chronic low-grade trauma.

HP:0003305.name: Block vertebrae
HP:0003305.definition: Congenital synostosis between two or more adjacent vertebrae (partial or complete fusion of adjacent vertabral bodies).

HP:0003306.name: Spinal rigidity
HP:0003306.definition: Reduced ability to move the vertebral column with a resulting limitation of neck and trunk flexion.

HP:0003307.name: Hyperlordosis
HP:0003307.definition: Abnormally increased curvature (anterior concavity) of the lumbar or cervical spine.

HP:0003308.name: Cervical subluxation
HP:0003308.definition: A partial dislocation of one or more intervertebral joints in the cervical vertebral column.

HP:0003310.name: Abnormal odontoid process morphology
HP:0003310.definition: Abnormal structure of the odontoid process, which is a part of the C2 or axis vertebra and forms pivot of the structures forming the craniovertebral junction. The odontoid process is also known as the dens of the axis.

HP:0003311.name: Hypoplasia of the odontoid process
HP:0003311.definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the dens of the axis.

HP:0003312.name: Abnormal form of the vertebral bodies

HP:0003316.name: Butterfly vertebrae
HP:0003316.definition: A butterfly vertebra (sagittal cleft vertebra or anterior rachischisis) is a sagittal defect in the vertebral body caused by failure of fusion of the two lateral chondrification centers during embryogenesis. The name is based on the appearance of the two hemivertebrae emerging as butterfly wings from the central cleft on x-ray.

HP:0011957.name: Abnormal pectoral muscle morphology
HP:0011957.definition: An abnormality of the pectoral muscle, comprising the pectoralis major, a thick, fan-shaped muscle of the anterior chest and the pectoralis minor, a thin, triangular muscle situated underneath the pectoralis major.

HP:0011958.name: Retinal perforation
HP:0011958.definition: A small hole through the whole thickness of the retina.

HP:0011959.name: Unilateral hypoplasia of pectoralis major muscle
HP:0011959.definition: Hypoplasia (underdevelopment) of the pectoralis minor on only one side of the chest.

HP:0011960.name: Substantia nigra gliosis
HP:0011960.definition: Focal proliferation of glial cells in the substantia nigra.

HP:0011961.name: Non-obstructive azoospermia
HP:0011961.definition: Absence of any measurable level of sperm in his semen, resulting from a defect in the production of spermatozoa in the testes. This can be differentiated from obstructive azoospermia on the basis of testicular biopsy.

HP:0011962.name: Obstructive azoospermia
HP:0011962.definition: Absence of any measurable level of sperm in his semen, resulting from post-testicular obstruction or retrograde ejaculation. This can be differentiated from obstructive azoospermia on the basis of testicular biopsy.

HP:0011963.name: Pretesticular azoospermia
HP:0011963.definition: Absence of any measurable level of sperm in his semen, due to a hypothalamic or pituitary abnormality diagnosed with hypo-gonadotropic-hypogonadism. The diagnosis is made on the basis of low LH and FSH levels and low or normal testosterone levels.

HP:0011964.name: Intermittent painful muscle spasms
HP:0011964.definition: History of repeated intermittent involuntary muscle contractions that were painful.

HP:0011965.name: Abnormal circulating citrulline concentration
HP:0011965.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of citrulline in the blood circulation.

HP:0011966.name: Elevated plasma citrulline
HP:0011966.definition: An increased concentration of citrulline in the blood.

HP:0011967.name: Decreased circulating copper concentration
HP:0011967.definition: A reduced concentration of copper in the blood.

HP:0011968.name: Feeding difficulties
HP:0011968.definition: Impaired ability to eat related to problems gathering food and getting ready to suck, chew, or swallow it.

HP:0011969.name: Elevated circulating luteinizing hormone level
HP:0011969.definition: An elevated concentration of luteinizing hormone in the blood.

HP:0011970.name: Cerebral amyloid angiopathy
HP:0011970.definition: Amyloid deposition in the walls of leptomeningeal and cortical arteries, arterioles, and less often capillaries and veins of the central nervous system.

HP:0011971.name: Dermatographic urticaria
HP:0011971.definition: An exaggerated whealing tendency when the skin is stroked, that is, formation of red, itchy bumps and lines on the skin as a result of pressure on the skin (for instance, stroking the skin with a pen or tongue depressor).

HP:0011972.name: Hypoglycorrhachia
HP:0011972.definition: Abnormally low glucose concentration in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0011973.name: Paroxysmal lethargy
HP:0011973.definition: Repeated episodes of sudden-onset and transient lethargy.

HP:0011974.name: Myelofibrosis
HP:0011974.definition: Replacement of bone marrow by fibrous tissue.

HP:0011975.name: Aminoglycoside-induced hearing loss
HP:0011975.definition: Partial or complete loss of hearing following ingestion of aminoglycoside antibiotics.

HP:0011976.name: Elevated urinary catecholamine level
HP:0011976.definition: The concentration of a catecholamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0011977.name: Elevated urinary homovanillic acid
HP:0011977.definition: An increased concentration of homovanillic acid in the urine.

HP:0011978.name: Elevated urinary vanillylmandelic acid
HP:0011978.definition: An increased concentration of vanillylmandelic acid in the urine.

HP:0011979.name: Elevated urinary dopamine level
HP:0011979.definition: The concentration of dopamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0011980.name: Cholesterol gallstones
HP:0011980.definition: Gallstones composed primarily of cholesterol, usually about 2-3 cm in length with an oval form and a yellow or green/brown color.

HP:0011981.name: Pigment gallstones
HP:0011981.definition: Gallstones composed primarily of bilirubin and calcium salts (calcium bilirubinate) with a low cholesterol concentration.

HP:0011982.name: Black pigment gallstones
HP:0011982.definition: A type of pigment gallstone that is hard and black, containing calcium carbonate and calcium phosphates.

HP:0011983.name: Brown pigment gallstones
HP:0011983.definition: A type of pigment gallstone that is brown, containing calcium fatty acids. These stones are softer than black pigment gallstones.

HP:0011984.name: Atretic gallbladder
HP:0011984.definition: Failure of formation of the lumen of the gallbladder, often associated with gallbladder hypoplasia.

HP:0011985.name: Acholic stools
HP:0011985.definition: Clay colored stools lacking bile pigment.

HP:0011986.name: Ectopic ossification
HP:0011986.definition: Formation of abnormal, extraskeletal bony tissue, i.e., the presence of bone in soft tissue where bone normally does not exist.

HP:0011987.name: Ectopic ossification in muscle tissue
HP:0011987.definition: Formation of abnormal bony tissue within muscle tissue.

HP:0011988.name: Ectopic ossification in tendon tissue
HP:0011988.definition: Formation of abnormal bony tissue within tendon tissue.

HP:0011989.name: Ectopic ossification in ligament tissue
HP:0011989.definition: Formation of abnormal bony tissue within ligament tissue.

HP:0011991.name: Abnormal total neutrophil count
HP:0011991.definition: A deviation from the normal range of neutrophil cell counts in the circulation.

HP:0011992.name: Abnormal neutrophil morphology
HP:0011992.definition: An abnormal form or size of neutrophils.

HP:0011993.name: Impaired neutrophil bactericidal activity
HP:0011993.definition: A reduction in the ability of neutrophils to kill bacteria.

HP:0011994.name: Abnormal atrial septum morphology
HP:0011994.definition: An abnormality of the interatrial septum.

HP:0011995.name: Atrial septal dilatation
HP:0011995.definition: A bulging of the interatrial septum towards one side. In adults, atrial septal aneurysm can be defined as a protrusion of the aneurysm of >10 mm beyond the plane of the atrial septum as measured by transesophageal echocardiography.

HP:0011996.name: Elevated coagulation factor V activity
HP:0011996.definition: Increased activity of coagulation factor V, Factor V, which is activated to factor Va by means of minute amounts of thrombin (and inactivated by larger amounts of thrombin). Activated factor V (fVa) is a cofactor in the formation of the prothrombinase complex.

HP:0011997.name: Postprandial hyperlactemia
HP:0011997.definition: Abnormally increased level of blood lactate following a meal.

HP:0011998.name: Postprandial hyperglycemia
HP:0011998.definition: An increased concentration of glucose in the blood following a meal.

HP:0011999.name: Paranoia
HP:0011999.definition: The feeling and belief that one is being targeted or is a focus of negative or untoward actions, overt or covert, from others. The affected individual expresses a concern that people are in general against the individual and are engaging in subtle behaviors to make things difficult for them. The origins of such thinking may arise from real events and become amplified over time. Paranoia may also arise in the absence of any action or interaction between the person and their environment.

HP:0012000.name: EEG with generalized spikes
HP:0012000.definition: EEG with generalized sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec.

HP:0012001.name: EEG with generalized polyspikes
HP:0012001.definition: EEG with repetitive generalized sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec.

HP:0012002.name: Experiential epileptic aura
HP:0012002.definition: Affective, mnemonic or composite perceptual auras with subjective qualities similar to those experienced in life but are recognized by the subject as occurring outside of actual context.

HP:0012003.name: Affective epileptic aura
HP:0012003.definition: Affective auras with subjective qualities similar to those experienced in life but are recognized by the subject as occurring outside of actual context.

HP:0012004.name: Focal cognitive seizure with deja vu/jamais vu
HP:0012004.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by memory phenomena such as feelings of familiarity (deja vu) and unfamiliarity (jamais vu) as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0012005.name: Deja vu aura
HP:0012005.definition: A subjective feeling that an experience which is occurring for the first time has been experienced before.

HP:0012006.name: Jamais vu aura
HP:0012006.definition: A subjective feeling that an experience which has occurred before is being experienced for the first time.

HP:0012007.name: Focal cognitive seizure with hallucination
HP:0012007.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by hallucination as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0012008.name: Focal cognitive seizure with illusion
HP:0012008.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by an alteration of actual perception involving visual, auditory, somatosensory, olfactory, and/or gustatory phenomena as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0012009.name: EEG with central focal spike waves
HP:0012009.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the central region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

HP:0012010.name: EEG with frontal focal spike waves
HP:0012010.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the frontal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

HP:0012011.name: EEG with occipital focal spike waves
HP:0012011.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the occipital region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

HP:0012012.name: EEG with parietal focal spike waves
HP:0012012.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the parietal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

HP:0012013.name: EEG with temporal focal spike waves
HP:0012013.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the temporal region, i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

HP:0012014.name: EEG with central focal spikes
HP:0012014.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the central region.

HP:0012015.name: EEG with frontal focal spikes
HP:0012015.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the frontal region.

HP:0012016.name: EEG with occipital focal spikes
HP:0012016.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the occipital region.

HP:0012017.name: EEG with parietal focal spikes
HP:0012017.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the parietal region.

HP:0012018.name: EEG with temporal focal spikes
HP:0012018.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves of a duration less than 80 msec in the temporal region.

HP:0012019.name: Lens luxation
HP:0012019.definition: Complete dislocation of the lens of the eye.

HP:0012020.name: Right aortic arch
HP:0012020.definition: Aorta descends on right instead of on the left.

HP:0012021.name: Persistent patent ductus venosus
HP:0012021.definition: Persistence of blood flow through the ductus venosus for longer than the normal time after birth.

HP:0012022.name: Congenital portosystemic venous shunt
HP:0012022.definition: A congenital defect of the vasculature such that there is a shunt (by-pass) of blood directly from the portal vein to the vena cava (i.e., the blood from the portal vein is not filtered through the liver).

HP:0012023.name: Galactosuria
HP:0012023.definition: Elevated concentration of galactose in the urine.

HP:0012024.name: Hypergalactosemia
HP:0012024.definition: Elevated concentration of galactose in the blood.

HP:0012025.name: Abnormal circulating ornithine concentration
HP:0012025.definition: Deviation from the normal concentration of ornithine in the blood circulation.

HP:0012026.name: Hyperornithinemia
HP:0012026.definition: Increased concentration of ornithine in the blood.

HP:0012027.name: Laryngeal edema
HP:0012027.definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling in the tissues of the larynx.

HP:0012028.name: Hepatocellular adenoma
HP:0012028.definition: A benign tumor of the liver of presumably epithelial origin.

HP:0012029.name: Abnormal urine hormone level
HP:0012029.definition: An abnormal concentration of a hormone in the urine.

HP:0012030.name: Increased urinary cortisol level
HP:0012030.definition: Abnormally increased concentration of cortisol in the urine.

HP:0012032.name: Lipoma
HP:0012032.definition: Benign neoplasia derived from lipoblasts or lipocytes of white or brown fat. May be angiomatous or hibernomatous.

HP:0012033.name: Sacral lipoma
HP:0012033.definition: Presence of a lipoma in the region of the sacrum.

HP:0012034.name: Liposarcoma
HP:0012034.definition: Malignant neoplasms which probably originate in primitive mesenchymal stem cell populations differentiating down a lipomatous pathway.

HP:0012035.name: Steatocystoma multiplex
HP:0012035.definition: Multiple, localized or widespread, asymptomatic or inflammatory dermal cysts involving the pilosebaceous units. Lesions can appear anywhere on the body, but steatocystoma multiplex is more commonly involved with those areas of the skin with a high density of developed pilosebaceous units (e.g., the axilla, groin, neck, and proximal extremities).

HP:0012036.name: Sternocleidomastoid amyotrophy
HP:0012036.definition: Wasting of the sternocleidomastoid muscle, the muscle in the anterior part of the neck that acts to flex and rotate the head.

HP:0012037.name: Pectoralis amyotrophy
HP:0012037.definition: Wasting of the pectoral muscles, i.e., of the pectoralis major and pectoralis minor. This finding is often manifested by prominent axillary creases or double axillary creases.

HP:0012038.name: Corneal guttata
HP:0012038.definition: Corneal guttata are droplet-like accumulations of non-banded collagen on the posterior surface of Descemet's membrane. The presence of focal thickenings of Descemet's membrane histologically named guttae. Cornea guttata can be easily diagnosed in vivo and ex vivo by means of specular microscopy as it gives dark areas where no endothelial cells are visible.

HP:0012039.name: Descemet Membrane Folds
HP:0012039.definition: Presence of folds in the Descemet membrane, which is the basement membrane of the endothelial (inner) cell layer of the cornea. Descemet membrane folds are generally a manifestation of inflammation or edema of the cornea.

HP:0012040.name: Corneal stromal edema
HP:0012040.definition: Abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling of the stroma of cornea.

HP:0012042.name: Aspirin-induced asthma
HP:0012042.definition: A type of asthma in which aspirin and other nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) that inhibit cyclooxygen-ase 1 (COX-1) exacerbate bronchoconstriction.

HP:0012043.name: Pendular nystagmus
HP:0012043.definition: Rhythmic, involuntary sinusoidal oscillations of one or both eyes. The waveform of pendular nystagmus may occur in any direction.

HP:0012044.name: Seesaw nystagmus
HP:0012044.definition: Seesaw nystagmus is a type of pendular nystagmus where a half cycle consists of the elevation and intorsion of one eye, concurrently with the depression and extortion of the fellow eye. In the other half cycle, there is an inversion of the ocular movements.

HP:0012045.name: Retinal flecks
HP:0012045.definition: Presence of multiple yellowish-white lesions of various size and configuration on the retina not related to vascular lesions.

HP:0012046.name: Areflexia of upper limbs
HP:0012046.definition: Inability to elicit tendon reflexes in the upper limbs.

HP:0012047.name: Hemeralopia
HP:0012047.definition: A visual defect characterized by the inability to see as clearly in bright light as in dim light. The word hemeralopia literally means day blindness.

HP:0012048.name: Oromandibular dystonia
HP:0012048.definition: A kind of focal dystonia characterized by forceful contractions of the face, jaw, and/or tongue causing difficulty in opening and closing the mouth and often affecting chewing and speech.

HP:0012049.name: Laryngeal dystonia
HP:0012049.definition: A form of focal dystonia that affects the vocal cords, associated with involuntary contractions of the vocal cords causing interruptions of speech and affecting the voice quality and often leading to patterned, repeated breaks in speech.

HP:0012050.name: Anasarca
HP:0012050.definition: An extreme form of generalized edema with widespread and massive edema due to effusion of fluid into the extracellular space.

HP:0012051.name: Reactive hypoglycemia
HP:0012051.definition: Hypoglycermia following a meal (or more generally, after intake of glucose).

HP:0012052.name: Low serum calcitriol
HP:0012052.definition: A reduced concentration of calcitriol in the blood. Calcitriol is also known as 1,25-dihydroxycholecalciferol or 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D3.

HP:0012053.name: Decreased circulating calcifediol concentration
HP:0012053.definition: A reduced concentration of calcifediol in the blood. Calcifediol is also known as calcidiol, 25-hydroxycholecalciferol and 25-Hydroxyvitamin D3.

HP:0012054.name: Choroidal melanoma
HP:0012054.definition: Malignant tumor of melanocytes of the choroid. The classic appearance of choroidal melanoma is a pigmented dome-shaped or collar button-shaped tumor with an associated exudative retinal detachment. Choroidal melanoma is usually pigmented, but can be variably pigmented and even amelanotic (non-pigmented).

HP:0012055.name: Ciliary body melanoma
HP:0012055.definition: Malignant tumor of melanocytes of the ciliary body.

HP:0012056.name: Cutaneous melanoma
HP:0012056.definition: The presence of a melanoma of the skin.

HP:0012057.name: Superficial spreading melanoma
HP:0012057.definition: A type of melanoma that is flat and irregular in shape and color, with different shades of black and brown.

HP:0012058.name: Nodular melanoma
HP:0012058.definition: A type of melanoma that starts as a raised area that is usually dark blackish-blue or bluish-red but may not have any color.

HP:0012059.name: Lentigo maligna melanoma
HP:0012059.definition: A subtype of melanoma in situ that typically develops on sun-damaged skin. The lesion is typically a large, irregularly pigmented macule that has developed from an ordinary lentigo (a small pigmented spot on the skin with a clearly-defined edge). Change to a malignant lentigo typically takes place over 20 years or more, and many patients accept the change as a consequence of aging.

HP:0012060.name: Acral lentiginous melanoma
HP:0012060.definition: A type of cutaneous melanoma localized to the palm, sole, or beneath the nail (subungual melanoma). Acral lentiginous melanoma starts as a slowly-enlarging flat patch of discolored skin and usually displays a size above 6 mm and often several centimeters or more in diameter upon diagnosis and variable pigmentation with a mixutre of colors including brown, and blue-grey, black and red. The surface of the lesion is initially smooth but later in the course may become thicker and irregular, and may ulcerate or bleed.

HP:0012061.name: Urinary excretion of sialylated oligosaccharides
HP:0012061.definition: Excretion of oligosaccharides conjugated to sialic acid in the urine.

HP:0012062.name: Bone cyst
HP:0012062.definition: A fluid filled cavity that develops with a bone.

HP:0012063.name: Aneurysmal bone cyst
HP:0012063.definition: Radiographic features include a dilated, radiolucent lesion typically located eccentrically within the metaphyseal portion of the bone, with fluid levels visible on magnetic resonance imaging.

HP:0012064.name: Unicameral bone cyst
HP:0012064.definition: A benign fluid filled simple cyst of bone filled with serous fluid.

HP:0012065.name: Multiple bony cystic lesions
HP:0012065.definition: Presence of multiple cystic changes in multiple areas or multiple bones.

HP:0012066.name: Increased urinary disaccharide excretion
HP:0012066.definition: Increased concentration of disaccharide in the urine.

HP:0012067.name: Glycopeptiduria
HP:0012067.definition: Increased excretion of glycopeptides in the urine. Glycopeptides are peptides with carbohydrate moieties covalently attached to the side chains of the amino acid residues.

HP:0012068.name: Aspartylglucosaminuria
HP:0012068.definition: Excretion of excess amounts of aspartylglucosamine in the urine.

HP:0012069.name: Keratan sulfate excretion in urine
HP:0012069.definition: An increased concentration of keratan sulfate in the urine.

HP:0012070.name: Chondroitin sulfate excretion in urine
HP:0012070.definition: An increased concentration of chondroitin sulfate (CHEBI:37397) in the urine.

HP:0012071.name: Abnormal circulating acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0012071.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of an acylcarnitine, which is produced by reversible esterification of the 3-hydroxyl group of carnitine.

HP:0012072.name: Aciduria
HP:0012072.definition: Excretion of urine with an acid pH, i.e., having an increased hydrogen ion concentration.

HP:0012073.name: Abnormal urinary acylglycine profile
HP:0012073.definition: An abnormal distribution of N-acylglycines in the urine. There are numerous different N-acylglycines, and this term refers to pathological alterations in their level or distribution.

HP:0012074.name: Tonic pupil
HP:0012074.definition: An abnormality of the pupillary light reaction characterized by a marked slowing of the light reaction of usually just one pupil. The pupil tends to be relatively dilated, and there is reduced accommodation.

HP:0012075.name: Personality disorder
HP:0012075.definition: A personality disorder is a deeply ingrained pattern of behavior of a specified kind that deviates markedly from the norms of generally accepted behavior. It is typically apparent by the time of adolescence and causes long-term difficulties in personal relationships or functioning in society.

HP:0012076.name: Borderline personality disorder
HP:0012076.definition: A personality disorder characterized by impulsive behavior and unpredictable, capricious mood. Affected individuals show a tendency to have outbursts of emotion and an inability to control these behavioral explosions. They generally experience an intense fear of abandonment or instability and also struggle with feelings of emptiness.

HP:0012077.name: Histrionic personality disorder
HP:0012077.definition: A personality disorder characterized by shallow and labile affectivity, self-dramatization, theatricality, exaggerated expression of emotions, suggestibility, egocentricity, self-indulgence, lack of consideration for others, easily hurt feelings, and continuous seeking for appreciation, excitement and attention.

HP:0012078.name: Motor conduction block
HP:0012078.definition: Blockade of impulses at a focal site along the course of a motor axon.

HP:0012079.name: Abnormality of central motor conduction
HP:0012079.definition: Any anomaly of the conduction of motor nerve impulses in the central nervous system.

HP:0012080.name: Cerebellar granular layer atrophy
HP:0012080.definition: Atrophy of the cerebellum affecting primarily the granular cell layer.

HP:0012081.name: Enlarged cerebellum
HP:0012081.definition: An abnormally increased size of the cerebellum compared to other brain structures.

HP:0012082.name: Cerebellar Purkinje layer atrophy
HP:0012082.definition: Atrophy of the cerebellum affecting primarily the Purkinje cell layer.

HP:0012083.name: Ubiquitin-positive cerebral inclusion bodies
HP:0012083.definition: Nuclear or cytoplasmic aggregates that show positive staining with antibodies against ubiquitin within cells of the brain.

HP:0012084.name: Abnormality of skeletal muscle fiber size
HP:0012084.definition: Any abnormality of the size of the skeletal muscle cell.

HP:0012085.name: Pyuria
HP:0012085.definition: The presence of 10 or more white cells per cubic millimeter in a urine specimen, 3 or more white cells per high-power field of unspun urine, a positive result on Gram staining of an unspun urine specimen, or a urinary dipstick test that is positive for leukocyte esterase.

HP:0012086.name: Abnormal urinary color
HP:0012086.definition: An abnormal color of the urine, that is, the color of the urine appears different from the usual straw-yellow color.

HP:0012087.name: Abnormal mitochondrial shape
HP:0012087.definition: An anomaly in the surface contour of mitochondria.

HP:0012088.name: Abnormal urinary odor
HP:0012088.definition: A deviation from the normal odor of the urine.

HP:0012091.name: Abnormality of pancreas physiology
HP:0012091.definition: An anomaly of the function of the pancreas.

HP:0012092.name: Abnormality of exocrine pancreas physiology
HP:0012092.definition: A functional anomaly of the acinar gland portion of the pancreas that secretes digestive enzymes.

HP:0012093.name: Abnormality of endocrine pancreas physiology
HP:0012093.definition: A function abnormality of the endocrine pancreas.

HP:0012094.name: Abnormal pancreas size
HP:0012094.definition: A deviation from the normal size of the pancreas.

HP:0012096.name: Intracranial epidermoid cyst
HP:0012096.definition: A congenital inclusion cysts that arises from ectodermal cells that normally form skin cells being left behind in the nervous system during development.

HP:0012097.name: Intracranial dermoid cyst
HP:0012097.definition: A congenital inclusion cysts that arises from the inclusion of ectodermally committed cells at the time of neural tube closure (3rd-5th week of embryogenesis). The capsule of dermoid cysts consists of simple epithelium supported by collagen. In thicker parts, the lining is supplemented with dermis containing hair follicles, sebaceous glands, and apocrine glands.

HP:0012098.name: Edema of the dorsum of feet
HP:0012098.definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin on the back of the feet.

HP:0012099.name: Abnormality of circulating catecholamine level
HP:0012099.definition: An abnormal catecholamine concentration in the blood.

HP:0012100.name: Abnormal circulating creatinine concentration
HP:0012100.definition: An abnormal concentration of creatinine in the blood.

HP:0012101.name: Decreased serum creatinine
HP:0012101.definition: An abnormally reduced amount of creatinine in the blood.

HP:0012102.name: Abnormal mitochondrial number
HP:0012102.definition: A deviation from the normal number of mitochondria per cell.

HP:0012103.name: Abnormality of the mitochondrion
HP:0012103.definition: An anomaly of the mitochondrion, the membranous cytoplasmic organelle the interior of which is subdivided by cristae. The mitochondrion is a self replicating organelle that is the site of tissue respiration.

HP:0012106.name: Rhizomelic leg shortening
HP:0012106.definition: Disproportionate shortening of the proximal segment of the leg (i.e. the femur).

HP:0012107.name: Increased fibular diameter
HP:0012107.definition: Increased width of the cross sectional diameter of the fibula.

HP:0012108.name: Open angle glaucoma
HP:0012108.definition: A type of glaucoma defined by an open, normal appearing anterior chamber angle and raised intraocular pressure,

HP:0012109.name: Angle closure glaucoma
HP:0012109.definition: A type of glaucomatous optic neuropathy in an eye that has evidence of angle closure (i.e. significant iridotrabecular contact).

HP:0012111.name: Abnormality of circulating glucocorticoid level
HP:0012111.definition: An abnormality of the concentration of a glucocorticoid in the blood.

HP:0012112.name: Abnormal circulating corticosterone level
HP:0012112.definition: An abnormality of the concentration of corticosterone in the blood.

HP:0012113.name: Abnormal circulating creatine concentration
HP:0012113.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of creatine in the blood circulation. Creatine is a derivative of glycine having methyl and amidino groups attached to the nitrogen. Creatine is naturally produced from amino acids, primarily in liver and kidney, and acts as an energy source for cells, primarily for muscle cells.

HP:0012114.name: Endometrial carcinoma
HP:0012114.definition: A carcinoma of the endometrium, the mucous lining of the uterus.

HP:0012116.name: Abnormal circulating albumin concentration
HP:0012116.definition: Deviation from normal concentration of albumin in the blood.

HP:0012117.name: Hyperalbuminemia
HP:0012117.definition: Elevation in the concentration of albumin in the blood.

HP:0012119.name: Methemoglobinemia
HP:0012119.definition: Abnormally increased levels of methemoglobin in the blood. In this form of hemoglobin, there is an oxidized ferric iron (Fe +3) rather than the reduced ferrous form (Fe 2+) that is normally found in hemoglobin. Methemoglobin has a reduced affinity for oxygen, resulting in a reduced ability to release oxygen to tissues.

HP:0012120.name: Methylmalonic aciduria
HP:0012120.definition: Increased concentration of methylmalonic acid in the urine.

HP:0012121.name: Panuveitis
HP:0012121.definition: Inflammation of the uveal tract in which inflammation affects the anterior chamber, vitreous, retina or choroid.

HP:0012122.name: Anterior uveitis
HP:0012122.definition: Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the anterior chamber.

HP:0012123.name: Posterior uveitis
HP:0012123.definition: Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the retina or choroid.

HP:0012124.name: Intermediate uveitis
HP:0012124.definition: Inflammation of the uveal tract in which the primary site of inflammation is the vitreous.

HP:0012126.name: Stomach cancer
HP:0012126.definition: A cancer arising in any part of the stomach.

HP:0012127.name: Uraciluria
HP:0012127.definition: Increased concentration of uracil in the urine.

HP:0012128.name: Basal ganglia necrosis
HP:0012128.definition: Death of cells in the basal ganglia. This finding can be confirmed by autopsy. It can be suspected with hyperintensities within the basal ganglia on FLAIR and T2-sequences on magnetic resonance imaging.

HP:0012129.name: Abnormality of bone marrow stromal cells

HP:0012130.name: Abnormal erythroid lineage cell morphology
HP:0012130.definition: An anomaly of erythroid lineage cells, that is, of the erythropoietic cells in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes.

HP:0012131.name: Abnormal number of erythroid precursors
HP:0012131.definition: A deviation from the normal count of erythroid precursor cells, that is, erythroid lineage cells in the bone marrow.

HP:0012132.name: Erythroid hyperplasia
HP:0012132.definition: Increased count of erythroid precursor cells, that is, erythroid lineage cells in the bone marrow.

HP:0012133.name: Erythroid hypoplasia
HP:0012133.definition: Decreased count of erythroid precursor cells, that is, erythroid lineage cells in the bone marrow.

HP:0012135.name: Abnormal granulocytopoietic cell morphology
HP:0012135.definition: An anomaly of cells involved in the formation of a granulocytes, that is, of the granulocytopoietic cell.

HP:0012139.name: Granulocytic hypoplasia
HP:0012139.definition: Decreased number of granulocyte precursors in the bone marrow.

HP:0012140.name: obsolete Abnormality of cells of the lymphoid lineage

HP:0012142.name: Pancreatic squamous cell carcinoma
HP:0012142.definition: A subtype of ductal pancreatic carcinoma that is thought to originate from squamous metaplasia of pancreatic ductal epithelium.

HP:0012143.name: Abnormal megakaryocyte morphology
HP:0012143.definition: Any structural anomaly of megakaryocytes. Mature blood platelets are released from the cytoplasm of megakaryocytes, which are bone-marrow resident cells.

HP:0012144.name: Abnormal monocyte morphology
HP:0012144.definition: Any structural anomaly of a myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

HP:0012145.name: Abnormality of multiple cell lineages in the bone marrow

HP:0012146.name: Abnormality of von Willebrand factor
HP:0012146.definition: Decreased quantity or activity of von Willebrand factor. Von Willebrand factor mediates the adhesion of platelets to the collagen exposed on endothelial cell surfaces.

HP:0012147.name: Reduced quantity of Von Willebrand factor
HP:0012147.definition: Decreased quantity of von Willebrand factor.

HP:0012148.name: Multiple lineage myelodysplasia
HP:0012148.definition: Myelodysplasia with dysplastic changes in two or more of the myeloid lineages: erythroid, granulocytic, megakaryocytic.

HP:0012149.name: Bilineage myelodysplasia
HP:0012149.definition: Myelodysplasia with dysplastic changes in two of the myeloid lineages: erythroid, granulocytic, megakaryocytic.

HP:0012150.name: Single lineage myelodysplasia
HP:0012150.definition: Abnormality/dysplasia of a single myeloid cell (erythroid, granulocytic, or megakaryocytic).

HP:0012151.name: Hemothorax
HP:0012151.definition: The presence of blood in the pleural space.

HP:0012152.name: Foveoschisis
HP:0012152.definition: Splitting of the retinal layers in the macula.

HP:0012153.name: Hypotriglyceridemia
HP:0012153.definition: An decrease in the level of triglycerides in the blood.

HP:0012154.name: Anhedonia
HP:0012154.definition: Decreased ability to experience or feel joy or pleasure from any experience that is usually found to be pleasurable by the individual. This applies to any of the senses, e.g., taste, smell, and sound. Food may no longer be tasty, or a musical experience may no longer be enjoyable. Anhedonia also refers to an inability to feel pleasure related to activities that an affected individual previously derived pleasure from.

HP:0012155.name: Decreased corneal sensation
HP:0012155.definition: Reduced ability of the cornea to respond to stimulation.

HP:0012156.name: Hemophagocytosis
HP:0012156.definition: Phagocytosis by macrophages of erythrocytes, leukocytes, platelets, and their precursors in bone marrow and other tissues.

HP:0012157.name: Subcortical cerebral atrophy
HP:0012157.definition: Atrophy of the cerebral subcortical white and gray matter, termed subcortical atrophy, reflects loss of nerve cells in the basal ganglia or fibers in the deep white matter.

HP:0012158.name: Carotid artery dissection
HP:0012158.definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the carotid artery wall.

HP:0012159.name: Internal carotid artery dissection
HP:0012159.definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the internal carotid artery wall.

HP:0012160.name: Intracranial internal carotid artery dissection
HP:0012160.definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the intracranial portion of the internal carotid artery wall.

HP:0012161.name: External carotid artery dissection
HP:0012161.definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the external carotid artery wall.

HP:0012162.name: Common carotid artery dissection
HP:0012162.definition: A separation (dissection) of the layers of the common carotid artery wall.

HP:0012163.name: Carotid artery dilatation
HP:0012163.definition: A dilatation (balooning or bulging out of the vessel wall) of a carotid artery.

HP:0012164.name: Asterixis
HP:0012164.definition: A clinical sign indicating a lapse of posture and is usually manifest by a bilateral flapping tremor at the wrist, metacarpophalangeal, and hip joints.

HP:0012165.name: Oligodactyly
HP:0012165.definition: A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of digits.

HP:0012166.name: Skin-picking
HP:0012166.definition: Repetitive and compulsive picking of skin which results in tissue damage.

HP:0012167.name: Hair-pulling
HP:0012167.definition: A phenomenon in which persons repetitively pull out their own hair, resulting in noticeable hair loss.

HP:0012168.name: Head-banging
HP:0012168.definition: Habitual striking of one's own head against a surface such as a mattress or wall of a crib.

HP:0012169.name: Self-biting
HP:0012169.definition: Habitual biting of one's own body.

HP:0012170.name: Nail-biting
HP:0012170.definition: Habitual biting of one's own fingernails.

HP:0010678.name: Enuresis diurna
HP:0010678.definition: Enuresis occurring during waking hours of the day.

HP:0010679.name: Elevated tissue non-specific alkaline phosphatase
HP:0010679.definition: An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

HP:0010680.name: Elevated alkaline phosphatase of renal origin
HP:0010680.definition: An abnormally increased level of kidney isoforms of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

HP:0010681.name: Elevated intestinal alkaline phosphatase
HP:0010681.definition: An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, intestinal type in the blood.

HP:0010682.name: Elevated placental alkaline phosphatase
HP:0010682.definition: An abnormally increased level of alkaline phosphatase, placental type in the blood.

HP:0010683.name: Low tissue non-specific alkaline phosphatase
HP:0010683.definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, tissue-nonspecific isozyme in the blood.

HP:0010684.name: Low alkaline phosphatase of bone origin
HP:0010684.definition: An abnormally reduced level of bone isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood.

HP:0010685.name: Low alkaline phosphatase of renal origin
HP:0010685.definition: An abnormally reduced level of kidney isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood.

HP:0010686.name: Low alkaline phosphatase of hepatic origin
HP:0010686.definition: An abnormally reduced level of liver isoforms of alkaline phosphatase in the blood.

HP:0010687.name: Low intestinal alkaline phosphatase
HP:0010687.definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, intestinal type in the blood.

HP:0010688.name: Low placental alkaline phosphatase
HP:0010688.definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase, placental type in the blood.

HP:0010689.name: Mirror image polydactyly
HP:0010689.definition: A hand or foot with more than five digits that has a recognizable A/P axis of symmetry. The axis can lie within a normally formed or partially duplicated digit resembling a middle finger, index finger, thumb, toe, or hallux. Alternatively, the axis can be in an interdigital space with a flanking pair of digits that resemble a middle finger, index finger, thumb, toe or hallux. The most lateral digits on each side of the hand/foot typically resemble fifth fingers/toes.

HP:0010690.name: Mirror image hand polydactyly
HP:0010690.definition: Mirror image duplication of digits affecting the hands only.

HP:0010691.name: Mirror image foot polydactyly
HP:0010691.definition: Mirror image duplication of digits affecting the feet.

HP:0010693.name: Pulverulent cataract
HP:0010693.definition: A kind of congenital cataract that is characterized by a hollow sphere of punctate opacities involving the fetal nucleus and that usually occurs bilaterally.

HP:0010694.name: Lamellar pulverulent cataract
HP:0010694.definition: A Lamellar cataract with a pulverulent (punctate, "dust-like" opacities) appearance.

HP:0010695.name: Sutural cataract
HP:0010695.definition: A type of congenital cataract in which the opacity follows the anterior or posterior Y suture.

HP:0010696.name: Polar cataract
HP:0010696.definition: A type of Congenital cataract in which the opacities occupy the subcapsular cortex at the anterior or posterior pole of the lens.

HP:0010697.name: Anterior pyramidal cataract
HP:0010697.definition: A type of anterior polar cataract which projects as a conical opacity into the anterior chamber.

HP:0010698.name: Nuclear pulverulent cataract
HP:0010698.definition: A type of nuclear cataract involving congenital dust-like (pulverulent) opacity of the embryonal and fetal nucleus.

HP:0010699.name: Triangular nuclear cataract
HP:0010699.definition: A nuclear cataract with a triangular form.

HP:0010701.name: Abnormal circulating immunoglobulin concentration
HP:0010701.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in blood.

HP:0010702.name: Increased circulating immunoglobulin concentration
HP:0010702.definition: An increased level of gamma globulin (immunoglobulin) in the blood.

HP:0010704.name: 1-2 finger cutaneous syndactyly
HP:0010704.definition: A soft tissue continuity in the anteroposterior axis between the thumb to the index finger that extends distally to at least the level of the proximal interphalangeal joints.

HP:0012574.name: Mesangial hypercellularity
HP:0012574.definition: Increased numbers of mesangial cells per glomerulus, defined as more than 3 nuclei fully surrounded by matrix in one or more mesangial areas, not including perihilar region, on a standard 3-micron-thick tissue section, best evaluated on periodic acid-Schiff (PAS) stain.

HP:0012575.name: Abnormal nephron morphology
HP:0012575.definition: A structural anomaly of the nephron.

HP:0012576.name: Glomerular C3 deposition
HP:0012576.definition: The presence of complement 3 deposits in the glomerulus.

HP:0012577.name: Thin glomerular basement membrane
HP:0012577.definition: Decreased thickness of the glomerular basement membrane (GBM), measured from endothelial to visceral epithelial plasma membrane and mainly attributable to a decrease in thickness of the lamina densa, generally to an overall thickness more than 2 standard deviations less than that of the normal mean GBM thickness for health age- and sex matched individuals. May be focal or diffuse, although the term thin GBMs generally implies thinning of over 50% of GBMs.

HP:0012578.name: Membranous nephropathy
HP:0012578.definition: A type of glomerulonephropathy characterized by thickening of the basement membrane and deposition of immune complexes in the subepithelial space.

HP:0012579.name: Minimal change glomerulonephritis
HP:0012579.definition: The presence of minimal changes visible by light microscopy but flattened and fused podocyte foot processes on electron microscopy in a person with nephrotic range proteinuria.

HP:0012580.name: Calcium phosphate nephrolithiasis
HP:0012580.definition: The presence of calcium- and phosphate-containing calculi (stones) in the kidneys.

HP:0012581.name: Simple renal cyst
HP:0012581.definition: An isolated cyst of the kidney.

HP:0012582.name: Bilateral renal dysplasia
HP:0012582.definition: A bilateral form of developmental dysplasia of the kidney.

HP:0012583.name: Unilateral renal hypoplasia
HP:0012583.definition: One sided hypoplasia of the kidney.

HP:0012584.name: Bilateral renal hypoplasia
HP:0012584.definition: Two sided hypoplasia of the kidney.

HP:0012586.name: Bilateral renal atrophy
HP:0012586.definition: A two-sided form of atrophy of the kidney.

HP:0012587.name: Macroscopic hematuria
HP:0012587.definition: Hematuria that is visible upon inspection of the urine.

HP:0012588.name: Steroid-resistant nephrotic syndrome
HP:0012588.definition: A form of nephrotic syndrome that does not respond to treatment with steroid medication, defined as persistent proteinuria despite 60mg/m2 or 2mg/kg for 8 weeks, after insuring no infection or non-adherence to medication.

HP:0012589.name: Multidrug-resistant nephrotic syndrome
HP:0012589.definition: A form of nephrotic syndrome that does not respond to any immunosuppresive treatment.

HP:0012590.name: Abnormal urine output
HP:0012590.definition: An abnormal amount of urine production.

HP:0012591.name: Abnormal urinary electrolyte concentration
HP:0012591.definition: An abnormality in the concentration of electrolytes in the urine.

HP:0012592.name: Albuminuria
HP:0012592.definition: Increased concentration of albumin in the urine.

HP:0012593.name: Nephrotic range proteinuria
HP:0012593.definition: Severely increased amount of excretion of protein in the urine, defined as 3.5 grams per day or more in adults and 40 mg per meter-squared body surface area per hour in children.

HP:0012594.name: Moderate albuminuria
HP:0012594.definition: The presence of moderately increased concentrations of albumin in the urine, defined as and albumin-creatinine ratio (ACR) of 30 to 299 mg/gm (3.4 to 34 mg/mmol).

HP:0012595.name: Mild proteinuria
HP:0012595.definition: Mildly increased levels of protein in the urine (150-500 mg per day in adults).

HP:0012596.name: Moderate proteinuria
HP:0012596.definition: Moderately increased levels of protein in the urine (500-1000 mg per day in adults).

HP:0012597.name: Heavy proteinuria
HP:0012597.definition: Severely increased levels of protein in the urine (1000-3000 mg per day in adults).

HP:0012598.name: Abnormal urine potassium concentration
HP:0012598.definition: An abnormal concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine.

HP:0012599.name: Abnormal urine phosphate concentration
HP:0012599.definition: An abnormal phosphate concentration in the urine.

HP:0012600.name: Abnormal urine chloride concentration
HP:0012600.definition: An abnormal concentration of chloride in the urine.

HP:0012601.name: Hypochloriduria
HP:0012601.definition: An decreased concentration of chloride in the urine.

HP:0012602.name: Renal chloride wasting
HP:0012602.definition: High urine chloride in the presence of hypochloridemia.

HP:0012603.name: Abnormal urine sodium concentration
HP:0012603.definition: An abnormal concentration of sodium in the urine.

HP:0012604.name: Hyponatriuria
HP:0012604.definition: An abnormally decreased sodium concentration in the urine.

HP:0012605.name: Hypernatriuria
HP:0012605.definition: An increased concentration of sodium(1+) in the urine.

HP:0012606.name: Renal sodium wasting
HP:0012606.definition: An abnormally increased sodium concentration in the urine in the presence of hyponatremia.

HP:0012607.name: Abnormal urine magnesium concentration
HP:0012607.definition: An abnormal concentration of magnesium the urine.

HP:0012608.name: Hypermagnesiuria
HP:0012608.definition: An increased concentration of magnesium the urine.

HP:0012609.name: Hypomagnesiuria
HP:0012609.definition: An decreased concentration of magnesium the urine.

HP:0012610.name: Abnormality of urinary uric acid level
HP:0012610.definition: Abnormal amount of urate in the urine.

HP:0012612.name: Abnormal urinary sulfate concentration
HP:0012612.definition: Abnormal concentration of sulfate in the urine.

HP:0012613.name: Increased urinary sulfate
HP:0012613.definition: Elevated concentration of SO4(2-), i.e., sulfate, in the urine.

HP:0012614.name: Abnormal urine cytology
HP:0012614.definition: An anomalous finding in the examination of the urine for cells.

HP:0012615.name: Cylindruria
HP:0012615.definition: The presence of renal casts (cylindrical, cigar-shaped structures produced by the kidney in certain disease states) in the urine.

HP:0012616.name: Leukocyte cylindruria
HP:0012616.definition: Presence of leukocyte casts (cylindrical structures produced by the kidney in certain disease states) in the urine.

HP:0012617.name: Erythrocyte cylindruria
HP:0012617.definition: Presence of erythrocyte casts (cylindrical structures produced by the kidney in certain disease states) in the urine.

HP:0012618.name: Urachal cyst
HP:0012618.definition: A cyst located along the allantois canal.

HP:0012619.name: Multiple bladder diverticula
HP:0012619.definition: Presence of a many diverticula (sac or pouch) in the wall of the urinary bladder.

HP:0012620.name: Cloacal abnormality
HP:0012620.definition: A developmental anomaly associated with the failure of rectum, vagina, and bladder to separate.

HP:0012621.name: Persistent cloaca
HP:0012621.definition: Developmental anomaly in which the vagina, bladder, and rectum fuse resulting in a common channel.

HP:0012622.name: Chronic kidney disease
HP:0012622.definition: Functional anomaly of the kidney persisting for at least three months.

HP:0012623.name: Stage 1 chronic kidney disease
HP:0012623.definition: A type of chronic kidney disease with normal or increased glomerular filtration rate (GFR at least 90 mL/min/1.73 m2).

HP:0012624.name: Stage 2 chronic kidney disease
HP:0012624.definition: A type of chronic kidney disease with mildly reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR 60-89 mL/min/1.73 m2).

HP:0012625.name: Stage 3 chronic kidney disease
HP:0012625.definition: A type of chronic kidney disease with moderately reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR 30-59 mL/min/1.73 m2).

HP:0012626.name: Stage 4 chronic kidney disease
HP:0012626.definition: A type of chronic kidney disease with severely reduced glomerular filtration rate (GFR 15-29 mL/min/1.73 m2).

HP:0012627.name: Pseudoexfoliation
HP:0012627.definition: Deposition of fibrillar material that can be found on all anterior segment structures bathed by aqueous humor.

HP:0012628.name: Abnormal suspensory ligament of lens morphology
HP:0012628.definition: An anomaly of the suspensory ligament of lens, also known as the ciliary zonule. These ligaments represent a series of fibers connecting the ciliary body and lens of the eye, holding the lens in place.

HP:0012629.name: Phakodonesis
HP:0012629.definition: Tremulousness (trembling) of the lens of the eye.

HP:0012630.name: Abnormal trabecular meshwork morphology
HP:0012630.definition: An anomaly of the trabecular meshwork, which is the porelike structure surrounding the entire circumference of the anterior chamber at the base of the cornea and near the ciliary body. The trabecular mesh work is responsible for draining the aqueous humor into the canal of Schlemm.

HP:0012631.name: Pigment deposition in the trabecular meshwork
HP:0012631.definition: Accumulation of abnormal amounts of pigment within the trabecular meshwork.

HP:0012632.name: Abnormal intraocular pressure
HP:0012632.definition: An anomaly in the amount of force per unit area exerted by the intraocular fluid within the eye.

HP:0012633.name: Asymmetry of intraocular pressure
HP:0012633.definition: A difference in the amount of intraocular pressure in the right and left eye.

HP:0012634.name: Iris pigment dispersion
HP:0012634.definition: Shedding of the pigment granules that normally adhere to the back of the iris into the aqueous humor.

HP:0012635.name: Iris hypoperfusion
HP:0012635.definition: Reduction in the amount of blood flow to the iris.

HP:0012637.name: Renal calcium wasting
HP:0012637.definition: High urine calcium in the presence of hypocalcemia.

HP:0012638.name: Abnormal nervous system physiology
HP:0012638.definition: A functional anomaly of the nervous system.

HP:0012639.name: Abnormal nervous system morphology
HP:0012639.definition: A structural anomaly of the nervous system.

HP:0012640.name: Abnormality of intracranial pressure
HP:0012640.definition: A deviation from the norm of the intracranial pressure.

HP:0012641.name: Decreased intracranial pressure
HP:0012641.definition: A reduction of the pressure inside the cranium (skull) and thereby in the brain tissue and cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0012642.name: Cerebellar agenesis
HP:0012642.definition: Cerebellar agenesis is defined by the near complete absence of cerebellar tissue with only remnants of the anterior vermis, flocculus, and/or middle cerebellar peduncles.

HP:0012643.name: Foveal hypopigmentation
HP:0012643.definition: Decreased amount of pigmentation in the fovea centralis.

HP:0012644.name: Increased caudate lactate level
HP:0012644.definition: An elevated concentration of lactate in the caudate nucleus. This finding can be elicited by magnetic resonance spectroscopy imaging.

HP:0012645.name: Enlarged peripheral nerve
HP:0012645.definition: Increase in size of a peripheral nerve. This finding can be appreciated by palpation along the axis of the nerve.

HP:0012646.name: Retractile testis
HP:0012646.definition: A testis that is located at the upper scrotum or lower inguinal canal and that can be made to descend completely into the scrotum without resistance by manual reduction but returns to its original position by the cremasteric reflex.

HP:0012647.name: Abnormal inflammatory response
HP:0012647.definition: Any anomaly of the inflammatory response, a response to injury or infection characterized by local vasodilation, extravasation of plasma into intercellular spaces and accumulation of white blood cells and macrophages.

HP:0012648.name: Decreased inflammatory response
HP:0012648.definition: An abnormal reduction in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.

HP:0012649.name: Increased inflammatory response
HP:0012649.definition: A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.

HP:0012650.name: Perisylvian polymicrogyria
HP:0012650.definition: Polymicrogyria (an excessive number of small gyri or convolutions) that is maximal in perisylvian regions (the regions that surround the Sylvian fissures), which may be symmetric or asymmetric and may extend beyond perisylvian regions. The Sylvian fissures often extend posteriorly and superiorly.

HP:0012651.name: Abasia
HP:0012651.definition: A severe form of gait ataxia such that an affected person cannot walk at all.

HP:0012653.name: Status asthmaticus
HP:0012653.definition: Severe asthma unresponsive to repeated courses of beta-agonist therapy such as inhaled albuterol, levalbuterol, or subcutaneous epinephrine.

HP:0012654.name: Abnormal CSF dopamine concentration
HP:0012654.definition: Abnormal concentration of dopamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0012655.name: Elevated CSF dopamine concentration
HP:0012655.definition: Increased concentration of dopamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0012656.name: Reduced CSF dopamine concentration
HP:0012656.definition: Decreased concentration of dopamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0012657.name: Abnormal brain positron emission tomography
HP:0012657.definition: A functional brain anomaly detectable by positron emission tomography (PET). PET scanning is a method for functional brain imaging, and its measurements reflect the amount of brain activity in the various regions of the brain.

HP:0012658.name: Abnormal brain FDG positron emission tomography
HP:0012658.definition: An anomaly detectable in [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) positron emission tomography (PET) brain scans. Glucose uptake measured with FDG-PET is a marker of neuronal metabolic activity.

HP:0012659.name: Prefrontal hypometabolism in FDG PET
HP:0012659.definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the prefrontal cortex as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

HP:0012660.name: Thalamic hypometabolism in FDG PET
HP:0012660.definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the thalamus as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

HP:0012661.name: Hypothalamic hypometabolism in FDG PET
HP:0012661.definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the hypothalamus as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

HP:0012662.name: Parietal hypometabolism in FDG PET
HP:0012662.definition: Reduced uptake of [18F]-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) in the parietal cortex as measured by positron emission tomography (PET) brain scan.

HP:0012663.name: Mildly reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
HP:0012663.definition: A small reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle. The normal range in adults is at least 50 percent, and a mild reduction is defined as 40-49 percent.

HP:0012664.name: Reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
HP:0012664.definition: A diminution of the volumetric fraction of blood pumped out of the ventricle with each cardiac cycle.

HP:0012665.name: Moderately reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
HP:0012665.definition: A medium reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle, defined as a left ventricular ejection fraction of 30-39 percent.

HP:0012666.name: Severely reduced left ventricular ejection fraction
HP:0012666.definition: A large reduction in the fraction of blood pumped from the left ventricle with each cardiac cycle. The normal range in adults is at over 50 percent, and a severe reduction is defined as less than 30 percent.

HP:0012667.name: Regional left ventricular wall motion abnormality
HP:0012667.definition: An abnormal motion of a segment of the left ventricle during the cardiac cycle.
