HP:0011788.definition: An elevated concentration of free 3,3',5-triiodo-L-thyronine in the blood circulation.

HP:0011789.name: Impaired sensitivity to thyroid stimulating hormone
HP:0011789.definition: Reduced sensitivity of thyroid follicle cells to stimulation by biologically active thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH).

HP:0011792.name: Neoplasm by histology
HP:0011792.definition: Neoplasm categorized according to type of histological abnormality.

HP:0011793.name: Neoplasm by anatomical site
HP:0011793.definition: Neoplasm categorized according to the anatomical site of origin of the neoplasm.

HP:0011794.name: Embryonal renal neoplasm
HP:0011794.definition: The presence of an embryonal neoplasm of the kidney that primarily affects children.

HP:0011795.name: Intralobar nephroblastomatosis
HP:0011795.definition: Presence of persistent islands of renal blastema in the postnatal kidney, anywhere within a renal lobe (a portion of a kidney consisting of a renal pyramid and the renal cortex above it).

HP:0011796.name: Perilobar nephroblastomatosis
HP:0011796.definition: Abnormally persistent foci of embryonal immature blastema located in the superficial cortical region (perilobar).

HP:0011797.name: Papillary renal cell carcinoma type 1
HP:0011797.definition: A type of papillary renal cell carcinoma that is characterized by small cuboidal cells covering thin papillae with a single line of uniform nuclei and small nucleoli.

HP:0011798.name: Renal oncocytoma
HP:0011798.definition: A renal tumor originating from an oncocyte, which is an epithelial cell characterized by an excessive amount of mitochondria, resulting in an abundant acidophilic, granular cytoplasm.

HP:0011800.name: Midface retrusion
HP:0011800.definition: Posterior positions and/or vertical shortening of the infraorbital and perialar regions, or increased concavity of the face and/or reduced nasolabial angle.

HP:0011801.name: Enlargement of parotid gland
HP:0011801.definition: Increased size of the parotid gland.

HP:0011802.name: Hamartoma of tongue
HP:0011802.definition: A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the tongue.

HP:0011803.name: Bifid nose
HP:0011803.definition: Visually assessable vertical indentation, cleft, or depression of the nasal bridge, ridge and tip.

HP:0011804.name: Abnormal muscle physiology
HP:0011804.definition: A functional abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

HP:0011805.name: Abnormal skeletal muscle morphology
HP:0011805.definition: A structural abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

HP:0011807.name: Type 1 muscle fiber atrophy
HP:0011807.definition: Atrophy (wasting) affecting primary type 1 muscle fibers. This feature in general can only be observed on muscle biopsy.

HP:0011808.name: Decreased patellar reflex
HP:0011808.definition: Decreased intensity of the patellar reflex (also known as the knee jerk reflex).

HP:0011809.name: Paradoxical myotonia
HP:0011809.definition: A type of myotonia that worsens with repeated muscle contractions.

HP:0011810.name: Impaired two-point discrimination
HP:0011810.definition: A reduced ability to distinguish tactile sensations at points that are very close to one another. This can be tested by using special calipers whose points can be set from 2mm to several centimeters apart.

HP:0011811.name: Impaired touch localization
HP:0011811.definition: A reduced ability to identify precisely the site of a touch. This test is usually carried out by asking a patient, whose eyes are closed or covered, to touch the same site with a fingertip.

HP:0011812.name: Agraphesthesia
HP:0011812.definition: Impaired ability to recognize letters or numbers drawn by an examiner's fingertip on the patient's skin (the patients eyes are closed or covered throughout this examination).

HP:0011813.name: Increased cerebral lipofuscin
HP:0011813.definition: Lipofuscin (age pigment) is a brown-yellow, electron-dense, autofluorescent material that accumulates progressively over time in lysosomes of postmitotic cells, such as neurons and cardiac myocytes. This term pertains if there is an increase in the accumulation of lipofuscin (also known as autofluorescent lipoprotein) more than expected for the age of the patient.

HP:0011814.name: Increased urinary hypoxanthine level
HP:0011814.definition: The concentration of hypoxanthine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0011815.name: Cephalocele
HP:0011815.definition: A congenital defect in the skull, whereby there is a protrusion of part of the cranial contents through a congenital defect in the cranium, usually covered with skin or mucous membrane. The term encephalocele refers to a subclass of these lesions in which brain tissue protrudes through the defect.

HP:0011816.name: Parietal encephalocele
HP:0011816.definition: An encephalocele located between bregma and lambda.

HP:0011817.name: Basal encephalocele
HP:0011817.definition: Basal encephalocele is an encephalocele that occurs along the cribriform plate or through the sphenoid bone. The mass may appear in the nasal cavity, nasopharynx, epipharynx, sphenoid sinus, posterior orbit, or pterygopalatine fossa. The important distinction from other types is that no external tumor is visible except in those rare instances of herniations so large that they protrude through the mouth or nares.

HP:0011819.name: Submucous cleft soft palate
HP:0011819.definition: A cleft of the muscular (soft) portion of the palate that is covered by mucous membrane. Soft-palate submucous clefts are characterized by a midline deficiency or lack of muscle tissue.

HP:0011820.name: Membranous choanal atresia
HP:0011820.definition: Absence of the normal opening of the choana (the posterior nasal aperture) as a result of an obstructing choanal membrane that may be thin and strandlike or thick and pluglike.

HP:0011821.name: Abnormal facial skeleton morphology
HP:0011821.definition: An abnormality of one or more of the set of bones that make up the facial skeleton.

HP:0011822.name: Broad chin
HP:0011822.definition: Increased width of the midpoint of the mandible (mental protuberance) and overlying soft tissue.

HP:0011823.name: Chin with horizontal crease
HP:0011823.definition: Horizontal crease or fold situated below the vermilion border of the lower lip and above the fatty pad of the chin, with the face at rest.

HP:0011824.name: Chin with H-shaped crease
HP:0011824.definition: H-shaped crease in the fat pad of the chin.

HP:0011825.name: Tented philtrum
HP:0011825.definition: Prominence of a triangular soft tissue area of the philtrum with the apex to the columella.

HP:0011826.name: Philtrum with midline raphe
HP:0011826.definition: Narrow ridge in the midline of the philtral groove.

HP:0011827.name: Malaligned philtral ridges
HP:0011827.definition: Absence of the usual parallel position of philtral ridges.

HP:0011828.name: Midline sinus of philtrum
HP:0011828.definition: Pit in the midline of the philtral groove.

HP:0011829.name: Narrow philtrum
HP:0011829.definition: Distance between the philtral ridges, measured just above the vermilion border, more than 2 standard deviations below the mean. Alternatively, an apparently decreased distance between the ridges of the philtrum.

HP:0011831.name: Deviated nasal tip
HP:0011831.definition: Nasal tip positioned to one side of the midline.

HP:0011832.name: Narrow nasal tip
HP:0011832.definition: Decrease in width of the nasal tip.

HP:0011833.name: Overhanging nasal tip
HP:0011833.definition: Positioning of the nasal tip inferior to the nasal base.

HP:0011834.name: Moyamoya phenomenon
HP:0011834.definition: A noninflammatory, progressive occlusion of the intracranial carotid arteries owing to the formation of netlike collateral arteries arising from the circle of Willis.

HP:0011836.name: Delayed talus ossification
HP:0011836.definition: Delayed maturation and calcification of the talus.

HP:0011837.name: Partial IgA deficiency
HP:0011837.definition: Detectable but decreased IgA levels that are more than 2 standard deviations below normal age-adjusted means.

HP:0011838.name: Sclerodactyly
HP:0011838.definition: Localized thickening and tightness of the skin of the fingers or toes.

HP:0011839.name: Abnormal T cell count
HP:0011839.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of absolute number of T cells or of a subset of T cells, commonly characterized as CD3+ lymphocytes, in the blood, per microlitre, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group. These may include both TCR alpha/beta and gamma/delta T cells.

HP:0011840.name: Abnormality of T cell physiology
HP:0011840.definition: A functional anomaly of T cells.

HP:0011841.name: Ventricular flutter
HP:0011841.definition: A potentially lethal cardiac arrhythmia characterized by an extremely rapid, hemodynamically unstable ventricular tachycardia (150-300 beats/min) with a large oscillating sine-wave appearance.

HP:0011842.name: Abnormal skeletal morphology
HP:0011842.definition: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.

HP:0011843.name: Abnormal musculoskeletal physiology
HP:0011843.definition: An abnormality of the function of the skeletal system.

HP:0011844.name: Abnormal appendicular skeleton morphology
HP:0011844.definition: An abnormality of the appendicular skeletal system, consisting of the of the limbs, shoulder and pelvic girdles.

HP:0011846.name: Osteoblastoma
HP:0011846.definition: A benign, painful, tumor of bone characterized by the formation of osteoid tissue, primitive bone and calcified tissue.

HP:0011847.name: Giant cell tumor of bone
HP:0011847.definition: A bone tumor composed of cellular spindle-cell stroma containing scattered multinucleated giant cells resembling osteoclasts.

HP:0011848.name: Abdominal colic
HP:0011848.definition: A type of abdominal pain that comes and goes in waves, most often starting and ending suddenly and being of severe intensity.

HP:0011849.name: Abnormal bone ossification
HP:0011849.definition: Any anomaly in the formation of bone or of a bony substance, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

HP:0011851.name: Hemopericardium
HP:0011851.definition: Accumulation of blood within the pericardial sac.

HP:0011852.name: Chylopericardium
HP:0011852.definition: Accumulation of chyle (the whitish fluid taken up by the lacteals in the intestine, consisting of an emulsion of lymph and triglyceride fat thatpasses into the veins by the thoracic duct) in the pericardium. Chylopericardium is generally caused by obstruction of or trauma to the thoracic duct.

HP:0011853.name: Serous pericardial effusion
HP:0011853.definition: Accumulation of serous fluid (pale yellow and transparent fluid) in the pericardial sac.

HP:0011854.name: Hemoperitoneum
HP:0011854.definition: Accumulation of blood in the peritoneal cavity owing to internal hemorrhage.

HP:0011855.name: Pharyngeal edema
HP:0011855.definition: Abnormal accumulation of fluid leading to swelling of the pharynx.

HP:0011856.name: Pica
HP:0011856.definition: An appetite for and the persistent ingestion of non-food substances such as clay. In order to diagnose pica, this behavior must have persisted over a period of at least one month.

HP:0011857.name: Plasmacytoma
HP:0011857.definition: A discrete mass of neoplastic monoclonal plasma cells either in the bone marrow or in an extramedullary location.

HP:0011858.name: Reduced factor IX activity
HP:0011858.definition: Decreased activity of coagulation factor IX. Factor IX, which itself is activated by factor Xa or factor VIIa to form factor IXa, activates factor X into factor Xa.

HP:0011859.name: Punctate keratitis
HP:0011859.definition: A type of keratitis characterized by inflammation in pinpoint areas of the corneal epithelium.

HP:0011860.name: Metaphyseal dappling
HP:0011860.definition: The presence of spots or rounded patches of abnormally increased density of metaphyseal bone.

HP:0011861.name: Bilateral trilobed lung
HP:0011861.definition: Both lungs have three lobes. Normally, the left lung has two lobes, whereas the right lung has three lobes.

HP:0011862.name: Abnormal bone collagen fibril morphology
HP:0011862.definition: Any structural anomaly of the connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of bone tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity.

HP:0011863.name: Abnormal sternal ossification
HP:0011863.definition: Any anomaly in the formation of the bony substance of the sternum.

HP:0011864.name: Elevated plasma pyrophosphate
HP:0011864.definition: An abnormally increased diphosphate(4-) concentration in the blood. Diphosphate(4-), as ester with two phosphate groups, is also known as pyrophosphate.

HP:0011867.name: Abnormal iliac wing morphology
HP:0011867.definition: An anomaly of the ilium ala. This is the large expanded portion of the ilum which bounds the greater pelvis laterally.

HP:0011868.name: Sciatica
HP:0011868.definition: Pain in the lower back and hip radiating in the distribution of the sciatic nerve.

HP:0011869.name: Abnormal platelet function
HP:0011869.definition: Any anomaly in the function of thrombocytes.

HP:0011870.name: Impaired arachidonic acid-induced platelet aggregation
HP:0011870.definition: Abnormal response to arachidonic acid as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of arachidonic acid.

HP:0011871.name: Impaired ristocetin-induced platelet aggregation
HP:0011871.definition: Abnormal response to ristocetin as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of ristocetin.

HP:0011872.name: Impaired thrombin-induced platelet aggregation
HP:0011872.definition: Abnormal response to thrombin or thrombin mimetics as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of thrombin (or thrombin mimetics).

HP:0011873.name: Abnormal platelet count
HP:0011873.definition: Abnormal number of platelets per volume of blood. In a healthy adult, a normal platelet count is between 150,000 and 450,000 per microliter of blood.

HP:0011874.name: Heparin-induced thrombocytopenia
HP:0011874.definition: Low platelet count following administration of unfractionated or (less commonly) low-molecular weight heparin.

HP:0011875.name: Abnormal platelet morphology
HP:0011875.definition: An anomaly in platelet form, ultrastructure, or intracellular organelles.

HP:0011876.name: Abnormal platelet volume
HP:0011876.definition: Anomalous size of platelets. Most normal sized platelets are 1.5 to 3 micrometers in diameter. Large platelets are 4 to 7 micrometers. Giant platelets are larger than 7 micrometers and usually 10 to 20 micrometers.

HP:0011877.name: Increased mean platelet volume
HP:0011877.definition: Average platelet volume above the upper limit of the normal reference interval.

HP:0011878.name: Abnormal platelet membrane protein expression
HP:0011878.definition: Presence of reduced amount of a membrane protein on the cell membrane of platelets. This feature is typically measured by flow cytometry.

HP:0011879.name: Decreased platelet glycoprotein Ib-IX-V
HP:0011879.definition: Decreased cell membrane concentration of the glycoprotein complex Ib-IX-V.

HP:0011880.name: Acute disseminated intravascular coagulation
HP:0011880.definition: An acute form of disseminated intravascular coagulation. Acute DIC can occur following sudden exposure of blood to procoagulants, with the compensatory hemostatic mechanisms becoming overwhelmed.

HP:0011881.name: Decreased platelet glycoprotein VI
HP:0011881.definition: Decreased cell membrane concentration of glycoprotein VI.

HP:0011882.name: Decreased platelet P2Y12 receptor
HP:0011882.definition: Decreased cell membrane concentration of P2Y12 receptor.

HP:0011883.name: Abnormal platelet granules
HP:0011883.definition: An anomaly of alpha or dense granules or platelet lysosomes.

HP:0011884.name: Abnormal umbilical stump bleeding
HP:0011884.definition: Abnormal bleeding of the umbilical stump following separation of the cord at approximately 7-10 days after birth.

HP:0011885.name: Hemorrhage of the eye
HP:0011885.definition: Bleeding from vessels of the various tissues of the eye.

HP:0011886.name: Hyphema
HP:0011886.definition: Bleeding in the anterior chamber of the eye.

HP:0011887.name: Choroid hemorrhage
HP:0011887.definition: Hemorrhage from the vessels of the choroid.

HP:0011888.name: Bleeding requiring red cell transfusion
HP:0011888.definition: Bleeding sufficiently severe as to require red cell transfusion (WHO Grade 3 or 4).

HP:0011889.name: Bleeding with minor or no trauma
HP:0011889.definition: Significant bleeding or hemorrhage without significant precipitating factor.

HP:0011890.name: Prolonged bleeding following procedure
HP:0011890.definition: Prolonged or protracted bleeding following an invasive procedure or intervention.

HP:0011891.name: Post-partum hemorrhage
HP:0011891.definition: Significant maternal hemorrhage/blood loss following deilvery of a child.

HP:0011892.name: Decreased circulating vitamin K concentration
HP:0011892.definition: The concentration of vitamin K in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0011893.name: Abnormal leukocyte count
HP:0011893.definition: Number of leukocytes per volume of blood beyond normal limits.

HP:0011894.name: Impaired thromboxane A2 agonist-induced platelet aggregation
HP:0011894.definition: Abnormal response to thromboxane as manifested by reduced or lacking aggregation of platelets upon addition of thromboxane A2 receptor agonists.

HP:0011895.name: Anemia due to reduced life span of red cells
HP:0011895.definition: A type of anemia related to a reduction in the average life span of red blood cells in the peripheral circulation, which is normally around 120 days.

HP:0011896.name: Subconjunctival hemorrhage
HP:0011896.definition: Bleeding beneath the mucous membrane that lines the inner surface of the eyelid.

HP:0011897.name: Increased total neutrophil count
HP:0011897.definition: Abnormal increase of absolute number of neutrophils in the blood, per microliter, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0011898.name: Abnormality of circulating fibrinogen
HP:0011898.definition: An abnormality of the level of activity of circulating fibrinogen.

HP:0011899.name: Hyperfibrinogenemia
HP:0011899.definition: Increased concentration of fibrinogen in the blood.

HP:0011900.name: Hypofibrinogenemia
HP:0011900.definition: Decreased concentration of fibrinogen in the blood.

HP:0011902.name: Abnormal hemoglobin
HP:0011902.definition: Anomaly in the level or the function of hemoglobin, the oxygen-carrying protein of erythrocytes.

HP:0011903.name: HbH hemoglobin
HP:0011903.definition: Hemoglobin H (HbH) contains four beta-globin chains. It is normally not present at all in blood, but may make up about 1-40 percent of all hemoglobin in HbH disease, a subform of alpha thalassemia.

HP:0011904.name: Persistence of hemoglobin F
HP:0011904.definition: Hemoglobin F (HbF) contains two globin alpha chains and two globin gamma chains. It is the main form of hemoglobin in the fetus during the last seven months of intrauterine development and in the half year of postnatal life. In adults it normally makes up less than one percent of all hemoglobin. This term refers to an increase in HbF above this limit. In beta thalassemia major, it may represent over 90 percent of all hemoglobin, and in beta thalassemia minor it may make up between 0.5 to 4 percent.

HP:0011905.name: Reduced hemoglobin A
HP:0011905.definition: Hemoglobin A (HbA) contains two globin alpha chains and two globin beta chains. HbA is normally the main adult hemoglobin, representing about 96-98 percent of all hemoglobin. This term represents a decreased in the proportion of HbA below this limit, and can be seen in various forms of thalassemia.

HP:0011906.name: Reduced beta/alpha synthesis ratio
HP:0011906.definition: A reduction in the ratio of production of beta globin to that of alpha globin. This is the major abnormality in the various forms of beta thalassemia.

HP:0011907.name: Reduced alpha/beta synthesis ratio
HP:0011907.definition: A reduction in the ratio of production of alpha globin to that of beta globin. This is the major abnormality in the various forms of alpha thalassemia.

HP:0011908.name: Unilateral radial aplasia
HP:0011908.definition: Missing radius bone on one side only associated with congenital failure of development.

HP:0011909.name: Flattened metacarpal heads
HP:0011909.definition: Abnormally flat shape of the heads of the metacarpal bones.

HP:0011910.name: Shortening of all phalanges of fingers
HP:0011910.definition: Abnormal reduction in length affecting all phalanges.

HP:0011911.name: Abnormal metacarpophalangeal joint morphology
HP:0011911.definition: An anomaly of a metacarpophalangeal joint.

HP:0011912.name: Abnormality of the glenoid fossa
HP:0011912.definition: An anomaly of the glenoid fossa, also known as the glenoid cavity, which is the articular surface of the scapula that articulates with the head of the humerus.

HP:0011913.name: Lumbar hypertrichosis
HP:0011913.definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the lumbar region.

HP:0011914.name: Thoracic hypertrichosis
HP:0011914.definition: Excessive, increased hair growth located in the thoracic region.

HP:0011915.name: Cardiovascular calcification
HP:0011915.definition: Abnormal calcification in the cardiovascular system.

HP:0011916.name: Toe extensor amyotrophy
HP:0011916.definition: Atrophy of the extensor digitorum longus muscles, which mediate extension of the toes.

HP:0011918.name: Clinodactyly of the 4th toe
HP:0011918.definition: Bending or curvature of a fourth toe in the tibial direction (i.e., towards the big toe).

HP:0011919.name: Pleural empyema
HP:0011919.definition: Accumulation of pus in the pleural cavity.

HP:0011920.name: Transudative pleural effusion
HP:0011920.definition: A type of pleural effusion with a transudate (extravascular fluid with low protein content and a low specific gravity). Pleural effusions can be classified as transudates or exudates based on Light's criteria, which classify an effusion as exudate if one or more of the following are present: (1) the ratio of pleural fluid protein to serum protein is greater than 0.5, (2) the ratio of pleural fluid lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) to serum LDH is greater than 0.6, or (3) the pleural fluid LDH level is greater than two thirds of the upper limit of normal for serum LDH.

HP:0011921.name: Exudative pleural effusion
HP:0011921.definition: A type of pleural effusion with a exudate (extravascular fluid that has exuded out of a tissue or its capillaries due to injury or inflammation). Pleural effusions can be classified as transudates or exudates based on Light's criteria, which classify an effusion as exudate if one or more of the following are present: (1) the ratio of pleural fluid protein to serum protein is greater than 0.5, (2) the ratio of pleural fluid lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) to serum LDH is greater than 0.6, or (3) the pleural fluid LDH level is greater than two thirds of the upper limit of normal for serum LDH.

HP:0011922.name: Abnormal activity of mitochondrial respiratory chain
HP:0011922.definition: An increased or decreased activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain.

HP:0011923.name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex I
HP:0011923.definition: A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex I, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria.

HP:0011924.name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial complex III
HP:0011924.definition: A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial respiratory chain complex III, which is part of the electron transport chain in mitochondria.

HP:0011925.name: Decreased activity of mitochondrial ATP synthase complex
HP:0011925.definition: A reduction in the activity of the mitochondrial proton-transporting ATP synthase complex, which makes ATP via oxidative phosphorylation, and is sometimes described as Complex V of the electron transport chain.

HP:0011926.name: Proximal placement of hallux
HP:0011926.definition: Proximal mislocalization of the big toe from its normal position.

HP:0011927.name: Short digit
HP:0011927.definition: One or more digit that appears disproportionately short compared to the hand/foot, whereby either the entire digit or a specific phalanx is shortened.

HP:0011928.name: Short proximal phalanx of toe
HP:0011928.definition: Developmental hypoplasia (shortening) of proximal phalanx of toe.

HP:0011929.name: Hypersegmentation of proximal phalanx of third finger
HP:0011929.definition: Presence of an additional phalanx-like bone, producing an extra, wedge-shaped bone at the base of the proximal phalanx of the third finger.

HP:0011931.name: Abnormal cerebellar peduncle morphology
HP:0011931.definition: An anomaly of the cerebellar peduncles. The superior, middle, and inferior cerebellar peduncles emerge from the cerebellum. The superior cerebellar penduncles connect the cerebellum to the midbrain, the middle cerebellar peduncles connect the cerebellum to the pons, and the inferior cerebellar peduncle connects the medulla spinalis and medulla oblongata with the cerebellum.

HP:0011932.name: Abnormal superior cerebellar peduncle morphology
HP:0011932.definition: An anomaly of the superior cerebellar peduncle.

HP:0011933.name: Elongated superior cerebellar peduncle
HP:0011933.definition: Increased length of the superior cerebellar peduncle.

HP:0011934.name: Dilatation of mesenteric artery
HP:0011934.definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the inferior mesenteric artery or superior mesenteric artery .

HP:0011935.name: Decreased urinary urate
HP:0011935.definition: Decreased concentration of urate in the urine.

HP:0011936.name: Decreased plasma total carnitine
HP:0011936.definition: A decreased concentration of total carnitine in the blood.

HP:0011937.name: Hypoplastic fifth toenail
HP:0011937.definition: Underdeveloped nails of the fifth toes.

HP:0011939.name: 3-4 finger cutaneous syndactyly
HP:0011939.definition: A soft tissue continuity in the A/P axis between fingers 3 and 4.

HP:0011940.name: Anterior wedging of T12
HP:0011940.definition: An abnormality of the shape of the thoracic vertebra T12 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front).

HP:0011941.name: Anterior wedging of L2
HP:0011941.definition: An abnormality of the shape of the lumbar vertebra L2 such that it is wedge-shaped (narrow towards the front).

HP:0011942.name: Increased urinary sulfite level
HP:0011942.definition: The concentration of SO3(2-), i.e., sulfite, in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0011943.name: Increased urinary thiosulfate
HP:0011943.definition: Increased concentration of thiosulfate(2-) in the urine.

HP:0011944.name: Small vessel vasculitis
HP:0011944.definition: A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) that affects blood vessels that are smaller than arteries, i.e., arterioles, venules, and capilllaries.

HP:0011945.name: Bronchiolitis obliterans organizing pneumonia
HP:0011945.definition: Bronchiolitis obliterans organizing pneumonia (BOOP) is and interstitial lung abnormalitiy characterized histopathologically by plugs of granulation tissue lying within small airways, alveolar ducts, and alveoli and by chronic inflammatory cell infiltration in alveolar walls. Patients with BOOP generally present with subacute illness, including shortness of breath, fever, malaise, and weight loss.

HP:0011946.name: Bronchiolitis obliterans
HP:0011946.definition: Inflammation and fibrosis of the bronchioles leading to partial or complete obstruction of these airways.

HP:0011947.name: Respiratory tract infection
HP:0011947.definition: An infection of the upper or lower respiratory tract.

HP:0011948.name: Recurrent acute respiratory tract infection
HP:0011948.definition: A history of repeated acute infections of the upper or lower respiratory tract.

HP:0011949.name: Acute infectious pneumonia
HP:0011949.definition: Acute inflammation of the lung due to an infection.

HP:0011951.name: Aspiration pneumonia
HP:0011951.definition: Pneumonia due to the aspiration (breathing in) of food, liquid, or gastric contents into the upper respiratory tract.

HP:0011952.name: Acute aspiration pneumonia
HP:0011952.definition: An acute episode of pneumonia due to the aspiration (breathing in) of food, liquid, or gastric contents into the upper respiratory tract.

HP:0011954.name: Nodular regenerative hyperplasia of liver
HP:0011954.definition: Diffuse benign transformation of the hepatic parenchyma into small regenerative nodules with minimal or no fibrosis.

HP:0011955.name: Hepatic granulomatosis
HP:0011955.definition: The presence of multiple granulomas in the liver as based on pathological examination. Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes.

HP:0011956.name: Intestinal lymphoid nodular hyperplasia
HP:0011956.definition: A lymphoproliferative abnormality of the intestine characterized by numerous visible mucosal nodules measuring up to, and rarely exceeding, 0.5 cm in diameter Histologically, hyperplastic lymphoid follicles with large germinal centers are seen in the lamina propria and superficial submucosa. There is enlargement of the mucosal B cell follicles caused by hyperplasia of the follicle centers; surrounded by a normal appearing mantle zone. Disease may involve the stomach, the entire small intestine, and the large intestine.

HP:0025702.name: Type 1 schizencephaly
HP:0025702.definition: A type of Schizencephaly in which there is a trans-mantle column of abnormal gray matter but no evidence of a CSF-containing cleft on MR imaging.

HP:0025703.name: Type 2 schizencephaly
HP:0025703.definition: A type of Schizencephaly in which CSF-containing cleft is present with abutting lining lips of abnormal gray matter that are opposed to each other.

HP:0025704.name: Type 3 schizencephaly
HP:0025704.definition: A type of Schizencephaly in which CSF-containing cleft present with non-abutting lining lips of abnormal gray matter.

HP:0025705.name: Abnormal fetal nasal bone visualization
HP:0025705.definition: Abnormal appearance or non-visualization (apparent absence) of the nasal bone of a fetus in first trimester sonographic screening. Assessment of the fetal nasal bone is generally performed at 11-14 weeks gestational age.

HP:0025706.name: Absent fetal nasal bone
HP:0025706.definition: The nasal bone is considered absent when it is not visualized on a midsagittal view of the profile. In the second trimester, a true midsagittal view of the fetal profile is obtained and magnified to fill the majority of the image space. The nasal bone appears as an echogenic linear structure below the skin edge. The optimal angle of insonation is 45 degrees to the longitudinal axis of the fetal nasal bone. If the angle of insonation is 0 or 180 degrees, the nasal bone may appear artificially absent. The presence or absence of the nasal bone may be determined at the time of the 11- to 14-week ultrasound examination and used as part of the risk assessment for aneuploidy.

HP:0025707.name: Hypoplastic fetal nasal bone
HP:0025707.definition: Length of the nasal bone below a predetermined cut-off as seen on antenatal ultrasound using standard imaging techniques.

HP:0025708.name: Early young adult onset
HP:0025708.definition: Onset of disease at an age of greater than or equal to 16 to under 19 years.

HP:0025709.name: Intermediate young adult onset
HP:0025709.definition: Onset of disease at an age of greater than or equal to 19 to under 25 years.

HP:0025710.name: Late young adult onset
HP:0025710.definition: Onset of disease at an age of greater than or equal to 25 to under 40 years.

HP:0025711.name: Convergence-retraction nystagmus
HP:0025711.definition: Convergence-retraction nystagmus is an irregular, jerky nystagmus in which both eyeballs rhythmically converge and retract into the orbit, particularly on attempting an upward gaze.

HP:0025712.name: Spontaneous chorioamniotic separation
HP:0025712.definition: Persistence separation of the chorionic and amnionic membranes after the 16th week of gestation (not as a result of a procedure such as amniocentesis).

HP:0025713.name: Neurite dystrophy
HP:0025713.definition: Dystrophic neurites are abnormal neuronal processes characterized microscopically by aberrant sprouting, dystrophic expansion, and accumulation of various cellular organelles and cytoskeletal/signaling proteins.

HP:0025714.name: Cerebral cortical microinfarct
HP:0025714.definition: An infarct located on the outer layer of the cerebrum that can only be observed microscopically. Cerebral microinfarcts are typically defined as sharply delimited microscopic regions of cellular death or tissue necrosis, sometimes with cavitation (that is, a central fluid-filled cavity). The term microscopic denotes that these lesions are not visible by gross inspection of the brain but seen by light microscopy. The term infarct is most commonly used for ischemia-related tissue loss, and indeed the pathologic appearance of microinfarcts is consistent with that of known ischemic infarctions.

HP:0025715.name: Abnormal umbilical artery doppler waveform during pregnancy
HP:0025715.definition: Abnormal waveforms the Doppler sonographic examination of bloodflow in the umbilical artery. vUmbilical arterial Doppler assessment is used in surveillance of fetal health in the third trimester.

HP:0025716.name: Fetal anemia
HP:0025716.definition: Low hemoglobin/hematocrit in a fetus as evidenced by percutaneous umbilical cord sampling and Doppler ultrasonographic assessment of the peak velocity of systolic blood flow in the middle cerebral artery.

HP:0025717.name: Skeletal muscle autophagosome accumulation
HP:0025717.definition: Abnormal accumulation of autophagosomes in skeletal muscle tissue.

HP:0025718.name: Skeletal muscle hyperechogenicity
HP:0025718.definition: An increased echo intensity of muscle tissue on sonography, defined as an increased amount of returning echoes per square area of muscle tissue. On cross-section, normal muscle appears as a relatively anechoic structure with hyperechoic speckles within the tissue representing perimysial septa, giving it a starry night appearance. The boundaries of each muscle are delineated by the presence of hyperechoic fascia. In muscle disorders, one of the hallmark findings is replacement of healthy muscle with fat and fibrosis, manifested by an increase in echogenicity from higher sound transitions in the muscle. This increase in echogenicity is most distinct in conditions that lead to chronic pathology, such as long-standing muscle inflammation, dystrophy, or denervation.

HP:0025719.name: Maternal vascular malperfusion
HP:0025719.definition: Gross findings of maternal vascular malperfusion include placental hypoplasia, placental infarction, and retroplacental hemorrhage. If information is available, it is preferable to annotate using the HPO terms that corresponding to the specific abnormalities.

HP:0025720.name: Limited horizontal extraocular movement
HP:0025720.definition: Limited mobility of the eye to move from side to side (horizontally) within its socket.

HP:0025721.name: Limited vertical extraocular movement
HP:0025721.definition: Limited mobility of the eye to move up and down (vertically) within its socket.

HP:0025722.name: Cerebral infarct
HP:0025722.definition: A necrotic lesion in the cerebrum resulting from a sudden insufficiency of arterial or venous blood supply due to emboli, thrombi or mechanical factors.

HP:0025723.name: Abnormal fetal skin morphology
HP:0025723.definition: Any structural anomaly of the skin of the fetus or newborn. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

HP:0025724.name: Caseous vernix-like desquamation
HP:0025724.definition: Vernix caseosa is a physiological, viscous biofilm that is produced by desquamated fetal skin and sebaceous glands covering the fetus at the third trimester in-utero. The substance's gross morphology in post-partum is described by the etymology, as vernix means varnish, and caseosa means cheesy-like matter. This finding refers to an abnormally thick and greasy vernix caseosa-like scale present at birth.

HP:0025725.name: Type 1 congenital pulmonary airway malformation
HP:0025725.definition: A type of congenital pulmonary airway malformation that is characterized by multiple large cysts or a single dominant cyst.

HP:0025726.name: Type 2 congenital pulmonary airway malformation
HP:0025726.definition: A type of congenital pulmonary airway malformation that is characterized by multiple evenly spaced cysts (sponge-like appearance).

HP:0025727.name: Type 3 congenital pulmonary airway malformation
HP:0025727.definition: A type of congenital pulmonary airway malformation that is characterized by a bulky firm mass with an adenomatoid appearance.

HP:0025728.name: Periventricular pseudocyst
HP:0025728.definition: Pseudocysts that lack an epithelial lining, PVPCs are frequently observed in the caudothalamic groove or in the infero-lateral aspect of the frontal horns of the lateral ventricles, but may also be located elsewhere along the periventricular germinal matrix, as in the temporal or occipital horns.

HP:0025729.name: Fetal vascular malperfusion
HP:0025729.definition: The term fetal vascular malperfusion (FVM) is used to describe placental pathology that is thought to result from an obstruction in fetal blood flow that could result from a number of conditions (eg, umbilical cord lesions, hypercoagulability, complications of fetal cardiac dysfunction, such as hypoxia, etc.).

HP:0025730.name: Foramen ovale aneurysm
HP:0025730.definition: Foramen ovale aneurysm (FOA) or atrial septal aneurysm is abnormal redundancy of the atrial septum primum, with bulging of the septum by at least half the width of the atrial chamber, or by at least 10 mm beyond the level of the atrial septum. The abnormal protrusion of the interatrial septum results in decreased left atrial volume. On color Doppler there is reduced left ventricular inflow.

HP:0025731.name: Anti-glycosylphosphatidylinositol anchored high-density lipoprotein binding protein 1 antibody positivity
HP:0025731.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glycosylphosphatidylinositol anchored high-density lipoprotein binding protein 1.

HP:0025732.name: Abnormal social development
HP:0025732.definition: A substantial lag in the ahcievement of or divergence from typical milestones in social interaction and communication skills. Social-emotional competencies in young children include helping, sharing, comforting, and exhibiting empathy and compliance.

HP:0025733.name: Streak gonad
HP:0025733.definition: A type of gonadal dysgenesis in which the gonadal tissue is underdeveloped and appears as fibrous, streak-like structures instead of fully formed ovaries or testes.

HP:0025734.name: Elevated urinary 5-hydroxyhexanoic acid level
HP:0025734.definition: The amount of 5-hydroxyhexanoic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0025735.name: Abnormal third cranial nerve morphology
HP:0025735.definition: Any structural abnormality of the third (oculomotor) cranial nerve.

HP:0025736.name: Long-bone fracture
HP:0025736.definition: A partial or complete breakage of a lone bone (e.g., the femur, tibia, fibula, humerus, radius, and ulna).

HP:0025737.name: Abnormal subthalamic nucleus morphology
HP:0025737.definition: Any structural anomaly of the subthalamic nucleus, a small lens-shaped structure located within the diencephalon near the junction with the midbrain. The subthalamic nucleus composes the majority of the subthalamus along with the subthalamic fasciculus, ansa lenticularis, and several other smaller structures.

HP:0025738.name: Ring-enhancing cerebral lesion
HP:0025738.definition: An abnormal neuroimaging finding consisting in an area of decreased density surrounded by a bright rim from concentration of the enhancing contrast dye.

HP:0025739.name: Optic nerve mass
HP:0025739.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the optic nerve. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0025740.name: Elevated brain succinate level by MRS
HP:0025740.definition: An increase in the level of succinate in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

HP:0025741.name: Brainstem lucency
HP:0025741.definition: A lesion located in the brainstem that appears areas less dense on magnetic resonance imaging or lighter on computed tomography.

HP:0025742.name: Elevated urine L-xylulose level
HP:0025742.definition: The amount of L-xylulose in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0025743.name: Elevated urine biliverdin level
HP:0025743.definition: The amount of biliverdin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0025744.name: Elevated urine dodecanedioic acid level
HP:0025744.definition: The amount of dodecanedioic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0025746.name: Diminished urine glutamine level
HP:0025746.definition: The amount of glutamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0025747.name: Tongue spasticity
HP:0025747.definition: Spasticity (velocity-dependent increase in tonic stretch reflexes with increased muscle tone and hyperexcitable tendon reflexes) in the muscles of the tongue.

HP:0025748.name: Restricted tongue movement
HP:0025748.definition: Limited ability to move the tongue related to mechanical restrictions such as akyloglossia and not associated with tongue muscle weakness.

HP:0025749.name: Asymmetric blood pressure between limbs
HP:0025749.definition: A substantial difference in blood pressure (e.g., 20 mmHg) between the right and left limb (arm or leg or both).

HP:0025750.name: Asymmetric blood pressure between legs
HP:0025750.definition: A substantial difference in blood pressure (e.g., 20 mmHg) between the right and left legs.

HP:0025751.name: Reduced anterior scleral thickness
HP:0025751.definition: A reduction in the height of the anterior portion of the sclera.

HP:0025752.name: Reduced posterior scleral thickness
HP:0025752.definition: A reduction in the height of the posterior portion of the sclera.

HP:0025753.name: Elevated urinary 2-aminoisobutyric acid
HP:0025753.definition: The amount of 2-aminoisobutyric acid in the urine, when normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0025754.name: Reduced beta-hexosaminidase A activity
HP:0025754.definition: The concentration or activity of beta hexosaminidase A in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0025755.name: Abnormal nail shape
HP:0025755.definition: An abnormality affecting the outline (shape) or contour of the nail.

HP:0025756.name: Abnormal nail attachment
HP:0025756.definition: An anomaly of the connection of the nail to the nailbed.

HP:0025757.name: Abnormal nail surface
HP:0025757.definition: An anomaly of the surface of the nail.

HP:0025758.name: Characteristic of mass
HP:0025758.definition: A mass is a general term for a lump or growth that may be caused by the abnormal growth of cells, a cyst, hormonal changes, or an immune reaction. This term refers to a property (characteristic) of a mass.

HP:0025759.name: Mobile lump
HP:0025759.definition: This modifier is applied to a palpable mass or swelling in the body that can be moved or shifted under the skin when pressed or manipulated.

HP:0025760.name: Immobile lump
HP:0025760.definition: This modifier is applied to a palpable mass or swelling in the body that cannot be moved or shifted under the skin when pressed or manipulated.

HP:0025761.name: Painless mass
HP:0025761.definition: This modifier is applied to a palpable mass or swelling in the body that does not elicit pain upon palpation.

HP:0025762.name: Anti-ganglionic acetylcholine receptor antibody positivity
HP:0025762.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against acetylcholine receptors of the ganglionic type.

HP:0025763.name: Positive urine anion gap
HP:0025763.definition: The urine anion gap (UAG), calculated as [(Na+ + K+) - (Cl-)] has been used to roughly estimate whether urine ammonium is increased or decreased in the evaluation of hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis. The more ammonium in the urine, the lower the UAG is, which achieves negative values within a wide range (0 to -200 mEq/L) during hyperchloremic metabolic acidosis. In patients with distal renal tubular acidosis (RTA) of several etiologies, the UAG is positive, despite the prevailing metabolic acidosis, and this is a useful bedside diagnostic index of impaired ammonium excretion.

HP:0025764.name: Nasoethmoidal encephalocele
HP:0025764.definition: A type of encephalocele that is characterized by herniation through the foramen cecum into the prenasal space and nasal cavity under the nasal bones and above the nasal septum.

HP:0025765.name: Rubber-like lump
HP:0025765.definition: This modifier is applied to a palpable mass or swelling in the body that has a rubber-like consistency, that is, it is soft and somewhat compressible.

HP:0025766.name: Abnormal affect
HP:0025766.definition: An anomaly in intensity, frequency, or duration of the verbal or behavioral expression of emotions, feelings, or thoughts.

HP:0025767.name: Abnormal positive emotional state
HP:0025767.definition: Persistent and pathologically elevated emotional experiences, preoccupations, or internal state that may arise spontaneously or may be related to positive perceptions of self, the world, and the future.

HP:0025768.name: Inappropriate elation
HP:0025768.definition: A feeling of cheerfulness expressed in speech or actions, including facial expressions, movements, or gesticulations, that is considered beyond the norm for the context and interactions. It is a sustained elevated emotional state that is generally not responsive to contextual cues and frequently stands out for being inappropriate or out of place in a social circumstance.

HP:0025769.name: Disordered formal thought process
HP:0025769.definition: An abnormality in the dynamic mode, rate, or form of thought processes as recognized from the flow of ideas expressed in speech. Successive thoughts and speech are easily diverted by external stimuli or internal superficial associations. Unable to maintain a constant train of thought and loose themselves in side issues, losing the thread and are unable to recover it. Superficial connections appear to drive the subject matter.

HP:0025771.name: Ruminations
HP:0025771.definition: Recurrent thoughts that have a thematic thread that is typically familiar to the individual and are often willfully brought forth or occur in the context of an anxious preoccupation or worry about a relevant concern which may be out of proportion to the context. Ruminations may be of normal thinking rate and are characterized by a recurring theme that usually has a negative connotation.

HP:0025772.name: Abnormal lexical patterns
HP:0025772.definition: A persistent abnormality in patterns or meanings of expressed language. Words and phrases are disorganized in relationship to each other and often used incorrectly or inappropriately for the context and background culture of the person.

HP:0025773.name: Abnormal semantics
HP:0025773.definition: Odd use of words that are out of context and inappropriate for the social situation.

HP:0025774.name: Idiosyncratic use of words
HP:0025774.definition: Words or phrases and their expression that are used in a manner that is not consistent with the current and accepted meaning for the context and social circumstance. This does not apply to peer or culture driven novel uses of words that are accepted within the given social circles.

HP:0025775.name: Tangential speech
HP:0025775.definition: Patterns of expressed speech that have many words to describe a feature, but are themselves vague and approximations. The speech does not get to the point, but rather seems to go around and around and is inconcise and difficult to grasp the primary issue or purpose of the communicated words.

HP:0025776.name: Thought insertion
HP:0025776.definition: The experience that thoughts are forced into the conscious awareness by external and foreign entities. The affected individual typically does not recognize the thoughts as coming from themselves and may develop secondary delusional ideas to explain the source of the process.

HP:0025777.name: Thought broadcasting
HP:0025777.definition: The experience that thoughts are being broadcasted from their head/conscious experience, some report that their thoughts are escaping, while others may believe that their thoughts are being picked up by a nearby receiver only to be further propagated. The person subsequently believes that everyone knows what they are thinking and feels that they have no privacy.

HP:0025778.name: Thought echo
HP:0025778.definition: The personal experience that thoughts are echoing around them and that they are hearing their own thoughts as they are experiencing them internally.

HP:0025779.name: Disorder of thought content
HP:0025779.definition: Thought content disorders are characterized by abnormal beliefs and convictions (that are to be assessed given the culture and personal background of the affected individual).

HP:0025780.name: Abnormal volitional state
HP:0025780.definition: An abnormality of internal states of motivation or drive that compromise, or interfere with, the ability of the person to attend to basic personal, social, or vocational activities.

HP:0025781.name: Abnormally rapid thought process
HP:0025781.definition: Increased rate or speed of thoughts.

HP:0025782.name: Abnormal syntax
HP:0025782.definition: Persistent abnormalities in sentence structure exceeding that of the context and background culture of the person.

HP:0025783.name: Diagnostic behavioral phenotype
HP:0025783.definition: The Human Phenotype Ontology provides terms to describe specific phenotypic abnormalities rather than disease diagnoses. Nevertheless, it is common for descriptions such as 'Autism' to be used to describe individuals affected with Mendelian forms of neurodevelopmental disease and many other conditions. If possible, we recommend annotation using specific terms in other branchs of the Atypical behavior subontology, but if this is not possible, then terms from this branch may be used.

HP:0025784.name: Word salad
HP:0025784.definition: Speech that consists of a series of recognizable words that are randomly strung together with no meaningful connection.

HP:0025785.name: Abnormal preoccupation
HP:0025785.definition: Preoccupations refers to being absorbed in any particular thought, activity, or concern that captures the attention of the individual. It may have a positive or negative connotation.

HP:0025786.name: Intraosseous lipoma
HP:0025786.definition: Intraosseous lipomas are rare benign lesions composed of mature fat that reside within the intramedullary canal.

HP:0025787.name: Paraphilia
HP:0025787.definition: Intense and typically recurring sexual arousal to atypical objects, fantasies, places, or individuals that frequently, but not always, lead to engagement of non-conventional sexual acts. This is a broad class of desires and behaviors that may include innocuous fetish behavior to illegal behaviors involving non-consenting individuals.

HP:0025788.name: Radiographic modifier
HP:0025788.definition: A characteristic of a lesion on radiography.

HP:0025789.name: Radiolucent
HP:0025789.definition: Applies to a lesion that allows x-rays to penetrate through them and expose the receptor (radiolucency). Soft tissues appear black or dark on the processed radiograph and are called radiolucent.

HP:0025790.name: Radiodense
HP:0025790.definition: Applies to a lesion that attenuates X-rays and appears radiodense (white) on a radiograph.

HP:0025791.name: Delusion of guilt
HP:0025791.definition: Delusional belief of one's personal guilt for an event, real or imagined, and that one caused an outcome that is somehow catastrophic. It is generally impossible or fantastical that this could have happened in the manner believed by the person, that they were somehow responsible for an event despite not be anywhere near where it allegedly occurred.

HP:0025793.name: Abnormal change in sexual drive
HP:0025793.definition: An abnormal change in libido (sexual desire), typically accompanied by an altered frequency of sexual activity compared to from a person's previous norm.

HP:0025794.name: Reduced MHC I cell surface expression
HP:0025794.definition: Expression of major histocompatibility complex class I molecules at the cell surface is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0025795.name: Positive urine infectious agent test
HP:0025795.definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in the urine positive (abnormal).

HP:0025796.name: Positive urine Legionella pneumophila antigen test
HP:0025796.definition: Demonstration of an antigen specific to Legionella pneumophila in urine.

HP:0025797.name: Unilateral sensorineural hearing impairment
HP:0025797.definition: A form of sensorineural hearing impairment that affects one ear.

HP:0025798.name: Abnormal wrist morphology
HP:0025798.definition: Any structural anomaly of the wrist.

HP:0025799.name: Abnormal wrist physiology
HP:0025799.definition: Any functional anomaly of the wrist.

HP:0025800.name: Wrist instability
HP:0025800.definition: Subjective or objective feeling of clunking/clicking in the wrist with movement, wrist giving way or difficulty twisting objects.

HP:0025801.name: Nail elevation
HP:0025801.definition: Elevation of the nail from the nail bed.

HP:0025802.name: Talipes varus
HP:0025802.definition: Inversion of the foot, resulting in the outer side of the sole only touching the ground; usually some degree of talipes equinus is associated with it, and often talipes cavus.

HP:0025803.name: Mucocutaneous lesion painful
HP:0025803.definition: Applies to pain that colocalizes with lesions in the skin or mucous membranes.

HP:0025804.name: Painful lymphadenopathy
HP:0025804.definition: Applies to pain that is localizes to a swollen lymph node.

HP:0025805.name: Absent circulating T cells
HP:0025805.definition: Absence of detectable circulating T cells, commonly characterized as CD3+ lymphocytes, in the blood. These may include both TCR alpha/beta and gamma/delta T cells. Usually, less than 50 T cells per microlitre is considered to be an absence.

HP:0025806.name: Abnormal total B cell count
HP:0025806.definition: The absolute number of B cells in the blood, per microliter is above or below the upper limits of normal of the reference range for the appropriate sex and age-group.

HP:0025807.name: Decreased natural killer cell degranulation
HP:0025807.definition: Abnormal decrease of NK cell degranulation in response to stimulation, commonly measured through surface CD107a expression in response to cocultivation with a murine cell line. Other methods may be used by different laboratories.

HP:0025808.name: Decreased natural killer cell-induced killing of target cells

HP:0025809.name: Generalized scaling
HP:0025809.definition: Desquamation (scaling) involving nearly all of the surface of the skin.

HP:0025810.name: Ichthyosis linearis circumflexa
HP:0025810.definition: A type of ichthyosis characterized by migratory, annular and polycyclic erythematous patches with double-edged scales at the periphery of the lesions.

HP:0025811.name: Trichorrhexis invaginata
HP:0025811.definition: A type of hair shaft dysmorphology in which the proximal part of the hair shaft overlaps the distal part, showing a bamboo-like appearance. This feature is pathognomic for Netherton syndrome, and can be ascertained by light microscopy.

HP:0025813.name: Eyebrow scaling skin
HP:0025813.definition: Loss of the outer layer of the epidermis in the area of the eyebrow in large, scale-like flakes.

HP:0025814.name: Patchy stratum granulosum of epidermis
HP:0025814.definition: The stratum granulosum of the epidermis (granular layer) displays areas of discontinuity.

HP:0025815.name: Absent stratum granulosum of epidermis
HP:0025815.definition: The stratum granulosum of the epidermis (granular layer) cannot be observed.

HP:0025816.name: Hypogranulosis
HP:0025816.definition: The height (thickness) of the stratum granulosum of the epidermis (granular layer) is below the lower limit of normal but the stratum granulosum is visible.

HP:0025817.name: Psoriasiform acanthosis
HP:0025817.definition: A type of epidermal acanthosis characterized by regular elongated rete ridges.

HP:0025818.name: Intraepidermal microabscess formation
HP:0025818.definition: Infiltrating neutrophils in the epidermis, mostly into the stratum corneum. Characteristic for psoriasis.

HP:0025819.name: Palmoplantar pealing
HP:0025819.definition: Splitting within the the upper lyer (stratum corneum) of the epidermis clinically characterized by shedding of dead cells from the outermost layer of skin.

HP:0025820.name: Offspring of consanguineous relationship
HP:0025820.definition: The parents of the index patient are related as second cousins or closer.

HP:0025821.name: Lower eyelid erythema
HP:0025821.definition: Redness of the skin of the lower eyelid, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.

HP:0025822.name: Upper eyelid erythema
HP:0025822.definition: Redness of the skin of the upper eyelid, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.

HP:0025823.name: Positive provocative functional shoulder test
HP:0025823.definition: Abnormal result of a physical test of the shoulder that attempts to provoke pain in order to diagnosis a specific injury.

HP:0025824.name: Decreased neutrophil phagocytosis
HP:0025824.definition: Abnormal decrease of neutrophil phagocytic activity, commonly measured after stimulation with E. coli using flow cytometry.

HP:0025825.name: Decreased neutrophil adhesion
HP:0025825.definition: Abnormal decrease of neutrophil adhesion capacity, commonly measured as surface expression of CD18, CD11a or CD11b using flow cytometry.

HP:0025826.name: Severely decreased neutrophil count
HP:0025826.definition: Severe decrease in circulating neutrophils, usually characterized as fewer than 500 neutrophils per microlitre.

HP:0025827.name: Abnormal Th1 T cell proportion
HP:0025827.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of Th1 cells, commonly characterized through the intracellular synthesis of IFNg or surface expression of CXCR3, measured as proportion of total CD3+CD4+ T cells, usually after stimulation. The stimulation is usually unspecific and may include the use of anti-CD3 beads or antibodies or the use of phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) with ionomycin. Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025828.name: Increased Th1 T cell proportion
HP:0025828.definition: Abnormal increase of Th1 cells, commonly characterized through the intracellular synthesis of IFNg or surface expression of CXCR3, measured as proportion of total CD3+CD4+ T cells, usually after stimulation. The stimulation is usually unspecific and may include the use of anti-CD3 beads or antibodies or the use of phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) with ionomycin. Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025829.name: Decreased Th1 T cell proportion
HP:0025829.definition: Abnormal decrease of Th1 cells, commonly characterized through the intracellular synthesis of IFNg or surface expression of CXCR3, measured as proportion of total CD3+CD4+ T cells, usually after stimulation. The stimulation is usually unspecific and may include the use of anti-CD3 beads or antibodies or the use of phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) with ionomycin. Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025830.name: Abnormal Th17 T cell proportion
HP:0025830.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of Th17 cells, commonly characterized through the intracellular synthesis of IL-17 or surface expression of CCR6, measured as proportion of total CD3+CD4+ T cells, usually after stimulation. The stimulation is usually unspecific and may include the use of anti-CD3 beads or antibodies, the use of phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) with ionomycin, or staphylococcal enterotoxin B (SEB). Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025831.name: Increased Th17 T cell proportion
HP:0025831.definition: Abnormal increase of Th17 cells, commonly characterized through the intracellular synthesis of IL-17 or surface expression of CCR6, measured as proportion of total CD3+CD4+ T cells, usually after stimulation. The stimulation is usually unspecific and may include the use of anti-CD3 beads or antibodies, the use of phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) with ionomycin, or staphylococcal enterotoxin B (SEB). Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025832.name: Decreased Th17 T cell proportion
HP:0025832.definition: Abnormal decrease of Th17 cells, commonly characterized through the intracellular synthesis of IL-17 or surface expression of CCR6, measured as proportion of total CD3+CD4+ T cells, usually after stimulation. The stimulation is usually unspecific and may include the use of anti-CD3 beads or antibodies, the use of phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) with ionomycin, or staphylococcal enterotoxin B (SEB). Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025833.name: Decreased PMA/ionomycin-induced T-cell proliferation
HP:0025833.definition: Abnormal decrease of T cell proliferation in response to phorbol-12-myristate-13-acetate (PMA) and ionomycin stimulation. This is commonly measured through intracellular expression of Ki67, decreasing surface expression of carboxyfluorescein diacetate (CFSE), or 3H-thymidine incorporation. Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025834.name: Decreased PHA-induced T-cell proliferation
HP:0025834.definition: Abnormal decrease of T cell proliferation in response to stimulation with phytohaemagglutinin. This is commonly measured through intracellular expression of Ki67, decreasing surface expression of carboxyfluorescein diacetate (CFSE), or 3H-thymidine incorporation. Length of incubation and strength of stimulation may vary between laboratories.

HP:0025835.name: Decreased CD8+ T cell degranulation
HP:0025835.definition: Abnormal decrease of CD8-positive T cell degranulation in response to stimulation, commonly measured through surface CD107a expression in response to cocultivation with a murine cell line. Other methods may be used by different laboratories.

HP:0025836.name: Increased CD8+ T cell proportion
HP:0025836.definition: Abnormal increase of cytotoxic CD3+CD8+ T cells, measured as percentage of total CD3+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group. These are usually measured within the TCR alpha/beta positive population.

HP:0025837.name: Abnormal proportion of RTE CD4+ T cells
HP:0025837.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of the recent thymic emmigrant (RTE) CD4+ T cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD45RA+, CD45RO-, or CD27+, with the necessary expression of CD31+, measured as percentage of total CD4+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group. These cells are sometimes also characterized as CD62L+ and CCR7+.

HP:0025838.name: Increased proportion of RTE CD4+ T cells
HP:0025838.definition: Abnormal increase of the recent thymic emmigrant (RTE) CD4+ T cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD45RA+, CD45RO-, or CD27+, with the necessary expression of CD31+, measured as percentage of total CD4+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group. These cells are sometimes also characterized as CD62L+ and CCR7+.

HP:0025839.name: Decreased proportion of RTE CD4+ T cells
HP:0025839.definition: Abnormal decrease of the recent thymic emmigrant (RTE) CD4+ T cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD45RA+, CD45RO-, or CD27+, with the necessary expression of CD31+, measured as percentage of total CD4+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group. These cells are sometimes also characterized as CD62L+ and CCR7+.

HP:0025840.name: Abnormal HLA DR+ CD4+ T cell proportion
HP:0025840.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of the activated HLA-DR+ CD4+ T cell subpopulation, measured as percentage of total CD4+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0025841.name: Decreased HLA DR+ CD4+ T cell proportion
HP:0025841.definition: Abnormal reduction of the activated HLA-DR+ CD4+ T cell subpopulation, measured as percentage of total CD4+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0025842.name: Abnormal HLA DR+ CD8+ T cell proportion
HP:0025842.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of the activated HLA-DR+ CD8+ T cell subpopulation, measured as percentage of total CD8+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0025843.name: Increased HLA DR+ CD8+ T cell proportion
HP:0025843.definition: Abnormal increase of the activated HLA-DR+ CD8+ T cell subpopulation, measured as percentage of total CD8+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0025844.name: Decreased HLA DR+ CD8+ T cell proportion
HP:0025844.definition: Abnormal decrease of the activated HLA-DR+ CD8+ T cell subpopulation, measured as percentage of total CD8+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0025845.name: Abnormal TCR repertoire
HP:0025845.definition: Abnormal distribution of the TCR repertoire expressed on T cells. This usually means oligoclonality (fewer TCR clonotypes compared to a healthy age-matched control) or monoclonality (one dominant TCR clone detected). This may be measured through different methods depending on the lab, but commonly include TCR spectratyping or TCRB CDR3 sequencing.

HP:0025846.name: Decreased natural killer cell perforin expression
HP:0025846.definition: Abnormal decrease of intracellular expression of perforin within NK cells, commonly characterized as CD3-CD19- and CD16+ or CD56+ lymphocytes, ex vivo.

HP:0025847.name: Fish allergy
HP:0025847.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against fish.

HP:0025848.name: Shellfish allergy
HP:0025848.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against shellfish (an aquatic shelled mollusc such as an oyster or mussel, or a crustacean such as a crab or shrimp).

HP:0025849.name: Localized along nerve distribution
HP:0025849.definition: Refers to findings sich as paresthesias or weakness that are distributed according to the anatomical location of a periperipheral nerve.

HP:0030000.name: EMG: repetitive nerve stimulation abnormality
HP:0030000.definition: Abnormality observed upon electromyography when nerve studied is electrically stimulated six to ten times at 2 or 3 Hertz.

HP:0030001.name: Lagophthalmos
HP:0030001.definition: A condition in which the eyelids do not close to cover the eye completely.

HP:0030002.name: Nocturnal lagophthalmos
HP:0030002.definition: The inability to close the eyelids during sleep.

HP:0030003.name: Paralytic lagophthalmos
HP:0030003.definition: A type of lagophthalmos that occurs in association with facial nerve palsy.

HP:0030004.name: Cicatricial lagophthalmos
HP:0030004.definition: A type of lagophthalmos that occurs following trauma or surgery.

HP:0030005.name: Capillary leak
HP:0030005.definition: An acute phenomenon characterized by hypotension and anasarca due to the loss of plasma volume into peripheral tissues, with evidence of decreased plasma volume (hemoconcentration) and protein loss from the intravascular space (hypoalbuminemia) during acute episodes.

HP:0030006.name: Single fiber EMG abnormality
HP:0030006.definition: Abnormality in single fiber EMG recording, a technique that allows identification of action potentials (APs) from individual muscle fibers.

HP:0030007.name: EMG: positive sharp waves
HP:0030007.definition: These are spontaneous firing action potentials stimulated by needle movement of an injured muscle fiber. There is propagation to, but not past, the needle tip. This inhibits the display of the negative deflection of the waveform.

HP:0030008.name: Cervical agenesis
HP:0030008.definition: Congenital absence of the uterine cervix.

HP:0030009.name: Cervical insufficiency
HP:0030009.definition: A cervix that shows a painless dilation and shortening during the second trimester of pregnancy with resultant recurrent pregnancy loss or delivery is considered incompetent

HP:0030010.name: Hydrometrocolpos
HP:0030010.definition: Hydrometrocolpos is an accumulation of uterine and vaginal secretions as well as menstrual blood in the uterus and vagina.

HP:0030011.name: Imperforate hymen
HP:0030011.definition: A congenital disorder where the hymen (a membrane that surrounds or partially covers the external vaginal opening) does not have an opening and completely obstructs the vagina.

HP:0030014.name: Female sexual dysfunction
HP:0030014.definition: A problem occurring during any phase of the female sexual response cycle that prevents the individual from experiencing satisfaction from the sexual activity

HP:0030015.name: Female anorgasmia
HP:0030015.definition: The persistent of recurrent difficulty, delay in, or absence of attaining orgasm following sufficient sexual stimulation and arousal.

HP:0030016.name: Dyspareunia
HP:0030016.definition: Recurrent or persistent genital pain associated with sexual intercourse.

HP:0030017.name: Vaginismus
HP:0030017.definition: Recurrent or persistent involuntary spasms of the musculature of the outer third of the vagina that interferes with vaginal penetration, and which causes personal distress.

HP:0030022.name: Question mark ear
HP:0030022.definition: Cleft between the helix and the lobe.

HP:0030023.name: Quelprud nodule
HP:0030023.definition: Small cartilaginous prominence on the posterior concha.

HP:0030024.name: Pretragal ectopia
HP:0030024.definition: Variably shaped, cartilage-containing tissue anterior to the external auditory meatus.

HP:0030025.name: Auricular pit
HP:0030025.definition: Small indentation in the lower part of the ascending helix, concha, or in the crus helix.

HP:0030026.name: Squared superior portion of helix
HP:0030026.definition: Flattening instead of curving or rounded superior helix, allowing the superior helix to run more horizontally than usual.

HP:0030027.name: Abnormal nasal cartilage morphology
HP:0030027.definition: A morphological anomaly of the nasal cartilage.

HP:0030028.name: Absent nasal cartilage
HP:0030028.definition: Lack of a palpable nasal cartilage.

HP:0030029.name: Splayed fingers
HP:0030029.definition: Divergence of digits along the A/P axis (in the plane of the palm).

HP:0030030.name: Absent ray
HP:0030030.definition: The absence of all phalanges of a digit and the associated metacarpal /metatarsal.

HP:0030031.name: Small toe
HP:0030031.definition: Significant reduction in both length and girth of the toe compared to the contralateral toe, or alternatively, compared to a typical toe size for an age-matched individual.

HP:0030032.name: Partial absence of foot
HP:0030032.definition: An incomplete absence of the foot, with no bony elements distal to the tarsals, but with preservation of some or all of the tarsals.

HP:0030033.name: Small finger
HP:0030033.definition: Significant reduction in both length and girth of the finger compared to the contralateral finger, or alternatively, compared to a typical finger size for an age-matched individual.

HP:0030034.name: Glomerular basement membrane lamellation
HP:0030034.definition: Presence of abnormal additional layers of the basement membrane of the glomerulus.

HP:0030035.name: Struvite nephrolithiasis
HP:0030035.definition: Presence of struvite (magnesium ammonium phosphate) containing calculi (kidney stones).

HP:0030036.name: Isothenuria
HP:0030036.definition: Inability of the kidneys to produce either concentrated or dilute urine.

HP:0030038.name: Enchondroma
HP:0030038.definition: A solitary, benign, intramedullary cartilage tumor that is often found in the short tubular bones of the hands and feet, distal femur, and proximal humerus.

HP:0030039.name: Fused thoracic vertebrae
HP:0030039.definition: A congenital anomaly characterized by a joining (fusion) of two or more thoracic vertebral bodies with one another.

HP:0030040.name: Fused lumbar vertebrae
HP:0030040.definition: A congenital anomaly characterized by a joining (fusion) of two or more lumbar vertebral bodies with one another.

HP:0030041.name: Schmorl's node
HP:0030041.definition: A Schmorl's node is the herniation of nucleus pulposus through the cartilaginous and bony end plate into the body of the adjacent vertebra.

HP:0030042.name: Incomplete ossification of pubis
HP:0030042.definition: Failure to complete ossification (maturation and calcification) of the pubic bone.

HP:0030043.name: Hip subluxation
HP:0030043.definition: A partial dislocation of the hip joint, whereby the head of the femur is partially displaced from the socket.

HP:0030044.name: Flexion contracture of digit
HP:0030044.definition: A bent (flexed) finger or toe joint that cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement of joints.

HP:0030046.name: Hypoglycosylation of alpha-dystroglycan
HP:0030046.definition: A reduction in the degree of glycosylation of alpha-dystroglycan in muscle tissue.

HP:0030047.name: Abnormal lateral ventricle morphology
HP:0030047.definition: A morphological anomaly of the lateral ventricle.

HP:0030048.name: Colpocephaly
HP:0030048.definition: Colpocephaly is an anatomic finding in the brain manifested by occipital horns that are disproportionately enlarged in comparison with other parts of the lateral ventricles.

HP:0030049.name: Brain abscess
HP:0030049.definition: A collection of pus, immune cells, and other material in the brain.

HP:0030050.name: Narcolepsy
HP:0030050.definition: An abnormal phenomenon characterized by a classic tetrad of excessive daytime sleepiness with irresistible sleep attacks, cataplexy (sudden bilateral loss of muscle tone), hypnagogic hallucinations, and sleep paralysis.

HP:0030051.name: Tip-toe gait
HP:0030051.definition: An abnormal gait pattern characterized by the failure of the heel to contact the floor at the onset of stance during gait.

HP:0030052.name: Inguinal freckling
HP:0030052.definition: The presence in the inguinal region (groin) of an increased number of freckles, small circular spots on the skin that are darker than the surrounding skin because of deposits of melanin.

HP:0030054.name: Perifollicular fibrosis
HP:0030054.definition: Presence of excess fibrous connective tissue surrounding hair follicules.

HP:0030055.name: Hyperconvex toenail
HP:0030055.definition: When viewed on end (with the tip of the toe pointing toward the examiner's eye) the curve of the toenail forms a tighter curve of convexity.

HP:0030056.name: Uncombable hair
HP:0030056.definition: Hair that is disorderly, stands out from the scalp, and cannot be combed flat.

HP:0030057.name: Autoimmune antibody positivity
HP:0030057.definition: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against the organism's own cells or tissues.

HP:0030058.name: Sickled erythrocytes
HP:0030058.definition: An irreversible distortion of the morphology of an erythrocyte such that the cells are elongated and curved, resembling the blade of a sickle (the hand-held agricultural tool traditionally used to harvest grains).

HP:0030059.name: Mitochondrial depletion
HP:0030059.definition: An abnormal reduction in mitochondrial DNA content of cells.

HP:0030060.name: Nervous tissue neoplasm
HP:0030060.definition: A neoplasm derived from nervous tissue (not necessarily a neoplasm located in the nervous system).

HP:0030061.name: Neuroectodermal neoplasm
HP:0030061.definition: A neoplasm arising in the neuroectoderm, the portion of the ectoderm of the early embryo that gives rise to the central and peripheral nervous systems, including some glial cells.

HP:0030062.name: Craniopharyngioma
HP:0030062.definition: A benign pituitary-region neoplasm that originates from Rathke's pouch. Craniopharyngiomas are benign slow growing tumors that are located within the sellar and para sellar region of the central nervous system.

HP:0030063.name: Neuroepithelial neoplasm
HP:0030063.definition: A neoplasm composed of neural epithelium, not necessarily a neoplasm located in the neural epithelium or neuroepithelium.

HP:0030064.name: Neurocytoma
HP:0030064.definition: A benign brain tumor composed of neural elements which most often arise from the septum pellucidum and the walls of the lateral ventricles.

HP:0030065.name: Primitive neuroectodermal tumor
HP:0030065.definition: A tumor that originates in cells from the primitive neural crest. This group of tumors is characteirzed by the presence of primitive cells with elements of neuronal and/or glial differentiation.

HP:0030066.name: Ependymoblastoma
HP:0030066.definition: A highly malignant embryonal tumor of infancy and young childhood characterized by neuroectodermal elements organized in distinctive multilayered rosettes. Ependymoblastomas are large lesions that occur in the supratentorial compartment, typically displaying a physical connection to the ventricular system.

HP:0030067.name: Peripheral primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm
HP:0030067.definition: A primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm that occurs extracranially in soft tissue and bone.

HP:0030068.name: Olfactory esthesioneuroblastoma
HP:0030068.definition: A malignant olfactory neuroblastoma arising from the olfactory epithelium of the superior nasal cavity and cribriform plate.

HP:0030069.name: Primary central nervous system lymphoma
HP:0030069.definition: A form of extranodal, high-grade non-Hodgkin B-cell neoplasm, usually large cell or immunoblastic type that originates in the brain, leptomeninges, spinal cord, or eyes and typically remains confined to the CNS.

HP:0030070.name: Central primitive neuroectodermal tumor
HP:0030070.definition: A primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm that occurs in the central nervous system.

HP:0030071.name: Medulloepithelioma
HP:0030071.definition: A primitive neuroectodermal tumor that originates from the cells of the embryonic medullary canal.

HP:0030072.name: Paranasal sinus neoplasm
HP:0030072.definition: A tumor that originates in the paranasal sinus.

HP:0030074.name: Chemodectoma
