HP:0009182.name: Triangular shaped middle phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009182.definition: Triangular shaped middle phalanx of the 5th (little) finger. A triangular or so called delta shaped phalanx is a typical result after a bracket epiphysis of the affected phalanx.

HP:0009183.name: Joint contracture of the 5th finger
HP:0009183.definition: Chronic loss of joint motion in the 5th finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue. The term camptodactyly of the 5th finger is used if the distal and/or proximal interphalangeal joints are affected.

HP:0009184.name: Contracture of the distal interphalangeal joint of the 5th finger
HP:0009184.definition: Chronic loss of joint motion of the distal interphalangeal joint of the 5th finger due to structural changes in non-bony tissue.

HP:0009185.name: Contracture of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the 5th finger
HP:0009185.definition: Proximal interphalangeal (PIP) flexion deformity of the little finger. That is, the PIP joint of a little finger is bent (flexed) and cannot be straightened actively or passively. It is thus a chronic loss of joint motion due to structural changes in muscle, tendons, ligaments, or skin that prevents normal movement.

HP:0009186.name: Contracture of the metacarpophalangeal joint of the 5th finger

HP:0009193.definition: A pseudoepiphysis is a secondary ossification center distinct from the normal epiphysis. The normal metacarpal epiphyses are located at the distal ends of the metacarpal bones. HP:0009196.name: Absent metacarpal epiphyses

HP:0009197.name: Bracket epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 5th finger

HP:0009204.name: Bracket epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger

HP:0009322.definition: An abnormality of the middle phalanx of the third finger in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side.

HP:0009323.name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009323.definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of the phalanx.

HP:0009324.name: Enlarged epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009324.definition: Abnormally large size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009325.name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009325.definition: Fragmented appearance of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009326.name: Irregular epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009326.definition: Irregular radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009327.name: Ivory epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009327.definition: Sclerosis of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

HP:0009328.name: Pseudoepiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009328.definition: A secondary ossification center in the middle phalanx of the third finger that is distinct from the normal epiphysis that does not contribute to the longitudinal growth of a tubular bone.

HP:0009329.name: Small epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009329.definition: Abnormally small size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009330.name: Stippling of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009330.definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009331.name: Triangular epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009331.definition: A triangular appearance of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger of the hand. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat.

HP:0009332.name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger

HP:0009333.name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger

HP:0009334.name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger

HP:0009335.name: Absent epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009335.definition: Absence of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009336.name: Bracket epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009336.definition: An abnormality of the distal phalanx of the third finger in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side.

HP:0009337.name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009337.definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of the phalanx.

HP:0009338.name: Enlarged epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009338.definition: Abnormally large size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009339.name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009339.definition: Fragmented appearance of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009340.name: Irregular epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009340.definition: Irregular radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009341.name: Ivory epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009341.definition: Sclerosis of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

HP:0009342.name: Pseudoepiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009342.definition: A secondary ossification center in the distal phalanx of the third finger that is distinct from the normal epiphysis that does not contribute to the longitudinal growth of a tubular bone.

HP:0009343.name: Small epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009343.definition: Abnormally small size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009344.name: Stippling of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009344.definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009345.name: Triangular epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009345.definition: A triangular appearance of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger of the hand. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat.

HP:0009346.name: Absent epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009346.definition: Absence of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009347.name: Bracket epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009347.definition: An abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the third finger in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side.

HP:0009348.name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009348.definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of the phalanx.

HP:0009349.name: Enlarged epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009349.definition: Abnormally large size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009350.name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009350.definition: Fragmented appearance of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009351.name: Irregular epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009351.definition: Irregular radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009352.name: Ivory epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009352.definition: Sclerosis of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

HP:0009353.name: Pseudoepiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009353.definition: A secondary ossification center in the proximal phalanx of the third finger that is distinct from the normal epiphysis that does not contribute to the longitudinal growth of a tubular bone.

HP:0009354.name: Small epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009354.definition: Abnormally small size of the epiphysis located at the proximal end of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009355.name: Stippling of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009355.definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger.

HP:0009356.name: Triangular epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009356.definition: A triangular appearance of the epiphysis of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger of the hand. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat.

HP:0009357.name: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger

HP:0009358.name: Abnormality of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger

HP:0009374.name: Broad phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0009374.definition: Increased width of the phalanges of the 5th finger.

HP:0009375.name: Bullet-shaped phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0009375.definition: A fifth finger with short and wide phalanx that tapers distally. Bullet-shaped phalanges lack the normal diaphyseal constriction.

HP:0009376.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0009376.definition: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the 5th finger.

HP:0009377.name: Patchy sclerosis of 5th finger phalanx
HP:0009377.definition: Uneven increase in bone density of one or more of the phalanges of the 5th finger.

HP:0009378.name: Triangular shaped phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0009378.definition: Triangular shaped phalanges of the 5th (little) finger. A triangular or so called delta shaped phalanx is a typical result after a bracket epiphysis of the affected phalanx.

HP:0009379.name: Rhomboid or triangular shaped 5th finger distal phalanx
HP:0009379.definition: Rhomboid or triangular shaped 5th (little) finger distal phalanx.

HP:0009380.name: Finger aplasia
HP:0009380.definition: A developmental defect resulting in the presence of fewer than the normal number of fingers (i.e., aplasia of one or more fingers).

HP:0009381.name: Short finger
HP:0009381.definition: Abnormally short finger associated with developmental hypoplasia.

HP:0009382.name: Absent epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009382.definition: Absence of one or more epiphyses of the 5th finger.

HP:0009383.name: Bracket epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009383.definition: An abnormality of the fifth finger in which the epiphysis surrounds a phalangeal bone, having a bracket-like form and reaching from the proximal side of a phalanx to the distal side.

HP:0009384.name: Cone-shaped epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009384.definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphyses of the 5th finger of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of a phalanx.

HP:0009385.name: Enlarged epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009385.definition: Abnormally large size of the epiphyses of the 5th finger with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0009386.name: Fragmentation of the epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009386.definition: Fragmented appearance of the epiphyses of the 5th finger.

HP:0009387.name: Irregular epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009387.definition: Irregular radiographic opacity of the epiphyses of the 5th finger.

HP:0009388.name: Ivory epiphyses of the 5th finger
HP:0009388.definition: Sclerosis of the epiphyses of the 5th finger, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

HP:0031769.name: Peripheral fixation
HP:0031769.definition: Fixation of an object in a peripheral area of the retina.

HP:0031770.name: Epicanthus palpebralis
HP:0031770.definition: A type of epicanthus in which a medial vertical fold is present between upper and lower lids.

HP:0031771.name: Epicanthus tarsalis
HP:0031771.definition: A type of epicanthus in which a primarily upper lid fold is present.

HP:0012171.name: Stereotypical hand wringing
HP:0012171.definition: Habitual clasping and wringing of the hands in the middle of the body, similar to a hand-washing movement.

HP:0012172.name: Stereotypical body rocking
HP:0012172.definition: Habitual repetitive movement of the entire body, front to back or side to side.

HP:0012173.name: Orthostatic tachycardia
HP:0012173.definition: An increase in heart rate with standing of 30 beats per minute or more.

HP:0012174.name: Glioblastoma multiforme
HP:0012174.definition: A tumor arising from glia in the central nervous system with macroscopic regions of necrosis and hemorrhage. Microscopically, glioblastoma multiforme is characterized by regions of pseudopalisading necrosis, pleomorphic nuclei and cells, and microvascular proliferation.

HP:0012175.name: Resistance to activated protein C
HP:0012175.definition: Poor anticoagulant response to activated protein C. A plasma is termed 'APC resistant' when the addition of exogenous APC fails to prolong its clotting time in an activated partial thromboplastin time assay.

HP:0012176.name: Abnormal natural killer cell morphology
HP:0012176.definition: An anomaly of the natural killer cell, which is a lymphocyte that can spontaneously kill a variety of target cells without prior antigenic activation via germline encoded activation receptors. It also regulates immune responses via cytokine release and direct contact with other cells.

HP:0012177.name: Abnormal natural killer cell physiology
HP:0012177.definition: Abnormal response of natural killer (NK) cells to stimuli.

HP:0012178.name: obsolete Reduced natural killer cell activity

HP:0012179.name: Craniofacial dystonia
HP:0012179.definition: A form of focal dystonia affecting the face and especially the jaw that is induced by the act of speaking. It is an involuntary contraction of the masticatory muscles, resulting in dysarthria or dysphagia.

HP:0012180.name: Cystic medial necrosis
HP:0012180.definition: A disorder of large arteries, in particular the aorta, characterized by an accumulation of basophilic ground substance in the media with cyst-like lesions associated with degenerative changes of collagen, elastin and the vascular smooth muscle cells.

HP:0012181.name: Entrapment neuropathy
HP:0012181.definition: Malfunction of a peripheral nerve resulting from mechanical compression of the nerve roots from internal or external causes and leading to a conduction block or axonal loss.

HP:0012182.name: Oropharyngeal squamous cell carcinoma
HP:0012182.definition: A squamous cell carcinoma that originates in the oropharnyx.

HP:0012183.name: Hyperplastic colonic polyposis
HP:0012183.definition: Presence of multiple hyperplastic polyps in the colon. Hyperplastic polyps are generally about 5 mm in size and show hyperplastic mucosal proliferation.

HP:0012184.name: Increased HDL cholesterol concentration
HP:0012184.definition: An elevated concentration of high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL) in the blood.

HP:0012185.name: Constrictive median neuropathy
HP:0012185.definition: Injury to the median nerve caused by its entrapment at the wrist as it traverses through the carpal tunnel. Clinically, constrictive median neuropathy is characterized by pain, paresthesia, and weakness in the median nerve distribution of the hand.

HP:0012186.name: Entrapment neuropathy of the ulnar nerve at elbow
HP:0012186.definition: An entrapment neuropathy of the ulnar nerve in the cubital tunnel (in the elbow) characterized by numbness in the ring and little fingers and weakness of the intrinsic muscles in the hand.

HP:0012187.name: Increased erythrocyte protoporphyrin concentration
HP:0012187.definition: Concentration of protoporphyrins in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0012188.name: Hyperemesis gravidarum
HP:0012188.definition: Excessive vomiting in early pregnancy, leading to the loss of 5% or more of body weight.

HP:0012189.name: Hodgkin lymphoma
HP:0012189.definition: A type of lymphoma characterized microscopically by multinucleated Reed-Sternberg cells.

HP:0012190.name: T-cell lymphoma
HP:0012190.definition: A type of lymphoma that originates in T-cells.

HP:0012191.name: B-cell lymphoma
HP:0012191.definition: A type of lymphoma that originates in B-cells.

HP:0012192.name: Cutaneous T-cell lymphoma
HP:0012192.definition: A type of T-cell lymphoma that exhibits malignant infiltration of the skin.

HP:0012193.name: Anaplastic large-cell lymphoma
HP:0012193.definition: A type of T-cell lymphoma that is characterized by so-called hallmark cells with a pleomorphic appearance that express the CD30 antigen, are lobulated, and have indented nuclei.

HP:0012194.name: Episodic hemiplegia
HP:0012194.definition: Transient episodes of weakness of the arm, leg, and in some cases the face on one side of the body.

HP:0012196.name: Cheyne-Stokes respiration
HP:0012196.definition: An abnormal pattern of respiration characterized by cycles of respiration that are increasingly deeper then shallower with possible periods of apnea. Affected patients may display a 10 to 20 second episode of hypoventilation or apnea, followed by respiration of increased depth and frequency over the course of about one minute. The cycle repeats every 45 seconds to 3 minutes.

HP:0012197.name: Insulinoma
HP:0012197.definition: A type of tumor of the pancreatic beta cells that secretes excess insulin and can result in hypoglycemia.

HP:0012198.name: Juvenile colonic polyposis
HP:0012198.definition: The presence of more than 5 juvenile polyps of the colon. The term juvenile polyps refer to a special histopathology and not the age of onset as the polyp might be diagnosed at all ages. The juvenile polyp has a spherical appearance and is microscopically characterized by overgrowth of an oedematous lamina propria with inflammatory cells and cystic glands.

HP:0012199.name: Cluster headache
HP:0012199.definition: A type of headache characterized by repeated attacks of unilateral pain lasting 15 to 180 minutes and associated with local autonomic signs.

HP:0012200.name: Abnormality of prothrombin
HP:0012200.definition: An anomaly of clotting factor II, which is known as prothrombin, a vitamin K-dependent proenzyme that functions in the blood coagulation cascade.

HP:0012202.name: Increased serum bile acid concentration
HP:0012202.definition: An increase in the concentration of bile acid in the blood.

HP:0012203.name: Onychomycosis
HP:0012203.definition: A fungal infection of the toenails or fingernails that tends to cause the nails to thicken, discolor, disfigure, and split.

HP:0012204.name: Recurrent vulvovaginal candidiasis
HP:0012204.definition: Recurrent infection involving the vulva, vagina, and adjacent crural areas, whereby the causative agent belongs to the genus Candida.

HP:0012205.name: Globozoospermia
HP:0012205.definition: Any structural anomaly of the acrosome resulting in a round sperm head.

HP:0012206.name: Abnormal sperm motility
HP:0012206.definition: An anomaly of the mobility of ejaculated sperm.

HP:0012207.name: Reduced sperm motility
HP:0012207.definition: An abnormal reduction in the mobility of ejaculated sperm.

HP:0012208.name: Immotile sperm
HP:0012208.definition: A lack of mobility of ejaculated sperm.

HP:0012209.name: Juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia
HP:0012209.definition: Juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia (JMML) is a lethal myeloproliferative disease of young childhood characterized clinically by overproduction of myelomonocytic cells and by the in vitro phenotype of hematopoietic progenitor hypersensitivity to granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor.

HP:0012210.name: Abnormal renal morphology
HP:0012210.definition: Any structural anomaly of the kidney.

HP:0012211.name: Abnormal renal physiology
HP:0012211.definition: An abnormal functionality of the kidney.

HP:0012212.name: Abnormal glomerular filtration rate
HP:0012212.definition: An abnormally increased or reduced amount of fluid filtered out of plasma through glomerular capillary walls into Bowman's capsules per unit of time.

HP:0012213.name: Decreased glomerular filtration rate
HP:0012213.definition: An abnormal reduction in the volume of fluid filtered out of plasma through glomerular capillary walls into Bowman's capsules per unit of time.

HP:0012214.name: Increased glomerular filtration rate
HP:0012214.definition: An abnormal rise in the volume of water filtered out of plasma through glomerular capillary walls into Bowman's capsules per unit of time.

HP:0012215.name: Testicular microlithiasis
HP:0012215.definition: The deposition of calcium phosphate microliths within the seminiferous tubules.

HP:0012216.name: Entrapment neuropathy of suprascapular nerve
HP:0012216.definition: An entrapment neuropathy of the suprascapular nerve, presenting with shoulder weakness confined to the supraspinatus muscle (this muscle initiates shoulder abduction) or to the infraspinatus (this muscle externally rotates the arm), as well as with pain in the posterior part of the shoulder and upper periscapular region.

HP:0012217.name: Increased urinary porphobilinogen
HP:0012217.definition: The concentration of porphobilinogen in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0012218.name: Alveolar soft part sarcoma
HP:0012218.definition: A type of soft tissue sarcoma with a histological appearance reminiscent of alveoli because of its reticulated fibrous stroma enclosing groups of sarcoma cells, which resemble epithelial cells and are enclosed in alveoli walled with connective tissue.

HP:0012219.name: Erythema nodosum
HP:0012219.definition: An erythematous eruption commonly associated with drug reactions or infection and characterized by inflammatory nodules that are usually tender, multiple, and bilateral.

HP:0012220.name: Non-caseating epithelioid cell granulomatosis
HP:0012220.definition: The presence of multiple epithelioid cell granulomas consist of highly differentiated mononuclear phagocytes (epithelioid cells and giant cells) and lymphocytes, not exhibiting caseation (a form of necrosis in which the tissue changes into a dry, amorphous mass said to resemble cheese).

HP:0012221.name: Pretibial blistering
HP:0012221.definition: A type of blistering that affects the skin of the tibial region.

HP:0012222.name: Arachnoid hemangiomatosis
HP:0012222.definition: The presence of multiple hemangiomas in the arachnoid.

HP:0012223.name: Splenic rupture
HP:0012223.definition: A breach of the capsule of the spleen.

HP:0012224.name: Circulating immune complexes
HP:0012224.definition: Persistence of immune complexes in the blood circulation.

HP:0012226.name: Ovarian teratoma
HP:0012226.definition: The presence of a teratoma in the ovary.

HP:0012227.name: Urethral stricture
HP:0012227.definition: Narrowing of the urethra associated with inflammation or scar tissue.

HP:0012228.name: Tension-type headache
HP:0012228.definition: A type of headache that last hours with continuous pain of mild or moderate intensity, bilateral location, a pressing/tightening (non-pulsating) quality and that is not aggravated by routine physical activity such as walking or climbing stairs.

HP:0012229.name: CSF pleocytosis
HP:0012229.definition: An increased white blood cell count in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0012230.name: Rhegmatogenous retinal detachment
HP:0012230.definition: A type of retinal detachment associated with a retinal tear, that is, with a break in the retina that allows fluid to pass from the vitreous space into the subretinal space between the sensory retina and the retinal pigment epithelium.

HP:0012231.name: Exudative retinal detachment
HP:0012231.definition: A type of retinal detachment arising from damage to the outer blood-retinal barrier that allows fluid to access the subretinal space and separate the neurosensory retina from the retinal pigment epithelium.

HP:0012232.name: Shortened QT interval
HP:0012232.definition: Decreased time between the start of the Q wave and the end of the T wave as measured by the electrocardiogram (EKG).

HP:0012233.name: Intramuscular hematoma
HP:0012233.definition: Blood clot formed within muscle tissue following leakage of blood into the tissue.

HP:0012234.name: Absence of circulating granulocytes
HP:0012234.definition: Absence of detectable circulating granulocytes in the blood. Usually a value of less than 50 cells per microliter is considered to be an absence.

HP:0012235.name: Drug-induced agranulocytosis
HP:0012235.definition: Absence of detectable circulating granulocytes in the blood caused by an exposure to a drug. Usually a value of less than 50 granulocytes per microliter is considered to be an absence.

HP:0012236.name: Elevated sweat chloride
HP:0012236.definition: An increased concentration of chloride in the sweat.

HP:0012237.name: Urocanic aciduria
HP:0012237.definition: An increased concentration of urocanic acid in the urine.

HP:0012238.name: Increased circulating chylomicron concentration
HP:0012238.definition: Increased plasma concentrations of chylomicrons, the large lipid droplet (up to 100 mm in diameter) of reprocessed lipid synthesized in epithelial cells of the small intestine and containing triacylglycerols, cholesterol esters, and several apolipoproteins.

HP:0012239.name: Atransferrinemia
HP:0012239.definition: Absence of transferrin, a protein that transports iron, in the blood.

HP:0012240.name: Increased intramyocellular lipid droplets
HP:0012240.definition: An abnormal increase in intracellular lipid droplets In a muscle. The number and size of these drops can increase with somd disorders of lipid metabolism affecting muscle. See PMID 20691590 for histological images.

HP:0012241.name: Levator palpebrae superioris atrophy
HP:0012241.definition: Atrophy of the levator palpebrae superioris, the extraocular muscle that elevates the superior eyelid.

HP:0012242.name: Superior rectus atrophy
HP:0012242.definition: Atrophy of the superior rectus, the extraocular muscle whose primary function is to elevate the globe.

HP:0012243.name: Abnormal reproductive system morphology
HP:0012243.definition: A structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the genital system.

HP:0012244.name: Abnormal sex determination
HP:0012244.definition: Anomaly of primary or secondary sexual development or characteristics.

HP:0012245.name: Sex reversal
HP:0012245.definition: Development of the reproductive system is inconsistent with the chromosomal sex.

HP:0012246.name: Oculomotor nerve palsy
HP:0012246.definition: Reduced ability to control the movement of the eye associated with damage to the third cranial nerve (the oculomotor nerve).

HP:0012248.name: Prolonged PR interval
HP:0012248.definition: Increased time for the PR interval (beginning of the P wave to the beginning of the QRS complex).

HP:0012249.name: Abnormal ST segment
HP:0012249.definition: An electrocardiographic anomaly of the ST segment, which is the segment that connects the QRS complex and the T wave. The ST segment normally has a duration of 80 to 120 ms, is flat and at the same level (isoelectric) as the PR and TP segment.

HP:0012250.name: ST segment depression
HP:0012250.definition: An electrocardiographic anomaly in which the ST segment is observed to be located inferior to the isoelectric line.

HP:0012251.name: ST segment elevation
HP:0012251.definition: An electrocardiographic anomaly in which the ST segment is observed to be located superior to the isoelectric line.

HP:0012252.name: Abnormal respiratory system morphology
HP:0012252.definition: A structural anomaly of the respiratory system.

HP:0012253.name: Abnormal respiratory epithelium morphology
HP:0012253.definition: Any structural anomaly of the pseudostratified ciliated epithelium that lines much of the conducting portion of the airway, including part of the nasal cavity and larynx, the trachea, and bronchi.

HP:0012254.name: Ewing sarcoma
HP:0012254.definition: A malignant tumor of the bone which always arises in the medullary tissue, occurring more often in cylindrical bones.

HP:0012255.name: Dynein arm defect of respiratory motile cilia
HP:0012255.definition: An anomaly of the dynein arms of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy.

HP:0012256.name: Absent outer dynein arms
HP:0012256.definition: Absence of the outer dynein arms of respiratory motile cilia, which normally are situated outside of the peripheral microtubules of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy.

HP:0012257.name: Absent inner dynein arms
HP:0012257.definition: Absence of the inner dynein arms of respiratory motile cilia, which normally are situated within the peripheral microtubules of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy.

HP:0012258.name: Abnormal axonemal organization of respiratory motile cilia
HP:0012258.definition: Abnormal arrangement of the structures of the axoneme, which is the cytoskeletal structure that forms the inner core of the motile cilium and displays a canonical 9+2 microtubular pattern of motile cilia studded with dynein arms.

HP:0012259.name: Absent inner and outer dynein arms
HP:0012259.definition: Complete absence of the dynein arms of respiratory motile cilia, that is, absence of the inner and the outer dynein arms, which normally are situated inside and outside of the peripheral microtubules of motile cilia. This feature is usually appreciated by electron microscopy.

HP:0012260.name: Abnormal central microtubular pair morphology of respiratory motile cilia
HP:0012260.definition: A structural anomaly of the two central microtubules of motile cilia with a 9+2 microtubuluar configuration.

HP:0012261.name: Abnormal respiratory motile cilium physiology
HP:0012261.definition: Any functional anomaly of the respiratory motile cilia.

HP:0012262.name: Abnormal ciliary motility
HP:0012262.definition: Any anomaly of the normal motility of motile cilia. Evaluation of ciliary beat frequency and ciliary beat pattern requires high-speed videomicroscopy of freshly obtained ciliary biopsies that are maintained in culture media under controlled conditions.

HP:0012264.name: Absent central microtubular pair morphology of respiratory motile cilia
HP:0012264.definition: Absence of the two central microtubules of motile cilia with a 9+2 microtubuluar configuration.

HP:0012265.name: Ciliary dyskinesia
HP:0012265.definition: A deviation from the normally well coordinated pattern of intracellular and intercellular synchrony of motile cilia. Dyskinetic cilia usually beat out of synchrony relative to neighboring cilia.

HP:0012266.name: T-wave alternans
HP:0012266.definition: A periodic beat-to-beat variation in the amplitude or shape of the T wave in an EKG.

HP:0012267.name: Absent respiratory ciliary axoneme radial spokes
HP:0012267.definition: Absence of the radial spokes of the axoneme of the respiratory cilium.

HP:0012268.name: Myxoid liposarcoma
HP:0012268.definition: A liposarcoma that contains myxomatous tissue.

HP:0012269.name: Abnormal muscle glycogen content
HP:0012269.definition: Any anomaly in the amount of glycogen in muscle tissue.

HP:0012270.name: Decreased muscle glycogen content
HP:0012270.definition: A decreased amount of glycogen in muscle tissue.

HP:0012271.name: Episodic upper airway obstruction
HP:0012271.definition: Intermittent episodes of increased resistance to the passage of air in the upper airway.

HP:0012272.name: J wave
HP:0012272.definition: The J wave is a positive convex deflection that occurs at the junction of the QRS complex and ST segment, the J-point.

HP:0012273.name: Increased carotid artery intimal medial thickness
HP:0012273.definition: An increase in the combined thickness of the intima and media of the carotid artery.

HP:0012274.name: Autosomal dominant inheritance with paternal imprinting
HP:0012274.definition: A type of autosomal dominant inheritance involving a gene that is imprinted with paternal silencing.

HP:0012275.name: Autosomal dominant inheritance with maternal imprinting
HP:0012275.definition: A type of autosomal dominant inheritance involving a gene that is imprinted with maternal silencing.

HP:0012276.name: Digital flexor tenosynovitis
HP:0012276.definition: Inflammation of the flexor digitorum tendon, often associated with the Kanavel signs: (i) finger held in slight flexion, (ii) fusiform swelling, (iii) tenderness along the flexor tendon sheath, and (iv) pain with passive extension of the digit.

HP:0012277.name: Hypoglycinemia
HP:0012277.definition: An abnormally reduced concentration of glycine in the blood.

HP:0012278.name: Abnormal circulating serine concentration
HP:0012278.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of serine in the blood circulation.

HP:0012279.name: Hyposerinemia
HP:0012279.definition: Reduced concentration of serine in the blood.

HP:0012280.name: Hepatic amyloidosis
HP:0012280.definition: A form of amyloidosis that affects the liver.

HP:0012281.name: Chylous ascites
HP:0012281.definition: Extravasation of chyle into the peritoneal cavity.

HP:0012282.name: Morbilliform rash
HP:0012282.definition: An exanthema consisting of widespread pink-to-red macules (flat spots of 2-10 mm in diameter) or papules (red bumps) that blanch with pressure. The macules and papules may cluster and merge to form sheets over several days.

HP:0012283.name: Small distal femoral epiphysis
HP:0012283.definition: Reduced size of the Distal epiphysis of femur.

HP:0012284.name: Small proximal tibial epiphyses
HP:0012284.definition: Reduced size of the proximal epiphysis of the tibia.

HP:0012285.name: Abnormal hypothalamus physiology
HP:0012285.definition: An abnormal functionality of the hypothalamus.

HP:0012286.name: Abnormal hypothalamus morphology
HP:0012286.definition: Any structural anomaly of the hypothalamus.

HP:0012287.name: Hypothalamic luteinizing hormone-releasing hormone deficiency
HP:0012287.definition: Decreased secretion of luteinizing hormone-releasing hormone by the hypothalamus.

HP:0012288.name: Neoplasm of head and neck
HP:0012288.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the head and neck region with origin in the lip, oral cavity, nasal cavity, paranasal sinuses, pharynx, or larynx.

HP:0012289.name: Facial neoplasm
HP:0012289.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the face.

HP:0012292.name: Fusion of gums
HP:0012292.definition: A congenital defect with an abnormal joining of the gums of the upper and lower jaw.

HP:0012293.name: Abnormal genital pigmentation
HP:0012293.definition: An abnormal pigmentation pattern of the external genitalia.

HP:0012294.name: Abnormal occipital bone morphology
HP:0012294.definition: Abnormality of the occipital bone of the skull.

HP:0012295.name: Slender middle phalanx of finger
HP:0012295.definition: Reduced diameter of the middle phalanx of finger.

HP:0012296.name: Slender distal phalanx of finger
HP:0012296.definition: Reduced diameter of the distal phalanx of finger.

HP:0012297.name: Slender proximal phalanx of finger
HP:0012297.definition: Reduced diameter of the proximal phalanx of finger.

HP:0012298.name: Long middle phalanx of finger
HP:0012298.definition: Increased length of the middle phalanx of finger.

HP:0012299.name: Long distal phalanx of finger
HP:0012299.definition: Increased length of the distal phalanx of finger.

HP:0012300.name: Ureteral agenesis
HP:0012300.definition: Failure of the ureter to undergo development.

HP:0012301.name: Type II transferrin isoform profile
HP:0012301.definition: Abnormal transferrin isoform profile consistent with a type II congenital disorder of glycosylation.

HP:0012302.name: Herpes simplex encephalitis
HP:0012302.definition: Infection of the brain parenchyma with herpes simplex virus, resulting in inflammation of the brain parenchyma with neurologic dysfunction.

HP:0012303.name: Abnormal aortic arch morphology
HP:0012303.definition: An anomaly of the arch of aorta.

HP:0012304.name: Hypoplastic aortic arch
HP:0012304.definition: Underdevelopment of the arch of aorta.

HP:0012305.name: Coarctation of the descending aortic arch
HP:0012305.definition: Narrowing or constriction of the aorta localized to the region of the descending trunk of arch of aorta.

HP:0012306.name: Abnormal rib ossification
HP:0012306.definition: An anomaly of the process of rib bone formation.

HP:0012307.name: Spatulate ribs
HP:0012307.definition: Ribs that are increased in width and taper to the posterior ends.

HP:0012308.name: Decreased circulating complement C9 concentration
HP:0012308.definition: Concentration of the complement component C9 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0012309.name: Cutaneous amyloidosis
HP:0012309.definition: The presence of amyloid deposition in the superficial dermis.

HP:0012310.name: Abnormal monocyte count
HP:0012310.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of total monocytes, or their phenotype, in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group, measured ex vivo.

HP:0012311.name: Increased total monocyte count
HP:0012311.definition: Abnormal increase of absolute number of monocytes in the blood, per microlitre, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0012312.name: Decreased total monocyte count
HP:0012312.definition: Abnormal decrease of absolute number of monocytes in the blood, per microlitre, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0012313.name: Heberden node
HP:0012313.definition: Bony swelling of the distal interphalangeal joint (DIP) associated with the formation of osteophytes (calcific spurs) of the articular (joint) cartilage that are visible radiographically.

HP:0012314.name: Bouchard node
HP:0012314.definition: Bony swelling of the proximal interphalangeal joint (PIP) associated with the formation of osteophytes (calcific spurs) of the articular (joint) cartilage that are visible radiographically.

HP:0012316.name: Fibrous tissue neoplasm
HP:0012316.definition: Any neoplasm composed of fibrous tissue.

HP:0012317.name: Sacroiliac arthritis
HP:0012317.definition: Inflammation of the sacroiliac joint, generally accompanied by lower back pain.

HP:0012318.name: Occipital neuralgia
HP:0012318.definition: A distinct type of headache characterized by piercing, throbbing, or electric-shock-like chronic pain in the upper neck, back of the head, and behind the ears, usually on one side.

HP:0012319.name: Absent pigmentation of the abdomen
HP:0012319.definition: Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the abdomen.

HP:0012320.name: Absent pigmentation of the limbs
HP:0012320.definition: Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the arms and legs.

HP:0012321.name: D-2-hydroxyglutaric aciduria
HP:0012321.definition: An increased concentration of 2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the urine.

HP:0012323.name: Sleep myoclonus
HP:0012323.definition: Myoclonus that occurs during the initial phases of sleep.

HP:0012324.name: Myeloid leukemia
HP:0012324.definition: A leukemia that originates from a myeloid cell, that is the blood forming cells of the bone marrow.

HP:0012325.name: Chronic myelomonocytic leukemia
HP:0012325.definition: A myelodysplastic/myeloproliferative neoplasm which is characterized by persistent monocytosis, absence of a Philadelphia chromosome and BCR/ABL fusion gene, fewer than 20 percent blasts in the bone marrow and blood, myelodysplasia, and absence of PDGFRA or PDGFRB rearrangement.

HP:0012326.name: Abnormal celiac artery morphology
HP:0012326.definition: An anomaly of the celiac artery.

HP:0012328.name: Cementoma
HP:0012328.definition: An odontogenic tumor of the cementum of tooth.

HP:0012329.name: Tufted angioma
HP:0012329.definition: A vascular tumor of the skin and subcutaneous tissues and characterized by slow angiomatous proliferation.

HP:0012330.name: Pyelonephritis
HP:0012330.definition: An inflammation of the kidney involving the parenchyma of kidney, the renal pelvis and the kidney calices.

HP:0012331.name: Abnormal autonomic nervous system morphology
HP:0012331.definition: A structural abnormality of the autonomic nervous system.

HP:0012332.name: Abnormal autonomic nervous system physiology
HP:0012332.definition: A functional abnormality of the autonomic nervous system.

HP:0012333.name: Abnormal sudomotor regulation
HP:0012333.definition: An abnormal regulation of the sweat glands by the sympathetic nervous system associated with abnormal perspiration.

HP:0012334.name: Extrahepatic cholestasis
HP:0012334.definition: Impairment of bile flow due to obstruction in large bile ducts outside the liver.

HP:0012335.name: Abnormality of folate metabolism
HP:0012335.definition: An abnormality of the metabolism of folic acid, which is also known as vitamin B9.

HP:0012337.name: Abnormal homeostasis
HP:0012337.definition: An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.

HP:0012338.name: Abnormal energy expenditure
HP:0012338.definition: Any anomaly in the utilization of energy (calories).

HP:0012339.name: Increased resting energy expenditure
HP:0012339.definition: An increase in the number of calories used per unit time.

HP:0012340.name: Decreased resting energy expenditure
HP:0012340.definition: A reduction in the number of calories used per unit time.

HP:0012341.name: Microprolactinoma
HP:0012341.definition: A pituitary prolactin cell adenoma of less than 10 mm diameter.

HP:0012342.name: Macroprolactinoma
HP:0012342.definition: A pituitary prolactin cell adenoma of more than 10 mm diameter.

HP:0012343.name: Decreased circulating ferritin concentration
HP:0012343.definition: Abnormally reduced concentration of ferritin, a ubiquitous intracellular protein that stores iron, in the blood.

HP:0012345.name: Abnormal glycosylation
HP:0012345.definition: An anomaly of a glycosylation process, i.e., a process involved in the covalent attachment of a glycosyl residue to a substrate molecule.

HP:0012346.name: Abnormal protein glycosylation
HP:0012346.definition: An anomaly of a protein glycosylation process, i.e., of a protein modification process that results in the addition of a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit to a protein amino acid, e.g. the addition of glycan chains to proteins.

HP:0012347.name: Abnormal protein N-linked glycosylation
HP:0012347.definition: An anomaly of protein N-linked glycosylation, i.e., an abnormality of the protein glycosylation process in which a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit is added to a protein via a nitrogen atom in an amino acid residue in a protein.

HP:0012348.name: Decreased galactosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012348.definition: A reduction in the amount of galactose residues of N-glycans.

HP:0012349.name: Abnormal sialylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012349.definition: An anomaly of the addition of sialic acids to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012350.name: Decreased sialylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012350.definition: Decreased addition of sialic acids to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012351.name: Increased sialylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012351.definition: Increased addition of sialic acids to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012352.name: Abnormal fucosylation of protein N-linked glycosylation
HP:0012352.definition: An anomaly of the addition of fucose sugar units to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012353.name: Decreased fucosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012353.definition: Decreased addition of fucose sugar units to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012354.name: Increased fucosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012354.definition: Increased addition of fucose sugar units to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012355.name: Abnormal mannosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012355.definition: An anomaly of the addition of mannose to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012356.name: Decreased mannosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012356.definition: Reduced addition of mannose to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012357.name: Increased mannosylation of N-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012357.definition: Increased addition of mannose to N-linked glycans.

HP:0012358.name: Abnormal protein O-linked glycosylation
HP:0012358.definition: An anomaly of protein O-linked glycosylation, i.e., of the process in which a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit is added to a protein via the hydroxyl group of a serine or threonine residue.

HP:0012359.name: Abnormal fucosylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012359.definition: An anomaly of the addition of fucose sugar units to O-linked glycans.

HP:0012360.name: Decreased fucosylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012360.definition: A reduction of the addition of fucose sugar units to O-linked glycans.

HP:0012361.name: Increased fucosylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012361.definition: Increased addition of fucose sugar units to O-linked glycans.

HP:0012362.name: Abnormal sialylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012362.definition: An anomaly of the addition of sialic acids to O-linked glycans.

HP:0012363.name: Decreased sialylation of O-linked protein glycosylation
HP:0012363.definition: An reduced addition of sialic acids to O-linked glycans.

HP:0012364.name: Decreased urinary potassium
HP:0012364.definition: A decreased concentration of potassium(1+) in the urine.

HP:0012365.name: Hypophosphaturia
HP:0012365.definition: An abnormally decreased phosphate concentration in the urine.

HP:0012366.name: Basilar invagination
HP:0012366.definition: Projection of the tip of the dens more than 5 mm above a line joining the hard palate to the posterior lip of the foramen magnum (Chamberlain's line) or the tip of the dens is greater than 7 mm above McGregor's line (the back of the hard palate to the lowest point of the occipital squama).

HP:0012367.name: Extra fontanelles
HP:0012367.definition: Bony defects situated along the cranial suture lines or at the junction of the bone plates of the skull.

HP:0012368.name: Flat face
HP:0012368.definition: Absence of concavity or convexity of the face when viewed in profile.

HP:0012370.name: Prominence of the zygomatic bone
HP:0012370.definition: Large or prominent malar surface of the zygomatic bone of the skull, which is convex and forms the prominence of the 'cheek bones'.

HP:0012371.name: Hyperplasia of midface
HP:0012371.definition: Abnormally anterior positioning of the infraorbital and perialar regions, or increased convexity of the face, or increased nasolabial angle. The midface includes the maxilla, the cheeks, the zygomas, and the infraorbital and perialar regions of the face

HP:0012372.name: Abnormal eye morphology
HP:0012372.definition: A structural anomaly of the globe of the eye, or bulbus oculi.

HP:0012373.name: Abnormal eye physiology
HP:0012373.definition: A functional anomaly of the eye.

HP:0012377.name: Hemianopia
HP:0012377.definition: Partial or complete loss of vision in one half of the visual field of one or both eyes.

HP:0012378.name: Fatigue
HP:0012378.definition: A subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation.

HP:0012379.name: Abnormal circulating enzyme concentration or activity
HP:0012379.definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0012380.name: Reduced tissue carnitine O-palmitoyltransferase 2 activity
HP:0012380.definition: Reduced carnitine O-palmitoyltransferase (CPT II; EC 2.3.1.21) activity or level, leading to a reduced activity of the reaction: palmitoyl-CoA + L-carnitine = CoA + L-palmitoylcarnitine. (CPT II activity can be measured in tissues including fibroblasts, lymphoblasts, and skeletal muscle.

HP:0012381.name: Delayed self-feeding during toddler years
HP:0012381.definition: A delay in the development of skills required to feed oneself in the toddler period (between one and three years of age).

HP:0012382.name: Left-to-right shunt
HP:0012382.definition: Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from the left side of the heart to the right.

HP:0012383.name: Bidirectional shunt
HP:0012383.definition: Pattern of blood flow in the heart that deviates from the normal circuit of the circulatory system from both right side of the heart to the left and vice versa.

HP:0012384.name: Rhinitis
HP:0012384.definition: Inflammation of the nasal mucosa with nasal congestion.

HP:0012385.name: Camptodactyly
HP:0012385.definition: The distal interphalangeal joint and/or the proximal interphalangeal joint of the fingers or toes cannot be extended to 180 degrees by either active or passive extension.

HP:0012386.name: Absent hallux
HP:0012386.definition: Aplasia of the hallux, that is, a development defect such that the big toe does not develop.

HP:0012387.name: Bronchitis
HP:0012387.definition: Inflammation of the large airways in the lung including any part of the bronchi from the primary bronchi to the tertiary bronchi.

HP:0012388.name: Acute bronchitis
HP:0012388.definition: Inflammation of the large airways of the lung with rapid onset and short course usually associated with cough, mucus production, shortness of breath, wheezing, and chest tightness.

HP:0012389.name: Appendicular hypotonia
HP:0012389.definition: Muscular hypotonia of one or more limbs.

HP:0012390.name: Anal fissure
HP:0012390.definition: A small tear in the thin, moist tissue (mucosa) that lines the anus. It appears as a crack or slit in the mucous membrane of the anus.

HP:0012391.name: Hyporeflexia of upper limbs
HP:0012391.definition: Reduced intensity of muscle tendon reflexes in the upper limbs. Reflexes are elicited by stretching the tendon of a muscle, e.g., by tapping.

HP:0012392.name: Jaw hyporeflexia
HP:0012392.definition: Reduced intensity of muscle tendon reflexes in jaw.

HP:0012393.name: Allergy
HP:0012393.definition: An allergy is an immune response or reaction to substances that are usually not harmful.

HP:0012394.name: Iodine contrast allergy
HP:0012394.definition: Allergy to iodine contrast media used in radiological studies.

HP:0012395.name: Seasonal allergy
HP:0012395.definition: An allergy experienced at a particular time of year when trees or grasses pollinate and elicit an allergic reaction.

HP:0012396.name: Biliary dyskinesia
HP:0012396.definition: A motility disorder characterized by biliary colic in the absence of gallstones with a reduced gallbladder ejection fraction.

HP:0012397.name: Aortic atherosclerotic lesion
HP:0012397.definition: The presence of atheromas or atherosclerotic plaques in the aorta.

HP:0012398.name: Peripheral edema
HP:0012398.definition: An abnormal accumulation of interstitial fluid in the soft tissues of the limbs.

HP:0012399.name: Pressure ulcer
HP:0012399.definition: A type of ulcer that is caused when an area of skin is subject to pressure over a prolonged period of time, ranging in range in severity from patches of discolored skin to open wounds that expose the underlying bone or muscle. The most common sites are the sacrum, coccyx, heels and the hips.

HP:0012400.name: Abnormal circulating aldolase concentration
HP:0012400.definition: An abnormal concentration of aldolase in the serum. Aldolase is an enzyme responsible for converting fructose 1,6-bisphosphate into the triose phosphates dihydroxyacetone phosphate and glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate.

HP:0012401.name: Abnormal urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
HP:0012401.definition: A deviation from normal of the concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine.

HP:0012402.name: Increased urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
HP:0012402.definition: A greater than normal concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine.

HP:0012403.name: Decreased urine alpha-ketoglutarate concentration
HP:0012403.definition: A lower than normal concentration of 2-oxoglutaric acid in the urine.

HP:0012404.name: Abnormal urine citrate concentration
HP:0012404.definition: A deviation from normal of the concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine.

HP:0012405.name: Hypocitraturia
HP:0012405.definition: A lower than normal concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine.

HP:0012406.name: Hypercitraturia
HP:0012406.definition: A greater than normal concentration of citrate(3-) in the urine.

HP:0012407.name: Scissor gait
HP:0012407.definition: A type of spastic paraparetic gait in which the muscle tone in the adductors is marked. It is characterized by hypertonia and flexion in the legs, hips and pelvis accompanied by extreme adduction leading to the knees and thighs hitting, or sometimes even crossing, in a scissors-like movement. The opposing muscles (abductors) become comparatively weak from lack of use.

HP:0012408.name: Medullary nephrocalcinosis
HP:0012408.definition: The deposition of calcium salts in the parenchyma of the renal medulla (innermost part of the kidney).

HP:0012409.name: Cortical nephrocalcinosis
HP:0012409.definition: The deposition of calcium salts in the parenchyma of the renal cortex (the outer portion of the kidney between the renal capsule and the renal medulla).

HP:0012410.name: Pure red cell aplasia
HP:0012410.definition: A type of anemia resulting from suppression of erythropoiesis with little or no abnormality of leukocyte or platelet production. Erythroblasts are virtually absent in bone marrow; however, leukocyte and platelet production show little or no reduction.

HP:0012411.name: Premature pubarche
HP:0012411.definition: The onset of growth of pubic hair at an earlier age than normal.

HP:0012412.name: Premature adrenarche
HP:0012412.definition: Onset of adrenarche at an earlier age than usual.

HP:0012413.name: Notched primary central incisor
HP:0012413.definition: The presence of a V-shaped indentation (notch) in the primary central incisor.

HP:0012414.name: Duodenal atrophy
HP:0012414.definition: Wasting or decrease in size of all or part of the duodenum.

HP:0012415.name: Abnormal blood gas level
HP:0012415.definition: An abnormality of the partial pressure of oxygen or carbon dioxide in the arterial blood.

HP:0012416.name: Hypercapnia
HP:0012416.definition: Abnormally elevated blood carbon dioxide (CO2) level.

HP:0012417.name: Hypocapnia
HP:0012417.definition: Abnormally reduced blood carbon dioxide (CO2) level.

HP:0012418.name: Hypoxemia
HP:0012418.definition: An abnormally low level of blood oxygen.

HP:0012419.name: Hyperoxemia
HP:0012419.definition: An abnormally high level of blood oxygen.

HP:0012420.name: Meconium stained amniotic fluid
HP:0012420.definition: Amniotic fluid containing the earliest stools of a mammalian infant.

HP:0012421.name: Congenital absence of foreskin
HP:0012421.definition: Congenital lack of the skin of prepuce of penis, that is, of the double-layered fold of skin and mucous membrane that covers the glans penis.

HP:0012423.name: Colonic inertia
HP:0012423.definition: The inability of the colon to modify stool to an acceptable consistency and move the stool from the cecum to the rectosigmoid area at least once every three days.

HP:0012424.name: Chorioretinitis
HP:0012424.definition: An inflammation of the choroid and retina.

HP:0012425.name: Stercoral ulcer
HP:0012425.definition: An ulcer of the colon due to pressure and irritation from retained fecal masses.

HP:0012426.name: Optic disc drusen
HP:0012426.definition: Optic disc drusen are acellular, calcified deposits within the optic nerve head. Optic disc drusen are congenital and developmental anomalies of the optic nerve head, representing hyaline-containing bodies that, over time, appear as elevated, lumpy irregularities on the anterior portion of the optic nerve.

HP:0012427.name: Increased femoral anteversion
HP:0012427.definition: An increased degree of femoral version, which is defined as the angular difference between axis of femoral neck and transcondylar axis of the knee. Thus, femoral anteversion is an inward twisting of the femur that causes the knees and feet to turn inward.

HP:0012429.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cerebral white matter
HP:0012429.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the cerebral white matter.

HP:0012430.name: Cerebral white matter hypoplasia
HP:0012430.definition: Underdevelopment of the cerebral white matter.

HP:0012431.name: Episodic fatigue
HP:0012431.definition: Intermittent and recurrent bouts of a subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation.

HP:0012432.name: Chronic fatigue
HP:0012432.definition: Subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation that persists for six months or longer.

HP:0012433.name: Abnormal social behavior
HP:0012433.definition: An abnormality of actions or reactions of a person taking place during interactions with others.

HP:0012434.name: Delayed early-childhood social milestone development
HP:0012434.definition: A failure to meet one or more age-related milestones of social behavior.

HP:0010846.name: EEG with persistent abnormal rhythmic activity

HP:0010847.name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (<2.5 Hz)
HP:0010847.definition: The presence of complexes of slow spikes and slow waves (<2.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010848.name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (2.5-3.5 Hz)
HP:0010848.definition: The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (2.5-3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010849.name: EEG with spike-wave complexes (>3.5 Hz)
HP:0010849.definition: The presence of complexes of spikes and waves (>3.5 Hz) in electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010850.name: EEG with spike-wave complexes
HP:0010850.definition: Complexes of spikes (<70 ms) and sharp waves (70-200 ms), which are sharp transient waves that have a strong association with epilepsy, in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010851.name: EEG with burst suppression
HP:0010851.definition: The burst suppression pattern in electroencephalography refers to a characteristic periodic pattern of low voltage (<10 microvolts) suppressed background and a relatively shorter pattern of higher amplitude slow, sharp, and spiking complexes.

HP:0010852.name: EEG with photoparoxysmal response
HP:0010852.definition: EEG abnormalities (epileptiform discharges) evoked by flashing lights or black and white striped patterns.

HP:0010853.name: EEG with periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges
HP:0010853.definition: Periodic lateralized epileptiform discharges (PLEDs)are periodic, lateralized, and epileptiform. PLEDs show a relatively constant interval between discharges (0.5 to 3 seconds).

HP:0010854.name: EEG with generalized low amplitude activity
HP:0010854.definition: An abnormal generalized reduction in amplitude of the cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010855.name: EEG with localized low amplitude activity
HP:0010855.definition: An abnormal localized reduction in amplitude of the cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010857.name: EEG with periodic abnormalities
HP:0010857.definition: Periodically recurring abnormalities in the EEG.

HP:0010858.name: EEG with hyperventilation-induced epileptiform discharges
HP:0010858.definition: Epileptiform discharges induced by hyperventilation (overbreathing) in cerebral electrical activity recorded along the scalp by electroencephalography (EEG).

HP:0010859.name: Frank breech presentation
HP:0010859.definition: A kind of breech presentation in which the hips are flexed and the knees are extended.

HP:0010860.name: Complete breech presentation
HP:0010860.definition: A kind of breech presentation in which the hips are flexed and the knees are flexed.

HP:0010861.name: Incomplete breech presentation
HP:0010861.definition: A kind of breech presentation in which one or both hips are extended and one or both of the fetus' feet are pointing down and entering the birth canal.

HP:0010862.name: Delayed fine motor development
HP:0010862.definition: A type of motor delay characterized by a delay in acquiring the ability to control the fingers and hands.

HP:0010863.name: Receptive language delay
HP:0010863.definition: A delay in the acquisition of the ability to understand the speech of others.

HP:0010864.name: Intellectual disability, severe
HP:0010864.definition: Severe mental retardation is defined as an intelligence quotient (IQ) in the range of 20-34.

HP:0010865.name: Oppositional defiant disorder
HP:0010865.definition: An enduring pattern of uncooperative, defiant, and hostile behavior towards authority figures that does not involve major antisocial violations, is not accounted for by the child's developmental stage, and results in significant functional impairment. A certain level of oppositional behavior is common in children and adolescents.

HP:0010866.name: Abdominal wall defect
HP:0010866.definition: An incomplete closure of the abdominal wall.

HP:0010867.name: Dyssynergia
HP:0010867.definition: A type of ataxia characterized by the impairment of the ability to smoothly perform the elements of a voluntary movement in the appropriate order and speed. With dyssynergia, a voluntary movement appears broken down into its component parts.

HP:0010868.name: Ocular dyssynergia
HP:0010868.definition: A type of dyssynergia affecting eye movements and characterized by the inability to smoothly follow a visual target across the visual field.

HP:0010869.name: Asynergia
HP:0010869.definition: A type of dyssynergy characterized by the lack of the ability to smoothly perform the elements of a voluntary movement in the appropriate order and speed.

HP:0010871.name: Sensory ataxia
HP:0010871.definition: Incoordination of movement caused by a deficit in the sensory nervous system. Sensory ataxia can be distinguished from cerebellar ataxia by asking the patient to close his or her eyes. Persons with cerebellar ataxia show only a minimal worsening of symptoms, whereas persons with sensory ataxia show a marked worsening of symptoms.

HP:0010872.name: T-wave inversion
HP:0010872.definition: An inversion of the T-wave (which is normally positive).

HP:0010873.name: Cervical spinal cord atrophy
HP:0010873.definition: Atrophy of the cervical segment of the spinal cord.

HP:0010874.name: Tendon xanthomatosis
HP:0010874.definition: The presence of xanthomas (intra-and extra-cellular accumulations of cholesterol) extensor tendons (typically over knuckles, Achilles tendon, knee, and elbows).

HP:0010875.name: Chaddock reflex
HP:0010875.definition: A diagnostic reflex elicited by stimulation of the skin over the surface of the lateral malleolus of the foot. The Chaddock refelx is present if there is extension of one or more or all of the toes with or without fanning of them when the external inframalleolar skin is stimulated. The Chaddock sign, similar to the Babinski sign, is taken to be an indication of disease of the spinocortical (pyramidal) tract.

HP:0010876.name: Abnormal circulating protein concentration
HP:0010876.definition: An abnormal level of a circulating protein in the blood.

HP:0010877.name: Monocular strabismus
HP:0010877.definition: A type of strabismus in which the fixating eye is always the same one, while the other eye is constantly deviated. Monocular strabismus is to be distinguished from alternating strabismus, in which either of the eyes 'squints' at different times.

HP:0010878.name: Fetal cystic hygroma
HP:0010878.definition: The presence during the prenatal period of a cystic mass with multiple septa with multiple, asymmetric, thin-walled cysts near the posterior aspect of the neck. Fetal cystic hygroma can be defined as nuchal translucency with or without septations measuring greater than 3.0 mm. Increased NT refers to a measurement above the 95th centile, and the term is used irrespective of whether the collection of fluid is septated or not, and whether it is confined to the neck or envelopes the whole fetus. After 14 weeks, increased NT usually resolves, but in some cases it evolves into nuchal edema or cystic hygromas.

HP:0010880.name: Increased nuchal translucency
HP:0010880.definition: Nuchal translucency is the sonographic appearance of subcutaneous accumulation of liquid in the back of the fetal neck in the first trimester of pregnancy (11-14 gestational weeks of pregnancy).

HP:0010881.name: Abnormality of the umbilical cord
HP:0010881.definition: An abnormality of the umbilical cord, which is the cord connecting the developing embryo or fetus to the placenta.

HP:0010882.name: Pulmonary valve atresia
HP:0010882.definition: A congenital disorder of the pulmonary valve in which the orifice of the valve fails to develop.

HP:0010883.name: Aortic valve atresia
HP:0010883.definition: A congenital disorder of the aortic valve in which the orifice of the valve fails to develop.

HP:0010884.name: Acromelia
HP:0010884.definition: Shortening of the extremities affecting primarily the distal parts of the limbs (hands and feet) in relation to the other segments of the limbs.

HP:0010885.name: Avascular necrosis
HP:0010885.definition: A disease where there is cellular death (necrosis) of bone components due to interruption of the blood supply.

HP:0010886.name: Osteochondritis dissecans
HP:0010886.definition: A joint disorder caused by blood deprivation in the subchondral bone causing the subchondral bone to die in a process called avascular necrosis. The bone is then reabsorbed by the body, leaving the articular cartilage it supported prone to damage. The result is fragmentation (dissection) of both cartilage and bone, and the free movement of these osteochondral fragments within the joint space, causing pain and further damage.

HP:0010888.name: Morbus Koehler
HP:0010888.definition: Morbus Koehler is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Os naviculare pedis.

HP:0010889.name: Morbus Kienboeck
HP:0010889.definition: Morbus Kienboeck is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Os lunatum.

HP:0010890.name: Morbus Osgood-Schlatter
HP:0010890.definition: Morbus Osgood-Schlatter is a Juvenile aseptic necrosis affecting the Tuberositas tibiae.

HP:0010891.name: Morbus Scheuermann
HP:0010891.definition: A developmental growth retardation of the vertebral end plates that may lead to secondary destruction of the vertebral end plates and protrusion of the nucleus pulposus into the vertebral body (so called Schmorl's nodes as seen on x-rays).

HP:0010892.name: Abnormal circulating branched chain amino acid concentration
HP:0010892.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a branched chain family amino acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010893.name: Abnormal circulating phenylalanine concentration
HP:0010893.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of phenylalanine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010894.name: Abnormal circulating serine family amino acid concentration
HP:0010894.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a serine family amino acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010895.name: Abnormal circulating glycine concentration
HP:0010895.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of glycine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010896.name: Hypersarcosinemia
HP:0010896.definition: An elevated plasma concentration of sarcosine.

HP:0010897.name: Hypersarcosinuria
HP:0010897.definition: An elevated urinary concentration of sarcosine.

HP:0010898.name: Abnormal circulating sarcosine concentration
HP:0010898.definition: An deviation from the normal concentration of sarcosine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010899.name: Abnormal circulating aspartate family amino acid concentration
HP:0010899.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of an aspartate family amino acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010900.name: Abnormal circulating threonine concentration
HP:0010900.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of threonine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010901.name: Abnormal circulating methionine concentration
HP:0010901.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of methionine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010902.name: Abnormal circulating glutamine family amino acid concentration
HP:0010902.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a glutamine family amino acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010903.name: Abnormal circulating glutamine concentration
HP:0010903.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of glutamine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010904.name: Abnormal circulating histidine concentration
HP:0010904.definition: An abnormality of a histidine metabolic process.

HP:0010906.name: Hyperhistidinemia
HP:0010906.definition: An increased concentration of histidine in the blood.

HP:0010907.name: Abnormal circulating proline concentration
HP:0010907.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of proline or a proline metabolite in the blood circulation.

HP:0010908.name: Abnormal circulating lysine concentration
HP:0010908.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of lysine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010909.name: Abnormal circulating arginine concentration
HP:0010909.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of arginine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010910.name: Hypervalinemia
HP:0010910.definition: An increased concentration of valine in the blood.

HP:0010911.name: Hyperleucinemia
HP:0010911.definition: An increased concentration of leucine in the blood.

HP:0010912.name: Abnormal circulating isoleucine concentration
HP:0010912.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of isoleucine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010913.name: Hyperisoleucinemia
HP:0010913.definition: An increased concentration of isoleucine in the blood.

HP:0010914.name: Abnormal circulating valine concentration
HP:0010914.definition: Any deviation from the normal circulation of valine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010915.name: Abnormal circulating pyruvate family amino acid concentration
HP:0010915.definition: An abnormality of a pyruvate family amino acid metabolic process.

HP:0010916.name: Abnormal circulating alanine concentration
HP:0010916.definition: An abnormality of an alanine metabolic process.

HP:0010917.name: Abnormal circulating tyrosine concentration
HP:0010917.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of tyrosine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010918.name: Abnormal circulating cysteine concentration
HP:0010918.definition: An abnormality of a cysteine metabolic process.

HP:0010919.name: Abnormal circulating homocysteine concentration
HP:0010919.definition: An abnormality of a homocysteine metabolic process.

HP:0010920.name: Zonular cataract
HP:0010920.definition: Zonular cataracts are defined to be cataracts that affect specific regions of the lens.

HP:0010921.name: Coralliform cataract
HP:0010921.definition: A 'coral-like' pattern of opacity in the lens of the eye. That is, a cataract with an irregular, stellate form.

HP:0010922.name: Membranous cataract
HP:0010922.definition: A form of cataract in which the lens substance has shrunk, leaving a collapsed, flattened capsule with little or no cortex or epithelium on the lens.

HP:0010923.name: Anterior subcapsular cataract
HP:0010923.definition: A type of cataract affecting the anterior pole of lens immediately adjacent to ('beneath') the lens capsule.

HP:0010924.name: Posterior cortical cataract
HP:0010924.definition: A cataract that affects the posterior part of the cortex of the lens.

HP:0010926.name: Aculeiform cataract
HP:0010926.definition: A kind of nuclear cataract characterized by fiberglasslike or needlelike crystals projecting in different directions, through or close to the axial region of the lens.

HP:0010927.name: Abnormal blood inorganic cation concentration
HP:0010927.definition: An abnormality of divalent inorganic cation homeostasis.

HP:0010928.name: obsolete Increased urinary orotic acid concentration

HP:0010930.name: Abnormal blood monovalent inorganic cation concentration
HP:0010930.definition: An abnormality of monovalent inorganic cation homeostasis.

HP:0010932.name: Abnormal circulating nucleobase concentration
HP:0010932.definition: An abnormality of a nucleobase metabolic process.

HP:0010933.name: Hyperxanthinemia
HP:0010933.definition: An increased level of xanthine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010934.name: Xanthinuria
HP:0010934.definition: An increased concentration of xanthine in the urine.

HP:0010935.name: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract
HP:0010935.definition: An abnormality of the upper urinary tract.

HP:0010936.name: Abnormality of the lower urinary tract
HP:0010936.definition: An abnormality of the lower urinary tract.

HP:0010937.name: Abnormal nasal skeleton morphology
HP:0010937.definition: An abnormality of the nasal skeleton.

HP:0010938.name: Abnormal external nose morphology
HP:0010938.definition: An abnormality of the external nose.

HP:0010939.name: Abnormal nasal bone morphology
HP:0010939.definition: An abnormality of the nasal bone, comprising the left nasal bone and the right nasal bone.

HP:0010940.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nasal bone
HP:0010940.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the nasal bone.

HP:0010942.name: Echogenic intracardiac focus
HP:0010942.definition: A finding of a focus of increased echogenicity upon prenatal ultrasound examination of the fetus. The foci may be present in one or both ventricles. Echogenic intracardiac focus (EICF) is defined as a focus of echogenicity comparable to bone, in the region of the papillary muscle in either or both ventricles of the fetal heart.

HP:0010943.name: Echogenic fetal bowel
HP:0010943.definition: Echogenic bowel is defined as fetal bowel with homogenous areas of echogenicity that are equal to or greater than that of surrounding bone.

HP:0010944.name: Abnormal renal pelvis morphology
HP:0010944.definition: An abnormality of the renal pelvis.

HP:0010945.name: Fetal pyelectasis
HP:0010945.definition: Mild pyelectasis is defined as a hypoechoic spherical or elliptical space within the renal pelvis that measures at least 5mm and not more than 10 mm. The measurement is taken on a transverse section through the fetal renal pelvis using the maximum anterior-to-posterior measurement.

HP:0010946.name: Dilatation of the renal pelvis
HP:0010946.definition: The presence of dilatation of the renal pelvis.

HP:0010947.name: Abnormality of ductus venosus blood flow
HP:0010947.definition: A first-trimester prenatal ultrasound finding of abnormal blood flow in the ductus venosus.

HP:0010948.name: Abnormal fetal cardiovascular morphology
HP:0010948.definition: A structural abnormality of the fetal circulation system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

HP:0010949.name: Abnormality of umbilical vein blood flow
HP:0010949.definition: A first-trimester prenatal ultrasound finding of abnormal blood flow in the umbilical vein.

HP:0010950.name: Abnormal fourth ventricle morphology
HP:0010950.definition: An abnormality of the fourth ventricle.

HP:0010951.name: Abnormal third ventricle morphology
HP:0010951.definition: An abnormality of the third ventricle.

HP:0010952.name: Mild fetal ventriculomegaly
HP:0010952.definition: A kind of ventriculomegaly occurring in the fetal period and usually diagnosed by prenatal ultrasound. Cerebral ventriculomegaly is defined by atrial measurements 10 mm or more. Mild ventriculomegaly (MVM) is defined as measurements between 10 and 15 mm. Measurements are obtained from an axial plane at the level of the thalamic nuclei just below the standard image to measure the BPD (PMID:16100637).

HP:0010953.name: Noncommunicating hydrocephalus
HP:0010953.definition: A form of hydrocephalus in which the flow of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) within the cerebral ventricular system or in the outlets of the CSF to the arachnoid space is obstructed.

HP:0010954.name: Hypoplastic right heart
HP:0010954.definition: Underdevelopment of the right-sided structures of the heart.

HP:0010955.name: Dilatation of the bladder
HP:0010955.definition: The presence of a dilated urinary bladder.

HP:0010956.name: Fetal megacystis
HP:0010956.definition: Fetal megacystis is an abnormally enlarged bladder identified at any gestational age.

HP:0010957.name: Congenital posterior urethral valve
HP:0010957.definition: A developmental defect resulting in an obstructing membrane in the posterior male urethra.

HP:0010958.name: Bilateral renal agenesis
HP:0010958.definition: A bilateral form of agenesis of the kidney.

HP:0010959.name: Congenital pulmonary airway malformation
HP:0010959.definition: Congenital pulmonary airway malformation (CPAM) - previously known as congenital cystic adenomatoid malformation (CCAM) - is a relatively rare developmental malformation of the lower respiratory tract. It is a hamartomatous, dysplastic developmental abnormality of the lung characterized by abnormal airway patterning during lung branching morphogenesis and is formed by abnormal branching of the immature bronchioles.

HP:0010963.name: Absence of stomach bubble on fetal sonography
HP:0010963.definition: By the 14th week of gestation it is nearly always possible to visualized the fluid-filled fetal stomach bubble on prenatal sonography. This term refers to the absence of a normal fetal stomach bubble on fetal ultrasonography performed at around 16 to 20 weeks' gestation.

HP:0010964.name: Abnormal circulating long-chain fatty-acid concentration
HP:0010964.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a long-chain fatty acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010965.name: Abnormal circulating phytanic acid concentration
HP:0010965.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of phytanic acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010966.name: Abnormal circulating fatty-acid anion concentration
