HP:0010966.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a fatty acid anion in the blood circulation.

HP:0010967.name: Abnormal circulating carnitine concentration
HP:0010967.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation.

HP:0010970.name: Blood group antigen abnormality
HP:0010970.definition: An abnormality of an erythrocyte cell surface molecule.

HP:0010971.name: Absence of Lutheran antigen on erythrocytes
HP:0010971.definition: Absence of the Lutheran antigen (a type I integral membrane glycoprotein) from the surface of red blood cells.

HP:0010972.name: Anemia of inadequate production
HP:0010972.definition: A kind of anemia characterized by inadequate production of erythrocytes.

HP:0010975.name: Abnormal B cell count
HP:0010975.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of total B cells or any deviation of the propoortion of a B cell subtype. B cells are commonly characterized as CD19+ or CD20+ lymphocytes, or their subpopulations, in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group, measured ex vivo.

HP:0010976.name: Decreased total B cell count
HP:0010976.definition: The absolute number of B cells in the blood, per microlitre is below the lower limit of normal of the reference range for the appropriate sex and age-group.

HP:0010977.name: Abnormal phagocytosis
HP:0010977.definition: An abnormal functioning of phagocytosis. Phagocytosis is an elegant but complex process for the ingestion and elimination of pathogens, but it is also important for the elimination of apoptotic cells and hence fundamental for tissue homeostasis. Phagocytosis can be divided into four main steps: (i) recognition of the target particle, (ii) signaling to activate the internalization machinery, (iii) phagosome formation, and (iv) phagolysosome maturation.

HP:0010978.name: Abnormality of immune system physiology
HP:0010978.definition: A functional abnormality of the immune system.

HP:0010979.name: Abnormality of lipoprotein cholesterol concentration
HP:0010979.definition: An abnormal increase or decrease in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

HP:0010980.name: Hyperlipoproteinemia
HP:0010980.definition: An abnormal increase in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

HP:0010981.name: Hypolipoproteinemia
HP:0010981.definition: An abnormal decrease in the level of lipoprotein cholesterol in the blood.

HP:0010982.name: Polygenic inheritance
HP:0010982.definition: A mode of inheritance that depends on a mixture of major and minor genetic determinants possibly together with environmental factors. Diseases inherited in this manner are termed complex diseases.

HP:0010983.name: Oligogenic inheritance
HP:0010983.definition: A type of multifactorial inheritance governed by the simultaneous action of a few gene loci. It is recommended this term be used for traits governed by three loci, although it is noted that usage of this term in the literature is not uniform.

HP:0010984.name: Digenic inheritance
HP:0010984.definition: A type of multifactorial inheritance governed by the simultaneous action of two gene loci.

HP:0010987.name: Abnormal cellular immune system morphology
HP:0010987.definition: An abnormality of the morphology or counts of the cells that make up the immune system.

HP:0010988.name: Abnormality of the extrinsic pathway
HP:0010988.definition: An abnormality of the extrinsic pathway (also known as the tissue factor pathway) of the coagulation cascade.

HP:0010989.name: Abnormality of the intrinsic pathway
HP:0010989.definition: An abnormality of the intrinsic pathway (also known as the contact activation pathway) of the coagulation cascade.

HP:0010990.name: Abnormality of the common coagulation pathway
HP:0010990.definition: An abnormality of blood coagulation, common pathway.

HP:0010991.name: Abnormal morphology of the abdominal musculature
HP:0010991.definition: An abnormality of the abdominal musculature.

HP:0010992.name: Stress urinary incontinence
HP:0010992.definition: Involuntary urine leakage synchronous with exertion, or actions such as sneezing, or coughing.

HP:0010993.name: Abnormal cerebral subcortex morphology
HP:0010993.definition: An abnormality of the cerebral subcortex.

HP:0010994.name: Abnormal corpus striatum morphology
HP:0010994.definition: Abnormality of the striatum, which is the largest nucleus of the basal ganglia, comprising the caudate, putamen and ventral striatum, including the nucleus accumbens.

HP:0010995.name: Abnormal circulating dicarboxylic acid concentration
HP:0010995.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a dicarboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010996.name: Abnormal circulating monocarboxylic acid concentration
HP:0010996.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a monocarboxylic acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0010997.name: Chromosomal breakage induced by ionizing radiation
HP:0010997.definition: Increased amount of chromosomal breaks in cultured blood lymphocytes or other cells induced by treatment with ionizing radiation.

HP:0010998.name: Increased susceptibility to spontaneous sister chromatid exchange
HP:0010998.definition: An increase in the number of spontaneous sister chromatid exchanges observed in cell culture of lymphocytes or other cells.

HP:0011001.name: Increased bone mineral density
HP:0011001.definition: An abnormal increase of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones which is often referred to as osteosclerosis. Osteosclerosis can be detected on radiological examination as an increased whiteness (density) of affected bones.

HP:0011002.name: Osteopetrosis
HP:0011002.definition: Abnormally increased formation of dense trabecular bone tissue. Despite the increased density of bone tissue, osteopetrotic bones tend to be more fracture-prone than normal.

HP:0011003.name: High myopia
HP:0011003.definition: A severe form of myopia with greater than -6.00 diopters.

HP:0011004.name: Abnormal systemic arterial morphology
HP:0011004.definition: An abnormality of the systemic arterial tree, which consists of the aorta and other systemic arteries.

HP:0011005.name: Mixed cirrhosis
HP:0011005.definition: A type of cirrhosis characterized by the presence of regenerative nodules of a variety of sizes.

HP:0011006.name: Abnormal morphology of the musculature of the neck
HP:0011006.definition: An abnormality of the neck musculature.

HP:0011008.name: Temporal pattern
HP:0011008.definition: The speed at which disease manifestations appear and develop.

HP:0011009.name: Acute
HP:0011009.definition: Sudden appearance of disease manifestations over a short period of time.

HP:0011010.name: Chronic
HP:0011010.definition: Slow, creeping onset, slow progress and long continuance of disease manifestations.

HP:0011011.name: Subacute
HP:0011011.definition: Somewhat rapid onset and change of disease manifestations.

HP:0011012.name: Abnormal circulating polysaccharide concentration
HP:0011012.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of a polysaccharide in the blood circulation.

HP:0011013.name: Abnormal circulating carbohydrate concentration
HP:0011013.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of a carbohydrate in the blood circulation.

HP:0011015.name: Abnormal blood glucose concentration
HP:0011015.definition: An abnormality of the concentration of glucose in the blood.

HP:0011016.name: obsolete Abnormality of urine glucose concentration

HP:0011017.name: Abnormal cellular physiology
HP:0011017.definition: An abnormality in a cellular process.

HP:0011018.name: Abnormality of the cell cycle
HP:0011018.definition: An abnormality of the cell cycle.

HP:0011020.name: Abnormality of mucopolysaccharide metabolism
HP:0011020.definition: An abnormality of the metabolism of mucopolysaccharide.

HP:0011021.name: Abnormal circulating enzyme concentration
HP:0011021.definition: The concentration or activity of an enzyme in the blood circulation is outside of the limits of the normal range.

HP:0011022.name: Abnormal circulating unsaturated fatty acid concentration
HP:0011022.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of an unsaturated fatty acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0011023.name: Abnormal circulating prostaglandin circulation
HP:0011023.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a prostaglandin in the blood circulation.

HP:0011024.name: Abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
HP:0011024.definition: An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.

HP:0011025.name: Abnormal cardiovascular system physiology
HP:0011025.definition: Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.

HP:0011026.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the vagina
HP:0011026.definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the vagina.

HP:0011027.name: Abnormal fallopian tube morphology
HP:0011027.definition: An abnormality of the fallopian tube.

HP:0011029.name: Internal hemorrhage
HP:0011029.definition: The presence of hemorrhage within the body.

HP:0011030.name: Abnormal blood transition element cation concentration
HP:0011030.definition: An abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of transition element cation.

HP:0011031.name: Abnormality of iron homeostasis
HP:0011031.definition: An abnormality of the homeostasis (concentration) of iron cation.

HP:0011032.name: Abnormality of fluid regulation
HP:0011032.definition: An abnormality of the regulation of body fluids.

HP:0011033.name: Impairment of fructose metabolism
HP:0011033.definition: An impairment of a fructose metabolic process.

HP:0011034.name: Amyloidosis
HP:0011034.definition: The presence of amyloid deposition in one or more tissues. Amyloidosis may be defined as the extracellular deposition of amyloid in one or more sites of the body.

HP:0011035.name: Abnormal renal cortex morphology
HP:0011035.definition: An abnormality of the cortex of the kidney.

HP:0011036.name: Abnormality of renal excretion
HP:0011036.definition: An altered ability of the kidneys to void urine and/or specific substances.

HP:0011037.name: Decreased urine output
HP:0011037.definition: A decreased rate of urine production.

HP:0011039.name: Abnormal helix morphology
HP:0011039.definition: An abnormality of the helix. The helix is the outer rim of the ear that extends from the insertion of the ear on the scalp (root) to the termination of the cartilage at the earlobe.

HP:0011040.name: Abnormal intrahepatic bile duct morphology
HP:0011040.definition: An abnormality of the intrahepatic bile duct.

HP:0011041.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the cervical spine
HP:0011041.definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the cervical vertebral column.

HP:0011043.name: Abnormal circulating adrenocorticotropin concentration
HP:0011043.definition: An abnormal concentration of corticotropin in the blood.

HP:0011044.name: Abnormal number of permanent teeth
HP:0011044.definition: The presence of an altered number of of permanent teeth.

HP:0011045.name: Agenesis of permanent maxillary central incisor

HP:0011046.name: Agenesis of primary maxillary central incisor
HP:0011046.definition: Agenesis of upper central primary incisor.

HP:0011047.name: Agenesis of primary mandibular central incisor

HP:0011048.name: Agenesis of permanent mandibular central incisor

HP:0011049.name: Agenesis of primary maxillary lateral incisor
HP:0011049.definition: Agenesis of one or more maxillary lateral incisor, comprising the maxillary lateral primary incisor.

HP:0011050.name: Agenesis of permanent maxillary lateral incisor
HP:0011050.definition: Agenesis of one or more upper lateral secondary incisor.

HP:0011056.name: Agenesis of first permanent molar tooth
HP:0011056.definition: Agenesis of either maxillary first permanent molar or mandibular first permanent molar or both.

HP:0011057.name: Agenesis of second permanent molar
HP:0011057.definition: Agenesis of either mandibular second permanent molar or maxillary second permanent molar.

HP:0011060.name: Dentinogenesis imperfecta limited to primary teeth
HP:0011060.definition: Developmental dysplasia of dentin affecting only the primary dentition.

HP:0011061.name: Abnormality of dental structure
HP:0011061.definition: An abnormality of the structure or composition of the teeth.

HP:0011063.name: Abnormal incisor morphology
HP:0011063.definition: An abnormality of morphology of the incisor tooth.

HP:0011064.name: Abnormal number of incisors
HP:0011064.definition: The presence of an altered number of the incisor teeth.

HP:0011065.name: Conical incisor
HP:0011065.definition: An abnormal conical morphology of the incisor tooth.

HP:0011067.name: Mesiodens
HP:0011067.definition: A supernumerary tooth in the midline between the maxillary central incisors.

HP:0011069.name: Supernumerary tooth
HP:0011069.definition: The presence of one or more teeth additional to the normal number.

HP:0011070.name: Abnormal molar morphology
HP:0011070.definition: An abnormality of morphology of molar tooth.

HP:0011071.name: Abnormal permanent molar morphology
HP:0011071.definition: An abnormality of morphology of permanent molar.

HP:0011073.name: Abnormality of dental color
HP:0011073.definition: A developmental defect of tooth color.

HP:0011074.name: Localized hypoplasia of dental enamel
HP:0011074.definition: A localized form of developmental hypoplasia of the dental enamel.

HP:0011079.name: Impacted tooth
HP:0011079.definition: A tooth that has not erupted because of local impediments (overcrowding or fibrous gum overgrowth).

HP:0011080.name: Abnormal premolar morphology
HP:0011080.definition: An abnormality of morphology of premolar tooth.

HP:0011081.name: Incisor macrodontia
HP:0011081.definition: Increased size of the incisor tooth.

HP:0011082.name: Conical primary incisor
HP:0011082.definition: An abnormal conical morphology of the primary incisor.

HP:0011083.name: Conical maxillary incisor
HP:0011083.definition: An abnormal conical morphology of either maxillary primary incisor tooth or maxillary permanent incisor tooth or both.

HP:0011084.name: Hypocalcification of dental enamel
HP:0011084.definition: A form of hypomineralization of enamel characterized by reduced calcification.

HP:0011085.name: Hypomature dental enamel
HP:0011085.definition: A form of hypomineralization of enamel characterized by a chalky appearance of the enamel with orange, brown, or white color.

HP:0011086.name: Dentinogenesis imperfecta of primary and permanent teeth
HP:0011086.definition: Developmental dysplasia of dentin or both the primary dentition and the permanent dentition.

HP:0011087.name: Talon cusp
HP:0011087.definition: Talon cusp is an accessory cusp located near the cingulum (the portion of the lingual or palatal aspect of the tooth that forms a convex protuberance at the cervical third of the anatomic crown).

HP:0011088.name: Dens in dente
HP:0011088.definition: An abnormality of the incisor characterized by invagination of the enamel, giving a radiographic appearance that suggests a tooth within a tooth.

HP:0011090.name: Fused teeth
HP:0011090.definition: The union of two separately developing tooth germs typically leading to one less tooth than normal in the affected dental arch.

HP:0011091.name: Gemination
HP:0011091.definition: The development of two teeth from a single tooth bud, leading to a larger fused tooth.

HP:0011092.name: Mulberry molar
HP:0011092.definition: Mulberry molars are irregular teeth generally affecting the first molars and are characterized by a grossly deformed crown imitating, as the name implies, the surface of a mulberry.

HP:0011093.name: Molarization of premolar
HP:0011093.definition: Increased size and molar morphology of premolar tooth.

HP:0011094.name: Increased overbite
HP:0011094.definition: Maxillary teeth cover the mandibular teeth when biting to an increased degree. The feature is defined as a vertical overlap of the maxillary incisors over the mandibular incisors that exceeds 2 mm.

HP:0011095.name: Overjet
HP:0011095.definition: An abnormal anteroposterior extension of the maxillary teeth beyond the plane of the mandibular teeth upon jaw closure.

HP:0011096.name: Peripheral demyelination
HP:0011096.definition: A loss of myelin from the internode regions along myelinated nerve fibers of the peripheral nervous system.

HP:0011097.name: Epileptic spasm
HP:0011097.definition: A sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that is usually more sustained than a myoclonic movement but not as sustained as a tonic seizure. Limited forms may occur: Grimacing, head nodding, or subtle eye movements. Epileptic spasms frequently occur in clusters. Infantile spasms are the best known form, but spasms can occur at all ages

HP:0011098.name: Speech apraxia
HP:0011098.definition: A type of apraxia that is characterized by difficulty or inability to execute speech movements because of problems with coordination and motor problems, leading to incorrect articulation. An increase of errors with increasing word and phrase length may occur.

HP:0011099.name: Spastic hemiparesis
HP:0011099.definition: Unilateral paresis (weakness) with spasticity of the affected muscles and increased tendon reflexes.

HP:0011100.name: Intestinal atresia
HP:0011100.definition: An abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the intestine.

HP:0011102.name: Ileal atresia
HP:0011102.definition: An abnormal closure, or atresia of the tubular structure of the ileum.

HP:0011103.name: Abnormal left ventricular outflow tract morphology
HP:0011103.definition: An abnormality of the outflow tract of the left ventricle.

HP:0011104.name: Abnormality of blood volume homeostasis
HP:0011104.definition: An abnormality in the amount of volume occupied by intravascular blood.

HP:0011105.name: Hypervolemia
HP:0011105.definition: An increase in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood.

HP:0011106.name: Hypovolemia
HP:0011106.definition: An decrease in the amount of intravascular fluid, particularly in the volume of the circulating blood.

HP:0011107.name: Recurrent aphthous stomatitis
HP:0011107.definition: Recurrent episodes of ulceration of the oral mucosa, typically presenting as painful, sharply circumscribed fibrin-covered mucosal defects with a hyperemic border.

HP:0011110.name: Recurrent tonsillitis
HP:0011110.definition: Inflammation of the tonsils that has occurred repeatedly. The definition of recurrent may vary somewhat, but the criteria used recently as a measure of severity were five or more episodes of true tonsillitis per year, symptoms recurring for at least a year, and episodes that are disabling and that prevent normal functioning. In some cases recurrent tonsillitis may be related to immunosusceptibility. Evidence exists for a genetic predisposition for recurrent tonsillitis.

HP:0011111.name: Abnormal immune serum protein physiology
HP:0011111.definition: An abnormality of the concentration or function of circulating immune proteins.

HP:0011112.name: Abnormal circulating cytokine concentration
HP:0011112.definition: Abnormality of the cytokine levels in the blood, i.e., an abnormality of any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells.

HP:0011113.name: Abnormality of cytokine secretion
HP:0011113.definition: An abnormality in the production or cellular release of a cytokine (i.e., any of the non-antibody proteins made by inflammatory leukocytes and some non-leukocytic cells that affect the behavior of other cells).

HP:0011114.name: Defective production of NFKB1-dependent cytokines
HP:0011114.definition: An impairment in the production by leukocytes of NFKB1-dependent cytokines such as tumor necrosis factor-alpha and interferon-alpha.

HP:0011115.name: Abnormal circulating chemokine concentration
HP:0011115.definition: An abnormality in the production or cellular release of a chemokine (a class of cytokines).

HP:0011116.name: Abnormal circulating interferon concentration
HP:0011116.definition: The concentration of an interferon is outside the limits of normal.

HP:0011117.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin concentration
HP:0011117.definition: The concentration of an interleukin (a class of cytokines) is outside the limits of normal.

HP:0011118.name: Abnormality of tumor necrosis factor secretion
HP:0011118.definition: An abnormality in the production or cellular release of tumor necrosis factor.

HP:0011119.name: Abnormal nasal dorsum morphology
HP:0011119.definition: An abnormality of the nasal dorsum, also known as the nasal ridge.

HP:0011120.name: Concave nasal ridge
HP:0011120.definition: Nasal ridge curving posteriorly to an imaginary line that connects the nasal root and tip.

HP:0011121.name: Abnormal skin morphology
HP:0011121.definition: Any morphological abnormality of the skin.

HP:0011122.name: Abnormality of skin physiology
HP:0011122.definition: Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin.

HP:0011123.name: Inflammatory abnormality of the skin
HP:0011123.definition: The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes.

HP:0011124.name: Abnormal epidermal morphology
HP:0011124.definition: An abnormality of the morphology of the epidermis.

HP:0011125.name: Abnormality of dermal melanosomes
HP:0011125.definition: An abnormality of the melanosomes, i.e., of the cellular organelles in which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored within melanocytes (the cells that produce pigment in the dermis).

HP:0011126.name: Nephroptosis
HP:0011126.definition: A significant descent of the kidney as the patient moves from the supine to the erect position.

HP:0011127.name: Perioral eczema
HP:0011127.definition: A type of eczema that occurs in the lips and perioral area.

HP:0011128.name: Acute esophageal necrosis
HP:0011128.definition: A condition characterized by necrosis of the mucosal and submucosal layers of the esophagus not related to ingestion of caustic or other injurious agents. Endoscopically, there is a dark lesion ('black esophagus') distributed in a circumferential manner in the distal one-third of the esophagus with or without exudates. There is involvement of the distal esophagus ending sharply at the gastroesophageal junction.

HP:0011129.name: Bilateral fetal pyelectasis
HP:0011129.definition: A bilateral form of fetal pyelectasis.

HP:0011130.name: Abnormal renal calyx morphology
HP:0011130.definition: Any abnormality of the morphology of the major calices or minor calices of the kidney.

HP:0011131.name: Perianal dermatitis
HP:0011131.definition: The presence of a rash (change of color and texture) of the perianal skin.

HP:0011132.name: Chronic furunculosis
HP:0011132.definition: A furuncle (boil) is a skin infection involving an entire hair follicle and nearby skin tissue. Chronic furunculosis refers to recurrent episodes of furuncles, often caused by recurrent staphylococcus infection.

HP:0011133.name: Increased sensitivity to ionizing radiation
HP:0011133.definition: An abnormally increased sensitivity to the effects of ionizing radiation.

HP:0011134.name: Low-grade fever
HP:0011134.definition: Mild fever that does not exceed 38.5 degrees centigrade.

HP:0011135.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the sweat glands
HP:0011135.definition: Absence or developmental hypoplasia of the sweat glands.

HP:0011137.name: Non-pruritic urticaria
HP:0011137.definition: Pale reddish slightly elevated papules and plaques of 0.5-3 cm in diameter and not accompanied by pruritus.

HP:0011138.name: Abnormal skin adnexa morphology
HP:0011138.definition: An abnormality of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands.

HP:0011139.name: Gastric duplication
HP:0011139.definition: Gastric duplication is a usually cystic malformation of gastrointestinal tract, usually attached to the greater curvature of the stomach and has no communication with the stomach.

HP:0011140.name: Gastrointestinal duplication
HP:0011140.definition: A spherical hollow structure with a smooth muscle coat, lined by a mucous membrane, and attached to any part of the gastrointestinal tract, from the base of the tongue to the anus.

HP:0011141.name: Age-related cataract
HP:0011141.definition: A type of cataract (opacification of the lens) that forms during the course of aging.

HP:0011142.name: Age-related nuclear cataract
HP:0011142.definition: A type of age-related cataract that primarily affects the nucleus of the lens.

HP:0011143.name: Age-related cortical cataract
HP:0011143.definition: A type of age-related cataract that primarily affects the cortex of the lens.

HP:0011144.name: Age-related posterior subcapsular cataract
HP:0011144.definition: A type of age-related cataract consisting of granular opacities occurring mainly in the central posterior cortex just under the posterior capsule.

HP:0011145.name: Symptomatic seizures
HP:0011145.definition: A seizure that occurs in the context of a brain insult (systemic, toxic, or metabolic) and may not recur when the underlying cause has been removed or the acute phase has elapsed.

HP:0011146.name: Dialeptic seizure
HP:0011146.definition: A dialeptic seizure is a type of seizure characterized predominantly by reduced responsiveness or awareness and with subsequent at least partial amnesia of the event.

HP:0011147.name: Typical absence seizure
HP:0011147.definition: A typical absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by its sudden onset, interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare, possibly a brief upward deviation of the eyes. Usually the patient will be unresponsive when spoken to. Duration is a few seconds to half a minute with very rapid recovery. Although not always available, an EEG would usually show 3 Hz generalized epileptiform discharges during the event.

HP:0011148.name: obsolete Absence seizures with special features

HP:0011149.name: Absence seizure with eyelid myoclonia
HP:0011149.definition: An absence with eyelid myoclonia seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by forced upward jerking of the eyelids during an absence seizure.

HP:0011150.name: Myoclonic absence seizure
HP:0011150.definition: Myoclonic absence seizure is a type of generalized non-motor (absence) seizure characterized by an interruption of ongoing activities, a blank stare and rhythmic three-per-second myoclonic movements, causing ratcheting abduction of the upper limbs leading to progressive arm elevation, and associated with 3 Hz generalized spike-wave discharges on the electroencephalogram. Duration is typically 10-60 s. Whilst impairment of consciousness may not be obvious the ILAE classified this seizure as a generalized non-motor seizure in 2017.

HP:0011151.name: Atypical absence status epilepticus
HP:0011151.definition: Atypical absence status epilepticus is a type of generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma that is semiologically a prolonged atypical absence seizure.

HP:0011152.name: Early onset absence seizures
HP:0011152.definition: Typical absence seizures starting before the age of 4 years.

HP:0011153.name: Focal motor seizure
HP:0011153.definition: A type of focal-onset seizure characterized by a motor sign as its initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0011154.name: Focal autonomic seizure
HP:0011154.definition: An autonomic seizure is a type of focal non-motor seizure characterized by alteration of autonomic nervous system function as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0011155.name: obsolete Focal autonomic seizures with altered responsiveness

HP:0011156.name: obsolete Focal autonomic seizures without altered responsiveness

HP:0011157.name: Focal sensory seizure
HP:0011157.definition: A focal sensory seizure is a type seizure beginning with a subjective sensation.

HP:0011158.name: Focal sensory seizure with auditory features
HP:0011158.definition: A seizure characterized by elementary auditory phenomena including buzzing, ringing, drumming or single tones as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0011159.name: Focal autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation/nausea/vomiting/other gastrointestinal phenomena
HP:0011159.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by symptoms or signs pertaining to the gastrointestinal system as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0011160.name: Focal sensory seizure with gustatory features
HP:0011160.definition: A seizure characterized by taste phenomena including acidic, bitter, salty, sweet, or metallic tastes as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0011161.name: Focal sensory seizure with olfactory features
HP:0011161.definition: Seizures characterized by olfactory phenomena as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0011163.name: Focal sensory seizure with somatosensory features
HP:0011163.definition: A seizure characterized by sensory phenomena including tingling, numbness, electric-shock like sensation, pain, sense of movement, or desire to move as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0011165.name: Focal sensory seizure with visual features
HP:0011165.definition: A seizure characterized by elementary visual hallucinations such as flashing or flickering lights/colors, or other shapes, simple patterns, scotomata, or amaurosis as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0011166.name: Focal myoclonic seizure
HP:0011166.definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sudden, brief (<100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction(s) of muscles(s) or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal). Myoclonus is less regularly repetitive and less sustained than is clonus.

HP:0011167.name: Focal tonic seizure
HP:0011167.definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by sustained increase in muscle contraction, lasting a few seconds to minutes.

HP:0011168.name: Focal seizure with eyelid myoclonia
HP:0011168.definition: Focal seizure with eyelid myoclonia, not eyelid myoclonias in the context of absence seizures.

HP:0011169.name: Generalized clonic seizure
HP:0011169.definition: Generalized clonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by sustained bilateral jerking, either symmetric or asymmetric, that is regularly repetitive and involves the same muscle groups.

HP:0012435.name: Ventral shortening of foreskin
HP:0012435.definition: Reduction in length of the ventral (lower) skin of prepuce of penis.

HP:0012436.name: Nonocclusive coronary artery atherosclerosis
HP:0012436.definition: Coronary disease that has not progressed to the point of causing significant occlusion (blockage) of the coronary arteries.

HP:0012437.name: Abnormal gallbladder morphology
HP:0012437.definition: A structural anomaly of the gallbladder.

HP:0012438.name: Abnormal gallbladder physiology
HP:0012438.definition: A functional anomaly of the gallbladder.

HP:0012439.name: Abnormal biliary tract physiology
HP:0012439.definition: A functional abnormality of the biliary tree.

HP:0012440.name: Abnormal biliary tract morphology
HP:0012440.definition: A structural abnormality of the biliary tree.

HP:0012441.name: Sphincter of Oddi dyskinesia
HP:0012441.definition: Reduced motility through the sphincter of Oddi, resulting in impedance of bile and pancreatic juice flow from the common bile duct into the duodenum.

HP:0012442.name: Gallbladder dyskinesia
HP:0012442.definition: Reduced motility of the gallbladder with reduced emptying fraction.

HP:0012443.name: Abnormal brain morphology
HP:0012443.definition: A structural abnormality of the brain, which has as its parts the forebrain, midbrain, and hindbrain.

HP:0012444.name: Brain atrophy
HP:0012444.definition: Partial or complete wasting (loss) of brain tissue that was once present.

HP:0012446.name: Decreased CSF 5-methyltetrahydrofolate concentration
HP:0012446.definition: A reduced concentration of 5-methyltetrahydrofolate(2-) in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). 5-methyltetrahydrofolate is the active folate metabolite.

HP:0012447.name: Abnormal myelination
HP:0012447.definition: Any anomaly in the process by which myelin sheaths are formed and maintained around neurons.

HP:0012449.name: Sacroiliac joint synovitis
HP:0012449.definition: Inflammation of the synovial membrane of the sacroiliac joint.

HP:0012450.name: Chronic constipation
HP:0012450.definition: Constipation for longer than three months with fewer than 3 bowel movements per week, straining, lumpy or hard stools, and a sensation of anorectal obstruction or incomplete defecation.

HP:0012451.name: Acute constipation
HP:0012451.definition: Constipation of sudden onset and lasting for less than three months.

HP:0012452.name: Restless legs
HP:0012452.definition: Restless Leg Syndrome (RLS) is a condition characterized by an uncomfortable and restless sensation in the legs that occurs after going to bed, often leading to insomnia.

HP:0012453.name: Bilateral wrist flexion contracture
HP:0012453.definition: A chronic loss of wrist joint motion on the right and left sides.

HP:0012454.name: Unilateral wrist flexion contracture
HP:0012454.definition: A chronic loss of wrist joint motion on one side only.

HP:0012456.name: Medial arterial calcification
HP:0012456.definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of arteries.

HP:0012457.name: Medial calcification of medium-sized arteries
HP:0012457.definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of medium-sized (muscular or distributive) arteries.

HP:0012458.name: Medial calcification of small arteries
HP:0012458.definition: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the tunica media of small arteries.

HP:0012459.name: Hypnic headache
HP:0012459.definition: A headache disorder that occurs exclusively at night, waking the affected individual from sleep.

HP:0012460.name: Dysmorphic inferior cerebellar vermis
HP:0012460.definition: A structural anomaly of the inferior portion of the vermis of cerebellum.

HP:0012461.name: Bacteriuria
HP:0012461.definition: The presence of bacteria in the urine.

HP:0012462.name: Chin myoclonus
HP:0012462.definition: Involuntary and irregular twitches of the chin.

HP:0012463.name: Elevated transferrin saturation
HP:0012463.definition: An above normal level of saturation of serum transferrin with iron.

HP:0012464.name: Decreased transferrin saturation
HP:0012464.definition: A below normal level of saturation of serum transferrin with iron.

HP:0012465.name: Elevated hepatic iron concentration
HP:0012465.definition: An increased level of iron in liver tissues.

HP:0012466.name: Chronic respiratory acidosis
HP:0012466.definition: Longstanding impairment in ventilation such that the partial pressure of carbon dioxide (PaCO2) is elevated above the upper limit of the reference range (more than 45 mm Hg), with a normal or near-normal pH secondary to renal compensation and an elevated serum bicarbonate levels (more than30 mEq/L).

HP:0012467.name: Acute respiratory acidosis
HP:0012467.definition: Sudden onset of impairment in ventilation such that the removal of carbon dioxide by the respiratory system is less than the production of carbon dioxide in the tissues, leading to an elevation of the partial pressure of carbon dioxide (PaCO2) above the normal limits (more than 45 mm Hg) with an accompanying acidemia (pH less than 7.35).

HP:0012468.name: Chronic acidosis
HP:0012468.definition: Longstanding abnormal acid accumulation or depletion of base.

HP:0012469.name: Infantile spasms
HP:0012469.definition: Infantile spasms represent a subset of "epileptic spasms". Infantile Spasms are epileptic spasms starting in the first year of life (infancy).

HP:0012470.name: Setting-sun eye phenomenon
HP:0012470.definition: An ophthalmologic sign in young children resulting from upward-gaze paresis. In this condition, the eyes appear driven downward, the sclera may be seen between the upper eyelid and the iris, and part of the lower pupil may be covered by the lower eyelid.

HP:0012471.name: Thick vermilion border
HP:0012471.definition: Increased width of the skin of vermilion border region of upper lip.

HP:0012472.name: Eclabion
HP:0012472.definition: A turning outward of the lip or lips, that is, eversion of the lips.

HP:0012474.name: Carotid artery occlusion
HP:0012474.definition: Complete obstruction of a carotid artery.

HP:0012475.name: Decreased circulating level of specific antibody
HP:0012475.definition: The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against a specific antigen or microorganism.

HP:0012476.name: Decreased specific pneumococcal antibody level
HP:0012476.definition: The presence of normal overall immunoglobulin levels with deficiency of specific immunoglobulins directed against pneumococci.

HP:0012477.name: Vocal tremor
HP:0012477.definition: A wavering, unsteady voice that reflects involuntary and approximately sinusoidal oscillation of motor unit firings of laryngeal muscles. Vocal tremor results in low frequency modulations of voice frequency or amplitude and intermittent voice instability.

HP:0012478.name: Temporomandibular joint ankylosis
HP:0012478.definition: Bony fusion of the mandibular condyle to the base of the skull, resulting in limitation of jaw opening.

HP:0012479.name: Temporomandibular joint crepitus
HP:0012479.definition: Noises from the temporomandibular joint during mandibular movement (e.g., chewing). Temporomandibular joint crepitus is often described as a clicking, popping, grating sound.

HP:0012481.name: Cerebral venous angioma
HP:0012481.definition: A congenital malformation of veins which drain normal brain characterized by a caput medusae or an umbrellalike convergence of multiple venules on a single, or occasionally multiple, enlarged parenchymal or medullary vein, like the trunk of a tree or the shank of an umbrella. This dilated terminal vein penetrates the cortex to drain either (a) superficially to cortical veins or sinuses, (b) deeply to subependymal veins of the lateral ventricle and then into the galenic system, (c) to the fourth ventricle and then to the pontomesencephalic vein, or (d) to the precentral cerebellar vein and into the galenic system.

HP:0012482.name: Frontal venous angioma
HP:0012482.definition: A venous angioma of the frontal lobe of the brain.

HP:0012483.name: Abnormal alpha granules
HP:0012483.definition: Defective structure, size or content of alpha granules, platelet organelles that contain several growth factors destined for release during platelet activation at sites of vessel wall injury.

HP:0012484.name: Abnormal dense granules
HP:0012484.definition: Defective structure, size or content of dense granules, platelet organelles that contain granules proaggregatory factors such as adenosine diphosphate (ADP), adenosine triphosphate (ATP), ionized calcium, histamine and serotonin.

HP:0012485.name: Abnormal surface-connected open canalicular system
HP:0012485.definition: An anomaly of the invaginations of the surface membrane that form the open canalicular system (OCS). The OCS serve as the pathway for transport of substances into the cells and as conduits for the discharge of alpha granule products secreted during the platelet release reaction.

HP:0012487.name: Cerebellopontine angle arachnoid cyst
HP:0012487.definition: An arachnoid cyst located at the margin of the cerebellum and pons.

HP:0012488.name: Intraventricular arachnoid cyst
HP:0012488.definition: An arachnoid cyst located within the ventricular system.

HP:0012489.name: Suprasellar arachnoid cyst
HP:0012489.definition: An arachnoid cyst that progressively enlarges from an abnormality in the membrane of Liliequist or in the interpeduncular cistern, and typically, expands from the prepontine space, displacing the floor of the third ventricle upwards, the pituitary stalk and optic chiasm upwards and forwards, and the mammillary bodies upwards and backwards.

HP:0012491.name: Abnormal dense tubular system
HP:0012491.definition: An anomaly of the intracellular membrane complexes known as the dense tubular system.

HP:0012492.name: Cerebral artery stenosis
HP:0012492.definition: Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of a cerebral artery.

HP:0012493.name: Middle cerebral artery stenosis
HP:0012493.definition: Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the middle cerebral artery.

HP:0012494.name: Anterior cerebral artery stenosis
HP:0012494.definition: Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the anterior cerebral artery.

HP:0012495.name: Posterior cerebral artery stenosis
HP:0012495.definition: Narrowing or constriction of the inner surface (lumen) of the posterior cerebral artery.

HP:0012496.name: Reduced maximal inspiratory pressure
HP:0012496.definition: A decrease in the maximum amount of negative pressure a person can generate during an inhalation.

HP:0012497.name: Reduced maximal expiratory pressure
HP:0012497.definition: A decrease in the maximum amount of pressure of expired air achieved by a person after a full inspiration.

HP:0012498.name: Nuchal cord
HP:0012498.definition: A complication of pregnancy and delivery in which the umbilical cord wraps around the fetal neck once or multiple times.

HP:0012499.name: Descending aortic dissection
HP:0012499.definition: A separation of the layers within the wall of the descending aorta. Tears in the intimal layer result in the propagation of dissection (proximally or distally) secondary to blood entering the intima-media space.

HP:0012500.name: Verrucous papule
HP:0012500.definition: A wartlike (with multiple small elevated projections) papule.

HP:0012501.name: Abnormal brainstem white matter morphology
HP:0012501.definition: An anomaly of the white matter of brainstem.

HP:0012502.name: Abnormality of the internal capsule
HP:0012502.definition: An anomaly of the internal capsule, which is an area of white matter in the brain that separates the caudate nucleus and the thalamus from the putamen and the globus pallidus.

HP:0012503.name: Abnormal pituitary gland morphology
HP:0012503.definition: An anomaly of the pituitary gland.

HP:0012504.name: Abnormal size of pituitary gland
HP:0012504.definition: A deviation from the normal size of the pituitary gland.

HP:0012505.name: Enlarged pituitary gland
HP:0012505.definition: An abnormally increased size of the pituitary gland.

HP:0012506.name: Small pituitary gland
HP:0012506.definition: An abnormally decreased size of the pituitary gland.

HP:0012507.name: Weakness of orbicularis oculi muscle
HP:0012507.definition: Reduced strength of the orbicularis oculi, the circumorbital muscle in the face that closes the eyelid.

HP:0012508.name: Metamorphopsia
HP:0012508.definition: A visual anomaly in which images appear distorted. A grid of straight lines appears wavy and parts of the grid may appear blank.

HP:0012509.name: Reduced thyroxin-binding globulin
HP:0012509.definition: An abnormally decreased amount of thyroxin-binding globulin (TBG) in blood. TBG is responsible for carrying the thyroid hormones thyroxine (T4) and 3,5,3'-triiodothyronine (T3) in the bloodstream.

HP:0012510.name: Extra-axial cerebrospinal fluid accumulation
HP:0012510.definition: An increased amount of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) in the subarachnoid space.

HP:0012511.name: Temporal optic disc pallor
HP:0012511.definition: A pale yellow discoloration of the temporal (lateral) portion of the optic disc.

HP:0012512.name: Diffuse optic disc pallor
HP:0012512.definition: A pale yellow discoloration of the entire optic disc.

HP:0012513.name: Upper limb pain
HP:0012513.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the arm.

HP:0012514.name: Lower limb pain
HP:0012514.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the leg.

HP:0012515.name: Hip flexor weakness
HP:0012515.definition: Reduced ability to flex the femur, that is, to pull the knee upward.

HP:0012516.name: Tetralogy of Fallot with pulmonary atresia
HP:0012516.definition: An extreme form of tetralogy of Fallot characterized by absence of flow from the right ventricle to the pulmonary arteries.

HP:0012517.name: Reduced circulating catalase activity
HP:0012517.definition: Activity or concentration of catalase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0012518.name: Abnormal circle of Willis morphology
HP:0012518.definition: An anomaly of the circle of Willis, also known as the cerebral arterial circle.

HP:0012519.name: Hypoplastic posterior communicating artery
HP:0012519.definition: A developmental anomnaly characterized by underdevelopment of the posterior communicating artery.

HP:0012520.name: Dilation of Virchow-Robin spaces
HP:0012520.definition: Increased dimensions of the Virchow-Robin spaces (also known as perivascular spaces), which surround the walls of vessels as they course from the subarachnoid space through the brain parenchyma. Perivascular spaces are commonly microscopic, and not visible on conventional neuroimaging. This term refers to an increase of size of these spaces such that they are visible on neuroimaging (usually magnetic resonance imaging). The dilatations are regular cavities that always contain a patent artery.

HP:0012521.name: Optic nerve aplasia
HP:0012521.definition: Congenital absence of the optic nerve.

HP:0012522.name: Spider hemangioma
HP:0012522.definition: A form of telangiectasis characterized by a central elevated red dot the size of a pinhead, representing an arteriole, with numerous small blood vessels that radiate out thereby resembling the legs of a spider. Characteristically, compression of the central arteriole causes the entire lesion to blanch, and the lesion quickly refills once the compression is released.

HP:0012523.name: Oral aversion
HP:0012523.definition: Reluctance or refusal of a child to be breastfed or eat, manifested as gagging, vomiting, turning head away from food, or avoidance of sensation in or around the mouth (i.e. toothbrushing or face-washing).

HP:0012524.name: Abnormal platelet shape
HP:0012524.definition: A deviation from the normal discoid platelet shape.

HP:0012525.name: Abnormal alpha granule distribution
HP:0012525.definition: An anomalous location and arrangement of platelet alpha granules.

HP:0012526.name: Absence of alpha granules
HP:0012526.definition: A lack of platelet alpha granules. This typically results in the gray appearance of platelets in giemsa stained blood smears.

HP:0012527.name: Abnormal alpha granule content
HP:0012527.definition: A deviation from the normal contents of the platelet alpha granules, which normally contain hemostatic proteins such as fibrinogen, von Willebrand factor, and growth factors such as platelet-derived growth factor.

HP:0012528.name: Abnormal number of alpha granules
HP:0012528.definition: A deviation from the normal count of alpha granules per thrombocyte.

HP:0012529.name: Abnormal dense granule content
HP:0012529.definition: A deviation from the normal contents of the platelet alpha granules, which normally contain adenosine triphosphate (ATP), adenosine diphosphate (ADP), serotonin, calcium, and pyrophosphate, which are secreted when platelets are activated.

HP:0012530.name: Abnormal number of dense granules
HP:0012530.definition: A deviation from the normal count of dense granules per thrombocyte.

HP:0012531.name: Pain
HP:0012531.definition: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.

HP:0012532.name: Chronic pain
HP:0012532.definition: Persistent pain, usually defined as pain that has lasted longer than 3 to 6 months.

HP:0012533.name: Allodynia
HP:0012533.definition: Pain due to a stimulus that does not normally provoke pain.

HP:0012534.name: Dysesthesia
HP:0012534.definition: Painful sensations elicited by a nonpainful cutaneous stimulus such as a light touch or gentle stroking over affected areas of the body. Sometimes referred to as hyperpathia or hyperalgesia. Often perceived as an intense burning, dyesthesias may outlast the stimulus by several seconds.

HP:0012535.name: Abnormal synaptic transmission
HP:0012535.definition: An anomaly in the communication from a neuron to a target across a synapse. This is a four step process, comprising (i) synthesis and storage of neurotransmitters; (ii) neurotransmitter release; (iii) activation of postsynaptic receptors by the neurotransmitter; and (iv) inactivation of the neurotransmitter. Thus, this term is defined as an anomaly of neurotransmitter metabolic process.

HP:0012536.name: Maternal anticardiolipin antibody positive
HP:0012536.definition: The presence of circulating autoantibodies to anticardiolipin in the mother.

HP:0012537.name: Food intolerance
HP:0012537.definition: A detrimental reaction to a food, beverage, food additive, or compound found in foods that produces symptoms in one or more body organs and systems that is not mediated by an immune reaction.

HP:0012538.name: Gluten intolerance
HP:0012538.definition: A detrimental reaction to the presence of gluten in food, which may include abdominal pain, fatigue, headaches and paresthesia, or celiac disease.

HP:0012539.name: Non-Hodgkin lymphoma
HP:0012539.definition: A type of lymphoma characterized microscopically by the absence of multinucleated Reed-Sternberg cells.

HP:0012540.name: Axillary epidermoid cyst
HP:0012540.definition: An epidermoid cyst in the armpit.

HP:0012541.name: Cephalohematoma
HP:0012541.definition: Hemorrhage between the skull and periosteum of a newborn resulting from rupture of blood vessels that cross the periosteum.

HP:0012543.name: Hemosiderinuria
HP:0012543.definition: The presence of hemosiderin in the urine.

HP:0012544.name: Elevated circulating aldolase concentration
HP:0012544.definition: Concentration of fructose 1,6-bisphosphate aldolase in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0012545.name: Reduced circulating aldolase concentration
HP:0012545.definition: Concentration of fructose 1,6-bisphosphate aldolase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0012546.name: Skewed maternal X inactivation
HP:0012546.definition: A deviation from equal (50%) inactivation of each parental X chromosome in maternal cells.

HP:0012547.name: Abnormal involuntary eye movements
HP:0012547.definition: Anomalous movements of the eyes that occur without the subject wanting them to happen.

HP:0012548.name: Fatty replacement of skeletal muscle
HP:0012548.definition: Muscle fibers degeneration resulting in fatty replacement of skeletal muscle fibers

HP:0012549.name: Conjunctival lipoma
HP:0012549.definition: A lipoma (a benign tumor composed of adipose tissue) located in the conjunctiva.

HP:0012550.name: Colonic varices
HP:0012550.definition: The presence of varices (enlarged and convoluted blood vessels) in the colon.

HP:0012551.name: Absent neutrophil specific granules
HP:0012551.definition: Lack of specific granules in neutrophils.

HP:0012552.name: Increased neutrophil nuclear projections
HP:0012552.definition: Presence of an elevated number of projections from nuclei of neutrophils. These projections can have the shape of hooks, tags, or clubs.

HP:0012553.name: Hypoplastic thumbnail
HP:0012553.definition: A thumbnail that is diminished in length and width, i.e., underdeveloped thumb nail.

HP:0012556.name: Hyperbeta-alaninemia
HP:0012556.definition: Increased concentration of beta-alanine in the blood.

HP:0012557.name: EEG with centrotemporal focal spike waves
HP:0012557.definition: EEG with focal sharp transient waves in the centrotemporal region of the brain (also known as the central sulcus), i.e., focal sharp waves of a duration less than 80 msec followed by a slow wave.

HP:0012558.name: Abnormal T3/T4 ratio
HP:0012558.definition: A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that deviates from normal.

HP:0012559.name: Increased T3/T4 ratio
HP:0012559.definition: A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that is higher than normal.

HP:0012560.name: Decreased T3/T4 ratio
HP:0012560.definition: A ratio of serum triiodothyronine (T3) to thyroxine (T4) in the blood that is lower than normal.

HP:0012561.name: Unicuspid aortic valve
HP:0012561.definition: The presence of an aortic valve with one instead of the normal three cusps (flaps).

HP:0012562.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in hand
HP:0012562.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the hand, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0012563.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in foot
HP:0012563.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the foot, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0012564.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in tibia
HP:0012564.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the tibia, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0012565.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in fibula
HP:0012565.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the fibula, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0012566.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in radius
HP:0012566.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the radius, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0012567.name: Premature epimetaphyseal fusion in ulna
HP:0012567.definition: Stop of growth at the epiphyseal plate the hyaline cartilage plate in the metaphysis at one or more long bones in the ulna, at an earlier than normal age, resulting in growth arrest and shortening of the involved bone.

HP:0012568.name: Lower eyelid edema
HP:0012568.definition: Edema in the region of the Lower eyelid.

HP:0012569.name: Delayed menarche
HP:0012569.definition: First period after the age of 15 years.

HP:0012570.name: Synovial sarcoma
HP:0012570.definition: A type of mesenchymal tissue cell tumor that exhibits epithelial differentiation, which most frequently arises in the extremities.

HP:0012571.name: Ureter fissus
HP:0012571.definition: A partial duplication of the ureter where the duplicated ureters fuse to a single ureter before their insertion into the bladder.

HP:0012572.name: Ureter duplex
HP:0012572.definition: A complete duplication of the ureter, where the duplicated ureters have separate insertions into the bladder.

HP:0012573.name: Global proximal tubulopathy
HP:0012573.definition: A type of proximal renal tubulopathy characterized by resorption defects leading to glycosuria, aminoaciduria, tubular proteinuria, renal hypophosphatemia, and urate tubular hyporeabsorption with bicarbonate loss and resulting acidosis.

HP:0032416.name: Retinal microaneurysm
HP:0032416.definition: A localized dilation of microvasculature formed due to disruption of the internal elastic lamina of a retinal capillary blood vessel. The lesions present as small circular, red dots having distinct margins and are no larger than a blood vessel width at the disk margin. This expansion disturbs the normal flow pattern, changing shear force and pressure along the vessel. Shear force plays a key role in promoting the differentiation and proliferation of endothelial cells.

HP:0032417.name: Periglomerular fibrosis
HP:0032417.definition: Circumferential fibrosis in the interstitium surrounding Bowman's capsule

HP:0032418.name: Abnormal HDL subfraction concentration
HP:0032418.definition: An abnormal concentration of an HDL subfraction, which can be determined by methods such as electrophoresis followed by densitometric determination of the areas under the peaks. Large HDL subfractions are defined as HDL1 (greater than 12 nm), HDL2b (9.7-12 nm), and HDL2a (8.8-9.69 nm). Small HDL subfractions are defined as HDL3a (8.2-8.79 nm), HDL3b (7.8-8.19 nm), and HDL3c (7.20-7.79 nm).

HP:0032419.name: Abnormal HDL2a concentration
HP:0032419.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of the HDL2a subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL2a particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 8.80-9.69 nm.

HP:0032420.name: Increased HDL2a concentration
HP:0032420.definition: An elevation above the normal concentration of the HDL2a subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL2a particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 8.80-9.69 nm.

HP:0032421.name: Decreased HDL2a concentration
HP:0032421.definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of the HDL2a subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL2a particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 8.80-9.69 nm.

HP:0032422.name: Abnormal HDL2b concentration
HP:0032422.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of the HDL2b subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL2b particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 9.7-12 nm.

HP:0032423.name: Decreased HDL2b concentration
HP:0032423.definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of the HDL2b subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL2b particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 9.7-12 nm.

HP:0032424.name: Increased HDL2b concentration
HP:0032424.definition: An elevation above the normal concentration of the HDL2b subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL2b particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 9.7-12 nm.

HP:0032425.name: Abnormal HDL3a concentration
HP:0032425.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of the HDL3a subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3a particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 8.2-8.79 nm.

HP:0032426.name: Abnormal HDL3b concentration
HP:0032426.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of the HDL3b subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3b particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 7.8-8.19 nm.

HP:0032427.name: Abnormal HDL3c concentration
HP:0032427.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of the HDL3c subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3c particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 7.20-7.79 nm.

HP:0032428.name: Increased HDL3a concentration
HP:0032428.definition: An elevation above the normal concentration of the HDL3a subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3a particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 8.2-8.79 nm.

HP:0032429.name: Decreased HDL3a concentration
HP:0032429.definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of the HDL3a subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3a particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 8.2-8.79 nm.

HP:0032430.name: Increased HDL3b concentration
HP:0032430.definition: An elevation above the normal concentration of the HDL3b subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3b particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 7.8-8.19 nm.

HP:0032431.name: Decreased HDL3b concentration
HP:0032431.definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of the HDL3b subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3b particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 7.8-8.19 nm.

HP:0032432.name: Increased HDL3c concentration
HP:0032432.definition: An elevation above the normal concentration of the HDL3c subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3c particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 7.20-7.79 nm.

HP:0032433.name: Decreased HDL3c concentration
HP:0032433.definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of the HDL3c subfraction in the blood circulation. An HDL3c particle is defined as an HDL particle with a size of 7.20-7.79 nm.

HP:0032434.name: Delayed umbilical cord separation
HP:0032434.definition: Separation of the umbilical cord occurs at an abnormally late timepoint.

HP:0032435.name: Neonatal omphalitis
HP:0032435.definition: An infection of the umbilicus and/or surrounding tissues occurring in the neonatal period.

HP:0032436.name: Abnormal circulating C-reactive protein concentration
HP:0032436.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of C-reactive protein in the blood circulation.

HP:0032437.name: Reduced circulating C-reactive protein concecntration
HP:0032437.definition: An abnormal decrease of the C-reactive protein level in serum.

HP:0032438.name: Platelet anisocytosis
HP:0032438.definition: Abnormally increased variability in the size of platelets.

HP:0032439.name: Airborn particle hypersensitivity
HP:0032439.definition: An abnormally increased sensitivity to airborn particles. This can be diagnosed on the basis of the medical history, taking into account seasonality or a relationship to the concentration of airborn particles in the environment of the affected individual. Aerosol challenge is a gold standard of establishment of the symptom. There exist particle hypersensitivity (diesel exhaust, metals, inorganic material) vs. allergen (including pollen dander, etc) hypersensitivity. The responses are usually different and testing for allergen hypersensitivity is done in concert with serum IgE and or skin testing to the suspected allergen.

HP:0032440.name: Blood group B
HP:0032440.definition: ABO phenotype B, corresponding to the genotype BO or BB.

HP:0032441.name: Blood group AB
HP:0032441.definition: ABO phenotype AB, corresponding to the genotype AB.

HP:0032442.name: Blood group O
HP:0032442.definition: ABO phenotype O, corresponding to the genotype OO.

HP:0032443.name: Past medical history
HP:0032443.definition: In a medical encounter, the physician generally will interview the patient about his or her current problem, and may perform additional testing. The past medical history (PMH) in contrast records information about the patient's medical, personal and family history that might be relevant to the presenting illness or to provide optimal clinical management. The PMH generally includes (if relevant) other major illnesses, hospitalizations, surgeries, injuries, allergies, gynecologic and obstetric history, family history, personal history including occupational history, alcohol and drug use, etc.

HP:0032444.name: Status post organ transplantation
HP:0032444.definition: The affected individual has received an organ transplant previous to the current medical encounter.

HP:0032445.name: Pulmonary cyst
HP:0032445.definition: A round circumscribed space within a lung that is surrounded by an epithelial or fibrous wall of variable thickness. A cyst usually has a thin and regular wall (less than 2 mm) and contains air, although some may contain fluid.

HP:0032446.name: Pulmonary bulla
HP:0032446.definition: Pulmonary bullae are rounded focal regions of emphysema with a thin wall which measure more than 1 cm in diameter. They are often subpleural in location and are typically larger in the apices. In some cases, bullae can be very large and result in compression of adjacent lung tissue. A giant bulla is arbitrarily defined as one that occupies at least one third of the volume of a hemithorax. When large, bullae can simulate pneumothorax. The most common cause is paraseptal emphysema but bullae may also be seen in association with centrilobular emphysema.

HP:0032447.name: Pulmonary bleb
HP:0032447.definition: A bleb is a small gas-containing space within the visceral pleura or in the subpleural lung, not larger than 1 cm in diameter. CT findings show a bleb as a thin-walled cystic air space contiguous with the pleura.

HP:0032448.name: Achlorhydria
HP:0032448.definition: A condition in which production of hydrochloric acid in the stomach is absent.

HP:0032449.name: Abnormal dermoepidermal hemidesmosome morphology
HP:0032449.definition: An abnormal structure or appearance of hemidesmosomes, multiprotein complexes that facilitate the stable adhesion of basal epithelial cells to the underlying basement membrane.

HP:0032450.name: Positive blood arsenic test
HP:0032450.definition: Detection of arsenic in the blood circulation.

HP:0032451.name: Oral melanotic macule
HP:0032451.definition: Flat, distinct, discolored area of oral mucosal membrane less than 1 cm wide not associated with a change in the thickness or texture of the affected mucosal membrane. The lesions are small, solitary, well-circumscribed and often uniformly pigmented.

HP:0032452.name: Oral melanoacanthoma
HP:0032452.definition: Oral melanoacanthoma usually presents as an asymptomatic, ill-defined, rapidly enlarging, macular pigmentation. Although most lesions are heavily pigmented, the coloration may or may not be uniform. Any mucosal site may be affected, but buccal mucosal involvement is most common. Although typically solitary, rare patients may present with multifocal lesions.

HP:0032453.name: Abnormal lip pigmentation
HP:0032453.definition: Abnormal coloring of the lip, whereby the lip discolored, blotchy, or darker or lighter than normal.

HP:0032454.name: Labial melanotic macule
HP:0032454.definition: Flat, distinct, discolored area on the lip less than 1 cm wide not associated with a change in the thickness or texture.

HP:0032455.name: Reduced granulocyte CD18 level
HP:0032455.definition: Reduced level of CD18 on the granulocyte surface. This feature can be assessed by flow cytometry.

HP:0032456.name: Unlayered lissencephaly
HP:0032456.definition: A type of lissencephaly whereby upon neuropathological examination the cortical plate is severely disorganized with a festooned-like pattern and with neither lamination nor clear demarcation between white and gray matter.

HP:0032457.name: 2-3-layered lissencephaly
HP:0032457.definition: Pachygyria-agyria spectrum whereby at neuropathological examination the cortical plate consists of a two-three layered organization made up of a molecular layer, a relatively thin wavy layer with a higher cellular density and a third layer with lower cellularity.

HP:0032458.name: Narrowing of medullary canal
HP:0032458.definition: A reduction in diameter and volume of the central cavity of bone where red or yellow bone marrow is located.

HP:0032459.name: Abnormal phosphoribosylpyrophosphate synthetase level
HP:0032459.definition: Any deviation from the normal level of the enzyme phosphoribosyl pyrophosphatesynthetase, which catalyzes the synthesis of PP-ribose-P from ATP and ribose-5-phosphate.

HP:0032460.name: Decreased phosphoribosylpyrophosphate synthetase level
HP:0032460.definition: Abnormally reduced level of the enzyme phosphoribosyl pyrophosphatesynthetase, which catalyzes the synthesis of PP-ribose-P from ATP and ribose-5-phosphate.

HP:0032462.name: Increased circulating palmitate level
HP:0032462.definition: An elevation beyond the normal concentration of palmitate (palmitic acid) in the blood circulation.

HP:0032463.name: Reduced circulating fibronectin level
HP:0032463.definition: A reduction below the normal concentration of fibronectin the the blood circulation.

HP:0032465.name: Bladder trabeculation
HP:0032465.definition: Muscular projections that protrude into the lumen of the bladder, criss-crossing the walls of the bladder on its inner surface.

HP:0032466.name: Aplasia of the olfactory bulb
HP:0032466.definition: Lack of formation (congenital absence) of the olfactory bulb.

HP:0032467.name: Past obstetric history
HP:0032467.definition: Information about past pregnancies including gravidity (number of times a woman has been pregnant, regardless of the outcome), parity (total number of births), gestational age of births, and medical conditions related to past pregnancies.

HP:0032468.name: History of stillbirth
HP:0032468.definition: One or more previous pregnancies resulted in stillbirth, defined as death of a fetus in the later stages of pregnancy (definitions in the literature vary, with cut-offs ranging from 20 to 28 weeks gestation).

HP:0032469.name: Anti-asialoglycoprotein receptor antibody positivity
HP:0032469.definition: Presence of autoantibodies against the asialoglycoprotein receptor (ASGPR) in the blood circulation.

HP:0032470.name: Monilethrix
HP:0032470.definition: The hair shaft has a beaded appearance due to the presence of elliptical nodes that have the diameter of normal hair and are medullated, regularly separated by internodes that are narrow, devoid of medulla and are the site of fracture.

HP:0032471.name: Focal polymicrogyria
HP:0032471.definition: Polymicrogyria affecting one or multiple small areas of the cerebral cortex.

HP:0032472.name: Abnormal urine urobilinogen level
HP:0032472.definition: An abnormal concentration of urobilinogen in the urine.

HP:0032473.name: Decreased urine urobilinogen
HP:0032473.definition: An abnormally reduced concentration of urobilinogen in the urine.

HP:0032476.name: Abnormal circulating vitamin B6 concentration
HP:0032476.definition: An abnormal concentration of vitamin B6 in the blood circulation.

HP:0032477.name: Elevated circulating vitamin B6 concentration
HP:0032477.definition: An abnormally increased concentration of vitamin B6 in the blood circulation.

HP:0032478.name: Lateral spinal meningocele
HP:0032478.definition: Protrusion of the arachnoid and dura through spinal foramina.

HP:0032479.name: Preimplantation lethality
HP:0032479.definition: It is estimated that about 40-70 percent of human embryos produced in vitro fertilization (IVF) and intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI) are viable embryos, whereas others arrest at different early stages of development. The phenotype of preimplantation lethality is inferred if IVF and ICSI cycles fail because all of an individual's embryos are arrested at early stages of development.

HP:0032480.name: Beta-aminoisobutyric aciduria
HP:0032480.definition: An increased amount of beta-aminoisobutyric acid in the urine. Beta-aminoisobutyric acid is a non-protein amino acid originating from the catabolism of thymine and valine.

HP:0032481.name: Abnormal pituitary glycoprotein hormone alpha subunit level
HP:0032481.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of circulating alpha polypeptide of glycoprotein hormones (NCBI Gene 1081).

HP:0032482.name: Decreased pituitary glycoprotein hormone alpha subunit level
HP:0032482.definition: An reduced concentration of circulating alpha polypeptide of glycoprotein hormones (NCBI Gene 1081).

HP:0032484.name: Elevated fecal sodium
HP:0032484.definition: An elevated concentration of sodium in feces.

HP:0032485.name: Abnormal fecal osmolality
HP:0032485.definition: Abnormal concentration of feces as assessed by the total number of solute particles per kilogram.

HP:0032486.name: Elevated fecal osmolality
HP:0032486.definition: Abnormally high concentration of feces as assessed by the total number of solute particles per kilogram.

HP:0032487.name: Reduced fecal osmolality
HP:0032487.definition: Abnormally low concentration of feces as assessed by the total number of solute particles per kilogram.

HP:0032488.name: Abnormal fecal pH
HP:0032488.definition: Any deviation from the normal pH of feces. The pH reflects the acidity or alkalinity of a solution on a logarithmic scale on which 7 is neutral, whereby lower values are more acid and higher values more alkaline.

HP:0032489.name: Elevated fecal pH
HP:0032489.definition: Abnormally high fecal pH, i.e., abnormal alkalinity of feces.

HP:0032490.name: Decreased fecal pH
HP:0032490.definition: Abnormally low fecal pH, i.e., abnormal acidity of feces.

HP:0032491.name: Increased circulating argininosuccinic acid
HP:0032491.definition: An increased level of the non-proteinogenic amino acid argininosuccinic acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0032492.name: Anti-myelin oligodendrocyte glycoprotein antibody positivity
HP:0032492.definition: Presence of antibodies in the serum that react against myelin oligodendrocyte glycoprotein.

HP:0032493.name: Increased circulating trypsinogen
HP:0032493.definition: An abnormally high concentration of trypsinogen in the blood circulation.

HP:0032495.name: Abnormal terminal:vellus ratio
HP:0032495.definition: A deviation from the normal proportion of terminal to vellus hairs.

HP:0032496.name: Elevated terminal:vellus ratio
HP:0032496.definition: An increased proportion of terminal hairs compared to vellus hairs.

HP:0032497.name: Reduced terminal:vellus ratio
HP:0032497.definition: A terminal:vellus ratio under 4:1 is characteristic of androgenetic alopecia.

HP:0032499.name: Giant neutrophil granules
HP:0032499.definition: The presence of abnormally large granules in neutrophils. This finding can be appreciated on a peripheral blood smear. The finding is characteristic of Chediak Higashi syndrome. The giant granules are derived from azurophil granules, whereas peroxidase-negative granules are not involved in their formation.

HP:0032500.name: Exacerbated by tobacco use
HP:0032500.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by smoking tobacco products.

HP:0032501.name: Exacerbated by contraceptive medication exposure
HP:0032501.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by taking contraceptive medication.

HP:0032502.name: Exacerbated by barbiturate exposure
HP:0032502.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by taking barbituates.

HP:0032503.name: Ameliorated by ethanol ingestion
HP:0032503.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by drinking alcohol (ethanol).

HP:0032504.name: Lhermitte's sign
HP:0032504.definition: An electric shock-like sensation that occurs on flexion of the neck. This sensation radiates down the spine, often into the legs, arms, and sometimes to the trunk.

HP:0032505.name: Hydrophobia
HP:0032505.definition: The word hydrophobia has been used to describe the avoidance of drinking in the presence of hydrophobic spasms that can be observed in human rabies (described as a blockage in the throat with worsening of dyspnea). However, rarely, the same word has been used to describe panic reactions observed in a patient when offered a glass of water. This term does not refer to the latter meaning.

HP:0032506.name: Alien limb phenomenon
HP:0032506.definition: Alien limb phenomenon refers to involuntary motor activity of a limb in conjunction with the feeling of estrangement from that limb.

HP:0032507.name: Labiomental fasciculations
HP:0032507.definition: Fasciculations affecting the tongue muscle and the musculature of the chin.

HP:0032508.name: Polyembolokoilamania
HP:0032508.definition: Habitual insertion of foreign bodies into bodily orifices.

HP:0032509.name: Onychotillomania
HP:0032509.definition: Onychotillomania is characterized by the compulsive or irresistible urge in patients to pick at, pull off, or harmfully bite or chew their nails.

HP:0032510.name: Tendon pain
HP:0032510.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to a tendon.

HP:0032511.name: Superiorly positioned umbilicus
HP:0032511.definition: The position of the umbilicus (belly button) is abnormally high (superior).

HP:0032513.name: Four-vessel umbilical cord
HP:0032513.definition: Four-vessel umbilical cord containing two arteries and two veins.

HP:0032514.name: Supernumerary lacrimal punctum
HP:0032514.definition: A congenital developmental anomaly characterized by the presence of an additional lacrimal punctum in an eyelid.

HP:0032515.name: Deep dermatophytosis
HP:0032515.definition: A type of invasive dermatophyte infection of the deep dermis characterized by extensive dermal infiltration by fungal elements.

HP:0032516.name: Invasive dermatophyte infection
HP:0032516.definition: Infection that extends deeply into the dermis by dermatophytes, fungi that typically cause different types of superficial infection (tinea) or skin, hair, or nails.

HP:0032517.name: Majocchi's granuloma
HP:0032517.definition: Majocchi's granuloma (MG) is an inflammatory and granulomatous, dermatophytic infection characterized by a granulomatous inflammation around the hair follicle. Histopathologically, MG demonstrates a nodular perifollicular granulomatous infiltrate of lymphoid cells, macrophages, epithelioid cells, multinucleated giant cells, and neutrophils. Unlike superficial dermatophytoses, fungal hyphae and spores can be detected not only on the surface of the epidermis but also within or around the hair follicles.

HP:0032518.name: Disseminated dermatophytosis
HP:0032518.definition: A type of invasive dermatophyte infection characterized by vascular involvement and dissemination to other organs.

HP:0032519.name: Increased Burr cell count
HP:0032519.definition: Burr cells, also known as echinocytes, have a speculated border over the entire cell surface. Burr cells are commonly found in both end-stage renal disease and liver disease. Small numbers of Burr cells are commonly found in healthy individuals.

HP:0032520.name: Masseter muscular weakness
HP:0032520.definition: Reduced strength of the masseter muscle, whose primary function is to elevate the mandible and thereby raise the mandible towards the maxilla, closing the jaw.

HP:0032521.name: Self hugging
HP:0032521.definition: Involuntary, tic-like movements consisted of crossing both arms across the chest and tensing the body or clasping the hands and squeezing the arms to the sides. The movements last a few seconds and may occur in series or flurries, generally accompanied by facial grimacing and occasional grunting.

HP:0032522.name: Ameliorated by immunosuppresion
HP:0032522.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with immunosuppresive medication.

HP:0032523.name: Tendon thickening
HP:0032523.definition: An abnormal increase in the thickness (diameter) of a tendon.

HP:0032524.name: Long thumb
HP:0032524.definition: Length of the thumb is greater than normal.

HP:0032525.name: Exacerbated by acetylcholinesterase inhibitor exposure
HP:0032525.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor such as tensilon (edrophonium) or pyridostigmine (Mestinon).

HP:0032526.name: Ameliorated by acetylcholinesterase inhibitor
HP:0032526.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor such as mestinon or tensilon.

HP:0032527.name: Inferiorly positioned umbilicus
HP:0032527.definition: The position of the umbilicus (belly button) is abnormally low (inferior).

HP:0032528.name: Elevated urinary 4-hydroxybutyric acid
HP:0032528.definition: An increased amount of 4-hydroxybutyric acid in the urine.

HP:0032529.name: obsolete Elevated circulating gamma-aminobutyric acid concentration

HP:0032530.name: Decreased tissue succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase activity
HP:0032530.definition: Reduced level of succinic semialdehyde dehydrogenase (SSADH).
