HP:0032532.name: Elevated CSF 4-hydroxybutyric acid concentration
HP:0032532.definition: Abnormally increased level of 4-hydroxybutyric acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0032533.name: Elevated circulating acetone concentration
HP:0032533.definition: An increased level of acetone in the blood circulation. Acetone is one of the predominant ketone bodies.

HP:0032534.name: Exacerbated by methylxanthine ingestion
HP:0032534.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by ingestion of food containing a methylxanthine compound (for instance, coffee, caffeine, chocolate).

HP:0032535.name: Cervical (neck)
HP:0032535.definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in the neck.

HP:0032536.name: Increased number of lymph nodes
HP:0032536.definition: An abnormally elevated number of lymph nodes in an anatomical region.

HP:0032537.name: Delayed fracture healing
HP:0032537.definition: A delay in healing of a fracture past the expected duration.

HP:0032538.name: Pretibial dimple
HP:0032538.definition: A groove or crease on the shins (pretibial, i.e., over the shin bone). Pretibial creases may be obvious at birth and may range from 3 cm to over 15 cm in length and lengthen as the limb grows. They appear as an elongated dimple because of the attachment of skin to underlying tissue (e.g., to the tibia). The dimple or crease grows in proportion to the growth of the leg.

HP:0032539.name: Joint extensor surface localization
HP:0032539.definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in extensor surface of the joint. The extensor surface refers to the skin on the opposite side of a joint.

HP:0032540.name: Joint flexor surface localization
HP:0032540.definition: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in flexor surface of the joint. The flexor surface refers to the skin that touches when a joint is bent (flexed).

HP:0032541.name: Knuckle pad
HP:0032541.definition: Knuckle pads are benign fibrofatty subcutaneous pads located over the proximal interphalangeal (PIP) joints that can be mistaken for arthritis. Rarely they affect the dorsal aspect of the metacarpophalangeal (MCP) joints. Clinically they are painless and often affect both hands in an asymmetrical pattern.

HP:0032542.name: Exacerbated by pregnancy
HP:0032542.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by being pregnant.

HP:0032543.name: Lithoptysis
HP:0032543.definition: Expectoration (coughing up) of a broncholith. Broncholithiasis is defined as the presence of calculi in the tracheobronchial tree. It is a rare disease but can be characterized by clinical and radiological findings of a calcified lymph node eroding bronchial wall and opening into the bronchial lumen.

HP:0032544.name: Predominant small joint localization
HP:0032544.definition: Applies to an abnormality that mainly affects the small joints, including fingers, toes, interphalangeal, metacarpophalangeal, metatarsophalangeal, wrists, ankles, vertebrae, and neck.

HP:0032545.name: Abdominal rigidity
HP:0032545.definition: Involuntary tightening of the abdominal musculature that occurs in response to touching the abdomen to avoid pain. Rigidity can occur in the presence of abdominal inflammation and usually involves only the inflamed area.

HP:0032546.name: Abdominal guarding
HP:0032546.definition: A voluntary contraction of the abdominal wall musculature to avoid pain.

HP:0032547.name: Low intraocular pressure
HP:0032547.definition: An abnormal decrease of the pressure within the eye.

HP:0032549.name: Persistent asymmetrical tonic neck reflex
HP:0032549.definition: Persistence beyond the normal age (roughly the first half of the first year of life) of the asymmetric tonic neck reflex (ATNR), which is an easily elicited primitive reflex in the immediate newborn period. The ATNR refers to the phenomenon whereby when the face of an infant is turned to one side, the ipsilateral arm and leg extend and the contralateral arm and leg flex. This posture has been compared to a typical posture of fencers.

HP:0032550.name: Howell-Jolly bodies
HP:0032550.definition: Howell-Jolly bodies are small, intra-erythrocytic remnants of erythrocyte nuclei. These inclusions are solitary in each erythrocyte and strongly basophilic. These are often confused with overlying platelets, but can be distinguished by the presence of a halo around overlying platelets.

HP:0032551.name: Hemorrhoids
HP:0032551.definition: Enlarged, bulging blood vessels in and around the anus often associated with rectal bleeding, itching, and pain.

HP:0032552.name: Abnormal pulse
HP:0032552.definition: An anomaly of the rhythmic throbbing of an artery that reflects the widening of the artery as blood flows through it and is caused by successive contractions of the heart.

HP:0032553.name: Weak pulse
HP:0032553.definition: A diminution in the amplitude (strength) of the pulse such that the examiner has difficulty feeling the pulse.

HP:0032554.name: Absent pulse
HP:0032554.definition: The pulsation of an artery where the pulse is taken (e.g. the radial artery at the wrist) cannot be detected on physical examination.

HP:0032556.name: Circumoral cyanosis
HP:0032556.definition: Persistent blue color of the skin that surrounds the mouth.

HP:0032557.name: History of bone marrow transplant
HP:0032557.definition: A past medical history of hematopoietic stem cell transplantation involving myeloablative chemoradiotherapy followed by stem cell rescue with autologous or human leukocyte antigen (HLA)-matched stem cells derived from a donor.

HP:0032559.name: Short sperm flagella
HP:0032559.definition: Sperm cells with abnormally short flagella.

HP:0032560.name: Coiled sperm flagella
HP:0032560.definition: Sperm cells whose flagella are twisted (coiled).

HP:0032561.name: Microcephalic sperm head
HP:0032561.definition: Decreased size of the head of sperm.

HP:0032562.name: Tapered sperm head
HP:0032562.definition: Sperm with cigar-shaped heads that gradually dimish in diameter (taper).

HP:0032563.name: Dacryocytosis
HP:0032563.definition: Presence of teardrop-shaped red blood cells.

HP:0032567.name: Lipiduria
HP:0032567.definition: An increased lipid content in the urine.

HP:0032568.name: Urinary mulberry cells
HP:0032568.definition: Distal tubular epithelial cells in which globotriaosylceramide (Gb3) has accumulated. they are the characteristic feature of Fabry disease. Urinary mulberry bodies are a component of mulberry cells that can be distinguished easily from fat particles by their inner lamellar appearance.

HP:0032569.name: Temporal bossing
HP:0032569.definition: Prominence (bulging) in the temple region, which is the part of the skull where the frontal, parietal, temporal, and sphenoid bones join on the side of the head.

HP:0032570.name: Pontine ischemic lacunes
HP:0032570.definition: Lacunes are infarcts less than 15 mm in diameter in the cortical white matter or in the corona radiata, internal capsule, centrum semiovale, thalamus, basal ganglia, or pons.

HP:0032571.name: Increased oocyte death
HP:0032571.definition: An increase in death of oocytes, the female germ cell (egg cell), which can be observed clinically in the setting of in vitro fertilization.

HP:0032572.name: Abnormal urinary nucleobase concentration
HP:0032572.definition: A deviation from the normal level of a nucleobase in the urine. Nucleobases are nitrogen-containing biological compounds that form nucleosides: adenine (A), cytosine (C), guanine (G), thymine (T), and uracil (U).

HP:0032573.name: Elevated urinary cytidine
HP:0032573.definition: Increased levels of urinary cytidine, a pyrimidine nucleoside in which cytosine is attached to ribofuranose via a beta-N1 glycosidic bond.

HP:0032574.name: Elevated urinary uridine level
HP:0032574.definition: Increased levels of urinary uridine, a ribonucleoside composed of a molecule of uracil attached to a ribofuranose moiety via a beta-N1 glycosidic bond.

HP:0032575.name: Decreased circulating 12-HETE
HP:0032575.definition: A reduction in the concentration of 12-HETE in the blood circulation, a metabolite of arachidonic acid.

HP:0032576.name: Intracellular accumulation of Dol-PP-GlcNAc2Man5
HP:0032576.definition: Intracellular accumulation of the lipid-linked oligosaccharide intermediate Man5GlcNAc2-PP-dolichol.

HP:0032577.name: Clonal T cell receptor rearrangement
HP:0032577.definition: Presence of a predominant T cell clone. In PCR-based assays, this finding is inferred on the basis of one or two prominent bands within a valid size range. In NGS-based assays, this finding is inferred on the basis of a high number of reads that map to a single T cell receptor clone.

HP:0032578.name: Third ventricle colloid cyst
HP:0032578.definition: An epithelial lined cyst filled with gelatinous material. The gelatinous material commonly contains mucin, old blood, cholesterol, and ions. Most colloid cysts identified are currently asymptomatic and identified incidentally on imaging. When a colloid cyst does cause issues, it most commonly causes obstructive hydrocephalus.

HP:0032579.name: Vascular hamartoma
HP:0032579.definition: A benign focal growth composed of vascular tissue.

HP:0032580.name: Abnormal bulbus cordis morphology
HP:0032580.definition: Abnormal structure of the bulbus cordis, which is the single outflow tract of the heart during early embryogenesis.

HP:0032581.name: Abnormal renal insterstitial morphology
HP:0032581.definition: Any structural anomaly of the interstitium of the kidney. The renal interstitium is defined as the intertubular, extraglomerular, extravascular space of the kidney. It is bounded on all sides by tubular and vascular basement membranes and is filled with cells, extracellular matrix, and interstitial fluid.

HP:0032582.name: Renal interstitial foam cells
HP:0032582.definition: Accumulation of foam cells (FC) in the interstitium of the kidney. Renal FCs display phenotypic characteristics of macrophages and belong to the monocyte/macrophage lineage. Histologically, renal FCs are characterized by round cells with small nuclei and an abundant PAS-positive cytoplasm with lipid-containing vacuoles.

HP:0032584.name: Renal interstitial neutrophil infiltration
HP:0032584.definition: Increased numbers of neutrophils in the interstitial tissues of the kidney.

HP:0032585.name: Renal interstitial eosinophil infiltration
HP:0032585.definition: Increased numbers of eosinophils in the interstitial tissues of the kidney.

HP:0032586.name: Renal interstitial plasma cell infiltration
HP:0032586.definition: Increased numbers of plasma cells in the interstitial tissues of the kidney.

HP:0032587.name: Renal interstitial calcium oxalate
HP:0032587.definition: The presence of birefringent calcium- and oxalate deposits in interstitial cells of the kidney.

HP:0032588.name: Hand apraxia
HP:0032588.definition: Inability to perform purposeful (learned) movements with the hand upon command, even though the command is understood and there is a willingness to perform the movement. Hand apraxia includes the inability to grasp, pick up, and hold large and small objects.

HP:0032589.name: Renal lymphocytic tubulitis
HP:0032589.definition: Infiltration of the renal tubular epithelium by lymphocytes.

HP:0032590.name: Renal neutrophilic tubulitis
HP:0032590.definition: Infiltration of the renal tubular epithelium by neutrophils.

HP:0032591.name: Renal interstitial hemosiderin
HP:0032591.definition: Deposition of hemosiderin (a golden-brown, granular pigment derived from ferritin) in interstitial cells of the kidney.

HP:0032592.name: Aplasia of the right hemidiaphragm
HP:0032592.definition: Congenital absence of the right-sided diaphragm.

HP:0032593.name: Myoglobin casts
HP:0032593.definition: A type of acelluar casts with positive myoglobin staining A that have a surface composed of granules, which can vary in size. The granules can be rather heterogeneous, ranging from fine (finely granular cast) up to coarse (coarsely granular cast), dark, clear, and pigmented.

HP:0032594.name: Renal tubular basement membrane denudation
HP:0032594.definition: Naked basement membranes without tubular epithelium.

HP:0032595.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell detachment
HP:0032595.definition: Tubular cross section with a space between the basolateral aspect of tubular epithelium and its basement membrane; classified as global when at least 2/3 circumference of the tubular cross section are involved and segmental when less than 2/3 are involved.

HP:0032596.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell cytoplasmic vacuolization
HP:0032596.definition: Tubular cross section with intracytoplasmic vacuoles in at least one tubular epithelial cell. This feature is classified as isometric when vacuoles are round and similar in size and coarse when vacuoles were not round in shape or varied in size.

HP:0032597.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell sloughing
HP:0032597.definition: At least one free floating cell in the tubular lumen without attachment to adjacent cells or basement membrane in a tubular cross section without detachment. These cells must not aggregate into a tubular shape and completely fill the lumen, if so, it should be classified as a cast.

HP:0032598.name: Blebbing of apical cytoplasm of renal tubular epithelial cells
HP:0032598.definition: Tubular cross section with round/irregular cytoplasmic protrusion, shaped like the Greek capital letter Omega (or it may be more vertically elongated Omega), pinched off from apical membrane without apparent closure of the lumen, involving over 50 percent of the tubular cells in cross section. The feature can be further classified into proximal or distal tubule.

HP:0032599.name: Abnormal renal tubular epithelial morphology
HP:0032599.definition: Any structural anomaly of the renal tubular epithelial cells (RTEC), a layer of cells in the outer layer of the renal tubule. These cells play a role in the absorption of substances such as glucose and amino from the primary urine.

HP:0032600.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell hyaline droplets
HP:0032600.definition: Tubular epithelium with round strongly PAS-positive cytoplasmic droplet material in at least one tubular epithelial cell.

HP:0032601.name: Multinucleation of renal tubular epithelial cells
HP:0032601.definition: Tubular epithelial cells with greater than 3 nuclei in a single epithelial cell, often overlapping with each other in a single plane of view.

HP:0032602.name: Prominent nucleoli of renal tubular epithelial cells
HP:0032602.definition: Tubular epithelium with nucleoli clearly visible at 100-fold magnification.

HP:0032603.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell simplification
HP:0032603.definition: Tubular cross section with flattened tubular cell cytoplasm (height unequivocally less than width), with complete loss of brush border involving greater than 50 percent of the tubular cells in cross section, resulting in an apparent increase in the size of the lumen, without the presence of casts.

HP:0032604.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell mitosis
HP:0032604.definition: Tubular epithelial cells in any mitotic phase, identified by distinctively visible chromosome in either prophase, metaphase, anaphase or telophase configuration.

HP:0032605.name: High renal tubular epithelial cell N/C ratio
HP:0032605.definition: At least one tubular epithelial cell with average sized cytoplasmic area and a nuclear area 3 times greater than average sized nuclei.

HP:0032606.name: Renal tubular epithelial lipofuscin
HP:0032606.definition: Presence of increased amount of lipofuscin, a yellow, granular cytoplasmic pigment in the renal tubules.

HP:0032607.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell swelling
HP:0032607.definition: Tubular cross section lined entirely by tubular epithelium with convex apical cell membrane (i.e., cells are shaped like an upside down U, and lack a distinct smaller protrusion seen in blebbing as defined above) resulting in apparent complete closure of the lumen.

HP:0032608.name: Thyroidization-type tubular atrophy
HP:0032608.definition: A type of renal tubular atrophy characterized by a thyroid-like appearance, with small round tubules with markedly flattened, simplified epithelium and uniform intratubular casts.

HP:0032609.name: Endocrine-type tubular atrophy
HP:0032609.definition: A type of renal tubular atrophy characterized by endocrine-like appearance of tubules, which are small and have narrow lumina, clear cells, and relatively thin basement membranes.

HP:0032610.name: Tubulointerstitial mycobacterial infiltration
HP:0032610.definition: Renal tubulointerstitial infiltration of mycobacteria identified on acid-fast or Fite stains. Can be associated with granulomatous inflammation.

HP:0032611.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell hemosiderin
HP:0032611.definition: Tubular epithelial cells containing cytoplasmic hemosiderin, brown-golden granular pigment.

HP:0032612.name: Triphalangeal hallux
HP:0032612.definition: A hallux (big toe) with three phalanges in a single, proximo-distal axis.

HP:0032613.name: Renal interstitial amyloid deposits
HP:0032613.definition: Deposition of amyloid in the interstitial tissue of the kidney. Amyloid is is made up of 10 nm (on average) fibrils that are most commonly composed of monoclonal light chains (AL), transthyretin (TTR), amd LECT2, or occur in the setting of long standing systemic inflammation.

HP:0032614.name: Renal glomerular amyloid deposition
HP:0032614.definition: Amyloid deposits located in the glomeruli in a focal segmental, diffuse segmental or diffuse global fashion. This abnormality can be accompanied by mesangial involvement and in later stages also involvement of the peripheral capillaries.

HP:0032615.name: Abnormal diffusion weighted cerebral MRI morphology
HP:0032615.definition: A diffusion abnormality observed in diffusion-weighted magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the brain. Molecular diffusion refers to the notion that any type of molecule in a fluid (eg, water) is randomly displaced as the molecule is agitated by thermal energy. Restricted diffusion of water appears bright on diffusion-weighted images.

HP:0032616.name: Renal interstitial immunoglobulin deposits
HP:0032616.definition: Accumulation of an immunoglobulin in the interstitial tissue of the kidney. The immunoglobulin may be a monoclonal Ig or the corresponding heavy-chain (HC) or light-chain (LC) subunit. By convention this definition excludes Ig-derived amyloidosis (amyloidosis can be distinguished by its affinity for Congo red staining).

HP:0032617.name: Renal interstitial hemorrhage
HP:0032617.definition: A focal collection of 20 or more red blood cells within the interstitium, that is irregular in shape (i.e., collections do not conform to the shape of tubules or capillary networks), without surrounding endothelium or tubular epithelium, and is in an area of intact core.

HP:0032618.name: Renal necrosis
HP:0032618.definition: Cell death (necrosis) affecting one or more parts of the kidney.

HP:0032619.name: Perinephric abscess
HP:0032619.definition: A perinephric abscess is a collection of suppurative material in the perinephric space (i.e., the connective and adipose tissues surrounding the kidney).

HP:0032620.name: Intrarenal abscess
HP:0032620.definition: An encapsulated collection of pus and necrotic material within the renal parenchyma. The destruction of renal parenchyma is associated with suppurative/neutrophil-rich inflammation and necrosis.

HP:0032621.name: Hyperchromasia of renal tubular epithelial cells
HP:0032621.definition: At least one tubular cross section with all tubular epithelial nuclei having a chromatin pattern resembling normal mature lymphocytes.

HP:0032622.name: Tubular luminal dilatation
HP:0032622.definition: Dilatation (expansion beyond the normal dimension) of the cavity (lumen) of tubules of the kidney. The tubular cross section displays an attenuated brush border (apical PAS positivity greater than 10 percent of the normal expected height, but unequivocally less than normal expected height), resulting in an apparent increase in the size of lumen.

HP:0032623.name: Renal intratubular casts
HP:0032623.definition: Urinary casts are formed in the distal convoluted tubule or the collecting duct by solidification of protein in the lumen of the kidney tubules. This term refers to casts located within the tubuli of the kidney. More precisely, casts are defined as a material that completely fills and expands the tubular lumen with simplification of surrounding tubular epithelium. Casts are classified as either nuclear debris/granular brown material, red blood cell, white blood cell, myeloma, or myoglobin cast.

HP:0032624.name: Intratubular bilirubin casts
HP:0032624.definition: A type of acelluar intratubular casts that have a surface composed of granules, which can vary in size. On H&E (red brown), PAS (amaranth purple), trichrome (red with ragged contours), Hall (olive-emerald green).

HP:0032625.name: Intratubular erythrocyte cast
HP:0032625.definition: Casts that contain red blood cells and are located within the tubuli of the kidney.

HP:0032626.name: Intratubular vancomycin casts
HP:0032626.definition: Intratubular casts composed of vancomycin aggregates and uromodulin.

HP:0032627.name: Intratubular leukocyte casts
HP:0032627.definition: Casts that contain white blood cells and are located within the tubuli of the kidney.

HP:0032629.name: Intratubular dihydroxyadenuria crystals
HP:0032629.definition: Intratubular crystals composed of 2,8-dihydroxyadenine are small needle-shaped brownish crystals that are highly birefringent under polarized light and black by Jones methenamine silver.

HP:0032630.name: Intratubular light-chain casts
HP:0032630.definition: The presence of casts containing immunoglobulin light chains within the lumina of the renal tubules.

HP:0032631.name: Intratubular hemoglobin casts
HP:0032631.definition: A type of acelluar intratubular casts that have a surface composed of granules, which can vary in size. The granules can be rather heterogeneous, ranging from fine (finely granular cast) up to coarse (coarsely granular cast), dark, clear, and pigmented. On H&E (red granular), PAS (purple), trichrome (red granular), Hall (yellow brown). Stain positively for Hemoglobin A.

HP:0032632.name: Renal papillary necrosis
HP:0032632.definition: Premature death of cells in the renal papilla (the apex of a renal pyramid which projects into the cavity of a calyx of the kidney and through which collecting ducts discharge urine). Histologically, one observes pale tissue with typical appearance of coagulative necrosis, affecting the renal papillae. Necrosis can be identified by pyknotic nuclei and simplified, flattened epithelium of proximal tubules. The tubular and glomerular basement membranes are still visible without viable nuclei.

HP:0032633.name: Intratubular hyaline casts
HP:0032633.definition: A type of acellular urinary cast located within the distal tubules of the kidney and that is composed only of Tamm-Horsfall glycoprotein. Correspondingly, these casts have a low refractive index. Hyaline casts may display a spectrum of morphologies, which includes fluffy, compact, convoluted or wrinkled casts. Hyaline casts have a smooth texture and usually have parallel sides with clear margins and blunted ends.

HP:0032634.name: Intratubular myoglobin cast
HP:0032634.definition: Casts located within the tubuli of the kidney and that contain myoglobin. Myoglobin casts are composed of round granules that may line up in chains or aggregate in clusters. Their color ranges from pink to red-brown with hematoxylin and eosin stain, light brown to black with Jones methenamine silver stain, pink to bright magenta with periodic acid-Schiff stain, and bright red with trichrome stain. Immunoperoxidase staining with antibody to myoglobin is stronglypositive in the casts.Electron microscopy shows globular casts with an electron-dense core and a somewhat less-intense periphery. Substructure is absent. This feature may be accompanied by acute tubular injury with variable flattening of tubular epithelial cells, loss of brush borders, and intratubular sloughed epithelial cells.

HP:0032635.name: Tubulointerstitial microganismal infiltration
HP:0032635.definition: Infiltration of microorganisms into renal tubulointerstitial tissues as observed by appropriate staining procedures, e.g., bacteria on a bacterial stain (Brown and Hopps) or fungi on PAS or silver stain.

HP:0032636.name: Tubulointerstitial viral infiltration
HP:0032636.definition: Infiltration of viruses into renal tubulointerstitial tissues as demonstrated on renal biopsy by viral inclusions which can be seen on routine stains or with immunohistochemistry.

HP:0032637.name: Renal interstitial edema
HP:0032637.definition: Edema is characterized but the acute swelling of the stroma, with expansion of the interstitial space without the a concurrent increase in interstitial cells or extracellular matrix. Histologically this change is appreciated as interstitial areas of lower optical density.

HP:0032638.name: Elevated urine mevalonic acid level
HP:0032638.definition: An abnormally increased amount of mevanolate in the urine. Mevanolate is that hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of mevalonic acid.

HP:0032639.name: Elevated leukocyte cystine
HP:0032639.definition: An increased concentration of cystine within white blood cells.

HP:0032640.name: Elevated circulating CCL18 level
HP:0032640.definition: An increased concentration of C-C motif chemokine ligand 18 in the blood circulation.

HP:0032641.name: Renal interstitial granulomas
HP:0032641.definition: Interstital aggregates of histiciocytes, occasionally multinucleated with associated lymphoplasmacytic and occasionally eosinophilic inflammation. Organization can range from poorly-to-well defined and multinucleated giant cells may be present.

HP:0032642.name: Renal interstitial necrotizing granulomas
HP:0032642.definition: An organized collection of histiocytes (specifically macrophages) localized in the interstitial tissue of the kidney. Through light microscopy, the activated histiocytes appear as epithelioid cells with round to oval nuclei, often with irregular contours and abundant granular eosinophilic cytoplasm with indistinct cell borders. They may also coalesce to form multinucleated giant cells. Granulomas may be associated with a peripheral cuff of lymphoplasmacytic and occasionally eosinophilic inflammation. Organization can range from poorly-to-well defined. Granulomas can present as necrotizing or non-necrotizing. Microscopically, necrotizing granulomas distinctly have central necrosis with a palisaded lymphohistiocytic reaction and a cuff of chronic inflammation.

HP:0032643.name: Renal interstitial non-necrotizing granulomas
HP:0032643.definition: Interstital aggregates of histiciocytes, occasionally multinucleated with associated lymphoplasmacytic and occasionally eosinophilic inflammation. Organization can range from poorly-to-well defined and multinucleated giant cells may be present with no necrosis.

HP:0032644.name: Renal interstitial deposits
HP:0032644.definition: Abnormal accumulation of a metabolite, protein, or protein-derived substance in the interstitial region of the kidney.

HP:0032645.name: Renal interstitial mononuclear cell infiltration
HP:0032645.definition: Presence of interstitial mononuclear leukocytes, i.e., white blood ceclls with a single round nucleus, including lymphocytes and monocytes but not including granulocytes (which have multilobed nuclei).

HP:0032646.name: Renal interstitial xanthogranulomatous inflammation
HP:0032646.definition: Inflammation of interstitial tissues of the kidney consisting of foamy macrophages admixed with plasma cells, lymphocytes and neutrophils and occasional giant cells.

HP:0032647.name: Renal tubular epithelial cell apoptosis
HP:0032647.definition: Increased apoptosis (programmed cell death) of tubular epithelial cells. The cells are rounded with increased eosinophilia and contain fragmented, densely basophilic nuclear debris.

HP:0032648.name: Tubularization of Bowman capsule
HP:0032648.definition: The presence of cuboidal to columnar epithelium (height greater than width) lining the Bowman capsule, in an absence of adjacent segmental sclerosis, crescents, or collapsing variant of focal segmental glomerulosclerosis; scored as present or absent in at least one glomerulus.

HP:0032649.name: Skewfoot
HP:0032649.definition: A type of flat-foot characterized by hindfoot abductovalgus, metatarsus adductus, and Achilles tendon shortening. The predominant radiographic findings include forefoot adduction with lateral subluxation of the navicular on the talus and heel valgus. Very abnormal shoe wear is noted on the medial side. Calluses occur under the metatarsal heads and the head of the plantar-flexed talus.

HP:0032650.name: Elevated CSF glial fibrillary acidic protein concentration
HP:0032650.definition: Increased concentration of glial fibrillary acidic protein in cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0032651.name: Elevated CSF chitinase-3-like protein 1 concentration
HP:0032651.definition: Increased concentration of chitinase-3-like protein 1 in cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0032652.name: Elevated CSF chitotriosidase 1 concentration
HP:0032652.definition: Increased concentration of chitotriosidase 1 in cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0032653.name: Elevated lactate:pyruvate ratio
HP:0032653.definition: An abnormal increase in the molar ratio of lactate to pyruvate in the blood circulation.

HP:0032654.name: Impaired flow-mediated arterial dilatation
HP:0032654.definition: Flow-mediated dilatation is a noninvasive tests of endothelial function that leverages ultrasound to measure arterial diameter and its response to an increase in shear stress, which normally causes endothelium-dependent dilatation. This term pertains to an abnormal reduction in the magnitude of dilatation. Flow-mediated dilatation is usually measured at the brachial artery.

HP:0032655.name: Decreased adipose tissue tocopherol level
HP:0032655.definition: A reduced concentration of tocopherol in fat tissue.

HP:0032656.name: Febrile status epilepticus
HP:0032656.definition: A seizure lasting 30 minutes without fully regaining consciousness, provoked by fever (temperature greater than 38.0 degrees Celcius) at the time of seizure-onset, without a prior history of afebrile seizure and with no evidence of an acute central nervous system infection or insult.

HP:0032657.name: Elevated circulating lyso-globotriaosylsphingosine concentration
HP:0032657.definition: An abnormal increase in the level of globotriaosylsphingosine (Lyso-Gb3) in the blood circulation.

HP:0032658.name: Status epilepticus with prominent motor symptoms
HP:0032658.definition: Status epilepticus with prominent motor signs during the prolonged seizure.

HP:0032659.name: Non-convulsive status epilepticus with coma
HP:0032659.definition: A type of status epilepticus without prominent motor symptoms and in the presence of coma.

HP:0032660.name: Convulsive status epilepticus
HP:0032660.definition: A type of status epilepticus characterized by a prolonged bilateral tonic-clonic seizure, or repeated bilateral tonic-clonic seizures without recovery between.

HP:0032661.name: Generalized convulsive status epilepticus
HP:0032661.definition: A type of bilateral convulsive seizure of generalized onset that is sufficiently prolonged (or repeated without recovery) to reach the threshold for status epilepticus.

HP:0032662.name: Focal-onset seizure evolving into bilateral convulsive status epilepticus
HP:0032662.definition: A type of bilateral convulsive seizure of focal onset (which could be with awareness or impaired awareness, either motor or non- motor) that is sufficiently prolonged (or repeated without recovery) to reach the threshold for status epilepticus.

HP:0032663.name: Focal motor status epilepticus
HP:0032663.definition: Status epilepticus with focal motor signs originating within networks limited to one hemisphere. Involves musculature in any form. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement.

HP:0032664.name: Adversive status epilepticus
HP:0032664.definition: A type of focal motor status epilepticus characterized by continuous neck or body rotation and conjugate gaze deviation in a direction contralateral to the responsible epileptic focus. This includes some forms of tonic status epilepticus.

HP:0032665.name: Repeated focal motor seizures
HP:0032665.definition: A type of focal motor status epilepticus characterized by repeated motor, typically clonic events repeatedly affecting the same segments of the body with spread of clonic movements through contiguous body parts unilaterally, and repeating over a sufficiently prolonged period to reach a diagnosis of status epilepticus.

HP:0032666.name: Hyperkinetic status epilepticus
HP:0032666.definition: Status epilepticus characterized by continuous hyperkinetic proximal limb or axial muscles producing irregular sequential ballistic movements such as pedaling pelvic thrusting, thrashing, or rocking movements.

HP:0032667.name: Myoclonic status epilepticus
HP:0032667.definition: A type of motor status epilepticus with repeating bilateral sudden brief (less than 100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography.

HP:0032668.name: Myoclonic status epilepticus without coma
HP:0032668.definition: A type of myoclonic status epilepticus in the absence of coma.

HP:0032669.name: Myoclonic status epilepticus with coma
HP:0032669.definition: A type of myoclonic status epilepticus in the presence of coma.

HP:0032670.name: Tonic status epilepticus
HP:0032670.definition: Tonic status epilepticus is a type of status epilepticus characterized by focal or bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, which may be electrographically generalized or focal.

HP:0032671.name: Non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma
HP:0032671.definition: A type of status epilepticus without prominent motor symptoms in the absence of coma.

HP:0032672.name: Autonomic status epilepticus
HP:0032672.definition: Autonomic status epilepticus is a type of non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma with prominent autonomic features regardless of whether it is electrographically generalized or focal.

HP:0032673.name: Focal non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma
HP:0032673.definition: Focal non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma is a type of status epilepticus without prominent motor signs, which is electrographically focal. It is a prolonged focal non-motor seizure.

HP:0032674.name: Cutaneous wound
HP:0032674.definition: A cutaneous wound is a defined as a disruption of normal anatomic structure and function of the skin that occurs owing to an injury of the skin. Wound healing is a dynamic, interactive process involving soluble mediators, blood cells, extracellularmatrix, and parenchymal cells. Wound healing has three phases: inflammation, tissue formation, and tissue remodeling, that overlap in time.

HP:0032675.name: Acute cutaneous wound
HP:0032675.definition: A cutaneous wound that is proceeding through an orderly and timely reparative process that results in sustained restoration of the anatomic and functional integrity of the skin.

HP:0032676.name: Chronic cutaneous wound
HP:0032676.definition: A cutaneous wound that has failed to proceed through the orderly and timely process to produce an atomic and functional integrity, or proceeded through the repair process without establishing a sustained anatomic and functional result.

HP:0032677.name: Generalized-onset motor seizure
HP:0032677.definition: A generalized motor seizure is a type of generalized-onset seizure with predominantly motor (involving musculature) signs. The motor event could consist of an increase (positive) or decrease (negative) in muscle contraction to produce a movement.

HP:0032678.name: Eyelid myoclonia seizure
HP:0032678.definition: An eyelid myoclonia seizure is a type of generalized myoclonic seizure which may or may not be associated with loss of awareness.

HP:0032679.name: Focal non-motor seizure
HP:0032679.definition: A type of focal-onset seizure characterized by non-motor signs or symptoms (or behavior arrest) as its initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032680.name: Focal cognitive seizure
HP:0032680.definition: A focal cognitive seizure involves an alteration in a cognitive function (which can be a deficit or a positive phenomenon such as forced thought), which occurs at seizure onset. To be classified as a focal cognitive seizure, the change in cognitive function should be specific and out of proportion to other relatively unimpaired aspects of cognition, because all cognition is impaired in a focal impaired awareness seizure.

HP:0032681.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure
HP:0032681.definition: A focal aware cognitive seizure during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

HP:0032682.name: Focal aware non-motor seizure
HP:0032682.definition: A focal non-motor seizure in which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

HP:0032683.name: obsolete Focal aware cognitive seizure with impaired attention

HP:0032684.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with auditory agnosia
HP:0032684.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with auditory agnosia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032685.name: Focal cognitive seizure with auditory agnosia
HP:0032685.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by auditory agnosia as the initial semiological manifestation. For example a person may hear a ringing sound, but may not connect this with the concept that the sound is from a telephone ringing.

HP:0032686.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with memory impairment
HP:0032686.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with memory impairment characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032687.name: Focal cognitive seizure with memory impairment
HP:0032687.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by transient memory impairment as the initial semiological manifestation whilst other cognitive functions and awareness are preserved at seizure onset. The memory impairment may be an inability to recall events occurring prior to the seizure (retrograde amnesia), or failure to encode new memories for events occurring during the seizure (anterograde amnesia).

HP:0032688.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with dissociation
HP:0032688.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with dissociation characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032689.name: Focal cognitive seizure with dissociation
HP:0032689.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by an experience of being disconnected from, though aware of, self or environment as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032690.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with dyscalculia/acalculia
HP:0032690.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with dyscalculia and or acalculia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032691.name: Focal cognitive seizure with dyscalculia/acalculia
HP:0032691.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by dyscalculia / acalculia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032692.name: Focal cognitive seizure with forced thinking
HP:0032692.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by forced thinking as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032693.name: Focal cognitive seizure with neglect
HP:0032693.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by neglect as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032694.name: Focal cognitive seizure with dyslexia/alexia
HP:0032694.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by dyslexia / alexia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032696.name: Focal cognitive seizure with receptive dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032696.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by receptive dysphasia / aphasia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032697.name: obsolete Focal cognitive seizure with deja vu/jamais vu
HP:0032697.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by memory phenomena such as feelings of familiarity (deja vu) and unfamiliarity (jamais vu) as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032698.name: Focal cognitive seizure with conduction dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032698.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by conduction dysphasia / aphasia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032699.name: Focal cognitive seizure with dysgraphia/agraphia
HP:0032699.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by dysgraphia / agraphia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032700.name: Focal cognitive seizure with left-right confusion
HP:0032700.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by left-right confusion as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032701.name: Focal cognitive seizure with anomia
HP:0032701.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by anomia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032702.name: Focal cognitive seizure with expressive dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032702.definition: A focal cognitive seizure characterized by expressive dysphasia / aphasia as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032704.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with illusion
HP:0032704.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with illusion characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032705.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with forced thinking
HP:0032705.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with forced thinking characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032706.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with left-right confusion
HP:0032706.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with left-right confusion characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032707.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with dyslexia/alexia
HP:0032707.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with dyslexia / alexia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032708.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with anomia
HP:0032708.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with anomia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032709.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with dysgraphia/agraphia
HP:0032709.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with dysgraphia / agraphia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032710.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with receptive dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032710.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with receptive dysphasia / aphasia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032711.name: Focal aware clonic seizure
HP:0032711.definition: A type of focal clonic seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

HP:0032712.name: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure
HP:0032712.definition: A type of focal motor seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032713.name: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure with version
HP:0032713.definition: A focal motor seizure with version characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032714.name: Focal impaired awareness bilateral motor seizure
HP:0032714.definition: A focal bilateral motor seizure characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032715.name: Focal bilateral motor seizure
HP:0032715.definition: A type of focal motor seizure (it commences in one hemisphere) involving bilateral muscle groups rapidly at seizure onset.

HP:0032716.name: Focal impaired awareness non-motor seizure
HP:0032716.definition: A focal non-motor seizure characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032717.name: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure with dystonia
HP:0032717.definition: A focal motor seizure with dystonia characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032718.name: Focal motor seizure with dystonia
HP:0032718.definition: A focal motor seizure in which the initial semiological manifestation is the sustained contraction of both agonist and antagonist muscles producing athetoid or twisting movements, which produces abnormal postures.

HP:0032719.name: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure with dysarthria/anarthria
HP:0032719.definition: A focal motor seizure with dysarthria / anarthria characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032720.name: Focal motor seizure with dysarthria/anarthria
HP:0032720.definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by difficulty with articulation of speech, due to impaired coordination of muscles involved in speech sound production as the initial semiological manifestation. Receptive and expressive language functions are intact, however speech is poorly articulated and is less intelligible.

HP:0032721.name: Focal motor seizure with paresis/paralysis
HP:0032721.definition: A focal motor seizure characterized by weakness or complete paralysis of a muscle or group of muscles as the initial semiological manifestation.

HP:0032722.name: Focal aware tonic seizure
HP:0032722.definition: A type of focal tonic seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

HP:0032723.name: Focal aware motor seizure with dystonia
HP:0032723.definition: A focal motor seizure with dystonia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032724.name: Focal impaired awareness tonic seizure
HP:0032724.definition: A focal tonic seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032725.name: Focal impaired awareness clonic seizure
HP:0032725.definition: A type of focal clonic seizure during which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point in the seizure.

HP:0032726.name: Focal impaired awareness hyperkinetic seizure
HP:0032726.definition: A focal hyperkinetic seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032727.name: Focal emotional seizure with agitation
HP:0032727.definition: Focal emotional seizure with agitation is characterized by the presence of psychomotor agitation as an expressed or observed emotion, at the outset of the seizure. Because of the unpleasant nature of these seizures, patients may also have anticipatory anxiety about having seizures.

HP:0032728.name: Focal impaired awareness atonic seizure
HP:0032728.definition: A focal atonic seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032729.name: Focal emotional seizure with pleasure
HP:0032729.definition: Focal emotional seizure with pleasure is characterized by the presence of a positive emotional experience with pleasure, bliss, joy, enhanced personal well-being, heightened self-awareness or ecstasy.

HP:0032730.name: Focal impaired awareness myoclonic seizure
HP:0032730.definition: A focal myoclonic seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032731.name: Focal aware hyperkinetic seizure
HP:0032731.definition: A type of focal hypermotor seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

HP:0032732.name: Focal aware motor seizure with paresis/paralysis
HP:0032732.definition: A focal motor seizure with paresis / paralysis characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032733.name: Focal aware motor seizure with dysarthria/anarthria
HP:0032733.definition: A focal motor seizure with dysarthria / anarthria characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032734.name: Focal aware emotional seizure
HP:0032734.definition: A focal emotional seizure during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

HP:0032735.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with anger
HP:0032735.definition: Focal emotional seizure with anger in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032736.name: Focal emotional seizure with anger
HP:0032736.definition: Focal emotional seizure with anger is characterized by the presence of anger, as an expressed or observed emotion, at the outset of the seizure. It may be accompanied by aggressive behavior.

HP:0032737.name: Focal emotional seizure with paranoia
HP:0032737.definition: Focal emotional seizure with paranoia is characterized by the presence of paranoia as an expressed or observed emotion at the outset of the seizure.

HP:0032738.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with fear/anxiety/panic
HP:0032738.definition: Focal emotional seizure with anxiety, fear or panic as an expressed or observed emotion at the outset of the seizure, in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032739.name: Focal emotional seizure with fear/anxiety/panic
HP:0032739.definition: Focal emotional seizure with anxiety is characterized by the presence of anxiety, fear or panic as an expressed or observed emotion, at the outset of the seizure. Because of the unpleasant nature of these seizures, patients may also have anticipatory anxiety about having seizures.

HP:0032740.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure
HP:0032740.definition: A focal aware autonomic seizure has an initial manifestation pertaining to autonomic nervous system function, which may be objective (for example, pupillary dilation) or subjective (for example, nausea). As a type of focal aware seizure, awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032741.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with paranoia
HP:0032741.definition: Focal emotional seizure with paranoia in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032742.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with pleasure
HP:0032742.definition: Focal emotional seizure with pleasure in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032743.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with crying
HP:0032743.definition: Focal emotional seizure with crying (dacrystic)in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032744.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with agitation
HP:0032744.definition: Focal emotional seizure with agitation in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032745.name: Focal aware emotional seizure with laughing
HP:0032745.definition: Focal emotional seizure with laughing in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032746.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure
HP:0032746.definition: A focal emotional seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032747.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with pleasure
HP:0032747.definition: Focal emotional seizure with pleasure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032748.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with anger
HP:0032748.definition: Focal emotional seizure with anger in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032749.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with paranoia
HP:0032749.definition: Focal emotional seizure with paranoia in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032750.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with laughing
HP:0032750.definition: Focal emotional seizure with laughing in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032751.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with crying
HP:0032751.definition: Focal emotional seizure with crying in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032752.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with fear/anxiety/panic
HP:0032752.definition: Focal emotional seizure with anxiety, fear or panic as an expressed or observed emotion at the outset of the seizure, in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032753.name: Focal impaired awareness emotional seizure with agitation
HP:0032753.definition: A focal emotional seizure with agitation in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032754.name: Focal aware sensory seizure
HP:0032754.definition: A focal sensory seizure during which awareness is retained throughout the seizure.

HP:0032755.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure
HP:0032755.definition: A focal autonomic seizure characterized by impaired awareness at some point within the seizure.

HP:0032756.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure
HP:0032756.definition: A focal cognitive seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032757.name: Focal aware hemiclonic seizure
HP:0032757.definition: A focal hemiclonic seizure in which awareness is retained throughout.

HP:0032758.name: Focal aware myoclonic seizure
HP:0032758.definition: A type of focal myoclonic seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

HP:0032759.name: Focal sensory seizure with vestibular features
HP:0032759.definition: A seizure characterized by symptoms of dizziness, spinning, vertigo or sense of rotation as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0032760.name: Focal sensory seizure with hot-cold sensations
HP:0032760.definition: A seizure characterized by sensations of feeling hot or cold as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0032761.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with pallor/flushing
HP:0032761.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with pallor / flushing characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032762.name: Focal autonomic seizure with pallor/flushing
HP:0032762.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by changes of the skin as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032763.name: Focal autonomic seizure with pupillary dilation/constriction
HP:0032763.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by pupillary dilatation or contraction as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032764.name: Focal autonomic seizure with erection
HP:0032764.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by penile erection as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032765.name: Focal autonomic seizure with urge to urinate/defecate
HP:0032765.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by an urge to unripe or defecate as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032766.name: Focal autonomic seizure with hypoventilation/hyperventilation/altered respiration
HP:0032766.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by changes in respiratory rate as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032767.name: Focal autonomic seizure with piloerection
HP:0032767.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by piloerection (bristling of hairs due to the involuntary contraction of small muscles at the base of hair follicles) as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032768.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with pupillary dilation/constriction
HP:0032768.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with pupillary dilation / constriction characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032769.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with hypoventilation/hyperventilation/altered respiration
HP:0032769.definition: An autonomic seizure with hypoventilation / hyperventilation / altered respiration characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032770.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with erection
HP:0032770.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with erection characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032771.name: Focal autonomic seizure with lacrimation
HP:0032771.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by lacrimation as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032772.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with piloerection
HP:0032772.definition: A Focal autonomic seizure with piloerection (bristling of hairs due to the involuntary contraction of small muscles at the base of hair follicles) characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032773.name: Focal autonomic seizure with palpitations/tachycardia/bradycardia/asystole
HP:0032773.definition: A type of focal autonomic seizure characterized by changes in heart rate as the initial semiological feature.

HP:0032774.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with urge to urinate/defecate
HP:0032774.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with urge to urinate / defecate characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032775.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with hypoventilation/hyperventilation/altered respiration
HP:0032775.definition: An autonomic seizure with hypoventilation / hyperventilation / altered respiration characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032776.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with lacrimation

HP:0032777.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with pallor/flushing
HP:0032777.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with pallor / flushing characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032778.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation/nausea/vomiting/other gastrointestinal phenomena
HP:0032778.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation / nausea / vomiting / other gastrointestinal phenomena characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032779.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with pupillary dilation/constriction
HP:0032779.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with pupillary dilation / constriction characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032780.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with erection
HP:0032780.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with erection characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032781.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with urge to urinate/defecate
HP:0032781.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with urge to urinate / defecate characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032782.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with lacrimation
HP:0032782.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with lacrimation characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032783.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with piloerection
HP:0032783.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with piloerection (bristling of hairs due to the involuntary contraction of small muscles at the base of hair follicles) characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032784.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with palpitations/tachycardia/bradycardia/asystole
HP:0032784.definition: An autonomic seizure with palpitations / tachycardia / bradycardia / asystole characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032785.name: Focal aware autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation/nausea/vomiting/other gastrointestinal phenomena
HP:0032785.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with epigastric sensation / nausea / vomiting / other gastrointestinal phenomena characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032786.name: Migrating focal seizure
HP:0032786.definition: A migrating focal seizure is a seizure that involves different body parts, usually without overlap, in a consecutive manner so that the offset of a seizure in one part coincides with its onset in another, even shifting multiple times between the sides of the body. They can be associated with autonomic manifestations.

HP:0032787.name: Focal impaired awareness sensory seizure
HP:0032787.definition: A focal sensory seizure in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032788.name: Focal impaired awareness autonomic seizure with palpitations/tachycardia/bradycardia/asystole
HP:0032788.definition: A focal autonomic seizure with palpitations / tachycardia / bradycardia / asystole characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032789.name: Focal aware behavior arrest seizure
HP:0032789.definition: A focal behavior arrest seizure characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032790.name: Focal impaired awareness behavior arrest seizure
HP:0032790.definition: A focal behavior arrest seizure characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032791.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with anomia
HP:0032791.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with anomia characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032792.name: Tonic seizure
HP:0032792.definition: A tonic seizure is a type of motor seizure characterized by unilateral or bilateral limb stiffening or elevation, often with neck stiffening.

HP:0032793.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with receptive dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032793.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with receptive dysphasia / aphasia characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032794.name: Myoclonic seizure
HP:0032794.definition: A myoclonic seizure is a type of motor seizure characterized by sudden, brief (<100 ms) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal). Myoclonus is less regularly repetitive and less sustained than is clonus.

HP:0032795.name: Generalized myoclonic-tonic-clonic seizure
HP:0032795.definition: A generalized myoclonic-tonic-clonic seizure is a type of generalized motor seizure characterized by a single or multiple jerks of limbs bilaterally, followed by tonic and clonic phases. The initial jerks can be considered to be either a brief period of clonus or myoclonus.

HP:0032796.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with left-right confusion
HP:0032796.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with left-right confusion characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032797.name: Focal aware sensory seizure with olfactory features
HP:0032797.definition: Seizures characterized by olfactory phenomena at onset - usually an odor, which is often unpleasant.

HP:0032798.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with neglect
HP:0032798.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with neglect characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032799.name: Focal impaired awareness hemiclonic seizure
HP:0032799.definition: A focal hemiclonic seizure in which awareness is impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032800.name: Focal aware sensory seizure with vestibular features
HP:0032800.definition: A seizure characterized by symptoms of dizziness, spinning, vertigo or sense of rotation.

HP:0032801.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with memory impairment
HP:0032801.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with memory impairment characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032802.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with dyscalculia/acalculia
HP:0032802.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with dyscalculia / acalculia characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032803.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with dysgraphia/agraphia
HP:0032803.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with dysgraphia / agraphia characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032804.name: Focal impaired awareness sensory seizure with olfactory features
HP:0032804.definition: A focal sensory seizure with olfaction in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032805.name: Focal impaired awareness sensory seizure with vestibular features
HP:0032805.definition: A focal sensory seizure with vestibular features in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032806.name: Focal impaired awareness sensory seizure with visual features
HP:0032806.definition: A focal sensory seizure with visual features in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032807.name: Neonatal seizure
HP:0032807.definition: A seizure occurring within the neonatal period (28 days beyond the full term date).

HP:0032808.name: Neonatal seizure with electrographic correlate
HP:0032808.definition: Neonatal seizure is a seizure type that occurs in neonatal period and is characterized by an electrographic event with sudden, repetitive, evolving stereotyped waveforms with a beginning and an end. This event can be associated or not with a clinical manifestation.

HP:0032809.name: Neonatal electro-clinical seizure
HP:0032809.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical seizure is an electrographic event occurring in neonatal period and coupled with a clinical manifestation.

HP:0032810.name: Focal sensory seizure with cephalic sensation
HP:0032810.definition: A seizure characterized by a sensation in the head such as light-headedness or headache as its first clinical manifestation.

HP:0032811.name: Neonatal electrographic only seizure
HP:0032811.definition: Neonatal electrographic only seizure is an electrographic event with sudden, repetitive, evolving stereotyped waveforms with a beginning and an end, which is not associated with a clinical manifestation.

HP:0032813.name: Neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure
HP:0032813.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure with predominant motor features.

HP:0032814.name: Neonatal electro-clinical clonic seizure
HP:0032814.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical clonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is a regularly repeating jerking involving the same muscle groups; it can be symmetric or asymmetric.

HP:0032815.name: Neonatal electro-clinical myoclonic seizure
HP:0032815.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical myoclonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is sudden, brief (<100 msec) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal).

HP:0032816.name: Neonatal multifocal myoclonic seizure
HP:0032816.definition: Neonatal multifocal myoclonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is sudden, brief (<100 msec) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal) that occurs at multiple sites.

HP:0032817.name: Neonatal focal myoclonic seizure
HP:0032817.definition: Neonatal focal myoclonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is sudden, brief (<100 msec) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal) which occurs focally.

HP:0032818.name: Neonatal focal clonic seizure
HP:0032818.definition: Neonatal focal clonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical clonic seizure where the predominant motor feature is unilateral regularly repeating jerking involving the same muscle groups.

HP:0032819.name: Neonatal bilateral clonic seizure
HP:0032819.definition: Neonatal bilateral clonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical clonic seizure where the clonic jerking is bilateral.

HP:0032820.name: Neonatal multifocal clonic seizure
HP:0032820.definition: Neonatal focal clonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical clonic seizure where the predominant motor feature is a regularly repeating jerking involving the same muscle groups, which occurs at multiple sites.

HP:0032821.name: Neonatal electro-clinical tonic seizure
HP:0032821.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical tonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is a sustained increase in muscle tone, usually focal, that can be unilateral or bilateral, and lasting a few seconds to minutes.

HP:0032822.name: Neonatal electro-clinical autonomic seizure
HP:0032822.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical non-motor autonomic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure with predominant features of autonomic alterations, involving cardiovascular, pupillary, gastrointestinal, sudomotor, vasomotor, and thermoregulatory functions. May present as apnea.

HP:0032823.name: Neonatal electro-clinical seizure with behavior arrest
HP:0032823.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical non-motor seizure with behavior arrest is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure characterized by an arrest of activities, freezing, immobilization, with or without apnea and/or other autonomic manifestations.

HP:0032824.name: Neonatal focal tonic seizure
HP:0032824.definition: Neonatal focal tonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical tonic seizure with a focal sustained increase in muscle tone, lasting a few seconds to minutes.

HP:0032825.name: Neonatal electro-clinical sequential seizure
HP:0032825.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical sequential motor seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the predominant feature cannot be detected because of seizures presenting with a variety of clinical and electrographic signs, often changing lateralization within or between seizures.

HP:0032826.name: Focal neonatal sequential seizure
HP:0032826.definition: Focal neonatal electro-clinical sequential motor seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the predominant feature cannot be detected because of seizures presenting with a variety of clinical and electrographic focal signs, often changing lateralization within or between seizures.

HP:0032827.name: Multifocal neonatal sequential seizure
HP:0032827.definition: Multifocal neonatal electro-clinical sequential motor seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the predominant feature cannot be detected because of seizures presenting with a variety of clinical and electrographic multifocal signs.

HP:0032828.name: Neonatal bilateral symmetric tonic seizure
HP:0032828.definition: Neonatal bilateral symmetric tonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical tonic seizure where the sustained increase in muscle tone, lasting a few seconds to minutes, occurs at both sides of the body symmetrically.

HP:0032829.name: Neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure with automatism
HP:0032829.definition: Neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure with automatism is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the electrographic event is correlated with a coordinated motor activity, typically oral, usually with impaired awareness, and in association with other features.

HP:0032830.name: Neonatal seizure with bilateral asymmetric automatism
HP:0032830.definition: Neonatal seizure with bilateral asymmetric automatism is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the electrographic event is correlated with coordinated motor activity, typically oral, usually with impaired awareness, occurring at both sides of the body asymmetrically.

HP:0032831.name: Neonatal bilateral asymmetric tonic seizure
HP:0032831.definition: Neonatal bilateral asymmetric tonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical tonic seizure where the sustained increase in muscle tone, lasting a few seconds to minutes, occurs at both sides of the body but asymmetrically.

HP:0032832.name: Neonatal bilateral asymmetric myoclonic seizure
HP:0032832.definition: Neonatal bilateral asymmetric myoclonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is sudden, brief (<100 msec) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal) that occurs at both sides of the body asymmetrically.

HP:0032833.name: Neonatal epileptic spasm
HP:0032833.definition: A sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that is usually more sustained than a myoclonic movement but not as sustained as a tonic seizure. Limited forms may occur: grimacing, head nodding, or subtle eye movements. May occur in clusters.

HP:0032834.name: Neonatal seizure with unilateral automatism
HP:0032834.definition: Neonatal seizure with bilateral asymmetric automatisms is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the electrographic event is correlated with a coordinated motor activity, typically oral, usually with impaired awareness, occurring at one side of the body.

HP:0032835.name: Neonatal seizure with bilateral symmetric automatism
HP:0032835.definition: Neonatal seizure with bilateral asymmetric automatism is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the electrographic event is correlated with a coordinated motor activity, typically oral, usually with impaired awareness, occurring at both sides of the body symmetrically.

HP:0032836.name: Neonatal bilateral symmetric myoclonic seizure
HP:0032836.definition: Neonatal bilateral symmetric myoclonic seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical motor seizure where the predominant motor feature is sudden, brief (<100 msec) involuntary single or multiple contraction of muscles or muscle groups of variable topography (axial, proximal limb, distal) that occurs at both sides of the body symmetrically.

HP:0032837.name: Bilateral asymmetric neonatal sequential seizure
HP:0032837.definition: Asymmetric neonatal electro-clinical sequential motor seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the predominant feature cannot be detected because of seizures presenting asymmetrically with a variety of clinical and electrographic signs, often changing lateralization within or between seizures.

HP:0032838.name: Neonatal unilateral epileptic spasm
HP:0032838.definition: Neonatal unilateral epileptic spasm is a sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that occurs at one side of the body.

HP:0032839.name: Bilateral symmetric neonatal sequential seizure
HP:0032839.definition: Symmetric neonatal electro-clinical sequential motor seizure is a type of neonatal electro-clinical seizure where the predominant feature cannot be detected because of seizures presenting symmetrically but with a variety of clinical and electrographic signs.

HP:0032840.name: Neonatal bilateral symmetric epileptic spasm
HP:0032840.definition: Neonatal bilateral symmetric epileptic spasm is a sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that occurs symmetrically at both sides of the body.

HP:0032841.name: Neonatal bilateral asymmetric epileptic spasm
HP:0032841.definition: Neonatal bilateral asymmetric epileptic spasm is a sudden flexion, extension, or mixed extension-flexion of predominantly proximal and truncal muscles that occurs asymmetrically at both sides of the body.

HP:0032842.name: Generalized-onset epileptic spasm
HP:0032842.definition: A type of epileptic spasm of generalized onset.

HP:0032843.name: Focal-onset epileptic spasm
HP:0032843.definition: A type of epileptic spasm of focal onset.

HP:0032844.name: Focal impaired awareness epileptic spasm
HP:0032844.definition: A type of focal-onset epileptic spasm in which awareness is impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032845.name: Focal aware epileptic spasm
HP:0032845.definition: A type of focal-onset epileptic spasm in which awareness is preserved throughout the seizure.

HP:0032846.name: Focal motor seizure with negative myoclonus
HP:0032846.definition: A type of focal motor seizure characterized by a sudden interruption in normal tonic muscle activity lasting 500 ms or less, without evidence of preceding myoclonus as the initial semiological manifestation. The interruption in muscle tone is briefer than seen in a focal atonic seizure.

HP:0032847.name: Focal impaired awareness hemifacial clonic seizure
HP:0032847.definition: Focal seizure characterized at onset by clonic movements affecting half of the face with impairment of awareness in which awareness is impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032848.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with neglect
HP:0032848.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with neglect characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032849.name: Aphasic status epilepticus
HP:0032849.definition: Aphasic status epilepticus is a type of focal non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma characterized by a cognitive (rather than motor) language deficit.

HP:0032850.name: Focal aware cognitive seizure with expressive dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032850.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with expressive dysphasia / aphasia characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032851.name: Focal aware sensory seizure with visual features
HP:0032851.definition: A seizure characterized by elementary visual hallucinations such as flashing or flickering lights/colors, or other shapes, simple patterns, scotomata, or amaurosis.

HP:0032852.name: Focal impaired awareness cognitive seizure with conduction dysphasia/aphasia
HP:0032852.definition: A focal cognitive seizure with conduction dysphasia / aphasia characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032853.name: Focal impaired awareness sensory seizure with hot-cold sensations
HP:0032853.definition: A focal sensory seizure with hot-cold sensations in which awareness is partially or fully impaired at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032854.name: Focal aware hemifacial clonic seizure
HP:0032854.definition: Focal seizure characterized at onset by clonic movements affecting half of the face with retained awareness throughout.

HP:0032855.name: Photosensitive myoclonic-tonic-clonic seizure
HP:0032855.definition: Generalised myoclonic-tonic-clonic seizure provoked by flashing or flickering light.

HP:0032856.name: Focal aware bilateral motor seizure
HP:0032856.definition: A type of focal bilateral motor seizure during which awareness is fully retained throughout.

HP:0032857.name: Focal aware motor seizure with negative myoclonus
HP:0032857.definition: A focal motor seizure with negative myoclonus characterized by retained awareness throughout the seizure.

HP:0032858.name: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure with negative myoclonus
HP:0032858.definition: A focal motor seizure with negative myoclonus characterized by impairment of awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032859.name: Focal impaired awareness motor seizure with paresis/paralysis
HP:0032859.definition: A focal motor seizure with paresis / paralysis characterized by impaired awareness at some point during the seizure.

HP:0032860.name: Generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma
HP:0032860.definition: Generalized non-convulsive status epilepticus without coma is a type of status epilepticus without prominent motor signs, which is electrographically generalized. It is a prolonged absence seizure.

HP:0032861.name: Focal non-convulsive status epilepticus with impairment of consciousness
HP:0032861.definition: Focal non-convulsive status epilepticus with impairment of consciousness is a type of focal non-convulsive status epilepticus in which awareness is impaired.

HP:0032862.name: Status epilepticus with ictal paresis
HP:0032862.definition: A type of focal motor status epilepticus characterized by prolonged ictal paresis or inhibitory motor seizures.

HP:0032863.name: Typical absence status epilepticus
