HP:0030205.definition: The variation in the time interval between the two action potentials of the same motor unit is called jitter. This term therefore applies to increased variability in the interval between successive action potentials of the same motor unit, which is measured by electromyography (EMG).

HP:0030206.name: EMG: incremental response of compound muscle action potential to repetitive nerve stimulation
HP:0030206.definition: A compound muscle action potential (CMAP) is a type of electromyography (EMG). CMAP refers to a group of almost simultaneous action potentials from several muscle fibers in the same area evoked by stimulation of the supplying motor nerve and are recorded as one multipeaked summated action potential. This abnormality refers to an abnormal increase in the amplitude during the course of the investigation.

HP:0030207.name: Paradoxical respiration
HP:0030207.definition: Breathing movements in which the chest wall moves in on inspiration and out on expiration, in reverse of the normal movements. It may be seen in children with respiratory distress of any cause, which leads to indrawing of the intercostal spaces during inspiration. Patients with chronic airways obstruction also show indrawing of the lower ribs during inspiration, due to the distorted action of a depressed and flattened diaphragm. Crush injuries of the chest, with fractured ribs and sternum, can lead to a severe degree of paradoxical breathing.

HP:0030208.name: Anti-neuromuscular Junction acetylcholine receptor antibody positivity
HP:0030208.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against neuromuscular junction acetylcholine receptors.

HP:0030209.name: Calcium channel antibody positivity
HP:0030209.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against voltage-gated calcium channels.

HP:0030210.name: Anti-muscle-specific tyrosine kinase antibody
HP:0030210.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against muscle specific kinase (anti-MuSK Ab).

HP:0030211.name: Slow pupillary light response
HP:0030211.definition: Reduced velocity and acceleration in the pupillary light response.

HP:0030212.name: Collectionism
HP:0030212.definition: Excessive or pathological tendency to save and collect possessions.

HP:0030213.name: Emotional dearth
HP:0030213.definition: The inability to feel or express emotions. It is generally recognized by the person who often complains that they are unable to feel anything; sadness, joy, or contentment are not experienced, rather a sense of nothingness prevails. This may be dimensional, ranging from limited ability to experience emotions to the perceived complete inability to feel emotions.

HP:0030215.name: Inappropriate crying
HP:0030215.definition: Uncontrolled episodes of crying occur without any apparent motivating stimuli.

HP:0030216.name: Inertia
HP:0030216.definition: Reduction of goal-directed behaviors linked to the impairment in frontal executive functions (planning of an action for example).

HP:0030217.name: Limb apraxia
HP:0030217.definition: Difficulty in performing the correct execution of limbs movements in absence of motor impairment.

HP:0030218.name: Punding
HP:0030218.definition: Punding is a stereotypical motor behavior characterized by an intense fascination with repetitive, excessive and non-goal oriented handling, and examining of objects.

HP:0030219.name: Semantic dementia
HP:0030219.definition: A progressive loss of the ability to remember the meaning of words, faces and objects.

HP:0030220.name: Socially inappropriate behavior
HP:0030220.definition: Behavior that is not in line with social norms.

HP:0030221.name: Sweet craving
HP:0030221.definition: Excessive desire to eat sweet foods.

HP:0030222.name: Visual agnosia
HP:0030222.definition: The condition is known as visual agnosia, which refers to the inability to recognize objects that are visually presented, even though the individual may have normal visual field, acuity, color vision, brightness discrimination, language, and memory.

HP:0030223.name: Perseverative thought
HP:0030223.definition: The repetitive production of the same response to different commands.

HP:0030224.name: Abnormal muscle fiber desmin
HP:0030224.definition: A deviation from normal in the expression of desmin in muscle tissue. Desmin is an 53-kDa protein.

HP:0030225.name: Accumulation of muscle fiber desmin
HP:0030225.definition: Immunohistochemistry shows accumulation of desmin protein in the muscle biopsy.

HP:0030226.name: Abnormal muscle fiber myotilin
HP:0030226.definition: A deviation from normal in the expression of myotilin in muscle tissue. Myotilin is a 57kDa cytoskeletal protein.

HP:0030227.name: Accumulation of muscle fiber myotilin
HP:0030227.definition: Immunohistochemistry shows accumulation of myotilin protein in the muscle biopsy.

HP:0030228.name: Abnormal muscle fiber valosin-containing protein
HP:0030228.definition: A deviation from normal in the expression of valosin-containing protein in muscle tissue. Valosin-containing protein is an ubiquitously expressed multifunctional 100-kD protein that is a member of the AAA+ (ATPase associated with various activities) protein family.

HP:0030229.name: Accumulation of muscle fiber valosin-containing protein
HP:0030229.definition: Immunohistochemistry shows accumulation of valosin-containing protein in the muscle biopsy.

HP:0030230.name: Central core regions in muscle fibers
HP:0030230.definition: The presence of disorganized areas called cores in the center of muscle fibers. There is a typical appearance of the biopsy on light microscopy, where the muscle cells have cores that are devoid of mitochondria and specific enzymes. Cores are typically well demarcated and centrally located, but may occasionally be multiple and of eccentric.

HP:0030231.name: Glycogen accumulation in muscle fiber lysosomes
HP:0030231.definition: An increased amount of glycogen in muscle tissue found specifically in lysosomes.

HP:0030232.name: Increased sarcoplasmic glycogen
HP:0030232.definition: Elevated glycogen content in the sarcoplasm (cytoplasm) of muscle fibers.

HP:0030233.name: Bethlem sign
HP:0030233.definition: Limitation of wrist and finger extension on asking patient to form a prayer sign. This is a result of progressive wrist and finger flexion contractures.

HP:0030234.name: Highly elevated creatine kinase
HP:0030234.definition: An increased CPK level between 4X and 50X above the upper normal level.

HP:0030235.name: Extremely elevated creatine kinase
HP:0030235.definition: An increased creatine kinase level more than 50X above the upper normal level.

HP:0030236.name: Abnormality of muscle size
HP:0030236.definition: Abnormalities of the overall muscle bulk based on clinical observation.

HP:0030237.name: Hand muscle weakness
HP:0030237.definition: Reduced strength of the musculature of the hand.

HP:0030239.name: Hypoplasia of the upper arm musculature
HP:0030239.definition: Underdevelopment of the musculature of the upper arm, which may include the deltoid, the triceps, the biceps, and the brachioradialis.

HP:0030242.name: Portal vein thrombosis
HP:0030242.definition: Thrombosis of the portal vein and/or its tributaries, which include the splenic vein and the superior and inferior mesenteric veins.

HP:0030243.name: Hepatic vein thrombosis
HP:0030243.definition: An obstruction in the veins of the liver caused by a blood clot (thrombosis).

HP:0030244.name: Maternal fever in pregnancy
HP:0030244.definition: The occurrence of an elevated body temperature of the mother during pregnancy.

HP:0030245.name: Intrapartum fever
HP:0030245.definition: The occurrence of maternal fever during labor.

HP:0030246.name: Maternal first trimester fever
HP:0030246.definition: The occurrence of fever in a mother during the first trimester of pregnancy.

HP:0030247.name: Splanchnic vein thrombosis
HP:0030247.definition: The term splanchnic vein thrombosis encompasses Budd-Chiari syndrome (hepatic vein thrombosis), extrahepatic portal vein obstruction (EHPVO), and mesenteric vein thrombosis; the word splanchnic is used to refer to the visceral organs (of the abdominal cavity).

HP:0030248.name: Mesenteric venous thrombosis
HP:0030248.definition: A clot that obstructs blood flow in a mesenteric vein (the superior and the inferior mesenteric vein drain blood from the small and large intestine).

HP:0030249.name: Enanthema
HP:0030249.definition: A sudden eruption (rash) of the surface of a mucous membrane of the mouth or pharynx.

HP:0030250.name: Pulmonary granulomatosis
HP:0030250.definition: The presence of multiple granulomata (small nodular inflammatory lesions containing grouped mononuclear phagocytes) in the lung.

HP:0030251.name: Absence of memory B cells
HP:0030251.definition: Complete lack of memory B cells, that is, of mature B cell type that is long-lived, readily activated upon re-encounter of its antigenic determinant, and has been selected for expression of higher affinity immunoglobulin.

HP:0030252.name: Absent circulating B cells
HP:0030252.definition: Absence of detectable circulating B cells, commonly characterized as CD19+ or CD20+ lymphocytes, in the blood. Usually, less than 20 cells per microlitre is considered to be an absence.

HP:0030254.name: Nail bed hemorrhage
HP:0030254.definition: Small areas of bleeding (hemorrhage) under the fingernail or toenail.

HP:0030255.name: Large intestinal polyposis
HP:0030255.definition: The presence of multiple polyps in the large intestine.

HP:0030256.name: Small intestinal polyposis
HP:0030256.definition: The presence of multiple polyps in the small intestine.

HP:0030257.name: Freckled genitalia
HP:0030257.definition: One or more brown punctate macules on the skin of the genitalia.

HP:0030258.name: Hyperpigmented genitalia
HP:0030258.definition: Localized or generalized increased genital pigmentation.

HP:0030259.name: Hypopigmented genitalia
HP:0030259.definition: Localized or generalized decreased genital pigmentation.

HP:0030260.name: Microphallus
HP:0030260.definition: Length of penis more than 2 SD below the mean for age accompanied by hypospadias.

HP:0030262.name: Narrow penis
HP:0030262.definition: Penile width more than 2 standard deviations (SD) below the mean for age. Alternatively circumference of the flaccid penis more than 2 SD below the mean for age. Alternatively, apparently decreased penile width for age.

HP:0030263.name: Torsion of the penis
HP:0030263.definition: Rotated position of the glans, with or without the penile shaft, of 30 degrees or more.

HP:0030264.name: Webbed penis
HP:0030264.definition: Ventral skinfold extending from penis to scrotum.

HP:0030265.name: Wide penis
HP:0030265.definition: Distance between left and right side of the flaccid penis at the attachment to the skin above the pubic symphysis more than 2 standard deviations above the mean for age.

HP:0030266.name: obsolete Abnormality of the sacroiliac notch

HP:0030267.name: Calcification of the interosseus membrane of the forearm
HP:0030267.definition: Deposition of calcium salts in the fibrous sheet that connects the radius and the ulna.

HP:0030268.name: Hyperplastic callus formation
HP:0030268.definition: Increased growth of callus, the bony and cartilaginous material that forms a connecting bridge across a bone fracture during fracture healing.

HP:0030269.name: Increased circulating insulin-like growth factor 1 concentration
HP:0030269.definition: An elevated level of insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF1) in the blood circulation.

HP:0030270.name: Elevated red cell adenosine deaminase activity
HP:0030270.definition: Increase in the level of adenosine deaminase (ADA), an enzyme involved in purine metabolism, within erythrocytes. ADA is involved in the catabolism of adenosine.

HP:0030271.name: Reduced erythrocyte 2,3-diphosphoglycerate concentration
HP:0030271.definition: This term refers to an inappropriate low 2,3-DPG concentration in erythrocytes. 2,3-diphosphoglycerate (2,3-DPG) controls the movement of oxygen from red blood cells to tissues. Anemia is usually accompanied by an increased level of 2,3-DPG in order to promote tissue oxygenation.

HP:0030272.name: Abnormal erythrocyte enzyme concentration or activity
HP:0030272.definition: An altered level of any enzyme to act as catalysts within erythrocytes. This term includes changes due to altered activity of an enzyme.

HP:0030273.name: Reduced red cell adenosine deaminase level
HP:0030273.definition: Decrease in the level of adenosine deaminase (ADA), an enzyme involved in purine metabolism, within erythrocytes. ADA is involved in the catabolism of adenosine.

HP:0030274.name: Accessory scrotum
HP:0030274.definition: Additional scrotum, or part of a scrotum in an abnormal location.

HP:0030275.name: Ectopic scrotum
HP:0030275.definition: Scrotum in a position other than the usual position inferior to the base of the penis.

HP:0030277.name: Abnormal vertebral pedicle morphology
HP:0030277.definition: Abnormal morphology of a vertebral pedical.

HP:0030279.name: Hypoplastic L5 vertebral pedicle
HP:0030279.definition: Underdeveloped pedicle of the fifth lumbar vertebra.

HP:0030280.name: Rib gap
HP:0030280.definition: Radiolucent focal defect of a rib shaft.

HP:0030281.name: Cervical C3/C4 vertebral fusion
HP:0030281.definition: Fusion of cervical vertebrae at C3 and C4, caused by a failure in the normal segmentation or division of the cervical vertebrae during the early weeks of fetal development.

HP:0030282.name: Posterior rib gap
HP:0030282.definition: Radiolucent focal defect of the posterior portion of a rib shaft. The 'gaps' may lead to flail chest.

HP:0030283.name: Partial absence of the septum pellucidum
HP:0030283.definition: Only part of the septum pellucidum (a thin, triangular, vertical membrane separating the lateral ventricles of the brain) is present. This feature can be appreciated on magnetic resonance tomography or computed tomography of the brain.

HP:0030284.name: Triangular tongue
HP:0030284.definition: A form of macrogloassia (increased size of the tongue) characterized by a broad based root of the tongue but a small tongue tip, giving the appearance of a triangle.

HP:0030285.name: Splayed superior cerebellar peduncle
HP:0030285.definition: Abnormal splayed configuration (spreading out) of the superior cerebellar peduncle.

HP:0030286.name: Atrophic superior cerebellar peduncle
HP:0030286.definition: Atrophy of the superior cerebellar peduncle.

HP:0030289.name: Flattened femoral epiphysis
HP:0030289.definition: An abnormal flattening of an epiphysis of femur.

HP:0030290.name: Unossified sacrum
HP:0030290.definition: Lack of ossification of the sacrum.

HP:0030291.name: Lower-limb metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0030291.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of one or more metaphyses of a bone of the leg.

HP:0030292.name: Tibial metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0030292.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of a metaphysis of a tibia.

HP:0030293.name: Fibular metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0030293.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of a metaphysis of a fibula.

HP:0030299.name: Abnormal distal femoral metaphysis morphology
HP:0030299.definition: An anomaly of the metaphysis of the distal femur (close to the knee).

HP:0030300.name: 10 pairs of ribs
HP:0030300.definition: Presence of only 10 (instead of the usual 12) pairs of ribs.

HP:0030301.name: Abnormality of the anterior commissure
HP:0030301.definition: An anomaly of the anterior commissure, a bundle of nerve fibers that connect the two cerebral hemispheres across the midline. The anterior commissure plays a role in pain sensation and contains decussating fibers from the olfactory tracts.

HP:0030304.name: Abnormal number of vertebrae
HP:0030304.definition: A deviation from the normal number of vertebrae in the spinal column.

HP:0030306.name: 11 thoracic vertebrae
HP:0030306.definition: The presence of 11 instead of the normal 12 thoracic vertebrae.

HP:0030307.name: Flared lower limb metaphysis
HP:0030307.definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of one or more long bones of the leg.

HP:0030308.name: Flared distal tibial metaphysis
HP:0030308.definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of the distal tibia.

HP:0030309.name: Flared distal fibular metaphysis
HP:0030309.definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of the distal fibula.

HP:0030310.name: Upper extremity joint dislocation
HP:0030310.definition: Displacement or malalignment of one or more joints in the upper extremity (arm).

HP:0030311.name: Lower extremity joint dislocation
HP:0030311.definition: Displacement or malalignment of one or more joints in the lower extremity (leg).

HP:0030312.name: Obliteration of the calvarial diploe
HP:0030312.definition: Absence of the spongy bone structure (or tissue) of the internal part of the skull cap (i.e., of the calvarial diploe).

HP:0030313.name: Abnormal periosteum morphology
HP:0030313.definition: An anomalous structure of the periosteum, i.e., of the membrane that covers the outer surface of bones.

HP:0030318.name: Angular cheilitis
HP:0030318.definition: A type of inflammation of the lips involving one or both of the corners of the mouth.

HP:0030319.name: Weakness of facial musculature
HP:0030319.definition: Reduced strength of one or more muscles innervated by the facial nerve (the seventh cranial nerve).

HP:0030320.name: Increased intervertebral space
HP:0030320.definition: An increase in the vertical distance between adjacent vertebral bodies, observed as an increase in the intervertebral disk space.

HP:0030321.name: Abnormal vertebral artery morphology
HP:0030321.definition: An anomaly of the vertebral artery, the major artery of the neck that originates from the subclavian artery and merges to form the single midline basilar artery in a complex called the vertebrobasilar system.

HP:0030323.name: Unilateral vertebral artery hypoplasia
HP:0030323.definition: Underdevelopment of the vertebral artery on one side.

HP:0030324.name: Bilateral vertebral artery hypoplasia
HP:0030324.definition: Underdevelopment of the vertebral artery on both sides.

HP:0030325.name: Cervicomedullary schisis
HP:0030325.definition: Fissure within the spinal cord of the neck.

HP:0030326.name: Abnormal macrophage count
HP:0030326.definition: An anomaly in the number of macrophages.

HP:0030327.name: Abnormal osteoclast count
HP:0030327.definition: An anomaly in the number of osteoclasts in bone tissue, bone-resorbing cells that develop from macrophages. This finding can be observed by histological examination of bone tissue.

HP:0030328.name: Decreased osteoclast count
HP:0030328.definition: Decreased number of osteoclasts in bone tissue.

HP:0030329.name: Retinal thinning
HP:0030329.definition: Reduced anteroposterior thickness of the retina. This phenotype can be appreciated by retinal optical coherence tomography (OCT).

HP:0030330.name: Multinucleated giant chondrocytes in epiphyseal cartilage
HP:0030330.definition: The presence of cartilage cells (chondrocytes) that are substantially increased in size and contain more than one nucleus and are located within the resting zone of the epiphyseal cartilage.

HP:0030331.name: Impaired stimulus-induced skin wrinkling
HP:0030331.definition: A reduced ability of the skin of the fingertips to wrinkle when exposed to stimuli such as soaking in water or application of EMLA cream (the fingertip remains smooth).

HP:0030333.name: Abnormal alpha-beta T cell morphology
HP:0030333.definition: A structuraly anomaly of T cells that express an alpha-beta T cell receptor.

HP:0030334.name: Abnormal CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell morphology
HP:0030334.definition: A structural anomaly of a CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta T cell. These cells are regulatory T cells.

HP:0030335.name: Abnormal CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell count
HP:0030335.definition: A deviation from the normal count of CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cells.

HP:0030336.name: Absence of CD4-positive, CD25-positive regulatory T cells
HP:0030336.definition: Lack of CD4+CD25+ T regulatory cells.

HP:0030337.name: Elevated CD4-positive, CD25-positive regulatory T cell count
HP:0030337.definition: An increased number of CD4-positive, CD25-positive regulatory T cells.

HP:0030338.name: Abnormal circulating gonadotropin concentration
HP:0030338.definition: An anomaly of the circulating level of a gonadotropin, that is, of a protein hormone secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary of vertebrates. The primary gonadotropins are luteinizing hormone (LH) and follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

HP:0030339.name: Decreased circulating gonadotropin concentration
HP:0030339.definition: A reduction of the circulating level of a gonadotropin, that is, of a protein hormone secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary of vertebrates. The primary gonadotropins are luteinizing hormone (LH) and follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

HP:0030341.name: Decreased circulating follicle stimulating hormone concentration
HP:0030341.definition: A reduction of the circulating level of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

HP:0030344.name: Decreased circulating luteinizing hormone level
HP:0030344.definition: A reduction in the circulating level of luteinizing hormone (LH).

HP:0030345.name: Abnormal circulating luteinizing hormone concentration
HP:0030345.definition: An anomaly of the circulating level of luteinizing hormone (LH).

HP:0030346.name: Abnormal circulating follicle-stimulating hormone concentration
HP:0030346.definition: An anomaly of the circulating level of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).

HP:0030347.name: Abnormal circulating androgen level
HP:0030347.definition: An anomaly in the blood concentration of an androgen, that is, of a steroid hormone that controls development and maintenance of masculine characteristics. The androgens include testosterone and Dehydroepiandrosterone.

HP:0030348.name: Increased circulating androgen concentration
HP:0030348.definition: An elevation of the blood concentration of an androgen, that is, of a steroid hormone that controls development and maintenance of masculine characteristics. The androgens include testosterone and Dehydroepiandrosterone.

HP:0030349.name: Decreased circulating androgen concentration
HP:0030349.definition: A reduction in the blood concentration of an androgen, that is, of a steroid hormone that controls development and maintenance of masculine characteristics. The androgens include testosterone and Dehydroepiandrosterone.

HP:0030350.name: Erythematous papule
HP:0030350.definition: A circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid that is reddish (erythematous) in color.

HP:0030351.name: Urticarial plaque
HP:0030351.definition: A well-circumscribed, intensely pruritic, raised wheal (edema of the superficial skin) typically 1 to 2 cm in diameter.

HP:0030352.name: Abnormal serum insulin-like growth factor 1 level
HP:0030352.definition: An anomalous level of insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF1) in the blood circulation.

HP:0030353.name: Decreased serum insulin-like growth factor 1
HP:0030353.definition: A reduced level of insulin-like growth factor 1 (IGF1) in the blood circulation.

HP:0030355.name: Abnormal circulating interferon-gamma concentration
HP:0030355.definition: Abnormal levels of interferon gamma measured in the blood circulation.

HP:0030356.name: Increased circulating interferon-gamma concentration
HP:0030356.definition: An elevation in the concentration of interferon gamma measured in the blood circulation.

HP:0030357.name: Small cell lung carcinoma
HP:0030357.definition: Small cell lung cancer (SCLC) is a type of highly malignant lung cancer that is composed of small ovoid cells. In the past, SCLC was called oat cell carcinoma because the microscopic appearance of the cells was felt to resemble oats. SLCLC usually originates near the bronchi and in many cases may grow and metastasize quickly.

HP:0030359.name: Squamous cell lung carcinoma
HP:0030359.definition: A type of non-small cell lung carcinoma that is derived from stratified squamous epithelial cells.

HP:0030360.name: Large cell lung carcinoma
HP:0030360.definition: A type of non-small cell lung carcinoma that is derived from undifferentiated malignant neoplasms originating from transformed epithelial cells in the lung, and which is differentiate from small-cell lung carcinoma by the larger size of the anaplastic cells, a higher cytoplasmic-to-nuclear size ratio, and a lack of salt-and-pepper appearance of the chromatin.

HP:0030361.name: Abnormal circulating eicosanoid concentration
HP:0030361.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of an icosanoid (also known as eicosanoids). These are signaling molecules derived from oxidation of 20-carbon fatty acids. Most are produced from arachidonic acid, a 20-carbon polyunsaturated fatty acid (5,8,11,14-eicosatetraenoic acid).

HP:0030362.name: Reduced muscle carnitine level
HP:0030362.definition: A reduction in the level of carnitine in muscle tissue.

HP:0030363.name: Primary Caesarian section
HP:0030363.definition: Delivery by Caesarian section representing the first time the mother has delivered by Caesarian section.

HP:0030364.name: Secondary Caesarian section
HP:0030364.definition: Delivery by Caesarian section representing where the mother has already had a previous Cesarean delivery, and this is a repeat Cesarean birth.

HP:0030365.name: Vaginal birth after Caesarean
HP:0030365.definition: Vaginal birth after Caesarean (VBAC) refers to the situation where the mother has had a previous Cesarean delivery but has now delivered vaginally.

HP:0030366.name: Delivery by Odon device
HP:0030366.definition: The Odon device is an instrument for assisted vaginal deliveries that is applied on the head of the baby and used to apply traction to assist the birth process.

HP:0030367.name: Finger hyperphalangy
HP:0030367.definition: Hyperphalangy is a digit morphology in which increased numbers of phalanges are arranged linearly within a digit. That is, there is an accessory phalanx that is arranged linearly with the other phalanges.

HP:0030368.name: Hyperphalangy of the 2nd finger
HP:0030368.definition: An accessory phalanx of the index (second) finger that is arranged linearly with the other phalanges. Hyperphalangy of the index finger results from an accessory ossification center at the metacarpophalangeal joint, resulting in radial deviation of the index finger. Note that this term refers only to this type of hyperphalangy.

HP:0030369.name: Induced vaginal delivery
HP:0030369.definition: Vaginal delivery following induction of labor, a procedure used to stimulate uterine contractions during pregnancy before labor begins on its own.

HP:0030370.name: Abnormal naive B cell proportion
HP:0030370.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of the naive B cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD27-IgM+, measured as percentage of total B cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0030371.name: Increased naive B cell proportion
HP:0030371.definition: The proportion of naive B cellsin the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal with respect to the reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0030372.name: Decreased naive B cell proportion
HP:0030372.definition: The proportion of naive B cellsin the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal with respect to the reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0030373.name: Abnormal memory B cell proportion
HP:0030373.definition: A deviation of the normal proportion of memory B cells in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Memory B cells develop from naive B cells. Upon antigen rechallenge, memory B cells rapidly expand and differentiate into plasma cells under the cognate control of memory Th cells (Phase IV).

HP:0030374.name: Decreased proportion of memory B cells
HP:0030374.definition: A reduction in the normal proportion of memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. Memory B cells develop from naive B cells. Upon antigen rechallenge, memory B cells rapidly expand and differentiate into plasma cells under the cognate control of memory Th cells (Phase IV).

HP:0030375.name: Increased proportion of memory B cells
HP:0030375.definition: An elevation in the proportion of memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. Memory B cells develop from naive B cells. Upon antigen rechallenge, memory B cells rapidly expand and differentiate into plasma cells under the cognate control of memory Th cells (Phase IV).

HP:0030376.name: Abnormal immature B cell proportion
HP:0030376.definition: A deviation from normal proportion of immature B cells (CD19+/ CD21low) in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Immature B cells (IgM+) are still in final stages of development within the bone marrow. Naive B cells are those which have left the bone marrow, before they bind to the antigen for which they're specific (IgM+/IgD+).

HP:0030377.name: Increased immature B cell proportion
HP:0030377.definition: An elevation in the proportion above normal of immature B cells (CD19+/ CD21low) in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Immature B cells (IgM+) are still in final stages of development within the bone marrow. Naive B cells are those which have left the bone marrow, before they bind to the antigen for which they're specific (IgM+/IgD+).

HP:0030378.name: Decreased immature B cell proportion
HP:0030378.definition: A reduction in normal proportion of immature B cells (CD19+/ CD21low)in circulation relative to total number of B cells. Immature B cells (IgM+) are still in final stages of development within the bone marrow. Naive B cells are those which have left the bone marrow, before they bind to the antigen for which they're specific (IgM+/IgD+).

HP:0030379.name: Abnormal transitional B cell proportion
HP:0030379.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of the transitional B cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD27-CD24hiCD38hi or CD27-IgMhiCD38hi, measured as percentage of total B cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0030380.name: Decreased transitional B cell proportion
HP:0030380.definition: Abnormal decrease of the transitional B cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD27-CD24hiCD38hi or CD27-IgMhiCD38hi, measured as percentage of total B cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0030381.name: Increased transitional B cell proportion
HP:0030381.definition: Abnormal increase of the transitional B cell subpopulation, commonly characterized as CD27-CD24hiCD38hi or CD27-IgMhiCD38hi, measured as percentage of total B cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0030383.name: Abnormal proportion of marginal zone B cells
HP:0030383.definition: A deviation of the normal proportion of marginal zone B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells.

HP:0030384.name: Decreased proportion of marginal zone B cells
HP:0030384.definition: A reduction in the normal proportion of marginal zone B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells.

HP:0030385.name: Increased proportion of marginal zone B cells
HP:0030385.definition: An elevation in the normal proportion of marginal zone B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells.

HP:0030386.name: Abnormal class-switched memory B cell proportion
HP:0030386.definition: A deviation of the normal proportion of class-switched memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM-/IgD-) in circulation relative to the total number of B cells. Marginal zone B cells undergo limited somatic hypermutation and produce high-affinity IgM and some IgG, whereas class-switched memory B cells synthetize IgG, IgM, and IgA.

HP:0030387.name: Increased class-switched memory B cell proportion
HP:0030387.definition: An increase in the normal proportion of class-switched memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) relative to the total number of B cells. Marginal zone B cells undergo limited somatic hypermutation and produce high-affinity IgM and some IgG, whereas class-switched memory B cells synthetize IgG, IgM, and IgA.

HP:0030388.name: Decreased class-switched memory B cell proportion
HP:0030388.definition: A reduction in the normal proportion of class-switched memory B cells (CD19+/CD27+/IgM+/IgD+) relative to the total number of B cells. Marginal zone B cells undergo limited somatic hypermutation and produce high-affinity IgM and some IgG, whereas class-switched memory B cells synthetize IgG, IgM, and IgA.

HP:0030389.name: Abnormal circulating thromboxane concentration
HP:0030389.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration in the blood circulation of a thromboxane. Thromboxanes are derived from prostaglandin precursors in platelets, and stimulate aggregation of platelets and constriction of blood vessels.

HP:0030390.name: Reduced circulating leukotriene C4 concentration
HP:0030390.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of leukotriene C4 in the blood circulation.

HP:0030391.name: Spoken word recognition deficit
HP:0030391.definition: Reduced ability of lexical discrimination, which refers to the process of distinguishing a stimulus word from other phonologically similar words. Lexical discrimination can be defined as the process of correctly identifying words in the mental lexicon to match the phonological input of a stimulus.

HP:0030392.name: Choroid plexus carcinoma
HP:0030392.definition: Intraventricular papillary neoplasm derived from choroid plexus epithelium. Plexus tumors are most common in the lateral and fourth ventricles; while 80% of lateral ventricle tumors present in children, fourth ventricle tumors are evenly distributed in all age groups. Clinically, choroid plexus tumors tend to cause hydrocephalus and increased intracranial pressure. Histologically, choroid plexus papillomas correspond to WHO grade I, choroid plexus carcinomas to WHO grade III.

HP:0030393.name: Endolymphatic sac tumor
HP:0030393.definition: A low-grade papillary epithelial neoplasm (adenocarcinoma) with a slow growth pattern. The endolymphatic duct emerges from the posterior wall of the saccule (of the inner ear) and ends in a blind pouch, the endolymphatic sac. Endolymphatic sac tumors (ELSTs) are known under different names in the literature (Heffner tumor, aggressive papillary middle ear tumor, and low-grade adenocarcinoma of endolymphatic sac origin).

HP:0030394.name: Fallopian tube carcinoma
HP:0030394.definition: Carcinoma that originates in the Fallopian tube. It may be located in the wall or within the lumen as a growth attached to the wall by a stalk.

HP:0030396.name: Abnormal platelet granule secretion
HP:0030396.definition: Platelets are replete with secretory granules, which are critical to normal platelet function. Among the three types of platelet secretory granules - alpha-granules, dense granules, and lysosomes - the alpha-granule is the most abundant. Granule contents must be released from their intracellular repository in order to achieve their physiologic function, and this term refers to a functional defect in granule secretion.

HP:0030397.name: Abnormal platelet dense granule secretion
HP:0030397.definition: Abnormal release of dense granules from platelets.

HP:0030398.name: Abnormal platelet ATP dense granule secretion
HP:0030398.definition: Abnormal secretion of the platelet dense-granule content adenosine triphosphate (ATP).

HP:0030399.name: Abnormal platelet alpha granule secretion
HP:0030399.definition: Abnormal release of alpha granule contents from platelets.

HP:0030400.name: Abnormal platelet lysosome secretion
HP:0030400.definition: Abnormal release of lysosome contents from platelets.

HP:0030401.name: Abnormal platelet dense granule ATP/ADP ratio
HP:0030401.definition: Deviation from normal of the ratio of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) to adenosine diphosphate (ADP) within platelets.

HP:0030402.name: Abnormal platelet aggregation
HP:0030402.definition: An abnormality in the rate and degree to which platelets aggregate after the addition of an agonist that stimulates platelet clumping. Platelet aggregation is measured using aggregometer to measure the optical density of platelet-rich plasma, whereby platelet aggregation causes the plasma to become more transparent.

HP:0030403.name: Spontaneous platelet aggregation
HP:0030403.definition: Clumping together of platelets in the blood in a platelet aggregation test without addition of agents normally used to induce aggregation.

HP:0030404.name: Glucagonoma
HP:0030404.definition: An endocrine tumor of the pancreas that secretes excessive amounts of glucagon.

HP:0030405.name: Pancreatic endocrine tumor
HP:0030405.definition: A neuroendocrine tumor originating in a hormone-producing cell (islet cell) of the pancreas.

HP:0030406.name: Primary peritoneal carcinoma
HP:0030406.definition: A type of cancer that originates in the peritoneum. It is to be distinguished from metastatic cancer of the peritoneum. Peritoneal cancer can occur anywhere in the abdominal space, and affects the surface of organs contained inside the peritoneum.

HP:0030407.name: Pineocytoma
HP:0030407.definition: A type of pineal parenchymal cell neoplasm that is a mature well-differentiated tumor (WHO grade I).

HP:0030408.name: Pineoblastoma
HP:0030408.definition: Pineoblastoma is a rare primitive neuroectodermal tumor (PNET) arising in the pineal gland. Pineoblastomas are classified as a WHO grade IV tumor and comprise one-fourth to one-half of pineal parenchymal tumors. Pineoblastoma is a highly cellular tumor originating in the pineal gland and containing small, poorly differentiated cells.

HP:0030409.name: Renal transitional cell carcinoma
HP:0030409.definition: A malignant tumor that arises from the transitional (urothelial) epithelial cells lining the urinary tract from the renal calyces to the ureteral orifice.

HP:0030410.name: Sebaceous gland carcinoma
HP:0030410.definition: A carcinoma that arises in a sebaseous gland (an exocrine gland of the skin that secretes sebum, a waxy substance)

HP:0030411.name: Jejunal adenocarcinoma
HP:0030411.definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the jejunum.

HP:0030412.name: Ileal adenocarcinoma
HP:0030412.definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the ileum.

HP:0030413.name: Squamous cell carcinoma of the tongue
HP:0030413.definition: A carcinoma derived from a squamous epithelial cell of the tongue.

HP:0030414.name: Verrucous cell carcinoma of the tongue
HP:0030414.definition: A low-grade variant of squamous cell carcinoma of the tongue with a warty (verrucous) appearance.

HP:0030415.name: Sarcomatoid carcinoma of the tongue
HP:0030415.definition: Sarcomatoid (spindle cell) carcinomas of the tongue is a variant of squamous carcinoma of tongue that is monoclonal, having evolved from a conventional squamous carcinoma with dedifferentiation associated with sarcomatoid transformation.

HP:0030416.name: Vulvar neoplasm
HP:0030416.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the female external genital tract (vulva).

HP:0030417.name: Squamous cell carcinoma of the vulva
HP:0030417.definition: A cancer that originates in the squamous cells that line the surface of the vulva.

HP:0030418.name: Vulvar melanoma
HP:0030418.definition: A type of vulvar cancer that originates from melanocytes of the vulva.

HP:0030419.name: Bartholin gland carcinoma
HP:0030419.definition: A cancer arising in a cell of the Bartholin gland, a racemose gland located slightly posterior to the opening of the vagina.

HP:0030420.name: Vulvar adenocarcinoma
HP:0030420.definition: An adenocarcinoma arising in the vulva.

HP:0030421.name: Epididymal neoplasm
HP:0030421.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the epididymis, an duct that transports spermatozoa from the testis to the vas deferens.

HP:0030422.name: obsolete Papillary cystadenoma of the epididymis

HP:0030423.name: Splenic cyst
HP:0030423.definition: A closed sac located in the spleen.

HP:0030424.name: Epididymal cyst
HP:0030424.definition: A smooth, extratesticular, spherical cyst in the head of the epididymis.

HP:0030425.name: Calcified ovarian cyst
HP:0030425.definition: A cyst of the ovary that exhibits deposition of calcium salts.

HP:0030426.name: Ossifying fibroma
HP:0030426.definition: A benign central bone tumor composed of fibrous connective tissue within which bone is formed.

HP:0030427.name: Ossifying fibroma of the jaw
HP:0030427.definition: A benign central bone tumor of the jaw composed of fibrous connective tissue within which bone is formed.

HP:0030428.name: Cutaneous myxoma
HP:0030428.definition: A myxoma originating in the skin.

HP:0030429.name: Juvenile nasopharyngeal angiofibroma
HP:0030429.definition: A benign but highly vascular nasopharyngeal neoplasm. The tumor originates from the sphenopalatine foramen and involves both the pterygopalatine fossa and the posterior nasal cavity.

HP:0030430.name: Neuroma
HP:0030430.definition: A tumor made up of nerve cells and nerve fibers.

HP:0030431.name: Osteochondroma
HP:0030431.definition: A cartilage capped bony outgrowth of a long bone. Osteochondroma arises on the external surface of bone containing a marrow cavity that is continuous with that of the underlying bone.

HP:0030432.name: Chondroblastoma
HP:0030432.definition: A usually benign tumor composed of cells which arise from chondroblasts or their precursors and which tend to differentiate into cartilage cells.

HP:0030433.name: Osteoid osteoma
HP:0030433.definition: A bening tumor of bone composed of a central zone named nidus which is an atypical bone completely enclosed within a well vascularized stroma and a peripheral sclerotic reaction zone.

HP:0030434.name: Pilomatrixoma
HP:0030434.definition: Pilomatricoma is an asymptomatic slowly growing benign cutaneous tumor, differentiating towards the hair matrix of the hair follicle. It is covered by normal or hyperemic skin, and usually varies in size from 0.5 to 3 cm.

HP:0030436.name: Fibrofolliculoma
HP:0030436.definition: Fibrofolliculoma is a clinically asymptomatic, 2-4 mm, skin-colored, dome-shaped smooth papule. It usually arises in the form of multiple lesions in adults in different areas such as the scalp, forehead, face, and neck. According to histology, the lesion is a fibrotic hamartoma characterized by infundibular epithelial proliferation and perifollicular fibrous proliferation.

HP:0030438.name: Anal canal squamous cell carcinoma
HP:0030438.definition: A squamous cell carcinoma that originates in the anal canal.

HP:0030439.name: Anal canal adenocarcinoma
HP:0030439.definition: An adenoma carcinoma that originates in the anal canal.

HP:0030440.name: Anal margin neoplasm
HP:0030440.definition: A tumor of the anal margin.

HP:0030441.name: Anal margin Paget's disease
HP:0030441.definition: An intraepithelial adenocarcinoma originating in the anal margin and characterized by presence of typical Paget's cells, appearing as large rounded vacuolated cells.

HP:0030442.name: Anal margin squamous cell carcinoma
HP:0030442.definition: A squamous cell carcinoma that originates in the skin of the anal margin.

HP:0030443.name: Anal margin basal cell carcinoma
HP:0030443.definition: A basal cell carcinoma that originates in the anal margin.

HP:0030444.name: Anal margin melanoma
HP:0030444.definition: A melanoma that originates in the anal margin.

HP:0030445.name: Pulmonary carcinoid tumor
HP:0030445.definition: A malignant neuroendocrine tumor of the lung. According to histopathologic criteria (WHO 2004), carcinoids are divided into four groups i.e. typical and atypical carcinoids, large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma and small cell lung carcinoma.

HP:0030447.name: Merkel cell skin cancer
HP:0030447.definition: A malignant cutaneous tumor of the elderly that is characterized by an aggressive course with regional nodal involvement, distant metastases and a high rate of recurrence. Most patients present with rapidly growing, painless, firm, non-tender, dome-shaped red, occasionally ulcerated skin nodules, which have a red or bluish color, measuring up to several centimeters, on predominantly sun-exposed areas of the body. The overlying skin is smooth and shiny, sometimes exhibiting ulcerative, acneiform or telangiectatic features.

HP:0003961.name: Fractured forearm bone
HP:0003961.definition: Bone fracture in the radius, ulna, or wrist.

HP:0003963.name: Lytic defects of the forearm bones

HP:0003971.name: Broad forearm bones
HP:0003971.definition: Abnormally wide bone of the skeleton of forearm.

HP:0003974.name: Absent radius
HP:0003974.definition: Missing radius bone associated with congenital failure of development.

HP:0003982.name: Aplasia of the ulna
HP:0003982.definition: Missing ulna bone associated with congenital failure of development.

HP:0003991.name: Osteosclerosis of the ulna
HP:0003991.definition: Osteosclerosis (increased density related to increased bone mass) of the ulna.

HP:0003992.name: Slender ulna
HP:0003992.definition: Reduction in diameter of the ulna.

HP:0003994.name: Dislocated wrist
HP:0003994.definition: An injury of the wrist with displacement of any of the eight carpal bones.

HP:0004000.name: Cone-shaped distal radial epiphysis
HP:0004000.definition: The distal epiphysis (rounded portion of bone at the far end of the radius distal to the growth plate) has an abnormal cone-shaped appearance.

HP:0004012.name: Premature fusion of the radial epiphyseal plates
HP:0004012.definition: A premature fusion of the epiphyseal plates of the radius. Epiphyseal plates are located at the distal and proximal ends of the long bones, in this case of the radius and premature fusion will have an effect on the growh of the radial bone, inhibiting or at least disturbing the normal growth and development of the bone.

HP:0004014.name: Broad radial epiphyseal plate
HP:0004014.definition: Abnormal increase in width of the epiphyseal growth plate of the radius.

HP:0004018.name: Flared radial metaphysis
HP:0004018.definition: The presence of a splayed (i.e.,flared) metaphyseal segment of the radius.

HP:0004019.name: Radial metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0004019.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the metaphysis of the radius.

HP:0004020.name: Irregular ossification of the radial metaphysis

HP:0004022.name: Sclerotic radial metaphysis with longitudinal striations

HP:0004026.name: Broad radial metaphysis
HP:0004026.definition: Increase in width (breadth) of the radial metaphysis.

HP:0004027.name: Abnormality of radial diaphysis
HP:0004027.definition: An anomaly of the radial diaphysis.

HP:0004031.name: Broad radial diaphysis
HP:0004031.definition: Increase in width of the diaphysis of radius.

HP:0004032.name: Abnormal olecranon morphology
HP:0004032.definition: Any structural abnormality of the olecranon, a bony eminence of the proximal ulna.

HP:0004038.name: obsolete Bony spicule of ulnar epiphyseal plate

HP:0004039.name: Abnormal ulnar metaphysis morphology
HP:0004039.definition: Any structural abnormality of the portion of the ulna between the epiphysis and the diaphysis.

HP:0004042.name: Ulnar metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0004042.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the metaphysis of the ulna.

HP:0004045.name: Sloping ulnar metaphysis
HP:0004045.definition: A sloped configuration of the metaphysis (shaft) of the ulna.

HP:0004047.name: Wide ulnar metaphysis
HP:0004047.definition: Increase in width (breadth) of the ulnar metaphysis.

HP:0004050.name: Absent hand
HP:0004050.definition: The total absence of the hand, with no bony elements distal to the radius or ulna.

HP:0004051.name: Advanced ossification of the hand bones
HP:0004051.definition: Ossification of hand bones at an earlier age than normal.

HP:0004052.name: Delayed ossification of the hand bones
HP:0004052.definition: Ossification of hand bones is less advanced than would be expected according to age-adjusted norms.

HP:0004053.name: Dysharmonic maturation of the hand bones
HP:0004053.definition: Pattern of hand-wrist development does not fit the normal sequence of ossification of the individual bones of the hand.

HP:0004054.name: Sclerosis of hand bone
HP:0004054.definition: Osteosclerosis affecting one or more bones of the hand.

HP:0004057.name: Mitten deformity
HP:0004057.definition: Fusion of the hands and feet by a thin membrane of skin (scarring) seen in forms of dystrophic epidermolysis bullosa and leading to a "mitten" hand deformity.

HP:0004059.name: Radial club hand
HP:0004059.definition: Wrist is bent inward toward the thumb because of a congenital defect associated with shortening or absence of the radius. The hand is radially deviated at the distal forearm in the shape of a golf club.

HP:0004060.name: Trident hand
HP:0004060.definition: A hand in which the fingers are of nearly equal length and deflected at the first interphalangeal joint, so as to give a forklike shape consisting of separation of the first and second as well as the third and fourth digits.

HP:0004083.name: obsolete Laterally deviated terminal thumb phalanx

HP:0004090.name: obsolete Advanced maturation/advanced ossification of terminal thumb phalanx epiphysis

HP:0004097.name: Deviation of finger
HP:0004097.definition: Deviated fingers is a term that should be used if one or more fingers of the hand are deviated from their normal position, either to the radial or ulnar side. A deviation of a finger can be caused by an abnormal form of one or more of the phalanges of the affected finger, or by a deviation or displacement of one or more phalanges.

HP:0004099.name: Macrodactyly
HP:0004099.definition: Significant increase in the length and girth of most or all of a digit compared to its contralateral digit (if unaffected) or compared to what would be expected for age/body build. The increased girth is accompanied by an increase in the dorso-ventral dimension AND the lateral dimension of the digit.

HP:0004100.name: Abnormal 2nd finger morphology
HP:0004100.definition: An anomaly of the second finger, also known as the index finger.

HP:0004110.name: obsolete Radially deviated index finger phalanges

HP:0004112.name: Midline nasal groove
HP:0004112.definition: An abnormal groove on the midline of the nose that may extend to the nasal tip.

HP:0004121.name: obsolete Radially displaced proximal index finger phalanx

HP:0004122.name: Midline defect of the nose
HP:0004122.definition: This term groups together three conditions that presumably represent different degrees of severity of a midline defect of the nose or nasal tip.

HP:0004132.name: Dimple on nasal tip
HP:0004132.definition: An abnormal indentation of the skin in the region of the nasal tip.

HP:0004138.name: obsolete Metaphyseal abnormality of middle phalanx of the 2nd finger

HP:0004139.name: obsolete Flared metaphysis of middle phalanx of index finger

HP:0004143.name: obsolete Radially deviated terminal index finger phalanx

HP:0004144.name: obsolete Duplication of terminal index finger phalanx

HP:0004150.name: Abnormal 3rd finger morphology
HP:0004150.definition: An anomaly of the third finger.

HP:0004161.name: obsolete Periosteal new bone of middle finger phalanges

HP:0004162.name: obsolete Radially pointed middle finger phalanges

HP:0004168.name: obsolete Radially pointed proximal middle-finger phalanx

HP:0004172.name: Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger

HP:0004174.name: obsolete Accessory middle phalanx of middle finger

HP:0004175.name: obsolete Periosteal new bone of middle phalanx of middle-finger

HP:0004180.name: Short distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0004180.definition: Hypoplasia (congenital reduction in size) of the distal phalanx of the third finger.

HP:0004183.name: obsolete Abnormality of the epiphyses of the terminal phalanx of the middle finger

HP:0004184.name: obsolete Cone-shaped epiphysis of terminal phalanx of the middle finger

HP:0004185.name: obsolete Fused epiphysis of terminal phalanx of the middle finger

HP:0004186.name: obsolete Large epiphysis of terminal phalanx of the middle finger

HP:0004187.name: obsolete Prematurely fused epiphysis of terminal phalanx of the middle finger

HP:0004192.name: obsolete Bracket epiphyses of the 4th finger

HP:0004193.name: obsolete Expanded phalanges of the ring finger

HP:0004194.name: obsolete Hypoplastic phalanges of the ring finger

HP:0004195.name: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the 4th finger
HP:0004195.definition: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the 4th (ring) finger.

HP:0004196.name: obsolete Short phalanges of the ring finger

HP:0004197.name: Symphalangism of the 4th finger
HP:0004197.definition: Fusion of two or more bones of the 4th finger.

HP:0004198.name: obsolete Wide/broad phalanges of the ring finger

HP:0004201.name: obsolete Expanded proximal phalanx of the ring finger

HP:0004202.name: obsolete Lytic defects of the proximal phalanx of the ring finger

HP:0004203.name: obsolete Short proximal phalanx of the ring finger

HP:0004207.name: Abnormal 5th finger morphology
HP:0004207.definition: An abnormality affecting one or both 5th fingers.

HP:0004209.name: Clinodactyly of the 5th finger
HP:0004209.definition: Clinodactyly refers to a bending or curvature of the fifth finger in the radial direction (i.e., towards the 4th finger).

HP:0004213.name: Abnormal 5th finger phalanx morphology
HP:0004213.definition: Abnormality of the phalanges of the 5th (little) finger.

HP:0004216.name: Osteolytic defects of the phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0004216.definition: Dissolution or degeneration of bone tissue of the phalanges of the 5th finger.

HP:0004218.name: Symphalangism of the 5th finger
HP:0004218.definition: Fusion of two or more bones of the 5th finger.

HP:0004219.name: Abnormality of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger

HP:0004220.name: Short middle phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004220.definition: Hypoplastic/small middle phalanx of the fifth finger.

HP:0004222.name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004222.definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the little finger of the hand, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance. This epiphysis is located at the proximal end of the phalanx and is normally nearly flat. The related entity 'angel-shaped' epiphysis refers to a pronounced cone-shaped epiphysis in combination with a pseudoepiphysis at the distal end of the phalanx.

HP:0004223.name: Ivory epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004223.definition: Sclerosis of the epiphysis of the distal phalanx of the little finger, leading to an increased degree of radiopacity (white or ivory appearance) in X-rays.

HP:0004224.name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004224.definition: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the middle phalanx of the fifth finger. This epiphysis is located on the proximal end of the phalanx.

HP:0004225.name: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004225.definition: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the 5th (little) finger.

HP:0004226.name: Curved distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004226.definition: Curved appearance of the distal phalanx of the 5th (little) finger.

HP:0004227.name: Short distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0004227.definition: Hypoplastic/small distal phalanx of the fifth finger.

HP:0004230.name: Subluxation of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the little finger
HP:0004230.definition: A partial dislocation of the proximal interphalangeal joint of the little finger.

HP:0004231.name: Carpal bone aplasia
HP:0004231.definition: Congenital absence of a carpal bone.

HP:0004232.name: Accessory carpal bones
HP:0004232.definition: The presence of more than the normal number of carpal bones.

HP:0004233.name: Advanced ossification of carpal bones
HP:0004233.definition: Ossification of carpal bones at an abnormally early age.

HP:0004234.name: Bone-in-a-bone appearance of carpal bones
HP:0004234.definition: The bone-in-bone sign is a radiographic finding produced by increased sclerosis (abnormally dense bone) occurring intermittently with zones of relatively normal bone density. This term should be used to describe such a finding in the carpal bones.

HP:0004236.name: Irregular carpal bones
HP:0004236.definition: Carpal bones with irregular or fragmented margins.

HP:0004241.name: Stippled calcification in carpal bones
HP:0004241.definition: Point-shaped (punctate) calcifications affecting the carpal bones.

HP:0004243.name: Abnormal scaphoid morphology
HP:0004243.definition: Any structural anomaly of the scaphoid. The scaphoid is the largest bone of the proximal row of carpal bones. It is located on the same side as the thumb.

HP:0004244.name: Accessory scaphoid
HP:0004244.definition: Variations in the development of carpal bones are uncommon, with the scaphoid bone typically forming from the fusion of the os centrale carpi and the radial chondrification center during embryogenesis. A bipartite scaphoid is a rare congenital disorder that occurs when these ossification centers fail to fuse.

HP:0004246.name: Delayed ossification of the scaphoid
HP:0004246.definition: Formation of bone tissue of scaphoid is less than expected for age.

HP:0004248.name: Abnormal lunate bone morphology
HP:0004248.definition: Any structural anomaly of the lunate bone, which is located in the proximal row of carpal bones.

HP:0004251.name: Lunate-triquetral fusion
HP:0004251.definition: Osseous fusion of the lunate and triquetrum.

HP:0004252.name: Abnormal trapezium morphology
HP:0004252.definition: An anomaly of the trapezium, which is the carpal bone located at the base of the thumb.

HP:0004254.name: Delayed ossification of the trapezium
HP:0004254.definition: Formation of bone tissue of trapezium is less than expected for age.

HP:0004256.name: Abnormal trapezoid bone morphology
HP:0004256.definition: A structural anomaly of the trapezoid bone, which is the smallest bone in the distal row of carpal bones.

HP:0004257.name: Delayed ossification of the trapezoid bone
HP:0004257.definition: Formation of bone tissue of trapezoid is less than expected for age.

HP:0004259.name: Abnormal hamate bone morphology
HP:0004259.definition: A structural anomaly of the hamate bone, which is the ulnar-most bone located within the distal row of carpal bones, neighboured by the capitate bone radially.

HP:0004262.name: Abnormal capitate bone morphology
HP:0004262.definition: A structural anomaly of the capitate bone, which is the largest of the carpal bones in the human hand.

HP:0034882.name: Prostatic calculus
HP:0034882.definition: Calcium deposits in the prostate gland.

HP:0034883.name: Decreased portal vein velocity
HP:0034883.definition: A reduction in the velocity of portal venous flow, generally measured by Doppler ultrasound. Portal venous flow is normally towards the liver with peak systolic velocities in the range of 20-40 cm/s.

HP:0034884.name: Uterine cervix mass
HP:0034884.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the cervis of the uterus. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0034885.name: Abnormal urinary uromodulin level
HP:0034885.definition: The concentration of uromodulin (also known as Tamm Horsfall protein) in the urine, normalized for usine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

HP:0034886.name: Decreased urinary uromodulin level
HP:0034886.definition: The concentration of uromodulin (also known as Tamm Horsfall protein) in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034887.name: Increased urine phenylacetylglutamine level
HP:0034887.definition: The concentration of phenylacetylglutamine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034888.name: Decreased urine guanidinoacetic acid level
HP:0034888.definition: The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034889.name: Positive urine infectious agent nucleic acid test
HP:0034889.definition: Detection of DNA and RNA originating from an infectious agent (bacteria, viruses, parasites and fungi) in the urine.

HP:0034890.name: Positive CMV urine nucleic acid test
HP:0034890.definition: Detection of Cytomegalovirus (CMV) nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

HP:0034891.name: Positive Neisseria gonorrhoeae urine nucleic acid test
HP:0034891.definition: Detection of Neisseria gonorrhoeae nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

HP:0034892.name: Positive enterovirus urine nucleic acid test
HP:0034892.definition: Detection of enterovirus nucleic acid in the urine by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.

HP:0034893.name: Elevated brain glycine level by MRS
HP:0034893.definition: An increase in the level of glycine in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

HP:0034894.name: Elevated brain polyol compounds by MRS
HP:0034894.definition: An increase in the level of polyol compounds in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

HP:0034895.name: Elevated brain gamma-aminobutyric acid by MRS
HP:0034895.definition: An increase in the level of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) in the brain identified by magnetic resonance spectroscopy (MRS).

HP:0034896.name: History of recent anticoagulant ingestion
HP:0034896.definition: Medical history of ingestion of anticoagulants prior to presentation.

HP:0034897.name: Decreased circulating antidiuretic hormone concentration
HP:0034897.definition: Concentration of antidiuretic hormone, also known as vasopressin, is below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0034898.name: Elevated circulating growth hormone-releasing hormone concentration
HP:0034898.definition: Concentration of growth hormone-releasing hormone above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0034899.name: Abnormal amniotic fluid protein concentration
HP:0034899.definition: Any deviation of the concentration of a protein in the amniotic fluid from normal limits

HP:0034900.name: Decreased amniotic fluid alpha-fetoprotein concentration
HP:0034900.definition: Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the amniotic fluid below lower limit of normal.

HP:0034901.name: Increased circulating vitamin E concentration
HP:0034901.definition: Concentration of vitamin E in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034902.name: Abnormal circulating calcitonin concentration
HP:0034902.definition: Concentration of calcitonin, a 32-amino acid polypeptide hormone that is produced primarily by the parafollicular cells of the thyroid, in the blood circulation outside of normal limits.

HP:0034903.name: Decreased circulating calcitonin concentration
HP:0034903.definition: Concentration of calcitonin, a 32-amino acid polypeptide hormone that is produced primarily by the parafollicular cells of the thyroid, in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034904.name: Decreased circulating thyrotropin releasing hormone concentration
HP:0034904.definition: Concentration of thyrotropin releasing hormone below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0034905.name: Elevated circulating uroporphyrin concentration
HP:0034905.definition: Concentration of uroporphyrin in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034906.name: Increased urine pentacarboxylporphyrin level
HP:0034906.definition: Concentration of pentacarboxylporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034907.name: Increased urine hexacarboxylporphyrin level
HP:0034907.definition: Concentration of hexacarboxylporphyrin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034908.name: Increased circulating dehydroepiandrosterone concentration
HP:0034908.definition: Concentration of dehydroepiandrosterone in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034909.name: Increased erythrocyte coproporphyrin concentration
HP:0034909.definition: Concentration of coproporphyrin in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034910.name: Increased erythrocyte uroproporphyrin concentration
HP:0034910.definition: Concentration of uroproporphyrin in erythrocytes above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034911.name: Decreased circulating apolipoprotein E concentration
HP:0034911.definition: Concentration of apolipoprotein E below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034912.name: Elevated circulating apolipoprotein E concentration
HP:0034912.definition: Concentration of apolipoprotein E above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034913.name: Acrosomal hypoplasia
HP:0034913.definition: Reduction in the size of the acrosome of the head of spermatozoa.

HP:0034914.name: Oocyte maturation arrest
HP:0034914.definition: Oocyte maturation arrest (OMA) can manifest as failed in vitro fetilization/intracytoplasmic sperm injection (IVF/ICSI) attempts using affected oocytes.

HP:0034915.name: Abnormal anus morphology
HP:0034915.definition: A structural anomaly of the anus.

HP:0034916.name: Abnormal anus physiology
HP:0034916.definition: A functional anomaly of the anus.

HP:0034917.name: Weak anal sphincter tone
HP:0034917.definition: Reduced muscle tone of the sphincter of the anus.

HP:0034918.name: Reduced muscle 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase activity
HP:0034918.definition: Diminished activity of the enzyme 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase in muscle tissue.

HP:0034919.name: Reduced liver 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase activity
HP:0034919.definition: Diminished activity of the enzyme 2,4-dienoyl-CoA reductase in liver tissue.

HP:0034920.name: Nasal mucosa vasculitis
HP:0034920.definition: Inflammation of blood vessels in the mucosa of the nasal cavity.

HP:0034921.name: Pituitary blastoma
HP:0034921.definition: Pituitary blastoma is a distinctive anterior hypophyseal tumor of infants

HP:0034922.name: Peripheral axon spheroid formation
HP:0034922.definition: Axonal spheroids are bubble-like biological features that form on most degenerating axons.

HP:0034923.name: Reduced liver carboxylesterase 1 activity
HP:0034923.definition: Activity of the enzyme carboxylesterase 1 in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034924.name: Abnormal dermis morphology
HP:0034924.definition: A structural anomaly of the dermis, the layer of skin that lies beneath the epidermis and above the subcutaneous layer.

HP:0034925.name: Perivascular dermis hyaline deposition
HP:0034925.definition: Deposition of a largely amorphous hyaline (transparent and homogeneous) substance around blood vessels in the dermis layer of the skin.

HP:0034926.name: Perivascular small intestinal hyaline deposition
HP:0034926.definition: Deposition of a largely amorphous hyaline (transparent and homogeneous) substance around blood vessels in the wall of the small intestine.

HP:0034927.name: Large keratohyaline granules
HP:0034927.definition: Abnormally large keratohyalin granules (KHG). KHG are typically present in the stratum granulosum of the epidermal layer of the skin (and epithelium of the mucosae). KHG are protein structures found in the keratinocytes of the stratum granulosum.

HP:0034928.name: Decreased muscle lipoic acid content
HP:0034928.definition: Reduced amount of lipoic acid in muscle tissue.

HP:0034929.name: Reduced hepatic cystathionine gamma-lyase activity
HP:0034929.definition: Activity of cystathionine gamma-lyase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034930.name: Digestive system neoplasm
HP:0034930.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the digestive system.

HP:0034931.name: Lumbar spondylosis
HP:0034931.definition: Arthrosis, i.e., of degenerative joint disease, affecting the lumbar vertebral column.

HP:0034932.name: Decreased circulating acid maltase activity
HP:0034932.definition: Activity of the enzyme acid maltase (also known as alpha-1,4-glucosidase) below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034934.name: Abnormal circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
HP:0034934.definition: Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal.

HP:0034935.name: Decreased circulating 7-dehydrocholesterol concentration
HP:0034935.definition: Concentration of 7-dehydrocholesterol in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034936.name: Elevated circulating lathosterol concentration
HP:0034936.definition: Concentration of lathosterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034937.name: Elevated circulating desmosterol concentration
HP:0034937.definition: Concentration of desmosterol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034938.name: Decreased circulating sialic acid concentration
HP:0034938.definition: Concentration of sialic acid in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034939.name: Purulent synovial fluid
HP:0034939.definition: The synovial fluid (also known as synovia, i.e., the fluid found in the cavities of synovial joints) contains increased quantities of white blood cells.

HP:0034940.name: Muscle fiber calsequestrin 1-containing inclusion bodies
HP:0034940.definition: The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that demonstrate immunoreactivity for calsequestrin 1.

HP:0034941.name: Palatine myxoma
HP:0034941.definition: A myxoma (A benign tumor composed of myxomatous tissue composed of loosely-arranged spindle, polygonal, and stellate cells) localized to the palate. Clinically, such tumors may present as a sessile nodule on the hard palate.

HP:0034942.name: Vaginal myxoma
HP:0034942.definition: A myxoma (tumor of primitive connective tissue) localized in the vagina.

HP:0034943.name: Decreased dermal collagen
HP:0034943.definition: Abnormally reduced amount of collagen fibers in the dermis.

HP:0034944.name: Irregularly shaped keratohyaline granules
HP:0034944.definition: Abnormal shape of keratohyaline granules in dermal keratinocytes.

HP:0034945.name: Tubular shadows
HP:0034945.definition: Tubular shadows are characterized by a complete absence of cells in the testicular tubules, meaning that germ cells as well as somatic Sertoli cells are absent. The cells have been replaced by hyalinization.

HP:0034946.name: Multiple eyelid margin cysts
HP:0034946.definition: Presence of many apocrine hidrocystoma (cysts) on the margins of the eyelids.

HP:0034947.name: Altered location of the longitudinal column in the fibrous sheath
HP:0034947.definition: The fibrous sheath is a structure in the midpiece of the sperm flagellum surrounding the outer dense fibers. It comprises two longitudinal columns and transverse ribs. In case of altered location of the longitudinal column in the fibrous sheath the symmetrical structure is lost, most commonly with the columns not being opposite to each other, which can be visualized by electron microscopy.

HP:0034948.name: Uterine myxoma
HP:0034948.definition: A myxoma (tumor of primitive connective tissue) localized to the uterus.

HP:0034949.name: Uterine cervix myxoma
HP:0034949.definition: A myxoma (tumor of primitive connective tissue) localized to the the cervix of the uterus.

HP:0034950.name: Typified by complete penetrance
HP:0034950.definition: Penetrance describes the proportion of genotype positive individuals that develop disease given a lifespan of 80 years. For example, penetrance of Neurofibromatosis type 1 is close to 100%.

HP:0034951.name: Osteochondromyxoma
HP:0034951.definition: A rare benign chondroid and osteoid matrix-producing neoplasm of bone characterized by extensive myxoid changes. OMX originate from bony cortices and have been observed in the nasal region, as well as the tibia and radius.

HP:0034952.name: Gangliocytoma
HP:0034952.definition: A low-grade central nervous system tumor composed of dysplastic ganglion cells, usually presenting in children or young adults and located in the cerebral hemispheres.

HP:0034953.name: Duodenal gastrinoma
HP:0034953.definition: A gastrinoma, a neuroendocrine tumors characterized by the secretion of gastrin with resultant excessive gastric acid production, that is localized to the duodenum.

HP:0034955.name: Bone marrow eosinophilia
HP:0034955.definition: Count of eosinophils in the bone marrow above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034956.name: Exacerbated by lithium exposure
HP:0034956.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with lithium.

HP:0034957.name: Reduced hepatic glycogen debrancher enzyme activity
HP:0034957.definition: Activity of glycogen debrancher enzyme (also known as amylo-1,6-glucosydase, 4-alpha-glucantransferase) in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034958.name: Asymmetrical insertion of the midpiece into the head
HP:0034958.definition: Insertion of the neck and midpiece into the head of a spermatozoon on an axis that diverges from the midline axis of the spermatozoon head. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this defect is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034959.name: Bent sperm neck
HP:0034959.definition: Sharply angled insertion of the neck and midpiece into the head of a spermatozoon. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this feature is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034960.name: Elevated urine 3,6-epoxydicarboxylic acid level
HP:0034960.definition: The concentration of 3,6-epoxydicarboxylic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034961.name: Gallbladder biliary sludging
HP:0034961.definition: Presence of biliary sludge (a mixture of particulate solids that have precipitated from bile) in the gallbladder. Such sediment consists of cholesterol crystals, calcium bilirubinate pigment, and other calcium salts. Sludge is usually detected on transabdominal ultrasonography.

HP:0034962.name: Exacerbated by amiodarone exposure
HP:0034962.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with amiodarone.

HP:0034963.name: Ureteral mass
HP:0034963.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the ureter. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0034964.name: Wide cavum septum pellucidum
HP:0034964.definition: Width of the cavum septum pellucidum above the upper limit of normal, which is defined as a separation of greater than one cm of the leaves of the cavum septum pellucidum.

HP:0034965.name: Hypoplastic trochlear nerve
HP:0034965.definition: Underdevelopment of the trochlear nerve, which is the fourth cranial nerve and one of the ocular motor nerves that controls eye movement.

HP:0034966.name: Thymic cyst
HP:0034966.definition: A closed sac of tissue (cyst) located in the thymus. Thymic cysts are a rare, benign anomaly, are usually asymptomatic, and mostly occur in the anterior mediastinum .

HP:0034967.name: Uterine cyst
HP:0034967.definition: A closed sack of tissue (cyst) located in the uterus.

HP:0034968.name: Urinary bladder mass
HP:0034968.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the urinary bladder. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0034969.name: Endosteal scalloping
HP:0034969.definition: A series of indentations or erosions on a normally smooth margin of the inner layer of the cortex (i.e. the endosteum) of bones.

HP:0034970.name: Urinary bladder hamartoma
HP:0034970.definition: A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the urinary bladder.

HP:0034971.name: Peritoneal mass
HP:0034971.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the peritoneal cavity. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0034972.name: Fallopian tube mass
HP:0034972.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the Fallopian tube. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0034973.name: Aplasia of the pyramids of the medulla oblongata
HP:0034973.definition: Congenital absence of the pyramids, that is, of the paired structures located at the medial aspect of the ventral medulla that flank the anterior median fissure.

HP:0034974.name: Bathrocephaly
HP:0034974.definition: A deformity of the posterior skull with bulging of the midportion of the occipital bone that is often associated with a benign variant of the mendosal suture.

HP:0034975.name: Occipital horn
HP:0034975.definition: Downward pointing exostoses of the occipital bone situated in the tendinous insertions of the sternocleidomastoid and trapezius muscles.

HP:0034976.name: Absent pituitary stalk
HP:0034976.definition: A developmental defect characterized by failure to develop of the pituitary stalk. The pituitary stalk, also known as the infundibulum or infundibular stalk, is the connection between the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland.

HP:0034977.name: Abnormal pituitary stalk morphology
HP:0034977.definition: A structural anomaly of the pituitary stalk, also known as the infundibulum or infundibular stalk, is the connection between the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland.

HP:0034978.name: Interrupted pituitary stalk
HP:0034978.definition: A developmental defect characterized by a discontinuity of the pituitary stalk. The pituitary stalk, also known as the infundibulum or infundibular stalk, is the connection between the hypothalamus and the pituitary gland.

HP:0034979.name: Facial synkinesis
HP:0034979.definition: Unintentional movement in one area of the face produced during intentional movement of another area of the face.

HP:0034980.name: Synkinesis
HP:0034980.definition: Unintentional movement in one area of the body produced during intentional movement of another area of the body.

HP:0034982.name: Perianal anesthesia
HP:0034982.definition: Loss of sensation to the area of buttocks, perianal space and thighs.

HP:0034983.name: Failure of phenylephrine to induce blanching of eye redness
HP:0034983.definition: Instillation of 2.5% phenylephrine drops into the eye does not induce blanching of eye redness. Failure to blanch suggests redness caused by scleral vessel engorgement (e.g., scleritis) or extravascular cause (e.g., hemorrhage), not episcleritis or conjunctivitis.

HP:0034984.name: Fetal alcohol exposure
HP:0034984.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to ethanol (alcohol).

HP:0034985.name: Reduced cellular cobalamin uptake
HP:0034985.definition: Diminished ability of cells to transport cobalamine from the extracellular space to the cytoplasm.

HP:0034986.name: Focal necrotic brainstem lesion
