HP:0034986.definition: A localized area of cell death, often accompanied by infiltration of inflammatory cells, in the brainstem.

HP:0034987.name: Focal necrotic optic nerve lesion
HP:0034987.definition: A localized area of cell death, often accompanied by infiltration of inflammatory cells, in the optic nerve.

HP:0034988.name: Focal necrotic thalamus lesion
HP:0034988.definition: A localized area of cell death, often accompanied by infiltration of inflammatory cells, in the thalamus.

HP:0034989.name: Interstitial dermal edema
HP:0034989.definition: Accumulation of fluid in the interstitial spaces of the skin. This finding can be appreciated my microscopic examination of a skin biopsy.

HP:0034991.name: Shoulder external rotation contracture
HP:0034991.definition: A type of shoulder contracture characterized by decreased internal rotation of shoulder, that is, by a chronic reduction in active and passive ability to internally rotate the humerus at the shoulder joint (if the arm is flexed at the elbow, Internal rotation of the shoulder rotates the forearm towards the center of the body).

HP:0034992.name: Thumb adduction contracture
HP:0034992.definition: A type of thumb contracture characterized by a chronic reduction in active and passive ability of the metacarpal-phalangeal and/or interphalangeal joints of the thumb to bring from medial side to neutral position, where the neutral position for the thumb is when the distal and proximal segments of the thumb joint are in linear alignment.

HP:0034995.name: Reduced tissue fructose-1,6-bisphosphatase activity
HP:0034995.definition: Activity of fructose-1,6-bisphosphatase (EC 3.1.3.11) below the lower limit of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including liver and leukocytes.

HP:0034996.name: Reduced hepatic carbamoylphosphate synthetase 1 activity
HP:0034996.definition: Activity of carbamoylphosphate synthetase 1 in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034997.name: Reduced intraepidermal small nerve fiber density
HP:0034997.definition: Reduced number of small nerve fibers in the skin.

HP:0034998.name: Femoral artery duplication
HP:0034998.definition: A developmental defect characterized by the presence of a supernumerary femoral artery.

HP:0034999.name: Intracellular accumulation of collagen VII
HP:0034999.definition: Collagen VII is the major molecular constituent of anchoring fibrils in the skin. Collagen VII is synthesized as three identical pro-alpha1(VII) polypeptide chains, which are hydroxylated and glycosylated in a coordinated manner and then fold into triple-helical procollagen VII in the endoplasmic reticulum (ER). Mature collagen VII undergoes a multistep fibril polymerization process to form the anchoring fibrils. Mutant pro-alpha1(VII) polypeptide chains or procollagen VII molecules do not pass the ER quality control and are retained in the ER or designated for ubiquitin-proteasome degradation resulting in reduced amounts of collagen VII in the skin.

HP:0035000.name: Reduced reticular lamina anchoring fibril density
HP:0035000.definition: Diminished amount of the anchoring fibrils in the basement membrane zone that normally attach the epithelium to the basement membrane.

HP:0035001.name: Reduced lamina lucida anchoring filament density
HP:0035001.definition: Diminished amount of the anchoring filaments that normally bridge the lamina lucida and insert into the lamina densa in the cutaneous basement membrane zone.

HP:0035002.name: Reduced epidermal keratin 5 protein expression
HP:0035002.definition: Amount of keratin 5 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy.

HP:0035003.name: Reduced epidermal keratin 14 protein expression
HP:0035003.definition: Amount of keratin 14 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy.

HP:0035004.name: Reduced epidermal keratin protein expression
HP:0035004.definition: Amount of one or more keratins in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy.

HP:0035005.name: Reduced hepatic alanine-glyoxylate aminotransferase activity
HP:0035005.definition: Activity of alanine-glyoxylate aminotransferase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0035006.name: Hepatic sinusoidal dilatation
HP:0035006.definition: Presence of an increased amount of blood in the hepatic capillaries.

HP:0035007.name: Thin spermatozoon midpiece
HP:0035007.definition: The cross-sectional size (diameter) of the midpiece of the spermatozoon is below the lower limit of normal. This term applies if the proportion of spermatozoa with this defect is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035008.name: Thick spermatozoon midpiece insertion
HP:0035008.definition: Increased width of the midpiece of the spermatozoon. The midpiece is the structure that is located between the head and the flagella (tail) of the spermatozoon. This term applies if the width of the midpiece increases progressively from the flagella to the head and if the proportion of individual spermatozoa with this anomaly is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035009.name: Shoulder adduction contracture
HP:0035009.definition: A type of shoulder contracture characterized by a chronic reduction in the active and passive ability to abduct the shoulder. This results in the shoulders being closer to midline. The affected individual is not able to position the shoulders away from the body.

HP:0035010.name: Occupational exposure history
HP:0035010.definition: Exposure to a substance that results from the performance of an employee's duties.

HP:0035011.name: Occupational silver exposure
HP:0035011.definition: A history of exposure to silver that has occurred in relation to performance of job duties.

HP:0035012.name: Abnormal femoral artery morphology
HP:0035012.definition: Any structural abnormality of the femoral artey, a large blood vessel that provides oxygenated blood to lower extremity structures and in part to the lower anterior abdominal wall.

HP:0035014.name: Extrahepatic bile duct fibrosis
HP:0035014.definition: Accumulation of fibrous connective tissue (collagen) in the extrahepatic bile ducts.

HP:0035015.name: Elevated circulating short-chain acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035015.definition: Concentration of short-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Short chain acylcarnitines have between two and five carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C2-C5),

HP:0035016.name: Elevated circulating C4 acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035016.definition: Concentration of C4 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C4 acylcarnitines have a four-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035017.name: Elevated circulating medium-chain acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035017.definition: Concentration of medium-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Medium-chain acylcarnitines have between six and twelve carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C6-C12),

HP:0035018.name: Elevated circulating long-chain acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035018.definition: Concentration of long-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Long-chain acylcarnitines have between thirteen and twenty carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C13-C20),

HP:0035019.name: Elevated circulating C5 acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035019.definition: Concentration of C5 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C5 acylcarnitines have a five-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035020.name: Elevated circulating C18 acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035020.definition: Concentration of C18 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C18 acylcarnitines have a eighteen-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035021.name: Elevated circulating C16 acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035021.definition: Concentration of C16 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C16 acylcarnitines have a sixteen-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035022.name: Elevated circulating very long-chain acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035022.definition: Concentration of very long-chain acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acylcarnitines are classified according to the number of carbon atoms in the acyl-chain. Very long-chain acylcarnitines have twentyone or more carbon atoms in the acyl-chain (C21 and higher),

HP:0035023.name: Elevated circulating acetylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035023.definition: Concentration of acetylcarnitine (C2 acylcarnitine) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Acetylcarnitine has a two-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035024.name: Elevated circulating methylmalonylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035024.definition: Concentration of methylmalonylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035025.name: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyhexadecanoylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035025.definition: Concentration of 3-hydroxyhexadecanoylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035026.name: Elevated circulating C6 acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035026.definition: Concentration of C6 acylcarnitines in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. C6 acylcarnitines have a six-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035027.name: Elevated circulating methylglutarylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035027.definition: Concentration of methylglutarylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035028.name: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyisovalerylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035028.definition: Concentration of 3-hydroxyisovalerylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035029.name: Elevated circulating 3-hydroxyhexanoylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035029.definition: Concentration of 3-hydroxyhexanoylcarnitine (C6-OH) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035030.name: Elevated circulating carnitine concentration
HP:0035030.definition: Concentration of carnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035031.name: Elevated circulating tiglylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035031.definition: Concentration of tiglylcarnitine (C5:1) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0035032.name: Reduced circulating acetylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035032.definition: Concentration of acetylcarnitine (C2 acylcarnitine) in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. Acetylcarnitine has a two-carbon acyl chain.

HP:0035033.name: Reduced circulating octadecenoylcarnitine concentration
HP:0035033.definition: Concentration of octadecenoylcarnitine (C18:1 acylcarnitine) in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040007.name: Absent pigmentation of chest
HP:0040007.definition: Lack of skin pigmentation (coloring) of the chest.

HP:0040009.name: Hyperparakeratosis
HP:0040009.definition: Histological term to illustrate the combined presence of parakeratosis and hyperkeratosis. Abnormal keratinization of the epidermal stratum corneum (horny layer) with increased keratin formation and preservation of the nuclei in the superficial cells.

HP:0040012.name: Chromosome breakage
HP:0040012.definition: Elevated rate of chromosomal breakage or interchanges occurring either spontaneously or following exposure to various DNA-damaging agents. This feature may be assayed by treatment of cultured lymphocytes with agents such as chemical mutagens, irradiation, and alkylating agents.

HP:0040015.name: Increased activity of mitochondrial respiratory chain

HP:0040021.name: obsolete Radial deviation of the thumb

HP:0040033.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the fifth metatarsal bone

HP:0040034.name: Abnormality of the second metatarsal bone

HP:0040035.name: Abnormality of the fourth metatarsal bone

HP:0040040.name: Toenail onycholysis
HP:0040040.definition: Painless and spontaneous separation of a toenail from the nail bed.

HP:0040042.name: Aplasia of the eccrine sweat glands

HP:0040043.name: Hypoplasia of the eccrine sweat glands

HP:0040048.name: obsolete Aplasia of the left hemidiaphragm

HP:0040049.name: Macular edema
HP:0040049.definition: Thickening of the retina that takes place due to accumulation of fluid in the macula as a nonspecific response to blood-retinal barrier breakdown. Macular edema is a common pathological response to a wide variety of ocular insults, most commonly after intraocular (e.g. cataract) surgery or in association with retinal vascular (e.g. diabetic eye disease, retinal vein occlusion) or inflammatory (e.g. uveitis) disease.

HP:0040063.name: Decreased adipose tissue
HP:0040063.definition: The amount of adipose tissue (fat) in the body or a part of the body is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040065.name: obsolete Abnormal morphology of bones of the upper limbs

HP:0040066.name: obsolete Abnormal morphology of bones of the lower limbs

HP:0040071.name: Abnormal morphology of ulna
HP:0040071.definition: Any structural anomaly of the ulna, a bone of the forearm the extends from the elbow to the little finger.

HP:0040077.name: obsolete Abnormal concentration of calcium in blood

HP:0040081.name: Abnormal circulating creatine kinase concentration
HP:0040081.definition: Any deviation from the normal circulating creatine kinase concentration.

HP:0040082.name: Happy demeanor
HP:0040082.definition: A conspicuously happy disposition, characterized by frequent smiling and laughing, which may be contextually inappropriate or unrelated to the situation.

HP:0040083.name: obsolete Toe walking
HP:0040083.definition: Toe walking is a pattern of walking in which a person walks on balls of his or her feet, with no contact between the heels and ground. Toe-walking is common in children who are learning to walk, but most children outgrow it around the age of two years. This term refers to the persistence of toe-walking beyond the usual age.

HP:0040084.name: Abnormal circulating renin concentration
HP:0040084.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of renin in the blood, a central hormone in the control of blood pressure and various other physiological functions.

HP:0040087.name: Abnormal blood folate concentration
HP:0040087.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of folate in the blood circulation.

HP:0040088.name: Abnormal lymphocyte count
HP:0040088.definition: Any abnormality in the total number of lymphocytes in the blood.

HP:0040089.name: Abnormal total natural killer cell count
HP:0040089.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of total natural killer (NK) cells, commonly characterized as CD3-CD19- and CD16+ or CD56+ lymphocytes, in the blood, per microlitre, or altered NK cell phenotype, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group, measured ex vivo.

HP:0040090.name: Abnormal tympanic membrane morphology
HP:0040090.definition: Any structural abnormality of the tympanic membrane

HP:0040091.name: Asymmetry of the size of ears

HP:0040092.name: Asymmetry of the shape of the ears

HP:0040093.name: Asymmetry of the position of the ears

HP:0040095.name: Neoplasm of the outer ear
HP:0040095.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the outer ear.

HP:0040096.name: Neoplasm of the inner ear
HP:0040096.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the inner ear.

HP:0040097.name: Neoplasm of the ceruminal gland
HP:0040097.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ceruminal gland.

HP:0040101.name: Cutaneous atresia of the external auditory canal

HP:0040102.name: Osseous atresia of the external auditory canal

HP:0040103.name: Cutaneous stenosis of the external auditory canal

HP:0040104.name: Osseous stenosis of the external auditory canal

HP:0040114.name: Absence of the reflex of the tensor tympani muscle

HP:0040115.name: Abnormal Eustachian tube morphology
HP:0040115.definition: A structural anomaly of the Eustachian tube (ET). The ET is a biomechanical valve between the nasopharynx and the middle ear. Physiologically, it controls the passive adaptation of the middle ear air pressure to the ambient air pressure primarily via direct muscular actions of the soft palate. In the closed state it protects the middle ear. Inadequate function of the ET causes middle ear ventilation disorders.

HP:0040120.name: Abnormality of the reflex of the tensor tympani muscle

HP:0040121.name: Abnormality of the acoustic reflex
HP:0040121.definition: An abnormality in the reflexive contraction of the middle-ear muscles in response to sound stimulation.

HP:0040122.name: Impairment of the the acoustic reflex

HP:0040123.name: Impairment of the reflex of the tensor tympani muscle

HP:0040126.name: Abnormal circulating vitamin B12 concentration
HP:0040126.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of cobalamin (vitamin B12) in the blood. Vitamin B12 is one of the eight B vitamins.

HP:0040127.name: Abnormal sweat homeostasis
HP:0040127.definition: An abnormality of the composition of sweat or the levels of its components.

HP:0040130.name: Abnormal circulating iron concentration
HP:0040130.definition: The concentration of iron in the blood circulation is outside the limits of normal.

HP:0040133.name: Abnormal circulating ferritin concentration
HP:0040133.definition: A deviation from the normal circulating concentration of ferritin. Ferritin concentration can be measured in serum or plasma.

HP:0040135.name: Abnormal transferrin saturation
HP:0040135.definition: Any abnormality in the serum transferrin saturation, which is calculated by dividing the serum iron level by total iron-binding capacity.

HP:0040137.name: Comedonal acne
HP:0040137.definition: A type of acne in which open and closed comedones comprise the majority of the lesions, with substantially fewer papules and pustules.

HP:0040138.name: Mucinous histiocytosis
HP:0040138.definition: Multiple subcutaneous non-fragile and skin-coloured papules characterized by interstitial infiltrate of spindle and epithelioid histiocytes, and mucin. There are well circumscribed aggregates of epithelioid histiocytes and mucin in the upper and middle dermis,with the histiocytes arranged between collagen bundles and separated from the epidermis by a Grenz zone.

HP:0040139.name: Lipogranulomatosis
HP:0040139.definition: Yellow nodules of lipoid material are deposited in the skin and mucosae. This gives rise to granulomatous reactions.

HP:0040142.name: Reduced circulating 5-oxoprolinase activity
HP:0040142.definition: Activity or concentration of 5-oxoprolinase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme catalyzes the reaction 5-oxo-L-proline + ATP + 2 H(2)O = L-glutamate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.

HP:0040143.name: Dystopic os odontoideum
HP:0040143.definition: Os odontoideum is classified into two anatomic types (orthotopic and dystopic). Os odontoideum is defined as an ossicle that consists of smooth and separate caudal portions of the odontoid process. With orthotopic os odontoideum, the ossicle moves with the anterior arch of the atlas, while the dystopic type consists of an ossicle near the basion, or one that is fused with the clivus

HP:0040144.name: L-2-hydroxyglutaric aciduria
HP:0040144.definition: An increase in the level of L-2-hydroxyglutaric acid in the urine.

HP:0040148.name: Cortical myoclonus
HP:0040148.definition: Cortical myoclonus mainly affects the distal upper limbs and face, which reflects the largest cortical representations of these body areas. It is often focal, but may be multifocal, bilateral or generalized, as a consequence of intracortical and transcallosal spreading of abnormal activity. It typically occurs on voluntary action and may affect speech and gait. Cortical myoclonic jerks are stimulus sensitive, typically to touch, but sensitivity to visual stimuli is also described. Most patients with cortical myoclonus have both positive myoclonus and NM, occurring either independently or together as a complex of the two kinds of myoclonus. If cortical myoclonus is prolonged and lasts for hours, days or weeks, it is called epilepsia partials continua and is considered to be a rare form of focal epileptic status. Focal cortical myoclonus almost always points to an underlining lesion of the sensori-motor cortex, which produces hyperexcitability (e.g. vascular, inflammatory or neoplastic).

HP:0040149.name: Woolly scalp hair
HP:0040149.definition: The presence of wooly hair on the scalp. The term wooly hair refers to an abnormal variant of hair that is fine, with tightly coiled curls, and often hypopigmented. Optical microscopy may reveal the presence of tight spirals and a clear diameter reduction as compared with normal hair. Electron microscopy may show flat, oval hair shafts with reduced transversal diameter.

HP:0040154.name: Acne inversa
HP:0040154.definition: A chronic skin condition involving the inflammation of the apocrine sweat glands, forming pimple-like bumps known as abscesses.

HP:0040155.name: Elevated urinary 3-hydroxybutyric acid
HP:0040155.definition: An increased amount of 3-hydroxybutyric acid in the urine.

HP:0040156.name: Elevated urinary carboxylic acid
HP:0040156.definition: An increased amount of carboxylic acid in the urine.

HP:0040162.name: Orthokeratosis
HP:0040162.definition: Formation of an anuclear keratin layer

HP:0040174.name: Abnormality of extrinsic muscle of tongue

HP:0040175.name: Platelet-activating factor acetylhydrolase deficiency
HP:0040175.definition: Reduced level of platelet-activating factor acetylhydrolase.

HP:0040176.name: Abnormal circulating phospholipid concentration
HP:0040176.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a phospholipid in the blood circulation.

HP:0040181.name: Chapped lip
HP:0040181.definition: Cracking, fissuring, and peeling of the skin of the lips.

HP:0040182.name: Inappropriate sinus tachycardia
HP:0040182.definition: Inappropriate sinus tachycardia is a nonparoxysmal tachyarrhythmia characterized by an increased resting heart rate (HR) and/or an exaggerated HR response to minimal exertion or a change in body posture. HR is constantly above the physiological range with no appropriate relation to metabolic or physiological demands.

HP:0040186.name: Maculopapular exanthema
HP:0040186.definition: A skin rash that is characterized by diffuse cutaneous erythema with areas of skin elevation. It may evolve to vesicles or papules as part of a more severe clinical entity. Different degrees of angioedema with involvement of subcutaneous tissue may also appear.

HP:0040187.name: Neonatal sepsis
HP:0040187.definition: Systemic inflammatory response to infection in newborn babies.

HP:0040188.name: Osteochondrosis
HP:0040188.definition: Abnormal growth ossification centers in children. Initially a degeneration/ necrosis followed by regeneration or recalcification.

HP:0040189.name: Scaling skin
HP:0040189.definition: Refers to the loss of the outer layer of the epidermis in large, scale-like flakes.

HP:0040192.name: APUdoma
HP:0040192.definition: An endocrine tumor arising from an APUD cell.

HP:0040194.name: Increased head circumference
HP:0040194.definition: An abnormally increased head circumference in a growing child. Head circumference is measured with a nonelastic tape and comprises the distance from above the eyebrows and ears and around the back of the head. The measured HC is then plotted on an appropriate growth chart.

HP:0040195.name: Decreased head circumference
HP:0040195.definition: An abnormally reduced head circumference in a growing child. Head circumference is measured with a nonelastic tape and comprises the distance from above the eyebrows and ears and around the back of the head. The measured HC is then plotted on an appropriate growth chart. Microcephaly is defined as a head circumference (HC) that is great than two standard deviations below the mean of age- and gender-matched population based samples. Severe microcephaly is defined with an HC that is three standard deviations below the mean.

HP:0040196.name: Mild microcephaly
HP:0040196.definition: Decreased occipito-frontal (head) circumference (OFC). For the microcephaly OFC must be between -3 SD and -2 SD compared to appropriate, age matched, normal standards (i.e. -3 SD <= OFC < -2 SD).

HP:0040197.name: Encephalomalacia
HP:0040197.definition: Encephalomalacia is the softening or loss of brain tissue after cerebral infarction, cerebral ischemia, infection, craniocerebral trauma, or other injury.

HP:0040200.name: Motor impersistence
HP:0040200.definition: The inability to maintain postures or positions (such as keeping eyes closed, protruding the tongue, maintaining conjugate gaze steadily in a fixed direction, or making a prolonged 'ah' sound) without repeated prompts.

HP:0040201.name: Simultanapraxia
HP:0040201.definition: A subset of motor impersistence, defined as the inability to perform more than two of the simple voluntary acts simultaneously, such as closing the eyes and protruding the tongue.

HP:0040202.name: Abnormal consumption behavior
HP:0040202.definition: Recurrent abnormal consumption of food, liquids, or objects that could have negative consequences for the individual.

HP:0040203.name: Abnormal CSF neopterin concentration
HP:0040203.definition: Abnormal concentration of neopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0040204.name: Elevated CSF neopterin level
HP:0040204.definition: Increased concentration of neopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0040205.name: Decreased CSF neopterin level
HP:0040205.definition: Decreased concentration of neopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0040206.name: Abnormal circulating neopterin concentration
HP:0040206.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of neopterin in the blood circulation.

HP:0040207.name: Abnormal CSF pterin concentration
HP:0040207.definition: Abnormal concentration of a pterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0040208.name: Elevated CSF biopterin level
HP:0040208.definition: Concentration of biopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0040209.name: Decreased CSF biopterin level
HP:0040209.definition: Concentration of biopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040210.name: Abnormal circulating biopterin concentration
HP:0040210.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of biopterin in the blood circulation.

HP:0040211.name: Abnormal skin morphology of the palm
HP:0040211.definition: An abnormality of the skin of the palm, that is, the skin of the front of the hand.

HP:0040212.name: Risus sardonicus
HP:0040212.definition: Fixed sarcastic grimace and anxious expression. Caused by spasms of the masseter and other facial muscles.

HP:0040213.name: Hypopnea
HP:0040213.definition: Hypopnea is referring to breathing that is abnormally shallow.

HP:0040214.name: Abnormal circulating insulin concentration
HP:0040214.definition: An abnormal concentration of insulin in the body.

HP:0040216.name: Hypoinsulinemia
HP:0040216.definition: A decreased concentration of insulin in the blood.

HP:0040217.name: Elevated hemoglobin A1c
HP:0040217.definition: An increased concentration of hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c), which is the product of nonenzymatic attachment of a hexose molecule to the N-terminal amino acid of the hemoglobin molecule. This reaction is dependent on blood glucose concentration, and therefore reflects the mean glucose concentration over the previous 8 to 12 weeks. The HbA1c level provides a better indication of long-term glycemic control than one-time blood or urinary glucose measurements.

HP:0040218.name: Reduced total natural killer cell count
HP:0040218.definition: The absolute count of natural killer cells in the blood, per microlitre, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040219.name: Absent natural killer cells
HP:0040219.definition: Absence of detectable circulating NK cells, commonly characterized as CD3-CD19- and CD16+ or CD56+ lymphocytes, in the blood. Usually, less than 20 cells per microlitre is considered to be an absence.

HP:0040220.name: Abnormal size of the dental root

HP:0040222.name: Maternal thrombophilia
HP:0040222.definition: An increased tendency towards thrombosis in the mother during a pregnancy.

HP:0040223.name: Pulmonary hemorrhage
HP:0040223.definition: Pulmonary hemorrhage is a bleeding within the lungs. Older children and adults may spit blood or bloody sputum. Neonates, infants and young children usually do not spit up blood. Anemia, pulmonary infiltrates, increasingling bloody return on BAL and the presence of hemosiderin-laden macrophages in broncho-alveolar lavage (BAL) fluid or lung biopsy can diagnose lung bleeding. Alveolar macrophages contain phagocytosed red blood cells and stain positive for hemosiderin, a product of hemoglobin degradation, after about 48-72 hours following pulmonary hemorraghe. Previous or recurrent bleeding can thus be distinguished from fresh events. A differentiation into local or diffuse is of importance. Also differentiate if pulmonary hemorrhage is due to a primary lung disorder or a manifestation of a systemic disease.

HP:0040224.name: Abnormality of fibrinolysis
HP:0040224.definition: Clinical phenotype characterized by delayed bleeding accelerated break down of blood clot (fibrinolysis)

HP:0040225.name: Decrease in high molecular weight von Willebrand factor Multimers
HP:0040225.definition: A decrease in high molecular weight von Willebrand factor multimers.

HP:0040226.name: Decreased level of heparin co-factor II
HP:0040226.definition: An abnormality of coagulation related to a decreased concentration of heparin co-factor II

HP:0040227.name: Decreased level of histidine-rich glycoprotein
HP:0040227.definition: Decrease of these levels result in increased inhibition of fibrinolysis and reduced inhibition of coagulation

HP:0034546.name: Presence of uterus in 46,XY individual
HP:0034546.definition: A developmental anomaly in which an individual with an X chromosome and a Y chromosome (usually 46,XY) has a uterus. The uterus and Fallopian tubes are derived from the Müllerian duct and thus this phenotype is generally also associated with the presence of Fallopian tubes.

HP:0034547.name: Intraluminal meconium calcification
HP:0034547.definition: Deposition of calcium in meconium present in the internal cavity of the fetal bowel. This manifestation may be the result of any distal intestinal obstruction.

HP:0034548.name: Portal vein hypoplasia
HP:0034548.definition: A developmental defect characterized by underdevelopment of the portal vein.

HP:0034549.name: Adrenal leiomyoma
HP:0034549.definition: Adrenal leiomyoma is a rare, benign solid tumor that develops from the smooth muscle of the adrenal vein and its tributaries

HP:0034550.name: Small intestinal lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate
HP:0034550.definition: Infiltration of the wall of the small intestine by lymphocytes and mature plasma cells.

HP:0034551.name: Triggered by neuroleptic medication
HP:0034551.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to neuroleptic (also known as antipsychotic) medication.

HP:0034552.name: Abnormal peroxisomal morphology
HP:0034552.definition: Structural anomaly of peroxisomes, which are small, membrane-enclosed metabolic organelles with roles in the metabolism of complex lipids and reactive ionic species.

HP:0034553.name: Absence of peroxisomes
HP:0034553.definition: Lack of observable peroxisomes. This feature can be observed by immunohistochemical staining of cultured cells (such as fibroblasts) or by electronmicroscopy.

HP:0034554.name: Paucity of peroxisomes
HP:0034554.definition: Reduced number of observable peroxisomes per cell. This feature can be observed by immunohistochemical staining of cultured cells (such as fibroblasts) or by electronmicroscopy.

HP:0034555.name: Reduced sulfide:quinone oxidoreductase activity
HP:0034555.definition: Reduced activity of the enzyme sulfide:quinone oxidoreductase, which typically is measured in a biopsy specimen from liver or muscle.

HP:0034556.name: Deficit at segmental level
HP:0034556.definition: Refers to distribution of neurological deficits that corresponds to a deficit of a specific spinal segment and all segments below it.

HP:0034557.name: Rhabdoid tumor
HP:0034557.definition: Rhabdoid tumors are rare aggressive malignancies in infants and young children with a poor prognosis. The most common anatomic localizations are the central nervous system, the kidneys, and other soft tissues.

HP:0034558.name: Rhabdoid tumor of the ovary
HP:0034558.definition: A highly aggressive, extremely rare neoplasm of the ovary that is usually seen in children. The term rhabdoid is used because the tumor cells resemble rhabdomyoblasts but lack myogenic markers.

HP:0034559.name: Cardiac rhabdoid tumor
HP:0034559.definition: A rare and aggressive neoplasms developing mainly in the kidney but also in cerebral and extra-cerebral tissues and rarely in the heart. Histologically, rhabdoid renal and extrarenal tumors share common characteristics. The cells are polygonal, with eccentric, vesicular nuclei and prominent nucleoli, eosinophilic cytoplasmic inclusions. The tumors have an infiltrative growth pattern, necrosis, and high proliferative index. The immunohistochemistry tools of investigation facilitate differential diagnosis by showing loss of INI-1 expression, usually accompanied by germline mutations of the SMARCB1 gene. When INI-1 is still expressed in the affected tissues, a rhabdoid tumor with SMARCA4 mutations should be considered.

HP:0034560.name: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of the bladder
HP:0034560.definition: A rhabdoid tumor (a rare aggressive malignancies in infants and young children with a poor prognosis) originating in the urinary bladder.

HP:0034561.name: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of liver
HP:0034561.definition: A malginant rhabdoid tumor (MRT) originating in the liver. MRT are best characterized by the presence of round or polygonal cells with abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm, typical eosinophilic perinuclear inclusions, vesicular nuclei and prominent nucleoli. Immunohistochemical expression of vimentin and epithelial markers and lack of staining for S-100, myoglobin and desmin are commonly found, but are non-specific.

HP:0034562.name: Malignant rhabdoid tumor of muscle
HP:0034562.definition: A malginant rhabdoid tumor (MRT) originating in muscle tissue.

HP:0034563.name: Neck teratoma
HP:0034563.definition: A teratoma located in the neck.

HP:0034564.name: Kidney teratoma
HP:0034564.definition: A teratoma located in a kidney.

HP:0034565.name: Elevated urinary 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide-riboside level
HP:0034565.definition: Increased amount of 5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide(AICA)-riboside in the urine. AICA-riboside is the dephosphorylated counterpart of AICAR, an intermediate of de novo purine biosynthesis.

HP:0034566.name: Aplasia of posterior communicating artery
HP:0034566.definition: A developmental anomnaly characterized by the lack of development of the posterior communicating artery.

HP:0034567.name: Optic pit
HP:0034567.definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by congenital excavation of the optic nerve head.

HP:0034568.name: Ameliorated by naloxone
HP:0034568.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with naloxone, an opioid antagonist.

HP:0034569.name: Ameliorated by pyridoxal phosphate
HP:0034569.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingestion of pyridoxal phosphate (activated vitamin B6).

HP:0034570.name: Thickened intrahepatic portal venules
HP:0034570.definition: Increased width of the vascular wall of portal venules within the liver.

HP:0034571.name: Ovarian fibrosis
HP:0034571.definition: Excessive proliferation of fibroblasts and deposition of extracellular matrix within the ovary.

HP:0034572.name: Pigment incontinence
HP:0034572.definition: A process in which melanosomes (melanin granules) are deposited in the dermis. The dermal melanosomes are observed to be mainly in macrophages. This phenomenon of pigmentary incontinence usually follows an inflammatory process with the basic feature of basal cell damage, such as in lichen planus, lupus erythematosus, Riehl's melanosis, incontinentia pigmenti (Bloch-Sulzberger), and fixed drug eruption. Incontinence of pigment, or dropping off of epidermal melanin into the dermis, frequently produces a clinically recognizable and characteristic slate-gray pigmentation.

HP:0034574.name: Reduced epidermal keratin 10 protein expression
HP:0034574.definition: Amount of keratin 10 in the epidermis below the lower limit of normal. The findiong is typically ascertained by immunofluorescent microscopy.

HP:0034575.name: Reduced epidermal collagen IV protein expression

HP:0034576.name: Reduced epidermal bullous pemphigoid antigen 1 protein expression
HP:0034576.definition: Lower than normal amount of bullous pemphigoid antigen 1 (BP230) in the epidermis.

HP:0034577.name: Reduced epidermal collagen VII protein expression

HP:0034578.name: Reduced epidermal collagen XVII protein expression

HP:0034579.name: Reduced epidermal integrin alpha6beta4 protein expression

HP:0034581.name: Bloodstream Trypanosoma cruzi
HP:0034581.definition: Presence of Trypanosoma cruzi in the blood stream. Trypanosoma cruzii is the etiological agent of Chagas disease.

HP:0034582.name: Abnormal lymph node cell composition
HP:0034582.definition: A deviation from the normal distribution of cell types or their relative proportions in a lymph node.

HP:0034583.name: Lipid-laden lymph node macrophages
HP:0034583.definition: Lymph node with increased numbers of macrophages heavily laden with lipids.

HP:0034585.name: Cochlear nerve hypoplasia
HP:0034585.definition: A developmental defect characterized by underdevelopment of the cochlear nerve.

HP:0034586.name: Glutathionuria
HP:0034586.definition: Level of glutathione in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034587.name: Nevus psiloliparus
HP:0034587.definition: Nevus psiloliparus is a rare fatty tissue nevus that is a marker for encephalocraniocutaneous lipomatosis, a neurocutaneous syndrome with ocular and central nervous system anomalies. Clinically, nevus psiloliparus is often described as a congenital alopecia and appears as an irregularly shaped, circumscribed area of alopecia on the scalp. Histopathology demonstrates a near-complete absence of mature hair follicles with preservation of arrector pili muscles and mature adipocytes within the dermis.

HP:0034588.name: Crypt hyperplasia
HP:0034588.definition: Crypt hyperplasia denotes elongation of the length of the crypts of Lieberkuhn, a process that initially precedes villous atrophy. Elongation may be caused by expansion of the lamina propria as a result of the proliferation of stromal cells, an influx of inflammatory cells and tissue remodeling.

HP:0034589.name: Increased circulating dehydroepiandrosterone-sulfate concentration
HP:0034589.definition: Concentration of dehydroepiandrosterone-sulfate in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034590.name: Abnormal circulating thyroxine-binding globulin concentration
HP:0034590.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of thyroxine-binding globulin (TBG) in the blood circulation.

HP:0034591.name: Decreased circulating thyroxine-binding globulin concentration
HP:0034591.definition: A reduction from the normal concentration of thyroxine-binding globulin (TBG) in the blood circulation.

HP:0034592.name: Elevated circulating beta-aminoisobutyric acid concentration
HP:0034592.definition: An increased concentration of beta-aminoisobutyric acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0034593.name: Elevated circulating dihydrouracil concentration
HP:0034593.definition: An increased concentration of dihydrouracil in the blood circulation. Dihydrouracil is an intermediate in the catabolism of uracil that is also known as 5,6-dihydrouracil.

HP:0034594.name: Elevated circulating dihydrothymine concentration
HP:0034594.definition: An increased concentration of dihydrothymine in the blood circulation. Dihydrouracil is an intermediate in the catabolism of thymine.

HP:0034595.name: Elevated circulating N-carbamoyl-beta-alanine concentration
HP:0034595.definition: An increased concentrationof N-carbamoyl-beta-alanine in the blood circulation.

HP:0034596.name: Elevated ciculating 5-hydroxymethyluracil concentration
HP:0034596.definition: An increased concentration of 5-hydroxymethyluracil in the blood circulation.

HP:0034597.name: Decreased CSF creatinine concentration
HP:0034597.definition: Concentration of creatinine in the cerebrrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034598.name: Elevated urinary creatine level
HP:0034598.definition: An increased amount of creatine in the urine.

HP:0034599.name: Decreased circulating biotin concentration
HP:0034599.definition: Concentration of biotin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034600.name: Elevated circulating thrombopoietin concentration
HP:0034600.definition: Concentration of thrombopoietin in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. Thrombopoietin is a glycoprotein hormone produced by the liver and kidney that stimulates the production and differentiation of megakaryocytes.

HP:0034601.name: Decreased circulating C1q concentration
HP:0034601.definition: Concentration or activity of the C1q protein in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal. C1q is the first component of the classical pathway and is composed of the C1qA chain, C1qB chain, and C1qC chain, which are encoded by C1qA, C1qB, and C1qC genes.

HP:0034602.name: Decreased circulating apolipoprotein A-II concentration
HP:0034602.definition: Concentration of apolipoprotein A-II below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034603.name: Elevated circulating CA19-9 concentration
HP:0034603.definition: Concentration of CA19-9 above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034604.name: Elevated circulating DOPA concentration
HP:0034604.definition: Concentration of DOPA (3,4-dihydroxyphenylalanine) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034605.name: Elevated CSF DOPA concentration
HP:0034605.definition: Concentration of DOPA (3,4-dihydroxyphenylalanine) in the cerebrospinal fluid above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034606.name: Elevated circulating porphyrin concentration
HP:0034606.definition: Concentration of porphyrins or of a specific porphryin above the upper limit of normal. The most commonly tested circulating porphyrins are coproporphyrin, protoporphyrin, and uroporphyrin. Normally protoporphyrin is present in the highest concentration.

HP:0034607.name: Decreased circulating 17-hydroxyprogesterone concentration
HP:0034607.definition: Concentration of 17-hydroxyprogesterone in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034608.name: Decreased circulating transcobalamin II concentration
HP:0034608.definition: Concentration of transcobalamin II in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034609.name: Polychromasia
HP:0034609.definition: Increased variation in the color of the erythrocytes (red blood cells), including pale red, normal or dark colors, indicating a highly variable hemoglobin concentration. Typically this indicates the release of immature erythrocytes in states of anemia.

HP:0034610.name: Decreased circulating myo-inositol concentration
HP:0034610.definition: Concentration of myo-inositol in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034611.name: Elevated circulating arabinitol concentration
HP:0034611.definition: Concentration of arabinitol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034612.name: Elevated urine arabitol level
HP:0034612.definition: Amount of arabitol in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034613.name: Elevated urine erythritol level
HP:0034613.definition: Amount of erythritol in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034614.name: Elevated circulating erythritol concentration
HP:0034614.definition: Concentration of erythritol in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034615.name: Reduced circulating matrix metalloproteinase 2 concentration
HP:0034615.definition: Concentration of matrix metalloproteinase 2 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034616.name: Abnormal circulating coenzyme concentration
HP:0034616.definition: Concentration of a coenzyme (an organic molecule that binds to the active sites of an enzyme to promote the catalysis of a reaction) is above or below the limits of normal.

HP:0034617.name: Elevated circulating S-adenosyl methionine concentration
HP:0034617.definition: Concentration of S-adenosyl methionine (SAM) in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal. SAM is a cosubstrate involved in methyl group transfers, transsulfuration, and aminopropylation.

HP:0034618.name: Abnormal circulating membrane cofactor protein concentration
HP:0034618.definition: Concentration of membrane cofactor protein in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal. Membrane cofactor protein (MCP, CD46) is a cell surface complement regulatory protein which acts as a cofactor for the factor I-mediated cleavage of the activated complement components C3b/C4b.

HP:0034619.name: Decreased circulating membrane cofactor protein concentration
HP:0034619.definition: Concentration of membrane cofactor protein in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034620.name: Elevated circulating membrane cofactor protein concentration
HP:0034620.definition: Concentration of membrane cofactor protein in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034621.name: Hepatic xanthomatosis
HP:0034621.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the liver. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034622.name: Adrenal xanthomatosis
HP:0034622.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the adrenal gland. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034623.name: Splenic xanthomatosis
HP:0034623.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the spleen. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034624.name: Spinal cord xanthomatosis
HP:0034624.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the spinal cord. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034625.name: Brain xanthomatosis
HP:0034625.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the brain. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034626.name: Pulmonary xanthomatosis
HP:0034626.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the lung. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034627.name: Bone marrow xanthomatosis
HP:0034627.definition: Lipid deposits localized within the bone marrow. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034628.name: Lymph node xanthomatosis
HP:0034628.definition: Lipid deposits localized within one or more lymph nodes. Xanthomas are benign but are often an important visible sign of systemic conditions such as familial hypercholesterolemia.

HP:0034629.name: Xanthoma of bone
HP:0034629.definition: Xanthoma of bone is an exceedingly rare benign primary bone tumor histologically characterized by mononuclear macrophage-like cells, abundant foam cells, and multinucleated giant cells.

HP:0034630.name: Ameliorated by folinic acid
HP:0034630.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with folinic acid.

HP:0034631.name: Triggered by succinylcholine anesthetic
HP:0034631.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a succinylcholine anesthetic such as suxamethonium.

HP:0034632.name: Exogenous androgen exposure
HP:0034632.definition: History of having been treated with an exogenous androgen medication.

HP:0034633.name: Reduced muscle enolase activity
HP:0034633.definition: Diminished activity of the enzyme enolase in muscle tissue. The enzyme enolase catalyzes the interconversion of 2-phosphoglycerate and phosphoenolpyruvate. In adult human muscle, over 90% of enolase activity is accounted for by the beta-enolase subunit, the protein product of the ENO3 gene.

HP:0034634.name: Dopamine antagonist exposure
HP:0034634.definition: History of having been treated with a dopamine antagonist including metaclopramide, phenothiazine; haloperidol, chlorpromazine, promethazine, prochlorperazine, ziprasidone, and quetiapine.

HP:0034635.name: Muscle fiber granulofilamentous inclusion bodies
HP:0034635.definition: The presence of inclusion bodies within the cytoplasm of muscle cells that contain a mxiture of granules and filaments.

HP:0034636.name: Bone marrow myeloid vacuolization
HP:0034636.definition: Formation of vacuoles (a space within a cell that is empty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in the cytoplasm of myeloid precursors in the bone marrow.

HP:0034637.name: Pulmonary cylindroma
HP:0034637.definition: A cylindroma located in the lung. Cylindromas are well-circumscribed, smooth, pale pink nodular tumors, often with arborizing vessels visible. The tumors are slow growing and vary in size from a few millimeters to over 5 mm.

HP:0034638.name: Colonic fibrinopurulent exudate
HP:0034638.definition: Fluid visible on the colonic surface containing fibrin, inflammatory cells, and cellular debris.

HP:0034639.name: Bloodstream microfilaria
HP:0034639.definition: Presence of filaria in the blood stream. Filariasis is a common cause of elephantiasis in Coastal Districts of India. The initial manifestations are repeated episodes of fever with chills and rigor, lymphadenopathy which gradually progress to elephantiasis. In India filarial infestation is commonly caused by W. bancrofti and Brugia malayi, the former responsible for almost 98 percent of all cases.

HP:0034640.name: Skin infectious agent
HP:0034640.definition: The presence of an infectious agent in the skin.

HP:0034641.name: Dermal microfilaria
HP:0034641.definition: Presence of filariae in the skin.

HP:0034642.name: Dermal papillary IgA deposition
HP:0034642.definition: Accumulation of immunoglobulin A (IgA) surrounding dermal papillae, which are specialized cells that support the hair follicle.

HP:0034643.name: Dermal immune complex deposition
HP:0034643.definition: Accumulation of antigen-bound antibody in the skin.

HP:0034644.name: Abnormal liver metabolite concentration
HP:0034644.definition: The concentration of a metabolite in the liver is above or below the limits of normal.

HP:0034645.name: Hepatic polyglucosan accumulation
HP:0034645.definition: Intracellular accumulation of polyglucosan bodies-containing amylopectinlike polysaccharide-in the liver.

HP:0034646.name: Urinary bladder neurofibroma
HP:0034646.definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) located in the urinary bladder.

HP:0034647.name: Synovial granuloma
HP:0034647.definition: An aggregation of macrophages (forming in response to chronic inflammation) localized in the lining of a joint (synovium).

HP:0034648.name: Elevated urine fumaric acid level
HP:0034648.definition: The concentration of fumaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034649.name: Elevated urine N-acetylaspartic acid level
HP:0034649.definition: The amount of N-acetylaspartate in the urine, when corrected for urine concentration, is above upper limit of normal. This feature can be measured using gas chromatography-mass spectrometry.

HP:0034650.name: Elevated urine suberylglycine level
HP:0034650.definition: Level of suberylglycine in urine above upper limit of normal.

HP:0034651.name: Elevated urine phenylpropionylglycine level
HP:0034651.definition: Level of phenylpropionylglycine in urine above upper limit of normal.

HP:0034652.name: Elevated urine octenedioic acid level
HP:0034652.definition: The concentration of octenedioic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034653.name: Monocarboxylic aciduria
HP:0034653.definition: Level of a monocarboxylic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal. A monocarboxylic acid is an oxoacid containing one carboxy group.

HP:0034654.name: Elevated urine octanoic acid level
HP:0034654.definition: Amount of octanoic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034655.name: Elevated urine glutaconic acid level
HP:0034655.definition: The concentration of glutaconic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034656.name: Elevated urine 3-hydroxyglutaric level
HP:0034656.definition: The concentration of 3-hydroxyglutaric acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034657.name: Elevated urine malonic acid level
HP:0034657.definition: The concentration of malonic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034658.name: Elevated urine propionylglycine level
HP:0034658.definition: Amount of propionylglycine in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034659.name: Elevated urine tiglylglycine level
HP:0034659.definition: Amount of tiglylglycine in the urine above upper limit of normal.

HP:0034660.name: Elevated urine 2-methylacetoacetic acid level
HP:0034660.definition: Amount of 2-methylacetoacetic acid in the urine above upper limit of normal.

HP:0034661.name: Elevated urine 3-hydroxypropionic acid level
HP:0034661.definition: Amount of 3-hydroxypropionic acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034662.name: Elevated urine 2-methylcitric acid level
HP:0034662.definition: Amount of 2-methylcitric acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034663.name: Elevated urine 4-hydroxyisovaleric acid level
HP:0034663.definition: Amount of 4-hydroxyisovaleric acid in urine above upper limit of normal.

HP:0034664.name: Elevated urine 2-hydroxy-3-methylvaleric acid level
HP:0034664.definition: Amount of 2-hydroxy-3-methylvaleric acid in the urine above the upper limit of normal. 2-Hydroxy-3-methylpentanoic acid or 2-hydroxy-3-methylvaleric acid (HMVA) is an organic acid generated by L-isoleucine metabolism.

HP:0034665.name: Shoulder contracture
HP:0034665.definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the shoulder joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

HP:0034666.name: Shoulder extension contracture
HP:0034666.definition: Lack of the full expected passive range of flexion of the shoulder joint (Shoulder flexion puts the arms from a resting position at one's sides to straight above the head; thus, with shoulder extension contracture it is not possible to raise the arms above the head fully).

HP:0034667.name: Thumb extension contracture
HP:0034667.definition: Movement in the sagittal plane that increases the angle of the thumb joint (straightens the joint); motion involving posterior bending of the vertebral column or returning to the upright position from a flexed position.

HP:0034668.name: Tongue myxoma
HP:0034668.definition: A myxoma (benign soft tissue neoplasm characterized by the presence of spindle and stellate cells, lobulated growth pattern, and myxoid stroma formation) localized in the tongue.

HP:0034669.name: Abnormal knee morphology
HP:0034669.definition: A structural abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures.

HP:0034670.name: Abnormal knee physiology
HP:0034670.definition: A functional anomaly of the knee joint.

HP:0034671.name: Knee contracture
HP:0034671.definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of the knee joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

HP:0034672.name: Knee extension contracture
HP:0034672.definition: A type of knee joint contracture in which the knee lacks full expected flexion, such that the upper and lower leg cannot be brought together.

HP:0034673.name: Abnormal ankle morphology
HP:0034673.definition: A structural anomaly of the ankle.

HP:0034674.name: Abnormal ankle physiology
HP:0034674.definition: A functional anomaly of the ankle.

HP:0034675.name: Toe joint contracture
HP:0034675.definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of a toe joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

HP:0034676.name: Extension contracture of toe
HP:0034676.definition: A type of toe joint contracture in which the joint lacks full expected flexion, so that the two bony segments on either side of their connecting joint cannot be brought together.

HP:0034681.name: Finger joint contracture
HP:0034681.definition: Lack of full passive range of motion (restrictions in flexion, extension, or other movements) of a finger joint resulting from structural changes of non-bony tissues, such as muscles, tendons, ligaments, joint capsules and/or skin.

HP:0034682.name: Extension contracture of finger
HP:0034682.definition: A type of finger joint contracture in which the joint lacks full expected flexion, so that the two bony segments on either side of their connecting joint cannot be brought together.

HP:0034683.name: Reduced muscle telethonin level
HP:0034683.definition: Amount of telethonin protein expression in muscle tissue below lower limit of normal. Telethonin is a 19-kDa sarcomeric protein, localized to the Z-disc of skeletal and cardiac muscles.

HP:0034684.name: Abnormal enzyme concentration or activity
HP:0034684.definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal.

HP:0034685.name: Abnormal liver enzyme activity or concentration
HP:0034685.definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in liver tissue.

HP:0034686.name: Reduced hepatic urocanase activity
HP:0034686.definition: Activity of urocanase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034687.name: Impaired cerebroside sulfate hydrolysis
HP:0034687.definition: Reduced hydrolysis (splitting of a bond and the addition of the hydrogen anion of water) of the sulfuric ester linkage in the molecule of cerebroside sulfate, possibly leading to accumuation of cerebroside sulfate.

HP:0034688.name: Reduced peroxisomal glutaryl-CoA oxidase activity
HP:0034688.definition: Diminished enzyme activity of peroxisomal glutaryl-CoA oxidase, an enzyme that metabolizes glutaryl-CoA (a metabolite of L-lysine, L-hydroxy-lysine and L-tryptophan) by dehydrogenation to glutaconyl-CoA directly followed by decarboxylation of this to crotonyl-CoA.

HP:0034689.name: Reduced sterol 27-hydroxylase activity
HP:0034689.definition: Diminished activity of the enzyme sterol 27-hydroxylase, which participates in the degradation of cholesterol to bile acid. Sterol 27-hydroxylase catalyzes the first step in the normal oxidation of the steroid side chain, converting cholesterol, as well as different 7a-hydroxylated cholesterol metabolites, to 27-oxygenated steroids.

HP:0034690.name: Reduced short-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
HP:0034690.definition: Diminished activity of the enzyme Short-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase (SCAD), a key enzyme of fatty acid beta-oxidation that catalyzes the first step in mitochondrial beta-oxidation of fatty acids.

HP:0034691.name: Reduced 3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase activity
HP:0034691.definition: Diminished activity of the enzyme 3-phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase (PGDH), which catalyzes the first step in the pathway by converting D-3-phosphoglycerate (PGA), an intermediate in glycolysis, to phosphohydroxypyruvate concomitant with the reduction of NAD+.

HP:0034693.name: Reduced hepatic methionine adenosyltransferase activity
HP:0034693.definition: Activity of methionine adenosyltransferase in the liver below the lower limit of normal. Note that there are multiple methionine adenosyltransferase isoezymes.

HP:0034694.name: Substantia nigra dopaminergic neuron loss
HP:0034694.definition: Degeneration and loss of neurons in the substantia nigra of the brain.

HP:0034696.name: Intramuscular lipoma
HP:0034696.definition: A lipoma that is located within a muscle.

HP:0034697.name: Cutaneous telangiectasia
HP:0034697.definition: Dilated blood vessels on the skin.

HP:0034698.name: Abnormal aromatase activity
HP:0034698.definition: Aromatase activity outside of the normal range.

HP:0034699.name: Elevated aromatase activity
HP:0034699.definition: Enzyme activity of aromatase above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034700.name: Reduced aromatase activity
HP:0034700.definition: Enzyme activity of aromatase below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034701.name: Corneal amyloidosis
HP:0034701.definition: A form of amyloidosis that is located in the cornea.

HP:0034702.name: Abnormal keratinocyte morphology
HP:0034702.definition: Any structural anomaly of the keratinocyte. The keratinocyte is the major cell type of the epidermis and is responsible for generating the protective barrier.

HP:0034703.name: Keratinocyte vacuolization
HP:0034703.definition: Increased number of vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles that areempty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in keratinocytes.

HP:0034704.name: Parotid gland adenocarcinoma
HP:0034704.definition: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the parotid gland.

HP:0034705.name: Pulmonary vasculitis
HP:0034705.definition: Cellular inflammation, vessel destruction, and tissue necrosis of the blood vessels of the lung.

HP:0034706.name: Reduced hepatic D-glycerate kinase activity
HP:0034706.definition: Activity of D-glycerate kinase in the liver below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034707.name: Lymph-node hemophagocytosis
HP:0034707.definition: Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages in a lymph node.

HP:0034708.name: Superior pubic ramus hypoplasia
HP:0034708.definition: Underdevelopment of the upper branch of the pubis bone (inferior pubic ramus).

HP:0034709.name: Uterine adenofibroma
HP:0034709.definition: A rare benign mullerian mixed tumor of the uterus composed of benign epithelial and mesenchymal components.

HP:0034710.name: Pulmonary hamartoma
HP:0034710.definition: A benign malformation of the lung that includes an abnormal mixture of tissue components such as cartilage, epithelium, fat, or muscle which are common to the lung but without preservation of the organ architecture.

HP:0034711.name: Peripheral axonal distension
HP:0034711.definition: An abnormal histological finding characterized by an increase in the cross-section area of peripheral nerve axons (up to 20-25 micrometers in diameter).

HP:0034712.name: Decreased circulating alpha-mannosidase activity
HP:0034712.definition: Concentration or activity of alpha mannosidase below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0034713.name: Abnormal hepatocyte morphology
HP:0034713.definition: A structural anomaly of the hepatocyte, which is the main cell type that makes up the liver perncyhma. Hepatocytes are usually binucleated and appear as sheets in the liver tissue.

HP:0034714.name: Hepatic melanin-like lysosomal pigmentation
HP:0034714.definition: Accumulation of dark, coarsely granular pigment localized in lysosomes of centrilobular hepatocytes.

HP:0034715.name: Reduced uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase activity
HP:0034715.definition: Activity of the enzyme uroporphyrinogen decarboxylase (UROD; EC 4.1.1.37) below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034716.name: Reduced heme oxygenase activity
HP:0034716.definition: Activity of the enzyme heme oxygenase below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034717.name: Swollen achromatic neurons in the cerebral cortex
HP:0034717.definition: The presence of enlarged and swollen neurons that lack Nissl bodies (the rough endoplasmic reticulum-achromasia refers to neurons that lack Nissl bodies) in the cortex of the brain.

HP:0034718.name: Vacuolated hepatocytes
HP:0034718.definition: Presence of vacuoles (membrane-bound organelles that areempty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in hepatocytes, which normally rarely contain vacuoles.

HP:0034719.name: Lack of oocyte pronucleus formation
HP:0034719.definition: An abnormality of oocyte maturation characterized by the inability of oocytes to form pronuclei after in vitro fertilization procedures. Oocytes normally show two pronuclei 17 to 20 hours after in vitro insemination.

HP:0034720.name: Self-healing squamous epithelioma
HP:0034720.definition: A type of skin tumor that initially presents as a reddish macule and subsequently becomes papular, enlarged, ulcerated and ultimately heals leaving pitted scars.

HP:0034721.name: Elevated circulating pristanic acid concentration
HP:0034721.definition: Concentration of pristanic acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034722.name: Sarcoplasmic bodies
HP:0034722.definition: Rounded or oval structures that appeared brown on hematoxylin and eosin and red on the modified Gomori trichrome stain.

HP:0034724.name: Reduced CSF cystine concentration
HP:0034724.definition: Concentration of cystine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal. Cystine is sulfur-containing amino acid obtained by the oxidation of two cysteine molecules which are then linked via a disulfide bond.

HP:0034725.name: Abnormal circulating beta-mannosidase activity
HP:0034725.definition: Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase outside normal limits. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides.

HP:0034726.name: Elevated circulating beta-mannosidase activity
HP:0034726.definition: Activity of the enzyme beta-mannosidase above the upper limit of normal. Beta-mannosidase is a lysosomal enzyme that catabolizes oligosaccharides.

HP:0034727.name: Reduced circulating alpha-L-fucosidase activity
HP:0034727.definition: Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034728.name: Abnormal circulating alpha-L-fucosidase activity
HP:0034728.definition: Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase in the blood circulation outside the limits of normal.

HP:0034729.name: Elevated circulating alpha-L-fucosidase activity
HP:0034729.definition: Activity of the enzyme alpha-L-fucosidase above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034730.name: Elevated circulating S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine concentration
HP:0034730.definition: Increased concentration of S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine in the blood circulation.

HP:0034731.name: Elevated circulating S-adenosyl-L-methionine concentration
HP:0034731.definition: Concentration S-adenosyl-L-methionine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034732.name: Exercise-triggered malignant hyperthermia
HP:0034732.definition: Malignant hyperthermia that is characterized by exercise-induced life-threatening hyperthermia with a body temperature over 40 degrees C and signs of encephalopathy ranging from confusion to convulsions or coma. Incidence increases with rising ambient temperature and relative humidity. Manifestations may include rhabdomyolysis (presenting with myalgia, muscle weakness, and myoglobinuria), tachycardia, and in severe cases multiorgan failure.

HP:0034733.name: Anesthesic-triggered malignant hyperthermia
HP:0034733.definition: Malignant hyperthermia that is characterized by a rapid increase in temperature to 39-42 degrees C in response to inhalational anesthetics such as halothane or to muscle relaxants such as succinylcholine.

HP:0034734.name: Elevated CSF argininosuccinic acid concentration
HP:0034734.definition: Concentration of argininosuccinic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034735.name: Elevated CSF aspartylglucosamine concentration
HP:0034735.definition: Concentration of aspartylglucosamine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034736.name: Elevated circulating alpha-oxoadipic acid concentration
HP:0034736.definition: Concentration of alpha-oxoadipic acid in the blood above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034737.name: Abnormal erythrocyte metabolite concentration
HP:0034737.definition: A deviation from the normal range of a metabolite in red blood cells.

HP:0034738.name: Reduced erythrocyte glutathione concentration
HP:0034738.definition: Concentration of glutathione in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. Glutathione (GSH) is an important redox active biomolecule critical in the maintenance and regulation of cellular and organismal health.

HP:0034739.name: Elevated CSF sarcosine concentration
HP:0034739.definition: Concentration of sarcosine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034740.name: Reduced CSF methionine concentration
HP:0034740.definition: Concentration of methionine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034741.name: Elevated circulating homoarginine concentration
HP:0034741.definition: Concentration of homoarginine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034742.name: Elevated urinary formiminoglutamic acid level
HP:0034742.definition: The concentration of formiminoglutamic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034743.name: Elevated CSF proline concentration
HP:0034743.definition: Concentration of proline in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034744.name: Elevated urinary S-sulfocysteine level
HP:0034744.definition: Level of S-sulfocysteine high in urine above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034745.name: Elevated circulating S-sulfocysteine concentration
HP:0034745.definition: Concentration of S-sulfocysteine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034746.name: Sertoli cell hyperplasia
HP:0034746.definition: Abnormal increase in the number of Sertoli cells in the testis.

HP:0034747.name: CSF infectious agent
HP:0034747.definition: The presence of an infectious agent in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0034748.name: CSF mycobacteria
HP:0034748.definition: Mycobacterium present in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF). This feature can be ascertained by CSF microscopy.

HP:0034749.name: Fungal bloodstream infection
HP:0034749.definition: Detection of a fungal organism (such as candida or coccidioides) in the blood stream.

HP:0034750.name: Supraclavicular lymphadenopathy
HP:0034750.definition: Enlarged lymph node located just above the clavicle (collarbone).

HP:0034751.name: Inguinal lymphadenopathy
HP:0034751.definition: Enlarged lymph node located in the inguinal region (groin).

HP:0034752.name: Axillary lymphadenopathy
HP:0034752.definition: Enlarged lymph node located in the axillary region (armpit).

HP:0034753.name: Positive Murphy sign
HP:0034753.definition: Murphy's sign is elicited in patients with acute cholecystitis by asking the patient to take in and hold a deep breath while palpating the subcostal region. In practice, Murphy's sign is performed by palpating the subcostal region during inspiration. If pain is elicited and the patient suddenly stops their inspiratory effort, a positive Murphy's sign has been elicited.

HP:0034754.name: Bilious emesis
HP:0034754.definition: Vomiting whereby the vomit has the color of bile, yellowish-green.

HP:0034755.name: Ameliorated by NSAID
HP:0034755.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID).

HP:0034756.name: Fetal exposure history
HP:0034756.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to a medication or other substance.

HP:0034757.name: Fetal barbiturate exposure
HP:0034757.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to barbiturate medications such as phenobarbital. Barbiturates are used medically as anxiolytics, hypnotics, and anticonvulsants.

HP:0034758.name: Fetal narcotic exposure
HP:0034758.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to narcotic medications such as morphine or codeine. Narcotics are used medically to treat moderate or severe pain.

HP:0034759.name: Ameliorated by ethosuximide
HP:0034759.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of ethosuximide. Ethosuximide is most often used to treat absence seizures.

HP:0034760.name: Reduced epidermal extracellular matrix protein 1 protein expression
HP:0034760.definition: Lower than normal amount of extracellular matrix protein 1 (ECM1) in the epidermis.

HP:0034761.name: Neurofibroma by anatomical location
HP:0034761.definition: Neurofibroma categorized according to the anatomical site of origin.

HP:0034762.name: Tongue neurofibroma
HP:0034762.definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the tongue.

HP:0034763.name: Cardiac neurofibroma
HP:0034763.definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the heart.

HP:0034764.name: Gastric neurofibroma
HP:0034764.definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the stomach.

HP:0034765.name: Renal neurofibroma
HP:0034765.definition: A neurofibroma (benign peripheral nerve sheath tumor) localized in the kidney.

HP:0034766.name: Muscle fiber polyglucosan inclusion bodies
HP:0034766.definition: Accumulation of a poorly branched and poorly spherical amylopectin-like glycogen (polyglucosan) in muscle fibers.

HP:0034767.name: Abnormal rete ridge morphology
HP:0034767.definition: Abnormal structure of the rete ridges (also known as rete pegs), which are downward projections of epithelium surrounding the connective tissue papillae in between the dermal papillae.

HP:0034768.name: Rete ridge elongation
HP:0034768.definition: Increased length of the rete rdiges of the epidermis.

HP:0034769.name: Pulmonary Langerhans cell histiocytosis
HP:0034769.definition: Accumulation of monoclonal CD1a-positive Langerhans cells in the bronchioles and alveolar interstitium that can cause damage to the lungs.

HP:0034770.name: Lumbar hypolordosis
HP:0034770.definition: Flattening of a curve in the spine in the lumbar (lower back) region.

HP:0034771.name: Battle sign
HP:0034771.definition: Battle sign is bruising over the mastoid process that is typically the result of head trauma. It is retroauricular or mastoid ecchymosis that is typically the result of head trauma. Battle sign typically requires significant head trauma and may indicate significant internal injury to the brain and not just the posterior cranial vault or mastoid.

HP:0034772.name: Decreased skull base length
HP:0034772.definition: Reduced anterioposterior dimension of the skull base.

HP:0034773.name: Oscillopsia
HP:0034773.definition: A visual disturbance in which objects in the visual field appear to oscillate (jump, jiggle, vibrate).

HP:0034774.name: Decreased blink rate
HP:0034774.definition: The frequency with which the eye is blinked is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034775.name: Abnormal blink rate
HP:0034775.definition: A deviation from the normal frequency of blinking the eye.

HP:0034776.name: Elevated blink rate
HP:0034776.definition: The frequecy with which the eye is blinked is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034778.name: Maternal hyperthyroidism
HP:0034778.definition: The mother of a fetus or index patient has a history of hyperthyroidism during the corresponding pregnancy.

HP:0034779.name: Perineal
HP:0034779.definition: Applies to an abnormality that affects the perineum (the region of skin between the genitals and the anus).

HP:0034780.name: Gadolinium exposure
HP:0034780.definition: History of exposure to gadolinium, a contrast medium often used for magnetic resonance imaging.

HP:0034781.name: Purulent parotid gland drainage
HP:0034781.definition: Excretion of pus (purulent discharge) from the opening of the parotid duct.

HP:0034782.name: Obstipation
HP:0034782.definition: Obstipation is the inability to pass either stool or flatus (gas).

HP:0034784.name: Vasculitis by anatomical site
HP:0034784.definition: Vasculitis categorized according to the anatomical site where the finding is localized.

HP:0034785.name: Vasculitis by histology
HP:0034785.definition: Vasculitis categorized according to type of histological abnormality.

HP:0034786.name: Leukocytoclastic vasculitis
HP:0034786.definition: A type of vasculitis characterized by the presence of debris of neutrophils within the blood vessel walls.

HP:0034787.name: Accumulation of lipid droplets in small-bowel enterocytes

HP:0034788.name: Pericardial friction rub
HP:0034788.definition: A pericardial friction rub is a grating, to-and-fro sound that occurs in phase with the heart sounds.

HP:0034790.name: Abnormal muscle succinate dehydrogenase staining
HP:0034790.definition: Any deviation from the normal amount of staining of succinate dehydrogenase in skeletal muscle tissue.

HP:0034793.name: Small intestinal hamartoma
HP:0034793.definition: A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the small intestine.

HP:0034794.name: Pyriform sperm head
HP:0034794.definition: Pyriform spermatozoa consist of a normally shaped acrosomal structure which can be normal in size or enlarged, while the post-acrosomal region shows severe elongation and an acute narrowing to the posterior end, ending in about the same thickness as the connecting mid-piece.

HP:0034795.name: Excess residual spermatozoal cytoplasm
HP:0034795.definition: Excess residual cytoplasm is associated with abnormal spermatozoa produced from a defective spermiation process. This abnormal excess cytoplasm should not be confused with more physiological cytoplasmic residues that can be observed in direct microscopy of the ejaculate but not in dried, fixed and stained morphology smears.

HP:0034796.name: Cardiomyocyte hyaline bodies
HP:0034796.definition: Subsarcolemmal, eosinophilic glass-like regions within the cytoplasm of cardiomyocytes.

HP:0034797.name: Hepatic hemophagocytosis
HP:0034797.definition: Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the liver.

HP:0034798.name: CSF hemophagocytosis
HP:0034798.definition: Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

HP:0034799.name: Splenic hemophagocytosis
