HP:0034799.definition: Phagocytosis of erythrocytes, lymphocytes or other hematopoietic precursors by histiocytes or macrophages observed in the spleen.

HP:0034800.name: Urinary bladder granulomatosis
HP:0034800.definition: The presence of multiple granulomas in the urinary bladder as based on pathological examination. Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes.

HP:0034801.name: Epidermal necrosis
HP:0034801.definition: Death of keratinocytes in the epidermis layer of the skin, which generally manifests as extensive exfoliation (separation of the epidermis from the underlying dermis).

HP:0034802.name: Exacerbated by flexion
HP:0034802.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is aggravated by (or made more painful by) bending of a limb or joint.

HP:0034803.name: Hemolacria
HP:0034803.definition: The presence of blood in tears.

HP:0034804.name: Corneal foreign body sensation
HP:0034804.definition: A perception that an object is in contact with the eye.

HP:0034805.name: Buttock pain
HP:0034805.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the buttock (round fleshy area at the lower rear area of a human trunk).

HP:0034806.name: Vaginal foreign body sensation
HP:0034806.definition: A perception that an object located in the vagina.

HP:0034807.name: Paroxysmal nocturnal dyspnea
HP:0034807.definition: Attacks of breathlessness that occur at night and may awaken the sleeping patient.

HP:0034808.name: Eyelid pain
HP:0034808.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the eyelid.

HP:0034809.name: Abnormal sperm physiology
HP:0034809.definition: Abnormality of a sperm function including protection of paternal DNA, traversing the female reproductive tract, oocyte localisation, penetration of the zona pellucida, oocyte activation and centriole deposition.

HP:0034810.name: Small acrosomal area
HP:0034810.definition: Reduction in size of the acrosome below the lower limit of normal. The acrosome is a unique membranous organelle located over the anterior part of the sperm nucleus. According to the World Health Organization criteria, the acrosome must be clearly visible, comprising approximately 40-70 percent of the sperm head.

HP:0034811.name: Bent sperm flagella
HP:0034811.definition: The proportion of sperm cells whose flagella is sharply curved or has a sharp angle is above normal limits.

HP:0034812.name: Spermiation failure
HP:0034812.definition: Spermiation failure is indicated by apparently normal spermiogenesis, but the presence of retained Sd2 spermatids in stages III-V of human spermatogenesis, whereas maturation arrest is indicated by a lack of late Sd1 and Sd2 spermatids in the epithelium.

HP:0034813.name: Hypospermatogenesis
HP:0034813.definition: A morphological abnormality visible upon biopsy of the germinal epithelium of the testis in which the cellularity of the germinal epithelium is reduced in general, so that all stages of germ cells (spermatogonia, spermatocytes, and spermatids) are present but reduced in number. This term applies to biopsies with some tubules showing diminished amounts of qualitatively complete spermatogenesis in combination with a vast majority of tubules that lack germ cells.

HP:0034814.name: Conjunctival membrane
HP:0034814.definition: Formation of a sheet of tissue by coagulum of exudate over the conjunctiva of the eye that if removed leaves behind a denuded bleeding surface.

HP:0034815.name: Extreme oligozoospermia
HP:0034815.definition: A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than zero but less than 2 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than zero but less than one million sperm per milliliter.

HP:0034816.name: Mild oligozoospermia
HP:0034816.definition: A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than 30 but less than 39 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than 10 but less than 15 million sperm per milliliter.

HP:0034817.name: Moderate oligozoospermia
HP:0034817.definition: A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than 10 but less than 29 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than 5 but less than 10 million sperm per milliliter.

HP:0034818.name: Severe oligozoospermia
HP:0034818.definition: A type of oligozoospermia characterized by a total number of more than 2 but less than 10 million sperm in the ejaculate or a concentration of more than 1 but less than 5 million sperm per milliliter.

HP:0034819.name: Iris nodule
HP:0034819.definition: The presence of a nodule (small rounded lump of tissue) in the iris.

HP:0034820.name: Koeppe nodules
HP:0034820.definition: A type of iris nodule consisting of inflammatory cell precipitates which lie at the pupillary margin.

HP:0034821.name: Bussaca nodules
HP:0034821.definition: A type of iris nodule consisting of inflammatory cell precipitates which lie on the iris surface.

HP:0034823.name: Decreased CSF copper concentration
HP:0034823.definition: Concentration of copper in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034824.name: Diffuse pulmonary lymphoid hyperplasia
HP:0034824.definition: Diffuse lymphoid hyperplasia (DLH) describes the pathological entity that lies between follicular bronchiolitis and lymphocytic interstitial pneumonia (LIP). It is pathologically characterized by a diffuse peribronchiolar proliferation of hyperplastic lymphoid follicles (BALT), extended along the lymphatics to involve the interlobular septa and pleura. Unlike LIP, DHL does not show uniform involvement of the alveolar septa.

HP:0034825.name: Ameliorated by steroid medication
HP:0034825.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by treatment with a steroid medication such as prednisone.

HP:0034827.name: Triggered by levothyroxin exposure
HP:0034827.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by administration of levothyroxin (thyroid hormone).

HP:0034828.name: Reduced muscle laminin alpha-2 chain staining
HP:0034828.definition: A decreased amount of laminin alpha-2 chain in muscle tissue. This feature can be shown by immunohistochemistry or Western blotting of muscle tissue.

HP:0034829.name: Adrenal cortical sclerosis
HP:0034829.definition: Abnormal thickening of of the outer layer (cortex) of the adrenal gland due to fibrosis.

HP:0034830.name: Reduced hepatic fructose-1,6-phosphate aldolase activity
HP:0034830.definition: Concentration or activity of fructose 1,6-bisphosphate aldolase in liver tissue below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034831.name: Pancreatic hamartoma
HP:0034831.definition: A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the pancreas.

HP:0034832.name: Liver angiomyolipoma
HP:0034832.definition: A benign liver neoplasm composed of fat, vascular, and smooth muscle elements.

HP:0034833.name: Cardiac lipoma
HP:0034833.definition: A lipoma that is located within a the heart.

HP:0034834.name: Peripheral nerve polyglucosan inclusion bodies
HP:0034834.definition: Accumulation of a poorly branched and poorly spherical amylopectin-like glycogen (polyglucosan) in peripheral nerve fibers.

HP:0034835.name: Cardiac polyglucosan accumulation
HP:0034835.definition: Accumulation of a poorly branched and poorly spherical amylopectin-like glycogen (polyglucosan) in myocardial tissue.

HP:0034836.name: Cystic nephroma
HP:0034836.definition: A benign cystic neoplasm of the kidney.

HP:0034837.name: Absent dermal elastic fibers
HP:0034837.definition: Elastic fibers not demonstrable in skin biopsy.

HP:0034838.name: Cleavage at junction of stratum corneum and stratum granulosum
HP:0034838.definition: Splitting of the skin (cell-cell adhesion of keratinocytes) localized to the interface between the stratum corneum and stratum granulosum layers of the epidermis.

HP:0034839.name: Lymphoid hyperplasia
HP:0034839.definition: An abnormal bone marrow finding characterized by many poorly circumscribed and occasionally confluent lymphoid nodules. The nodules contain small and uniform lymphocytes with rounded nuclei, clumped chromatin, and without prominent nucleoli.

HP:0034840.name: Absence of epidermal lamellar bodies
HP:0034840.definition: Lack of lamellar bodies (LBs) inthe epidermis. LBs are specialized organelles that contain pro-barrier lipids imparting a fully lamellar internal structure, but also other cargoes such as enzymes (lipid metabolizing and proteolytic), enzyme inhibitors, and antimicrobial peptides.

HP:0034841.name: Gastrointestinal granulomatosis
HP:0034841.definition: The presence of multiple granulomas in the gastrointestinal tract (Pylorus, esophagus, jejunum, ileum, cecum, rectum, perirectal area, esophagus) as based on pathological examination. Granulomas are small 0.5 to 2 mm collections of modified macrophages called epithelioid cells usually surrounded by lymphocytes.

HP:0034842.name: Enlarged sperm head vacuole
HP:0034842.definition: Increased size of sperm vacuoles, which are surface concavities typically located at the the tip or middle area of sperm heads. According to the WHO Laboratory Manual for the Examination and Processing of Human Semen, sperm head vacuoles are considered abnormal when exceeding 20% of the cross-sectional area of the head. Vacuoles are found in almost all samples with normal sperm morphology; this term applies if the proportion of sperm with abnormally large vacuoles is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0034843.name: Ureteral hamartoma
HP:0034843.definition: A benign (noncancerous) tumorlike malformation made up of an abnormal mixture of cells and tissues that originates in the ureter.

HP:0034844.name: Fetal methimazole exposure
HP:0034844.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to methimazole.

HP:0034845.name: Fetal procarbazine exposure
HP:0034845.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to procarbazine.

HP:0034846.name: Fetal fluorouracil exposure
HP:0034846.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to fluorouracil.

HP:0034847.name: Fetal cytarabine exposure
HP:0034847.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to cytarabine.

HP:0034848.name: Fetal tetracycline exposure
HP:0034848.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to tetracycline.

HP:0034849.name: Fetal quinine exposure
HP:0034849.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to quinine.

HP:0034850.name: Fetal cyclophosphamide exposure
HP:0034850.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to cyclophosphamide.

HP:0034851.name: Fetal metronidazole exposure
HP:0034851.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to metronidazole.

HP:0034852.name: Fetal phenobarbital exposure
HP:0034852.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to phenobarbital.

HP:0034853.name: Fetal phenytoin exposure
HP:0034853.definition: A history of exposure during pregnancy of the mother of a fetus or child to phenytoin.

HP:0034854.name: Periumbilical
HP:0034854.definition: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are located at or near the umbilicus (belly button).

HP:0034855.name: Maternal obesity during pregnancy
HP:0034855.definition: A history of obesity, which can be defined as a body mass index of 30 or greater, in the mother of a fetus or index patient.

HP:0034856.name: Maternal amniocentesis
HP:0034856.definition: A history of amniocentesis having been performed in the mother of a fetus or index patient.

HP:0034857.name: Typified by highly variable age of onset
HP:0034857.definition: Description of conditions in which age of onset is highly variable even in family members who share the same disease-associated variant or variants.

HP:0034858.name: Abnormal leukocyte enzyme concentration or activity
HP:0034858.definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme as measured in leukocytes is above or below the limits of normal.

HP:0034859.name: Reduced tissue beta-glucuronidase activity
HP:0034859.definition: Concentration or activity of beta-glucuronidase (EC 3.2.1.31) below the lower limit of normal. FECH enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including cultured fibroblasts and leukocytes.

HP:0034860.name: Reduced leukocyte alpha-L-fucosidase activity
HP:0034860.definition: Concentration or activity of an alpha-L-fucosidase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

HP:0034861.name: Reduced leukocyte arylsulfatase B activity
HP:0034861.definition: Concentration or activity of an arylsulfatase B as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

HP:0034862.name: Reduced leukocyte steroid sulfatase activity
HP:0034862.definition: Concentration or activity of an arylsulfatase C as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

HP:0034863.name: Reduced leukocyte arylsulfatase A activity
HP:0034863.definition: Concentration or activity of the lysosomal enzyme arylsulfatase A (EC 3.1.6.8) as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

HP:0034864.name: Decreased alpha-galactosidase A activity
HP:0034864.definition: Activity of the enzyme alpha-galactosidase below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034865.name: Positive fecal parasite test
HP:0034865.definition: Demonstration of parasite in stool specimen, e.g., Parasites present on wet mount of stool.e

HP:0034866.name: Positive stool infectious agent test
HP:0034866.definition: Any kind of test for an infectious agent in stool positive.

HP:0034867.name: Positive stool giardia antigen
HP:0034867.definition: Test for giardia antigen in stool such as immune assay or DFA positive.

HP:0034868.name: Entamoeba histolytica antibody positive in stool
HP:0034868.definition: Demonstration of antibody directed against Entamoeba histolytica in stool.

HP:0034869.name: Reduced erythrocyte free porphyrin concentration
HP:0034869.definition: Concentration of porphyrin in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034870.name: Reduced circulating urocanic acid concentration
HP:0034870.definition: The concentration of urocanic acid in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034871.name: Decreased urinary epinephrine level
HP:0034871.definition: The concentration of epinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034872.name: Decreased CSF epinephrine concentration
HP:0034872.definition: Concentration of epinephrine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034873.name: Decreased circulating epinephrine concentration
HP:0034873.definition: Concentration of epinephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034874.name: Decreased circulating norepinephrine concentration
HP:0034874.definition: Concentration of norepinephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034875.name: Decreased urinary norepinephrine level
HP:0034875.definition: The concentration of norepinephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034876.name: Decreased urinary metaepinephrine level
HP:0034876.definition: The concentration of metanephrine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034877.name: Decreased CSF metanephrine concentration
HP:0034877.definition: Concentration of metanephrine in the cerebrospinal fluid below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034878.name: Decreased circulating metanephrine concentration
HP:0034878.definition: Concentration of metanephrin in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0034879.name: Ovarian mass
HP:0034879.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the ovary. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0034880.name: Adrenal mass
HP:0034880.definition: A swelling or enlargement localized to the adrenal gland. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

HP:0009895.name: Abnormality of the crus of the helix
HP:0009895.definition: An abnormality of the crus of the helix, which is the horizontal piece of cartilage located outside the ear canal that divides the upper and lower parts of the ear.

HP:0009896.name: Abnormal antitragus morphology
HP:0009896.definition: An abnormality of the antitragus, which is a small tubercle opposite to the tragus of the ear. The antitragus and the tragus are separated by the intertragic notch.

HP:0009897.name: Horizontal crus of helix
HP:0009897.definition: An abnormal horizontal axis orientation of the crus of the helix. That is, the main axis of the crus of the helix is perpendicular to the medial longitudinal axis of the ear, instead of sloping inferoposteriorly.

HP:0009898.name: Underdeveloped crus of the helix
HP:0009898.definition: Developmental hypoplasia of the crus of the helix. That is, flatter and/or shorter crus helix than average.

HP:0009899.name: Prominent crus of helix
HP:0009899.definition: The presence of an abnormally prominent of the crus of the helix. That is, development of the crus helix to the same degree as an average antihelix stem or helix.

HP:0009900.name: Unilateral deafness
HP:0009900.definition: A unilateral absence of sensory perception of sound.

HP:0009901.name: Crumpled ear
HP:0009901.definition: Distortion of the course of the normal folds of the ear and the appearance of supernumerary crura and folds.

HP:0009902.name: Cleft helix
HP:0009902.definition: A notched form of the helix of the ear. That is, a defect in the continuity of the helix, which may occur at any point along its length.

HP:0009903.name: Conjunctival nodule
HP:0009903.definition: Presence of nodules in the conjunctiva of the eye.

HP:0009905.name: Thin ear helix
HP:0009905.definition: Decreased thickness of the helix of the ear.

HP:0009906.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the earlobes
HP:0009906.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the ear lobes.

HP:0009907.name: Attached earlobe
HP:0009907.definition: Attachment of the lobe to the side of the face at the lowest point of the lobe without curving upward.

HP:0009908.name: Anterior creases of earlobe
HP:0009908.definition: Sharply demarcated, typically linear and approximately horizontal, indentations in the outer surface of the ear lobe.

HP:0009909.name: Uplifted earlobe
HP:0009909.definition: An abnormal orientation of the earlobes such that they point out- and upward. That is, the lateral surface of ear lobe faces superiorly.

HP:0009910.name: Aplasia of the middle ear ossicles
HP:0009910.definition: Absence of the middle ear ossicles, malleus, incus, and stapes.

HP:0009911.name: Abnormal temporal bone morphology
HP:0009911.definition: Abnormality of the temporal bone of the skull, which is situated at the sides and base of the skull roughly underlying the region of the face known as the temple.

HP:0009913.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the tragus
HP:0009913.definition: Aplasia or developmental hypoplasia of the tragus.

HP:0009914.name: Cyclopia
HP:0009914.definition: Cyclopia is a congenital abnormality in which there is only one eye. That eye is centrally placed in the area normally occupied by the root of the nose.

HP:0009915.name: Corneal asymmetry
HP:0009915.definition: The presence of a size difference between the left and right cornea.

HP:0009916.name: Anisocoria
HP:0009916.definition: Anisocoria, or unequal pupil size, may represent a benign physiologic variant or a manifestation of disease.

HP:0009917.name: Persistent pupillary membrane
HP:0009917.definition: The presence of remnants of a fetal membrane that persist as strands of tissue crossing the pupil.

HP:0009918.name: Ectopia pupillae
HP:0009918.definition: A malposition of the pupil owing to a developmental defect of the iris.

HP:0009919.name: Retinoblastoma
HP:0009919.definition: A tumor of the eye originating from cells of the retina.

HP:0009920.name: Nevus of Ota
HP:0009920.definition: A dermal melanocytic hamartoma that presents as bluish hyperpigmentation on the face along the first or second branches of the trigeminal nerve. Nevus of Ota may involve the sclera.

HP:0009921.name: Duane anomaly
HP:0009921.definition: A condition associated with a limitation of the horizontal ocular movement with retraction of the globe and narrowing of the palpebral fissure on adduction

HP:0009922.name: Vascular remnant arising from the disk
HP:0009922.definition: Persistence of the hyaloid artery, which is the embryonic artery that runs from the optic disc to the posterior lens capsule may persist; the site of attachment may form an opacity. The hyaloid artery is a branch of the ophthalmic artery, and usually regresses completely before birth.

HP:0009924.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving the nose
HP:0009924.definition: Underdevelopment or absence of the nose or parts thereof.

HP:0009926.name: Epiphora
HP:0009926.definition: Abnormally increased lacrimation, that is, excessive tearing (watering eye).

HP:0009927.name: Aplasia of the nose
HP:0009927.definition: Complete absence of all nasal structures.

HP:0009928.name: Thick nasal alae
HP:0009928.definition: Increase in bulk of the ala nasi.

HP:0009929.name: Abnormal columella morphology
HP:0009929.definition: A structural abnormality of the columella.

HP:0009930.name: Asymmetry of the nares
HP:0009930.definition: Asymmetry or size difference between the left and right nostril.

HP:0009932.name: Single naris
HP:0009932.definition: The presence of only a single nostril.

HP:0009933.name: Narrow naris
HP:0009933.definition: Slender, slit-like aperture of the nostril.

HP:0009934.name: Supernumerary naris
HP:0009934.definition: The presence of more than two nostrils.

HP:0009935.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the nasal septum
HP:0009935.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the nasal septum.

HP:0009938.name: Sunken cheeks
HP:0009938.definition: Lack or loss of the soft tissues between the zygomata and mandible.

HP:0009940.name: Asymmetry of the mandible
HP:0009940.definition: Lack of symmetry between the left and right mandible.

HP:0009941.name: Asymmetry of the mouth
HP:0009941.definition: The presence of an asymmetric mouth.

HP:0009942.name: Duplication of thumb phalanx
HP:0009942.definition: Complete or partial duplication of the phalanges of the thumb. Depending on the severity, the appearance on x-ray can vary from a notched phalanx (the duplicated bone is almost completely fused with the phalanx), a partially fused appearance of the two bones (bifid), two separate bones appearing side to side, or completely duplicated phalanges (proximal and distal phalanx of the thumb and/or 1st metacarpal). In contrast to the phalanges of the digits 2-5 (proximal, middle and distal), the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits.

HP:0009943.name: Complete duplication of thumb phalanx
HP:0009943.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the thumb. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0009944.name: Partial duplication of thumb phalanx
HP:0009944.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the thumb. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0009945.name: Duplication of phalanx of 2nd finger
HP:0009945.definition: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0009947.name: Duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009947.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the second proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009948.name: Duplication of the distal phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009948.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the distal phalanx of index finger.

HP:0009949.name: Duplication of the middle phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009949.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the middle phalanx of index finger.

HP:0009950.name: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009950.definition: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of index finger.

HP:0009951.name: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009951.definition: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of index finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009952.name: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009952.definition: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of index finger.

HP:0009953.name: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009953.definition: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of index finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009954.name: Complete duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009954.definition: Complete duplication of the second proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009955.name: Partial duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 2nd finger
HP:0009955.definition: Partial duplication of the second proximal phalanx of hand, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009956.name: Partial duplication of the phalanges of the 2nd finger
HP:0009956.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0009957.name: Complete duplication of the phalanges of the 2nd finger
HP:0009957.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 2nd finger. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, is a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0009959.name: Duplication of phalanx of 3rd finger
HP:0009959.definition: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 3rd finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0009960.name: Complete duplication of the phalanges of the 3rd finger
HP:0009960.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 3rd finger. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0009961.name: Partial duplication of the phalanges of the 3rd finger
HP:0009961.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 3rd finger. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0009962.name: Duplication of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009962.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the distal phalanx of middle finger.

HP:0009963.name: Duplication of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009963.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the middle phalanx of middle finger.

HP:0009964.name: Duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009964.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the third proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009965.name: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009965.definition: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of middle finger

HP:0009966.name: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009966.definition: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of middle finger.

HP:0009967.name: Complete duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009967.definition: Complete duplication of the third proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009968.name: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009968.definition: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of middle finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009969.name: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009969.definition: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of middle finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009970.name: Partial duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 3rd finger
HP:0009970.definition: Partial duplication of the third proximal phalanx of hand, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009972.name: Duplication of phalanx of 4th finger
HP:0009972.definition: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 4th finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0009973.name: Complete duplication of the phalanges of the 4th finger
HP:0009973.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 4th finger. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0009974.name: Partial duplication of the phalanges of the 4th finger
HP:0009974.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 4th finger. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0009975.name: Duplication of the distal phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009975.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the distal phalanx of ring finger.

HP:0009976.name: Duplication of the middle phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009976.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the middle phalanx of ring finger.

HP:0009977.name: Duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009977.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the fourth proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009978.name: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009978.definition: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of ring finger.

HP:0009979.name: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009979.definition: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of ring finger.

HP:0009980.name: Complete duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009980.definition: Complete duplication of the fourth proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009981.name: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009981.definition: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of ring finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009982.name: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009982.definition: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of ring finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009983.name: Partial duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 4th finger
HP:0009983.definition: Partial duplication of the fourth proximal phalanx of hand, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009985.name: Duplication of phalanx of 5th finger
HP:0009985.definition: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the 5th finger are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0009986.name: Complete duplication of the phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0009986.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 5th finger. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0009987.name: Partial duplication of the phalanges of the 5th finger
HP:0009987.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the 5th finger. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0009988.name: Duplication of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009988.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the distal phalanx of little finger.

HP:0009989.name: Duplication of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009989.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the fifth middle phalanx of hand.

HP:0009990.name: Duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009990.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the fifth proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009991.name: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009991.definition: Complete duplication of the distal phalanx of little finger.

HP:0009992.name: Complete duplication of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009992.definition: Complete duplication of the fifth middle phalanx of hand.

HP:0009993.name: Complete duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009993.definition: Complete duplication of the fifth proximal phalanx of hand.

HP:0009994.name: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009994.definition: Partial duplication of the distal phalanx of little finger, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009995.name: Partial duplication of the middle phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009995.definition: Partial duplication of the fifth middle phalanx of hand, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009996.name: Partial duplication of the proximal phalanx of the 5th finger
HP:0009996.definition: Partial or complete duplication of the fifth proximal phalanx of hand, seen on x-rays as a broad and/or bifid phalanx.

HP:0009997.name: Duplication of phalanx of hand
HP:0009997.definition: This term applies if one or more of the phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0009998.name: Complete duplication of phalanx of hand
HP:0009998.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, is a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0009999.name: Partial duplication of the phalanx of hand
HP:0009999.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0010000.name: Complete duplication of the proximal phalanges of the hand
HP:0010000.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the proximal phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a Pseudoepiphyses (see according terms) sometimes also referred to as Hyperphalangism.

HP:0010001.name: Complete duplication of the distal phalanges of the hand
HP:0010001.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the distal phalanges of the hand.

HP:0010002.name: Complete duplication of the middle phalanges of the hand
HP:0010002.definition: A complete duplication affecting one or more of the middle phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a partial duplication were there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones, a complete duplication leads to two separate bones appearing side to side (radio-ulnar axis) as seen on x-rays. A duplication leading to an accessory bone appearing in the proximo-distal axis on x-rays, this is actually a different entity called a pseudoepiphysis (see corresponding terms) sometimes also referred to as hyperphalangism.

HP:0010003.name: Partial duplication of the proximal phalanges of the hand
HP:0010003.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the proximal phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0010004.name: Partial duplication of the distal phalanges of the hand
HP:0010004.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the distal phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0010005.name: Partial duplication of the middle phalanges of the hand
HP:0010005.definition: A partial duplication, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance, affecting one or more of the middle phalanges of the hand. As opposed to a complete duplication there is still a variable degree of fusion between the duplicated bones.

HP:0010006.name: Duplication of the proximal phalanx of hand
HP:0010006.definition: This term applies if one or more of the proximal phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0010008.name: Duplication of the middle phalanx of hand
HP:0010008.definition: This term applies if one or more of the middle phalanges of the hand are either partially duplicated, depending on severity leading to a broad or bifid appearance of the phalanges, or completely duplicated.

HP:0010009.name: Abnormal 1st metacarpal morphology
HP:0010009.definition: A structural anomaly of the first metacarpal.

HP:0010010.name: Abnormal 2nd metacarpal morphology
HP:0010010.definition: Any abnormality of the second metacarpal bone.

HP:0010011.name: Abnormal 3rd metacarpal morphology
HP:0010011.definition: Any abnormality of the third metacarpal bone.

HP:0010012.name: Abnormal 4th metacarpal morphology
HP:0010012.definition: Any abnormality of the fourth metacarpal bone.

HP:0010013.name: Abnormal 5th metacarpal morphology
HP:0010013.definition: Any abnormality of the fifth metacarpal bone.

HP:0010014.name: Abnormality of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010014.definition: In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits). The epiphysis of the first metacarpal is localized at the proximal end (as seen in the proximal phalanges of the other digits), whereas the epiphyses of the other metacarpal bones are located at the distal end. This term applies if the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal is in any way abnormal, referring to age and gender depending norms, as seen on x-rays.

HP:0010016.name: Bracket epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010016.definition: An epiphysis that curves around from its transverse orientation to a longitudinal one from proximal to distal along one side of the phalanx, thus resembling the letter 'C' and forming a bracket around the diaphysis. This results in a so called delta phalanx characterized by a triangular or trapezoidal shaped bone with a C-shaped epiphyseal plate.

HP:0010017.name: Cone-shaped epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010017.definition: A cone-shaped appearance of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal, producing a 'ball-in-a-socket' appearance.

HP:0010018.name: Enlarged epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010018.definition: Abnormally large size of the epiphyses of the 1st metacarpal with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0010019.name: Fragmentation of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010019.definition: Epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal having multiple bony fragments.

HP:0010020.name: Irregular epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010020.definition: Uneven radiographic opacity of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal.

HP:0010021.name: Ivory epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010021.definition: The epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal appears hard and dense like ivory. An ivory epiphysis has a uniformly dense appearance on radiographs.

HP:0010022.name: Pseudoepiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010022.definition: The epiphysis of the first metacarpal is localized at the proximal end of the metacarpal bone although an accessory epiphysis may be located at the distal end of the metacarpal.

HP:0010023.name: Small epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010023.definition: Abnormally small size of the epiphysis of the 1st metacarpal with respect to age-dependent norms.

HP:0010024.name: Epiphyseal stippling of the first metacarpal
HP:0010024.definition: The presence of abnormal punctate (speckled, dot-like) calcifications in the epiphyses of the first metacarpal bone.

HP:0010026.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010026.definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the metacarpals 2-5, the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5 (whereas the proximal phalanx of the thumb is equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits).

HP:0010027.name: Broad 1st metacarpal
HP:0010027.definition: Increased width of the 1st metacarpal. In contrast to the proximal phalanges of the digits 2-5, the proximal phalanx of the thumb is embryologically equivalent to the middle phalanges of the other digits, whereas the first metacarpal is embryologically of phalangeal origin and as such equivalent to the proximal phalanges of the other digits.

HP:0010028.name: Bullet-shaped 1st metacarpal
HP:0010028.definition: The presence of short and wide 1st metacarpal which tapers distally ("bullet shaped").

HP:0010029.name: Curved 1st metacarpal
HP:0010029.definition: A deviation from the normal straight shape of the first metacarpal.

HP:0010030.name: Osteolytic defects of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010030.definition: Dissolution or degeneration of bone tissue of the 1st metacarpal.

HP:0010031.name: Patchy sclerosis of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010031.definition: Uneven increase in bone density within the 1st metacarpal.

HP:0010033.name: Triangular shaped 1st metacarpal
HP:0010033.definition: This term applies to a triangular shaped 1st metacarpal.

HP:0010034.name: Short 1st metacarpal
HP:0010034.definition: A developmental defect characterized by reduced length of the first metacarpal (long bone) of the hand.

HP:0010035.name: Aplasia of the 1st metacarpal
HP:0010035.definition: Absent first metacarpal (long bone) of the hand.

HP:0010036.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 2nd metacarpal
HP:0010036.definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 2nd metacarpal.

HP:0010037.name: Aplasia of the 2nd metacarpal
HP:0010037.definition: Absence of the second long bone of the hand.

HP:0010038.name: Short 2nd metacarpal
HP:0010038.definition: Short second metacarpal bone because of developmental hypoplasia.

HP:0010039.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 3rd metacarpal
HP:0010039.definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 3rd metacarpal.

HP:0010040.name: Aplasia of the 3rd metacarpal
HP:0010040.definition: Absence of the third long bone of the hand.

HP:0010042.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 4th metacarpal
HP:0010042.definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 4th metacarpal.

HP:0010043.name: Aplasia of the 4th metacarpal
HP:0010043.definition: Absence of the fourth long bone of the hand.

HP:0010045.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the 5th metacarpal
HP:0010045.definition: Aplasia or Hypoplasia affecting the 5th metacarpal.

HP:0010046.name: Aplasia of the 5th metacarpal
HP:0010046.definition: Absence of the fifth long bone of the hand.

HP:0010048.name: Aplasia of metacarpal bones
HP:0010048.definition: Developmental defect associated with absence of one or more metacarpal bones.

HP:0010049.name: Short metacarpal
HP:0010049.definition: Diminished length of one or more metacarpal bones in relation to the others of the same hand or to the contralateral metacarpal.

HP:0010051.name: Deviation of the hallux
HP:0010051.definition: Displacement of the big toe from its normal position.

HP:0010052.name: Abnormal morphology of the proximal phalanx of the hallux
HP:0010052.definition: An abnormal shape or form of the proximal phalanx of the big toe.

HP:0010053.name: Abnormality of the distal phalanx of the hallux

HP:0010054.name: Abnormality of the first metatarsal bone
HP:0010054.definition: An anomaly of the first metatarsal bone.

HP:0010055.name: Broad hallux
HP:0010055.definition: Visible increase in width of the hallux without an increase in the dorso-ventral dimension.

HP:0010056.name: Abnormality of the epiphyses of the hallux

HP:0010058.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the phalanges of the hallux

HP:0010059.name: Broad hallux phalanx
HP:0010059.definition: An increase in width in one or more phalanges of the big toe.

HP:0041221.name: Fractured head of femur
HP:0041221.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the head of femur.

HP:0041222.name: Fractured fibula
HP:0041222.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the fibula.

HP:0041223.name: Fractured metatarsal bone of digit 5
HP:0041223.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the metatarsal bone of digit 5.

HP:0041224.name: Fractured manual digit bone
HP:0041224.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the manual digit bone.

HP:0041225.name: Fractured 1st metacarpal
HP:0041225.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the metacarpal bone of digit 1.

HP:0041226.name: Fractured distal tarsal bone
HP:0041226.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the distal tarsal bone.

HP:0041227.name: Fractured distal tarsal bone 2
HP:0041227.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the distal tarsal bone 2.

HP:0041228.name: Fractured distal tarsal bone 3
HP:0041228.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the distal tarsal bone 3.

HP:0041230.name: Fractured metatarsal bone of digit 4
HP:0041230.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the metatarsal bone of digit 4.

HP:0041231.name: Fractured metatarsal bone of digit 1
HP:0041231.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the metatarsal bone of digit 1.

HP:0041232.name: obsolete Fractured skeleton of manual acropodium

HP:0041233.name: Fractured ilium
HP:0041233.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the ilium.

HP:0041234.name: Fractured bone of jaw
HP:0041234.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the bone of jaw.

HP:0041235.name: Fractured hindlimb bone
HP:0041235.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the hindlimb bone.

HP:0041236.name: Fractured middle finger phalanx
HP:0041236.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the middle phalanx of a finger.

HP:0041237.name: Fractured patella
HP:0041237.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the patella.

HP:0041239.name: Fractured thumb phalanx
HP:0041239.definition: A partial or complete breakage of a phalanx of the thumb.

HP:0041240.name: Fractured phalanx of pes
HP:0041240.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the phalanx of pes.

HP:0041241.name: Fractured finger phalanx
HP:0041241.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the phalanx of a finger.

HP:0041243.name: Fractured proximal finger phalanx
HP:0041243.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the proximal phalanx of manus.

HP:0041244.name: Fractured scapula
HP:0041244.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the scapula.

HP:0041245.name: Fractured shoulder bone
HP:0041245.definition: A partial or complete breakage of a shoulder bone.

HP:0041246.name: Fractured sternum
HP:0041246.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the sternum.

HP:0041247.name: Fractured tarsal bone
HP:0041247.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the tarsal bone.

HP:0041248.name: Fractured carpal bone
HP:0041248.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the carpal bone.

HP:0041249.name: Fractured nose
HP:0041249.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the nose.

HP:0045004.name: Abnormal ossification of the trapezoid bone

HP:0045005.name: Neural tube defect
HP:0045005.definition: A neural tube defect arises when the neural tube, the embryonic precursor of the brain and spinal cord, fails to close during neurulation. The cranial region (anencephaly) or the low spine (open spina bifida; myelomeningocele) are most commonly affected although, in the severe NTD craniorachischisis, almost the entire neural tube remains open, from midbrain to low spine.

HP:0045007.name: Abnormal substantia nigra morphology
HP:0045007.definition: A structural anomaly of the substantia nigra, which is a midbrain dopaminergic nucleus which has a critical role in modulating motor movement and reward functions as part of the basal ganglia circuitry.

HP:0045009.name: obsolete Abnormal morphology of the radius

HP:0045010.name: Abnormal peripheral nerve morphology by anatomical site
HP:0045010.definition: Abnormal morphology of a specific peripheral nerve

HP:0045011.name: Decreased urine bicarbonate concentration
HP:0045011.definition: Abnormally decreased concentration of hydrogencarbonate in the urine.

HP:0045016.name: obsolete Elevated serum long-chain fatty acids

HP:0045017.name: Congenital malformation of the left heart
HP:0045017.definition: Defect or defects of the morphogenesis of the left heart identifiable at birth.

HP:0045025.name: Narrow palpebral fissure
HP:0045025.definition: Reduction in the vertical distance between the upper and lower eyelids.

HP:0045026.name: Abnormal mediastinum morphology
HP:0045026.definition: Any structural anomaly of the central compartment of the thoracic cavity.

HP:0045028.name: Microlissencephaly
HP:0045028.definition: Severe microcephaly and lissencephaly with granular surfaces with immature cortical plate, reduced in thickness, with focal polymicrogyria and immature small neurons with rare processes, intermingled with a considerable number of glial elements.

HP:0045029.name: Eosinophilic fasciitis
HP:0045029.definition: Inflammation and thickening (localized fibrosis) of the fascia, the tissue under the skin and over the muscle, typically associated with a build up of eosinophils in the muscles and tissues.

HP:0045034.name: Elevated urinary 3-aminoisobutyric acid
HP:0045034.definition: An increased amount of 3-aminoisobutyric acid in the urine.

HP:0045038.name: Gastric lymphoma
HP:0045038.definition: Lymphoma that originates in the stomach itself.

HP:0045039.name: Osteolysis involving bones of the upper limbs

HP:0045040.name: Abnormal circulating lactate dehydrogenase concentration
HP:0045040.definition: A deviation from the normal serum concentration/activity of lactate dehydrogenase (LDH), which catalyzes the reduction of pyruvate to form lactate.

HP:0045041.name: Reduced circulating lactate dehydrogenase concentration
HP:0045041.definition: Concentration of lactate dehydrogenase in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0045042.name: Decreased circulating complement C4 concentration
HP:0045042.definition: Concentration of the complement component C4 in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0045043.name: Decreased circulating complement C4a concentration
HP:0045043.definition: Concentration of the complement component C4a in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0045044.name: Decreased circulating complement C4b concentration
HP:0045044.definition: Concentration of the complement component C4b in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0045045.name: Elevated circulating acylcarnitine concentration
HP:0045045.definition: Concentration of acylcarnitine in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0045046.name: Reduced insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit concentration
HP:0045046.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit level in the blood circulation.

HP:0045047.name: HbS hemoglobin
HP:0045047.definition: Presence of an abnormal type of hemoglobin characterized by the substitution of a glutamic acid residue at position 7 following the initial methionine residue by a valine (the mutation causative of sickle cell disease). The mutation promotes the polymerization of the HbS under conditions of low oxygen concentration. HbS can be identified by multiple methodologies including hemoglobin electrophoresis and high-performance liquid chromatography.

HP:0045048.name: Increased HbA2 hemoglobin
HP:0045048.definition: An elevated concentration in the blood of hemoglobin A2 (HbA2), which is a normal variant of hemoglobin A that consists of two alpha and two delta chains and is normally present at low levels in adults but may be increased in beta thalassemia.

HP:0045049.name: Abnormal DLCO
HP:0045049.definition: An abnormal amount of oxygen passes into the blood from the lungs and/or an abnormal amount of carbon dioxide passes from the blood into the lungs.

HP:0045050.name: Increased DLCO
HP:0045050.definition: Increased ability of the lungs to transfer gas from inspired air to the bloodstream as measured by the diffusing capacity of the lungs for carbon monoxide (DLCO) test.

HP:0045051.name: Decreased DLCO
HP:0045051.definition: Reduced ability of the lungs to transfer gas from inspired air to the bloodstream as measured by the diffusing capacity of the lungs for carbon monoxide (DLCO) test.

HP:0045052.name: Abnormality of the brachial nerve plexus
HP:0045052.definition: Any abnormality of the brachial nerve plexus.

HP:0045053.name: Abnormality of the lumbosacral nerve plexus
HP:0045053.definition: Any abnormality of the lumbosacral nerve plexus.

HP:0045055.name: Tiger tail banding
HP:0045055.definition: An abnormal appearance of hair under polarizing microscopy (using crossed polarizers), whereby hair shafts show striking alternating bright and dark bands, often referred to as tiger tail banding.

HP:0045056.name: Abnormal circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
HP:0045056.definition: Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the blood circulation outside normal limits.

HP:0045057.name: Decreased circulating alpha-fetoprotein concentration
HP:0045057.definition: Concentration of alpha-fetoprotein in the blood circulation below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0045058.name: Abnormality of the testis size
HP:0045058.definition: An anomaly of the size of the testicle (the male gonad).

HP:0045059.name: Hyperkeratotic papule
HP:0045059.definition: A circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid, varying in size from a pinhead to less than 10mm in diameter at the widest point that is composed of localized hyperkeratosis (the latter may be demonstrated histopathologically).

HP:0045060.name: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving bones of the extremities

HP:0045063.name: Increased PIVKA-II
HP:0045063.definition: Des-gamma carboxyprothrombin (DCP) or pro-thrombin induced by vitamin K absence-II (PIVKA-II) is an abnormal prothrombin protein that is increased in the serum of patients with HCC. Generation of DCP is thought to be a result of an acquired defect in the post- translational carboxylation of the prothrombin precursor in malignant cells.

HP:0045079.name: Distal femoral metaphyseal irregularity
HP:0045079.definition: Irregularity of the normally smooth surface of the distal metaphysis of the femur.

HP:0045080.name: Decreased CD3+ T cell proportion
HP:0045080.definition: Any abnormality in the proportion of CD3-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

HP:0045081.name: Abnormality of body mass index
HP:0045081.definition: Anomaly in the weight-to-height squared ratio, calculated by dividing the individual's weight in kilograms by the square of the individual's height in meters and used as an indicator of obesity and underweight compared to averages.

HP:0045082.name: Decreased body mass index
HP:0045082.definition: Abnormally decreased weight-to-height squared ratio, calculated by dividing the individual's weight in kilograms by the square of the individual's height in meters and used as an indicator of underweight compared to averages.

HP:0045086.name: Knee joint hypermobility
HP:0045086.definition: The ability of the knee to move past its normal range of motion, (knee hyperextension is greater than 10 degrees).

HP:0045088.name: Clinical relevance
HP:0045088.definition: Subontology for annotating phenotypic features as distinctive or minor findings in patients. The subontology is intended to be used to annotate subjective clinical impressions of whether a certain finding is important for the differential diagnosis.

HP:0045089.name: Distinctive finding
HP:0045089.definition: In clinical parlance, findings are occasionally interpreted as being distinctive or minor, reflecting a subjective clinical impression of the importance of a feature for the differential diagnosis. A minor finding is taken to be one that is likely to have high utility in distinguishing the correct diagnosis from other candidates in the differential.

HP:0045090.name: Minor finding
HP:0045090.definition: In clinical parlance, findings are occasionally interpreted as being distinctive or minor, reflecting a subjective clinical impression of the importance of a feature for the differential diagnosis. A minor finding is taken to be one that is unlikely to help distinguish the correct diagnosis from other candidates in the differential.

HP:0046502.name: Anorgasmia
HP:0046502.definition: Inability of individual to reach orgasm.

HP:0046505.name: Hand pain
HP:0046505.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort localized to the hand.

HP:0046506.name: Pain in head and neck region

HP:0046507.name: Bradypnea
HP:0046507.definition: Bradypnea is referring to breathing that is abnormally slow.

HP:0046508.name: Abnormal cervical spine morphology
HP:0046508.definition: Any morphological abnormality of the cervical vertebral column.

HP:0100000.name: Early onset of sexual maturation
HP:0100000.definition: An early onset of puberty, in this case early does not refer to precocious.

HP:0100001.name: Malignant mesothelioma
HP:0100001.definition: Malignant mesothelioma is a form of cancer that originates from the cells of the mesothelium, a thin tissue layer surrounding the body's internal organs. Malignant mesothelioma is almost exclusively caused by asbestos exposure, pleural mesothelioma being the most common form, affecting the lining of the lungs called the pleura. Other forms such as perioneal-, percardial- or testicular- mesothelioma are much rarer.

HP:0100002.name: Pleural mesothelioma
HP:0100002.definition: A malignant mesothelioma originating from cells of the pleura (the thin layer of mesothelium lining the lungs). Pleural mesothelioma is the most common form of mesothelioma.

HP:0100003.name: Peritoneal mesothelioma
HP:0100003.definition: A Malignant mesothelioma originating from cells of the peritoneum (the thin layer of mesothelium lining the abdomen). Peritoneal mesothelioma is the second most common form of mesothelioma after pleural mesothelioma.

HP:0100004.name: Pericardial mesothelioma
HP:0100004.definition: A Malignant mesothelioma originating from cells of the pericardium (the thin layer of mesothelium lining the heart).

HP:0100005.name: Testicular mesothelioma
HP:0100005.definition: A Malignant mesothelioma of the testis.

HP:0100006.name: Neoplasm of the central nervous system
HP:0100006.definition: A neoplasm of the central nervous system.

HP:0100007.name: Neoplasm of the peripheral nervous system
HP:0100007.definition: A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumor) of the peripheral nervous system.

HP:0100008.name: Schwannoma
HP:0100008.definition: A benign nerve sheath tumor composed of Schwann cells.

HP:0100012.name: Neoplasm of the eye
HP:0100012.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the eye.

HP:0100013.name: Neoplasm of the breast
HP:0100013.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the breast.

HP:0100014.name: Epiretinal membrane
HP:0100014.definition: An epiretinal membrane is a thin sheet of fibrous tissue that can develop on the surface of the macular area of the retina and cause a disturbance in vision. An epiretinal membrane area can develop on the thin macular area of the retin. An epiretinal membrane is also sometimes called a macular pucker, premacular fibrosis, surface wrinkling retinopathy or cellophane maculopathy.

HP:0100015.name: Stahl ear
HP:0100015.definition: The presence of a supernumerary, i.e. third, crus of the helix in the helix, arising at or above the normal bifurcation of the antihelix.

HP:0100016.name: Abnormal mesentery morphology
HP:0100016.definition: Folds of membranous tissue (peritoneum, mesothelium) attached to the wall of the abdomen and enclosing viscera. Examples include the mesentery for the small intestine; the transverse mesocolon, which attaches the transverse portion of the colon to the back wall of the abdomen; and the mesosigmoid, which enfolds the sigmoid portion of the colon. Cells of the same embryologic origin also surround the other organs of the body such as the lungs (pleura) or the heart (pericardium).

HP:0100017.name: Capsular cataract
HP:0100017.definition: A cataract that affects the capsule of the lens.

HP:0100018.name: Nuclear cataract
HP:0100018.definition: A nuclear cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the lens nucleus. That is, a nuclear cataract is one that is located in the center of the lens. The nucleus tends to darken changing from clear to yellow and sometimes brown.

HP:0100019.name: Cortical cataract
HP:0100019.definition: A cataract which affects the layer of the lens surrounding the nucleus, i.e., the lens cortex. It is identified by its unique wedge or spoke appearance.

HP:0100020.name: Posterior capsular cataract
HP:0100020.definition: A cataract which is found in the back outer layer of the lens. This type often develops more rapidly.

HP:0100021.name: Cerebral palsy
HP:0100021.definition: Cerebral palsy describes a group of permanent disorders of the development of movement and posture, causing activity limitation, that are attributed to nonprogressive disturbances that occurred in the developing fetal or infant brain. The motor disorders of cerebral palsy are often accompanied by disturbances of sensation, perception, cognition, communication, and behavior, by epilepsy, and by secondary musculoskeletal problems.

HP:0100022.name: Abnormality of movement
HP:0100022.definition: An abnormality of movement with a neurological basis characterized by changes in coordination and speed of voluntary movements.

HP:0100023.name: Recurrent hand flapping
HP:0100023.definition: A type of repetitive behavior in which the affected individual repeatedly waves the hands and/or arms rhythmically.

HP:0100024.name: Conspicuously happy disposition
HP:0100024.definition: An unusually happy demeanor over time, which can also be observed during inappropriate situations that should, for example, cause distress, fear, or anger.

HP:0100025.name: Overfriendliness
HP:0100025.definition: A form of hypersociability that presents as mostly inappropriate friendliness towards others.

HP:0100026.name: Arteriovenous malformation
HP:0100026.definition: An anomalous configuration of blood vessels that shunts arterial blood directly into veins without passing through the capillaries.

HP:0031772.name: Abnormal posterior circulating artery morphology
HP:0031772.definition: Any structural anomaly of the posterior circulating artery (PCOM).

HP:0031773.name: Posterior communicating artery aneurysm
HP:0031773.definition: A widening (ballooning) localized in the wall of the posterior communicating artery.

HP:0031774.name: Posterior communicating artery infundibulum
HP:0031774.definition: A funnel-shaped symmetrical enlargement of the origin of the posterior communicating artery at its junction with the internal carotid artery.

HP:0031775.name: Neurogenic strabismus
HP:0031775.definition: An ocular deviation caused by a palsy to one or more of the extraocular muscles or nerves supplying them.

HP:0031776.name: Cyclotropia
HP:0031776.definition: A form of manifest strabismus (heterotropia) in which the one eye is wheel rotated so that the upper end of its vertical axis is nasal (incyclotropia) or temporal (excyclotropia).

HP:0031777.name: Cyclophoria
HP:0031777.definition: A form of latent strabismus (heterophoria) in which the occluded eye wheel-rotates on dissociation.

HP:0031778.name: Incyclophoria
HP:0031778.definition: A type of cyclophoria (latent strabismus in which the occluded eye wheel-rotates on dissociation.) in which the upper poles of the globes are rotated inward (medially) to each other.

HP:0031779.name: Excyclophoria
HP:0031779.definition: A type of cyclophoria (latent strabismus in which the occluded eye wheel-rotates on dissociation.) in which the upper poles of the globes are rotated outward (laterally) to each other.

HP:0031780.name: Eosinophilic ascites
HP:0031780.definition: A type of ascites in which there are large numbers of eosinophils in the ascitis fluid.

HP:0031781.name: Microtropia with identity
HP:0031781.definition: A type of microtropia with no manifest movement on cover test, the eccentric fixation point coinciding with the angle of ARC.

HP:0031782.name: Microtropia without identity
HP:0031782.definition: A type of microtropia in which the manifest movement is demonstrated on the cover-uncover test.

HP:0031783.name: Absent coronary sinus
HP:0031783.definition: A developmental defect in which the coronary sinus fails to form.

HP:0031784.name: Abnormal ascending aorta morphology
HP:0031784.definition: Any structural anomaly of the portion of the aorta that arises from the base of the left ventricle and extends upward to the aortic arch and from which the coronary arteries arise.

HP:0031785.name: Abnormal eyelid movement
HP:0031785.definition: An abnormality in voluntary or involuntary eyelid movements or their control.

HP:0031786.name: Cogan lid twitch
HP:0031786.definition: Transient eyelid retraction during refixation from down to straight ahead.

HP:0031787.name: Oblique astigmatism
HP:0031787.definition: Astigmatism in which the refractive power of the vertical meridian is the greatest.

HP:0031788.name: With the rule astigmatism
HP:0031788.definition: Refractive error in which the vertical meridian is relatively hypermetropic and the horizontal meridian is relatively myopic (or ocular astigmatism in which the refractive power of the horizontal meridian is the greatest).

HP:0031789.name: Against the rule astigmatism
HP:0031789.definition: Astigmatism with more plus power on the horizontal meridian.

HP:0031790.name: Mixed astigmatism
HP:0031790.definition: A type of astigmatism in which an unequal curvature of the cornea and some cases additionally of the lens causes one meridian of the eye to be hyperopic (farsighted) and a second meridian that is perpendicular to the first to be myopic (nearsighted).

HP:0031791.name: Lenticular astigmatism
HP:0031791.definition: A type of astigmatism related to an irregular shape of the lens.

HP:0031792.name: Irregular astigmatism
HP:0031792.definition: A type of astigmatism in which the principle meridians are not 90 degrees apart and which is associated with loss of vision.

HP:0031793.name: Increased serum leptin
HP:0031793.definition: An increased concentration of leptin in the blood.

HP:0031794.name: Decreased circulating glycerol level
HP:0031794.definition: A decrease below the normal concentration of glycerol in the blood.

HP:0031795.name: Abnormal circulating glycerol level
HP:0031795.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of glycerol in the blood.

HP:0031796.name: Recurrent
HP:0031796.definition: Applies to a sign, symptom or manifestation that occurs multiple times separated by intervals in which the sign, symptom, or manifestation is not present.

HP:0031797.name: Clinical course
HP:0031797.definition: The course a disease typically takes from its onset, progression in time, and eventual resolution or death of the affected individual.

HP:0031798.name: Elevated circulating apolipoprotein B concentration
HP:0031798.definition: Increased circulating level of apolipoprotein B, which is the main apolipoprotein of chylomicrons and low density lipoproteins. It occurs in plasma as two main isoforms, apoB-48 and apoB-100.

HP:0031799.name: Decreased circulating apolipoprotein A-I concentration
HP:0031799.definition: Concentration of apolipoprotein A-I below the lower limit of normal. Apolipoprotein A-I is the major protein component of high density lipoprotein (HDL) in plasma. Defects in this gene are associated with HDL deficiencies, including Tangier disease.

HP:0031800.name: Elevated circulating apolipoprotein A-II concentration
HP:0031800.definition: An increased concentration in blood of apolipoprotein A-II, a major component of HDL particles, associated with triglyceride and glucose metabolism.

HP:0031801.name: Vocal cord dysfunction
HP:0031801.definition: Any functional anomaly of the vocal cord.

HP:0031803.name: Fundus hemorrhage
HP:0031803.definition: Bleeding within the fundus of the eye.

HP:0031805.name: Intraretinal hemorrhage
HP:0031805.definition: A subtype of fundus hemorrhage occurring within the neurosensory retina. Intraretinal hemorrhages may be 'dot' or' blot' shaped or flame shaped depending upon their depth within the retina.

HP:0031806.name: Abnormal total basophil count
HP:0031806.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of absolute number of basophils in the blood, per microliter, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0031807.name: Increased total basophil count
HP:0031807.definition: Abnormal increase of absolute number of basophils in the blood, per microliter, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0031808.name: Decreased total basophil count
HP:0031808.definition: Abnormal decrease of absolute number of basophils in the blood, per microliter, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0031809.name: Archibald's sign
HP:0031809.definition: Shortening of the fourth and fifth metacarpals when the fist is clenched.

HP:0031810.name: Anti-ganglioside antibody positivity
HP:0031810.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react to gangliosides.

HP:0031811.name: Bilirubinuria
HP:0031811.definition: Presence of conjugated bilirubin in the urine.

HP:0031812.name: Nitrituria
HP:0031812.definition: Presence of nitrites in the urine.

HP:0031813.name: Colonic eosinophilia
HP:0031813.definition: An excess of eosinophilic cells in colonic tissue, i.e., eosinophilic infiltration in the colon.

HP:0031814.name: Palilalia
HP:0031814.definition: Palilalia is the involuntary repetition of one's own phrases, words, or syllables 2 or more times in a row. Typically, palilalic utterances decrease in volume with the increasing number of repetitions. Sometimes, the repetitions are also uttered with an accelerating speed.

HP:0031815.name: Abnormal oral physiology
HP:0031815.definition: A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).

HP:0031816.name: Abnormal oral morphology
HP:0031816.definition: Any structural anomaly of the mouth, which is also known as the oral cavity.

HP:0031817.name: Decreased circulating parathyroid hormone level
HP:0031817.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of parathyroid hormone.

HP:0031818.name: Abnormal waist to hip ratio
HP:0031818.definition: A deviation from normal of the waist to hip ratio, defined as the waist measurement divided by hip measurement.

HP:0031819.name: Increased waist to hip ratio
HP:0031819.definition: Increased waist-to-hip ratio (WHR) is a measurement above the average for the dimensionless ratio of the circumference of the waist to that of the hips. WHR is calculated as waist measurement divided by hip measurement.

HP:0031820.name: Decreased waist to hip ratio
HP:0031820.definition: Decreased waist-to-hip ratio (WHR) is a measurement below the average for the dimensionless ratio of the circumference of the waist to that of the hips. WHR is calculated as waist measurement divided by hip measurement.

HP:0031821.name: Abnormal hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase level
HP:0031821.definition: Altered level of the enzyme that catalyzes conversion of hypoxanthine to inosine monophosphate and guanine to guanosine monophosphate via transfer of the 5-phosphoribosyl group from 5-phosphoribosyl 1-pyrophosphate.

HP:0031822.name: Elevated hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase level
HP:0031822.definition: Abnormally increased level of the enzyme that catalyzes conversion of hypoxanthine to inosine monophosphate and guanine to guanosine monophosphate via transfer of the 5-phosphoribosyl group from 5-phosphoribosyl 1-pyrophosphate.

HP:0031823.name: Reduced hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase level
HP:0031823.definition: Abnormally decreased level of the enzyme that catalyzes conversion of hypoxanthine to inosine monophosphate and guanine to guanosine monophosphate via transfer of the 5-phosphoribosyl group from 5-phosphoribosyl 1-pyrophosphate.

HP:0031825.name: Freezing of gait
HP:0031825.definition: Freezing of gait is defined as a brief, episodic absence or marked reduction of forward progression of the feet despite the intention to walk.

HP:0031826.name: Abnormal reflex
HP:0031826.definition: Any anomaly of a reflex, i.e., of an automatic response mediated by the nervous system (a reflex does not need the intervention of conscious thought to occur).

HP:0031827.name: Absent abdominal reflex
HP:0031827.definition: Lack of contraction of abdominal muscles in the quadrant of the abdomen that is stimulated by scraping the skin tangential to or toward the umbilicus.

HP:0031828.name: Abnormal superficial reflex
HP:0031828.definition: An anomaly of a reflex that is elicited as a motor response to scraping of the skin. They are generally graded as present or absent. They differ from tendon reflexes in that the sensory signal must ascend the spinal cord to reach the brain and then descend the spinal cord to reach the motor neurons.

HP:0031829.name: Absent cremaster reflex
HP:0031829.definition: Lack of response to scratching of the skin of the medial thigh, which in males normally elicits a brisk, short elevation of the ipsilateral testis, a phenomenon that is referred to as the cremaster reflex.

HP:0031830.name: Pinguecula
HP:0031830.definition: A pinguecula is a yellowish to brown protruding lesion in the conjunctiva that is easily seen on the nasal and temporal sides of the cornea.

HP:0031831.name: Decreased serum zinc
HP:0031831.definition: A reduced concentration of zinc in the blood.

HP:0031832.name: Hypermetric downward saccades
HP:0031832.definition: Overshoot of downward saccadic eye movements.

HP:0031833.name: Hypometric upward saccades
HP:0031833.definition: Saccadic undershoot of upward saccadic eye movements, i.e., an upward saccadic eye movement that has less than the magnitude that would be required to gain fixation of the object.

HP:0031834.name: Aortopulmonary collateral arteries
HP:0031834.definition: Small ectopic arteries or arterial branches that connect the aorta, aortic branches and/or subclavian artery regions directly to the lung parenchyma, usually seen in conjunction with pulmonary atresia, ventricular septal defect (VSD) and/or closed ductus arteriosus.

HP:0031835.name: Abnormal circulating superoxide dismutase activity
HP:0031835.definition: Concentration or activity of superoxide dismutase is above or below the limits of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0031836.name: Increased circulating superoxide dismutase concentration
HP:0031836.definition: Concentration or activity of superoxide dismutase is above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0031837.name: Decreased circulating superoxide dismutase concentration
HP:0031837.definition: Concentration or activity of superoxide dismutase is below the lower limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:0031838.name: Presence of xenobiotic
HP:0031838.definition: Presence of a chemical substance found within an individual that is not naturally produced or expected to be present in human tissues or bodily fluids.

HP:0031840.name: Urine xenobiotic
HP:0031840.definition: The presence of a xenobiotic in urine.

HP:0031841.name: Positive urine methadone test
HP:0031841.definition: Detection of methadone or its metabolite 2-ethylidene-1,5-dimethyl-3,3- diphenylpyrrolidine (EDDP) in urine.

HP:0031842.name: Lymphangiectasis
HP:0031842.definition: Dilation of the lymphatic vessels, the basic process that may result in the formation of a lymphangioma.

HP:0031843.name: Abnormally slow thought process
HP:0031843.definition: An inner sense from the self that thoughts are abnormally slow and the individual feels that they are unable to increase their rate of thinking.
