HP:0410234.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against parasites, such as helminths (parasitic worms, such as Ascaris lumbricoides, Trichuris trichiura, Ancylostoma duodenalis, Necator americanus, Strongyloides stercoralis) or parasites such as Toxoplasma gondii.

HP:0410235.name: Increased anti-insect IgE antibody level
HP:0410235.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against antigens from insects such as moths, mosquitos, or cockroaches.

HP:0410236.name: Increased anti-venom IgE antibody level
HP:0410236.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against venom from insects such as bees, wasps, hornets, yellowjackets.

HP:0410238.name: Increased anti-plant product IgE antibody level
HP:0410238.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against antigens from plants and products derived from plants, such as wood or pollen.

HP:0410239.name: Positive urine norcotinine test
HP:0410239.definition: Detection of norcotinine, a metabolite of nicotine, in urine.

HP:0410240.name: Abnormal circulating IgA concentration
HP:0410240.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgA immunoglobulin in blood.

HP:0410241.name: Abnormal circulating IgE concentration
HP:0410241.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgE immunoglobulin in blood.

HP:0410242.name: Abnormal circulating IgG concentration
HP:0410242.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgG immunoglobulin in blood.

HP:0410243.name: Abnormal circulating IgM concentration
HP:0410243.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgM immunoglobulin in blood.

HP:0410244.name: Abnormal circulating IgD concentration
HP:0410244.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of IgD immunoglobulin in blood.

HP:0410245.name: Decreased circulating IgD concentration
HP:0410245.definition: An abnormally decreased level of immunoglobulin D (IgD) in blood.

HP:0410246.name: Increased circulating IgD concentration
HP:0410246.definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin D in blood.

HP:0410247.name: Increased anti-animal dander IgE antibody level
HP:0410247.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against animal dander, tiny scales shed from animal skin or hair, such as from pet dogs or cats.

HP:0410248.name: Increased anti-house dust mite IgE antibody level
HP:0410248.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against house dust mites, a common allergen.

HP:0410249.name: Increased anti-alpha-gal IgE antibody level
HP:0410249.definition: Increased level of IgE antibody against galactose-alpha-1, 3 galactose (alpha-gal), a carbohydrate found in mammalian meat.

HP:0410251.name: Decreased neutrophil toll-like receptor signalling
HP:0410251.definition: Abnormal decrease of neutrophil activation following toll-like receptor (TLR) ligation, commonly measured by evaluation of CD62L shedding after stimulation with lipopolysaccharide (LPS) using flow cytometry.

HP:0410252.name: Persistently decreased total neutrophil count
HP:0410252.definition: Abnormal decrease of the absolute number of neutrophils in the blood, per microlitre, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group, which persists for 3 or more months.

HP:0410253.name: Myeloid maturation arrest
HP:0410253.definition: Chornic neutropenia arising from an impaired proliferation and maturation of myeloid progenitor cells in the bone marrow.

HP:0410254.name: Cyclic neutropenia in myeloid maturation arrest in bone marrow
HP:0410254.definition: Cyclic neutropenia arising from an impaired proliferation and maturation of myeloid progenitor cells in the bone marrow.

HP:0410255.name: Transiently decreased total neutrophil count
HP:0410255.definition: Abnormal decrease of the absolute number of neutrophils in the blood, per microlitre, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group, which persists for less than 3 months and then spontaneously recovers, but does not recur cyclically.

HP:0410256.name: Infection associated neutropenia
HP:0410256.definition: Transient neutropenia caused by an infection, such as with a virus, bacteria or protozoan.

HP:0410257.name: Neutrophilia in presence of infection
HP:0410257.definition: An increased number of neutrophils circulating in the blood during an infection, such as with a bacteria, virus or fungus.

HP:0410258.name: Neutrophilia in absence of infection
HP:0410258.definition: An increased number of neutrophils circulating in the blood in the absence of an infection. Factors contributing to neutrophilia could include inflammation or congenital disorders.

HP:0410259.name: Hepatopulmonary fusion
HP:0410259.definition: Fusion of the liver with the lung.

HP:0410260.name: Asymmetrical gluteal crease
HP:0410260.definition: The presence of an asymmetrical gluteal crease, the horizontal crease formed by the inferior aspect of the buttocks and the posterior upper leg.

HP:0410261.name: Wide space between 4th and 5th toe
HP:0410261.definition: A widely spaced gap between the fourth toe and the fifth (pinky) toe.

HP:0410262.name: Lower cranial nerve dysfunction
HP:0410262.definition: A functional abnormality affecting the lower cranial nerves, which include the paired 9th (glossopharyngeal), 10th (vagal), 11th (accessory) and 12th (hypoglossal) cranial nerves.

HP:0410263.name: Brain imaging abnormality
HP:0410263.definition: An anomaly of metabolism or structure of the brain identified by imaging.

HP:0410264.name: Subglottic hemangioma
HP:0410264.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, located in the airway, typically below the vocal chords, that can cause severe obstruction of the airway.

HP:0410265.name: Supraglottic hemangioma
HP:0410265.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, located in the upper part of the larynx (voice box) including the epiglottis; the area above the vocal cords.

HP:0410266.name: Visceral hemangioma
HP:0410266.definition: A hemangioma arising from within visceral structures, the internal organs of the body.

HP:0410267.name: Intestinal hemangioma
HP:0410267.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, located in the intestines, which includes the bowel.

HP:0410268.name: Spleen hemangioma
HP:0410268.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the spleen.

HP:0410269.name: Labial hemangioma
HP:0410269.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the upper lip.

HP:0410270.name: Esophageal hemangioma
HP:0410270.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the esophagus.

HP:0410271.name: Laryngeal hemangioma
HP:0410271.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the glottic or supraglottic regions.

HP:0410272.name: Vulvar hemangioma
HP:0410272.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the vulva.

HP:0410273.name: Retropharyngeal hemangioma
HP:0410273.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the retropharyngeal space, the portion of the peripharyngeal space that is located posterior to the pharynx.

HP:0410274.name: Paraspinal hemangioma
HP:0410274.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the paraspinal muscular region, the muscles next to the spine.

HP:0410275.name: Lumbosacral hemangioma
HP:0410275.definition: A spinal cord hemangioma located in the lumbosacral spine region.

HP:0410276.name: Supraumbilical raphe
HP:0410276.definition: An abnormality of the sternum that presents at birth as a ventral sternal non-union defect, due to an abnormality of the fusion of the layers of the skin. It presents as a scar-like line that extends upward from the umbilicus (belly button).

HP:0410277.name: Sternal pit
HP:0410277.definition: A sternal pit is a small indentation or dimple in the skin overlying the sternum of the chest. In some cases, the skin defect can be linear, extending several inches over the sternum.

HP:0410278.name: Pituitary gland cyst
HP:0410278.definition: A fluid-filled sacs that develop on or near the pituitary gland.

HP:0410279.name: Atrophic pituitary gland
HP:0410279.definition: Partial or complete wasting (loss) of the pituitary gland.

HP:0410280.name: Pediatric onset
HP:0410280.definition: Onset of disease manifestations before adulthood, defined here as before the age of 16 years, but excluding neonatal or congenital onset.

HP:0410281.name: Dyspepsia
HP:0410281.definition: A heterogeneous group of symptoms that are localized in the epigastric region. Typical dyspeptic symptoms include postprandial fullness, early satiation, epigastric pain and epigastric burning, but other upper gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea, belching or abdominal bloating often occur.

HP:0410282.name: Abnormal circulating amylase concentration
HP:0410282.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands.

HP:0410283.name: Positive blood acetaminophen test
HP:0410283.definition: Detection of acetaminophen in the blood.

HP:0410284.name: Positive norpropoxyphene blood test
HP:0410284.definition: Detection of norpropoxyphene in the blood, a major metabolite of the opioid analgesic drug dextropropoxyphene.

HP:0410285.name: Positive meconium methadone test
HP:0410285.definition: Detection of methadone or its metabolite 2-ethylidene-1,5-dimethyl-3,3- diphenylpyrrolidine (EDDP) in meconium.

HP:0410286.name: Positive blood molindone test
HP:0410286.definition: Detection of molindone in the blood, an antipyschotic used for treatment of schizophrenia.

HP:0410287.name: Intrathoracic hemangioma
HP:0410287.definition: A hemangioma, a benign tumor of the vascular endothelial cells, that is located in the intrathoracic or chest region.

HP:0410288.name: Hyperamylasemia
HP:0410288.definition: Increased level of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands.

HP:0410289.name: Hypoamylasemia
HP:0410289.definition: Decreased level of amylase in the blood, an enzyme which helps digest glycogen and starch. It is produced mainly in the pancreas and salivary glands.

HP:0410291.name: Negativism
HP:0410291.definition: Opposing or not responding to instructions or external stimuli.

HP:0410292.name: Abnormal isohemagglutinin level
HP:0410292.definition: An abnormal level of isohemagglutinin in the blood. An isohemagglutinin refers to the naturally occurring antibodies in the ABO blood group system (i.e., anti-A in a group B person, anti-B in a group A person, and anti-A, anti-B, and anti-A,B in a group O person).

HP:0410293.name: Absent isohemagglutinin level
HP:0410293.definition: Absent or undetectable level of isohemagglutinin. An isohemagglutinin refers to the naturally occurring antibodies in the ABO blood group system (i.e., anti-A in a group B person, anti-B in a group A person, and anti-A, anti-B, and anti-A,B in a group O person).

HP:0410294.name: Decreased specific antibody response to protein vaccine
HP:0410294.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against proteins in vaccines, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410295.name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to tetanus vaccine
HP:0410295.definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a tetanus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410296.name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to hepatitis B vaccine
HP:0410296.definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a hepatisis B antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410297.name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to tetanus vaccine
HP:0410297.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a tetanus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410298.name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to hepatitis B vaccine
HP:0410298.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a hepatitis B antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410299.name: Decreased specific antibody response to polysaccharide vaccine
HP:0410299.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against polysaccharides in vaccines, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410300.name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to unconjugated pneumococcus vaccine
HP:0410300.definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a pneumococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410301.name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to unconjugated pneumococcus vaccine
HP:0410301.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a pneumococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410302.name: Decreased specific antibody response to protein-conjugated polysaccharide vaccine
HP:0410302.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against protein-conjugated polysaccharides in vaccines, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410303.name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) vaccine
HP:0410303.definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410304.name: Complete or near-complete absence of specific antibody response to meningococcus vaccine
HP:0410304.definition: The inability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a meningococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410305.name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) vaccine
HP:0410305.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a Haemophilus influenzae type b (Hib) antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410306.name: Partial absence of specific antibody response to meningococcus vaccine
HP:0410306.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize postvaccination antibodies against a meningococcus antigen, as measured by antibody titer determination following vaccination.

HP:0410307.name: Positive stool methadone test
HP:0410307.definition: Detection of methadone and its metabolites in the stool.

HP:0410308.name: Decreased specific antibody response to infection
HP:0410308.definition: A reduced ability to synthesize antibodies against antigens from an infectious agent or pathogen (such as bacteria, viruses, parasites, etc.), as measured by antibody titer determination following infection.

HP:0410309.name: Alpha-aminoadipic aciduria
HP:0410309.definition: The concentration of alpha-aminoadipic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0410310.name: Abnormality of neutrophil morphology in CSF
HP:0410310.definition: An abnormal form or size of neutrophils in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0410311.name: Hyposegmentation of neutrophil nuclei in CSF
HP:0410311.definition: Hyposegmented (hypolobulated) or bilobed neutrophil nuclei in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0410312.name: Hypersegmentation of neutrophil nuclei in CSF
HP:0410312.definition: An excessive division of the lobes of the nucleus of a neutrophil in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0410313.name: Abnormal urinary 1-methylhistidine concentration
HP:0410313.definition: Abnormal concentration of 1-methylhistidine in the urine.

HP:0410314.name: Decreased urinary 1-methylhistidine
HP:0410314.definition: Decreased concentration of 1-methylhistidine in the urine.

HP:0410315.name: Increased urinary 1-methylhistidine
HP:0410315.definition: Increased concentration of 1-methylhistidine in the urine.

HP:0410316.name: Abnormal urinary 3-methylhistidine level
HP:0410316.definition: Abnormal amount of 3-methylhistidine in the urine.

HP:0410317.name: Increased urinary 3-methylhistidine
HP:0410317.definition: Increased concentration of 3-methylhistidine in the urine.

HP:0410318.name: Decreased urinary 3-methylhistidine
HP:0410318.definition: Decreased concentration of 3-methylhistidine in the urine.

HP:0410319.name: Alpha-gal allergy
HP:0410319.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against alpha-gal.

HP:0410320.name: Animal protein allergy
HP:0410320.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against animal proteins.

HP:0410321.name: Animal dander allergy
HP:0410321.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against animal dander.

HP:0410322.name: Bacteria allergy
HP:0410322.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against bacteria.

HP:0410323.name: Drug allergy
HP:0410323.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against drugs.

HP:0410324.name: Dust mite allergy
HP:0410324.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against dust mites.

HP:0410326.name: Feather allergy
HP:0410326.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against feathers.

HP:0410327.name: Dairy allergy
HP:0410327.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against dairy.

HP:0410328.name: Egg allergy
HP:0410328.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against eggs.

HP:0410329.name: Gluten allergy
HP:0410329.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against gluten.

HP:0410330.name: Meat allergen allergy
HP:0410330.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against allergens contained in meat products.

HP:0410331.name: Nut food product allergy
HP:0410331.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against nut food products.

HP:0410332.name: Plant based food allergy
HP:0410332.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against plant based food allergens.

HP:0410333.name: Seafood allergy
HP:0410333.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against seafood.

HP:0410334.name: Fungi allergy
HP:0410334.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against fungus.

HP:0410335.name: Insect allergy
HP:0410335.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against insects.

HP:0410336.name: Venom allergy
HP:0410336.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against insect venom.

HP:0410337.name: Parasite allergy
HP:0410337.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against parasites.

HP:0410338.name: Plant product allergy
HP:0410338.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against plant products.

HP:0410339.name: Insect bite allergy
HP:0410339.definition: Hypersensitivity in form of an adverse immune reaction against insect bites.

HP:0410340.name: Focal epithelial hyperplasia of oral mucosa
HP:0410340.definition: The occurrence of multiple or unique whitish or normal in color small papules or nodules in oral cavity, especially on labial and buccal mucosa, lower lip and tongue, and less often on the upper lip, gingiva and palate.

HP:0410341.name: Abnormal circulating heparan sulfate level
HP:0410341.definition: An abnormal level of heparan sulfate in the blood.

HP:0410342.name: Increased circulating heparan sulfate level
HP:0410342.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of heparan sulfate in the blood.

HP:0410343.name: Decreased circulating heparan sulfate level
HP:0410343.definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of heparan sulfate in the blood.

HP:0410344.name: Shortened O-fucosylated glycan on properdin
HP:0410344.definition: Decreased length of O-fucosylated glycans present on properdin.

HP:0410345.name: Increased urinary polyhexose
HP:0410345.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of polyhexose in the urine.

HP:0410346.name: Increased urinary galactosylated oligosaccharide
HP:0410346.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of galactosylated oligosaccharides in urine.

HP:0410347.name: Increased urinary high-mannose-type oligosaccharide
HP:0410347.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of high-mannose-type oligosaccharides in the urine.

HP:0410348.name: Increased urinary multiantennary sialylated oligosaccharide
HP:0410348.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of multiantennary sialylated oligosaccharides in the urine.

HP:0410349.name: Decreased glycosyltransferase O-Fucosylpeptide 3-Beta-N-Acetylglucosaminyltransferase level
HP:0410349.definition: An abnormal decrease in glycosyltransferase O-fucosylpeptide 3-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase enzymatic level.

HP:0410350.name: Increased urinary fucosylated oligosaccharide
HP:0410350.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of small fucosylated oligosaccharides in the urine.

HP:0410351.name: Abnormal complex N-glycan level
HP:0410351.definition: An abnormal concentration of complex N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410352.name: Increased complex N-glycan level
HP:0410352.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of complex N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410353.name: Decreased complex N-glycan level
HP:0410353.definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of complex N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410354.name: Increased sialylated N-glycan level
HP:0410354.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of sialylated N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410355.name: Decreased sialylated N-glycan level
HP:0410355.definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of sialylated N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410356.name: Abnormal high-mannose N-glycan level
HP:0410356.definition: An abnormal concentration of high-mannose N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410357.name: Increased high-mannose N-glycan level
HP:0410357.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of high-mannose N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410358.name: Decreased high-mannose N-glycan level
HP:0410358.definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of high-mannose N-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410359.name: Abnormal core 1 O-glycan level
HP:0410359.definition: An abnormal in the concentration of core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410360.name: Increased core 1 O-glycan level
HP:0410360.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410361.name: Decreased core 1 O-glycan level
HP:0410361.definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410362.name: Decreased O-mannosyl glycans on alpha-dystroglycan
HP:0410362.definition: Hypoglycosylation of alpha-dystroglycan with O-mannosyl glycans. Alpha-dystroglycan is a functional target of O-mannosyl glycosylation and functional glycosylation of alpha-DG is essential in its interaction with the extracellular matrix.

HP:0410363.name: Increased monosialylated core 1 O-glycan level
HP:0410363.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of monosialylated core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410364.name: Decreased monosialylated core 1 O-glycan level
HP:0410364.definition: An abnormal decrease in the concentration of monosialylated core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410365.name: Increased disialylated core 1 O-glycan level
HP:0410365.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of disialylated core 1 O-glycans on glycoproteins.

HP:0410366.name: Increased globoside Gb4 level
HP:0410366.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of globoside Gb4.

HP:0410367.name: Increased hepatitis A virus antibody level
HP:0410367.definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin against hepatitis A virus in the blood.

HP:0410368.name: Increased globoside Gb3 level
HP:0410368.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of glycolipid globoside Gb3.

HP:0410369.name: Increased hepatitis B virus antibody level
HP:0410369.definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin against hepatitis B virus in the blood.

HP:0410371.name: Increased hepatitis C virus antibody level
HP:0410371.definition: An abnormally increased level of immunoglobulin against hepatitis C virus in the blood.

HP:0410372.name: Increased Tn-antigen level
HP:0410372.definition: An abnormal increase in the concentration of Tn antigen on glycoproteins.

HP:0040229.name: Decreased level of thrombomodulin
HP:0040229.definition: Thrombomodulin is a cofactor in the thrombin induced activation of Protein C. In the case of deficiency there will be less Protein C and tendency to clot

HP:0040230.name: Decreased level of tissue plasminogen activator
HP:0040230.definition: The tPA protein catalyzes the conversion of plasiminogen to plasmin, and thus break down of clots. When there is a deficiency there will be an increase of thrombosis

HP:0040232.name: Delayed onset bleeding
HP:0040232.definition: Abnormal bleeding related to a procedure or trauma which does not start at the time of the initial insult, but after delay by at least 24 hours.

HP:0040233.name: Factor XIII subunit A deficiency
HP:0040233.definition: Deficiency of factor XIII subunit A, leading to a reduced factor XIII activity. Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot.

HP:0040234.name: Factor XIII subunit B deficiency
HP:0040234.definition: Deficiency of factor XIII subunit B, leading to a reduced factor XIII activity. Activated Factor XIII cross-links fibrin polymers solidifying the clot.

HP:0040235.name: Leukocyte inclusion bodies
HP:0040235.definition: The presence of intraceullar inclusion bodies (aggregates of stainable substances, usually proteins) in leukocytes.

HP:0040236.name: Hyperfibrinolysis
HP:0040236.definition: Increased degradation of fibrin, associated with clot instability and bleeding

HP:0040237.name: Impaired binding of factor VIII to VWF
HP:0040237.definition: Impaired binding of factor VIII to von Willebrand Factor. This is determined using a modified ELISA assay.

HP:0040238.name: Impaired neutrophil chemotaxis
HP:0040238.definition: An impairment of the migration of neutrophils towards chemoattractants as part of the innate immune response

HP:0040239.name: Increased plasma vitamin K epoxide after vitamin K supplementation
HP:0040239.definition: Increased plasma vitamin K epoxide after vitamin K supplementation is present in VKCFD (vitamin K-dependent clotting factor deficiency) type 2, but not in VKCFD type 1.

HP:0040240.name: Increased ratio of VWF propeptide to VWF antigen
HP:0040240.definition: An increased VWF propeptide to VWF antigen indicates that deficiency of VWF is not due to impaired synthesis but due to rapid clearance. The VWF propeptide is measured by ELISA.

HP:0040241.name: Increased RIPA
HP:0040241.definition: Increased platelet agglutination in response to low-dose ristocetin

HP:0040243.name: Prolonged euglobulin clot lysis time
HP:0040243.definition: Abnormally increased length of time required for an in vitro clot to dissolve in the absence of the normal plasmin inhibitors. This test is a clinical assay used to measure fibrinolysis. The euglobulin fraction of plasma is precipitated and used to form clot by addition of thrombin; after clot forms the rate of clot breakdown (fibrinolysis) can be monitored.

HP:0040244.name: Prolonged Russell's viper venom time
HP:0040244.definition: Increased time to coagulation in the Russell's viper venom assay

HP:0040245.name: Reduced alpha-2-antiplasmin activity
HP:0040245.definition: Reduced activity of alpha-2-antiplasmin. This protein inactivates the protease plasmin that drives fibrinolysis.

HP:0040246.name: Reduced antithrombin antigen
HP:0040246.definition: Reduced antithrombin antigen. A reduced level of antithrombin may lead to an increased risk of thrombus formation.

HP:0040247.name: Reduced euglobulin clot lysis time
HP:0040247.definition: Abnormally decreased length of time required for an in vitro clot to dissolve in the absence of the normal plasmin inhibitors. This test is a clinical assay used to measure fibrinolysis. The euglobulin fraction of plasma is precipitated and used to form clot by addition of thrombin; after clot forms the rate of clot breakdown (fibrinolysis) can be monitored.

HP:0040248.name: Reduced plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 activity
HP:0040248.definition: Reduced activity of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1. This protein down-regulates fibrinolysis in the circulation by inhibiting the two major plasminogen activators: tissue-plasminogen activator and urokinase-plasminogen activator.

HP:0040249.name: Reduced plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 antigen
HP:0040249.definition: Reduced level of plasminogen activator inhibitor 1 antigen.

HP:0040250.name: Reduced prothrombin antigen
HP:0040250.definition: Reduced prothrombin antigen as measured by ELISA assay. Prothrombin is a vitamin K-dependent coagulation factor that is proteolytically cleaved to form thrombin.

HP:0040251.name: Hand dimple
HP:0040251.definition: A cutaneous indentation resulting from tethering of the skin to underlying structures (bone) of the hand.

HP:0040256.name: Aplastic/Hypoplastic nasopharyngeal adenoids
HP:0040256.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the nasopharyngeal adenoids.

HP:0040257.name: Abnormal size of nasopharyngeal adenoids
HP:0040257.definition: A deviation in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids.

HP:0040259.name: Aplastic nasopharyngeal adenoids
HP:0040259.definition: Absence of the nasopharyngeal adenoids as a developmental defect.

HP:0040260.name: Decreased size of nasopharyngeal adenoids
HP:0040260.definition: An abnormal decrease in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids.

HP:0040261.name: Increased size of nasopharyngeal adenoids
HP:0040261.definition: An abnormal increase in the size of nasopharyngeal adenoids.

HP:0040262.name: Glue ear
HP:0040262.definition: Middle ear is filled with glue-like fluid instead of air.

HP:0040264.name: Jaw pain
HP:0040264.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the jaw.

HP:0040265.name: Upper limb muscle hypertrophy
HP:0040265.definition: Abnormal increase in muscle size and mass of one or both arms not due to training.

HP:0040268.name: obsolete Recurrent infections of the middle ear

HP:0040270.name: Impaired glucose tolerance
HP:0040270.definition: An abnormal resistance to glucose, i.e., a reduction in the ability to maintain glucose levels in the blood stream within normal limits following oral or intravenous administration of glucose.

HP:0040272.name: Hyperintensity of MRI T2 signal of the spinal cord
HP:0040272.definition: A region of high intensity (brightness) observed upon magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scans of the spinal cord.

HP:0040273.name: Adenocarcinoma of the intestines
HP:0040273.definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the intestines.

HP:0040274.name: Adenocarcinoma of the small intestine
HP:0040274.definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the small intestine.

HP:0040275.name: Adenocarcinoma of the large intestine
HP:0040275.definition: A malignant epithelial tumor with a glandular organization that originates in the large intestine.

HP:0040279.name: Frequency
HP:0040279.definition: Class to represent frequency of phenotypic abnormalities within a patient cohort.

HP:0040280.name: Obligate
HP:0040280.definition: Always present, i.e. in 100% of the cases.

HP:0040281.name: Very frequent
HP:0040281.definition: Present in 80% to 99% of the cases.

HP:0040282.name: Frequent
HP:0040282.definition: Present in 30% to 79% of the cases.

HP:0040283.name: Occasional
HP:0040283.definition: Present in 5% to 29% of the cases.

HP:0040284.name: Very rare
HP:0040284.definition: Present in 1% to 4% of the cases.

HP:0040286.name: Abnormal axial muscle morphology
HP:0040286.definition: A structural anomaly of the muscles of the trunk and head.

HP:0040288.name: Nasogastric tube feeding
HP:0040288.definition: The condition of inability to eat normally treated by placement of a thin tube through the nose into the stomach that is then used to carry food.

HP:0040289.name: Cyclically decreased total neutrophil count
HP:0040289.definition: Abnormal decrease of the absolute number of neutrophils in the blood, per microlitre, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group, which occurs cyclically and then recovers without intervention.

HP:0040296.name: Abnormal location of the eyebrow
HP:0040296.definition: Anomalous anatomical placement of the eyebrow.

HP:0040297.name: Preauricular cyst
HP:0040297.definition: Preauricular sinus is an occasional finding and most frequently appears as a small pit close to the anterior margin of the ascending portion of the helix. The opening has also been reported along the postero superior margin of the helix, the tragus or the lobule. Preauricular sinus may lead to the formation of a subcutaneous cyst that is intimately related to the tragal cartilage and the anterior crus of the helix.

HP:0040299.name: Decreased circulating free fatty acid level

HP:0040300.name: Abnormal circulating free fatty acid concentration
HP:0040300.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of a free fatty acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0040301.name: Increased urinary glycerol
HP:0040301.definition: An increased concentration of glycerol in the urine.

HP:0040302.name: Hyperglycerolemia
HP:0040302.definition: Increased concentration of glycerol in the blood.

HP:0040303.name: Decreased circulating iron concentration
HP:0040303.definition: The concentration of iron in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040305.name: Increased male libido
HP:0040305.definition: Increased desire for sexual activity on the part of a male.

HP:0040306.name: Decreased male libido
HP:0040306.definition: Reduced desire for sexual activity on the part of a male.

HP:0040307.name: Male sexual dysfunction
HP:0040307.definition: A problem occurring during any phase of the male sexual response cycle that prevents the individual from experiencing satisfaction from the sexual activity

HP:0040308.name: Male anorgasmia
HP:0040308.definition: Inability of a male to reach orgasm.

HP:0040310.name: Sterile arthritis
HP:0040310.definition: An inflammatory arthritis characterized by purulent synovial fluid with neutrophil accumulation, but with negative cultures.

HP:0040311.name: Symmetric polyarthritis
HP:0040311.definition: Polyarthritis refers to a joint disease that involves at least five joints. One or more signs of inflammation, including pain, movement restriction, swelling, warmth, and redness, are seen in the joints involved. Polyarthritis is defined as symmetric if at least half of the joints involved are affected in a symmetric (i.e., both right and the left) fashion.

HP:0040313.name: Oligoarthritis
HP:0040313.definition: A type of arthritis that affects up to four joints in the first six months of disease.

HP:0040314.name: Blind vagina
HP:0040314.definition: The vagina ends in a blind pouch or sac rather than being connected to the internal genitalia.

HP:0040315.name: Tongue edema
HP:0040315.definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid and swelling in the tongue.

HP:0040317.name: Blue urine
HP:0040317.definition: An abnormal blue color of the urine.

HP:0040318.name: Red urine
HP:0040318.definition: An abnormal red color of the urine.

HP:0040319.name: Dark urine
HP:0040319.definition: An abnormal dark color of the urine.

HP:0040320.name: Red-brown urine
HP:0040320.definition: An abnormal red-brown color of the urine.

HP:0040321.name: Dark yellow urine
HP:0040321.definition: An abnormal dark-yellow color of the urine.

HP:0040322.name: Purple urine
HP:0040322.definition: An abnormal purple color of the urine.

HP:0040323.name: Eyelid erythema
HP:0040323.definition: Redness of the skin of the eyelids, caused by hyperemia of the capillaries in the lower layers of the skin.

HP:0040324.name: Heliotrope rash
HP:0040324.definition: In a heliotrope rash, the color of the skin turns to violet, which is the color of the heliotrope flower.

HP:0040325.name: Bull's eye rash
HP:0040325.definition: A cutaneous eruption that consists of multiple (at least two) concentric erythematous rings.

HP:0040327.name: Abnormal morphology of the olfactory bulb
HP:0040327.definition: An abnormal morphology of the olfactory bulb (bulbus olfactorius), which is involved in olfaction, i.e. the sense of smell.

HP:0040328.name: Focal hyperintensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
HP:0040328.definition: An abnormal area of increased brightness (hyperintensity) that is limited to one particular area.

HP:0040329.name: Multifocal hyperintensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
HP:0040329.definition: An abnormal area of increased brightness (hyperintensity) that occurs in several distinct areas.

HP:0040330.name: Confluent hyperintensity of cerebral white matter on MRI
HP:0040330.definition: Areas of brighter than expected MRI signal in the white matter of the brain whereby individual patches run together.

HP:0040331.name: Focal hypointensity of cerebral white matter on MRI

HP:0040332.name: Multifocal hypointensity of cerebral white matter on MRI

HP:0040333.name: Confluent hypointensity of cerebral white matter on MRI

HP:0040334.name: Purulent rhinitis
HP:0040334.definition: Chronic rhinitis accompanied by pus formation.

HP:0040402.name: Nipple localization
HP:0040402.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is distributed around the nipples or located in the nipples.

HP:0040403.name: Breast microcalcification
HP:0040403.definition: The term breast microcalcification is used to define calcium deposits in the breast with a diameter of less than 1 mm.

HP:0040404.name: Architectural distortion of breast
HP:0040404.definition: Architectural distortion is defined as an architectural disruption of the normal breast that does not have obvious mass opacities, which may be early signs of breast carcinoma.

HP:0040405.name: Asymmetric thickening of the nipple-areolar complex
HP:0040405.definition: Thickening of the skin around the nipple with a distribution that is not equal on all sides.

HP:0040406.name: Perimenopausal
HP:0040406.definition: Perimenopause, or the menopausal transition, encompasses that period of time during which physiologic changes mark progression toward a woman's final menstrual period. This phase begins with the onset of menstrual irregularities and continues until a woman reaches menopause, or one year after amenorrhea has occurred. Perimenopause can last for a variable amount of time, the median of which is four years.

HP:0040407.name: Mastitis
HP:0040407.definition: Mastitis is defined as an inflammation of the breast and may or may not be accompanied by infection.

HP:0040408.name: Ameliorated by menopause
HP:0040408.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by menopause.

HP:0040409.name: Fluctuance on palpation
HP:0040409.definition: Yielding to alternate pressure by palpating fingers so as to suggest that the area being felt contains fluid.

HP:0040410.name: History of vasectomy
HP:0040410.definition: A medical history of having undergone a vasectomy prior to the current presentation.

HP:0040411.name: Pain in penis
HP:0040411.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the penis.

HP:0040412.name: Left ventricular thrombus
HP:0040412.definition: A blood clot (thrombus) localized in the left ventricle. Left ventricular thrombus is a serious complication of acute myocardial infarction and also of non-ischemic cardiomyopathies.

HP:0040414.name: Gelatinous ascites
HP:0040414.definition: A type of ascites characterized by copious amounts of mucinous ascites and mucinous peritoneal implants, leading to progressive obliteration of the peritoneal cavity and intestinal obstruction.

HP:0040415.name: Diffuse breast nodularity
HP:0040415.definition: Breast tissue with a lumpy or ropelike texture.

HP:0040416.name: Abnormal urinary nitrogen compound level
HP:0040416.definition: The amount of a nitrogen compound in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside of normal limits.

HP:0040417.name: Decreased urinary biopterin level
HP:0040417.definition: The amount of biopterin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040418.name: Abnormal urine guanidinoacetic acid level
HP:0040418.definition: The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside normal limits.

HP:0040419.name: Elevated urine guanidinoacetic acid level
HP:0040419.definition: The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0040420.name: Decreased urinary neopterin level
HP:0040420.definition: The amount of neopterin in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0040421.name: Abnormal urinary inosine level
HP:0040421.definition: The amount of inosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

HP:0040422.name: Elevated urinary inosine level
HP:0040422.definition: The amount of inosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0040423.name: Abnormal urinary guanosine level
HP:0040423.definition: The amount of guanosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside the limits of normal.

HP:0040424.name: Elevated urinary guanosine level
HP:0040424.definition: The amount of guanosine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

HP:0040425.name: Abnormal urinary hypoxanthine level
HP:0040425.definition: The concentration of hypoxanthine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is outside of normal limits.

HP:0040426.name: Decreased urinary hypoxanthine level
HP:0040426.definition: The concentration of hypoxanthine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is below the lower limit of normal.

HP:0041042.name: Absent neutrophil lactoferrin
HP:0041042.definition: The absence of lactoferrin in neutrophil granules, which could be caused by either an isolated failure of synthesis of this protein (or the production of an antigenically unrecognizable form of lactoferrin) or a complete deficiency of specific granule production.

HP:0041043.name: Neutrophil nuclear clefts
HP:0041043.definition: An abnormality of the nucleus of neutrophils, which presents as either a type I nuclear cleft, where the nuclear cleft may show a transition into a round/oval shape. The second type nuclear cleft, which runs perpendicular to the nuclear surface, and this type of cleft might be related to nuclear lobe formation.

HP:0041044.name: Low neutrophil alkaline phosphatase
HP:0041044.definition: An abnormally reduced level of alkaline phosphatase in neutrophils, which could be due to absence of enzyme or the production of defective enzyme.

HP:0041045.name: Increased neutrophil mitochondria
HP:0041045.definition: An increased number of mitochondria detected in neutrophils.

HP:0041046.name: Increased neutrophil ribosomes
HP:0041046.definition: An increased number of ribosomes detected in neutrophils.

HP:0041047.name: Bladder outlet obstruction
HP:0041047.definition: A compression or resistance upon the bladder outflow channel at any location from the bladder neck to urethral meatus, which usually causes lower urinary tract symptoms (LUTS).

HP:0041048.name: Decreased expression of GPI-anchored proteins on the cell surface
HP:0041048.definition: A decrease in the protein expression of GPI-anchor proteins, such as CD55 and CD59, at the cell surface, which suggests a defect in GPI-anchor biosynthesis.

HP:0041050.name: Renal tubular cyst
HP:0041050.definition: Tubular lumnal dilatation/prominence lined by simple layer of cuboidal-to-flat tublar epihelial cells.

HP:0041051.name: Ageusia
HP:0041051.definition: A rare condition that is characterized by a complete loss of taste function of the tongue.

HP:0041052.name: Agenesis of putamen
HP:0041052.definition: A developmental defect characterized by the absence of the putamen owing to its failure to develop.

HP:0041054.name: obsolete Fractured thoracic segment of trunk

HP:0041055.name: Fractured humerus
HP:0041055.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the humerus.

HP:0041056.name: Hot cross bun sign
HP:0041056.definition: A cruciform-shaped hyperintensity within the pons found on T2-weighted magnetic resonance imaging (MRI).

HP:0041057.name: Transient decreased circulating IgG4
HP:0041057.definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood circulation.

HP:0041058.name: Chronic decreased circulating IgG4
HP:0041058.definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood.

HP:0041059.name: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG4
HP:0041059.definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG4 can be measured.

HP:0041060.name: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG4
HP:0041060.definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) in the blood.

HP:0041061.name: Fractured calcaneus
HP:0041061.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the calcaneus.

HP:0041062.name: Transient decreased circulating IgG2
HP:0041062.definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood circulation.

HP:0041063.name: Chronic decreased circulating IgG2
HP:0041063.definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood.

HP:0041065.name: Chronic (near) absent circulating IgG2
HP:0041065.definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG2 can be measured.

HP:0041066.name: Chronic partially decreased circulating IgG2
HP:0041066.definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G2 (IgG2) in the blood.

HP:0041067.name: Transient decreased circulating IgG1
HP:0041067.definition: A temporary reduction beneath the normal level of total immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood circulation.

HP:0041068.name: Chronic decreased circulating IgG1
HP:0041068.definition: A lasting decrease of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood.

HP:0041069.definition: A lasting absence of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood, whereby at most trace quantities of IgG1 can be measured.

HP:0041070.definition: A lasting limited decrease of immunoglobulin G1 (IgG1) in the blood.

HP:0041076.name: Abnormal immunoglobulin level in body fluid
HP:0041076.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in body fluids, such as mucous.

HP:0041078.name: Decreased immunoglobulin level in body fluid

HP:0041079.name: Decreased body fat percentage
HP:0041079.definition: The percentage of fat as a part of total body weight below the norm, usually defined as less than 14% for females and less than 8% for males.

HP:0041080.name: Abnormal proportion of exhausted T cells
HP:0041080.definition: A deviation from the normal proportion of exhausted T cell relative to T cell in the blood.

HP:0041083.definition: A partial or complete breakage of the phalanx.

HP:0041084.name: Compression-fractured thoracic vertebra
HP:0041084.definition: A fracture of the thoracic vertebra that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

HP:0041085.name: Compression-fractured vertebra
HP:0041085.definition: A fracture of the vertebra that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

HP:0041087.name: Compression-fractured lumbar vertebra

HP:0041088.name: Avulsion fractured humerus
HP:0041088.definition: A fractured in which a fragment of the humerus tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

HP:0041089.name: Avulsion fractured tibia
HP:0041089.definition: A fractured in which a fragment of the tibia tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

HP:0041090.name: Pelvic avulsion fracture
HP:0041090.definition: An avulsion fracture (i.e., a type of fracture in which a piece of bone tears away from the site where the muscle attaches to the bone) of a bone of the pelvis.

HP:0041091.name: Avulsion fractured epiphysis of femur
HP:0041091.definition: A fractured in which the fragment of the epiphysis of femur bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

HP:0041092.name: Emotional hypersensitivity
HP:0041092.definition: Heightened emotional reactivity to environmental stimuli, including the emotions of others.

HP:0041093.name: Beau's lines
HP:0041093.definition: A nail dystrophy that is preseents as grooved lines that run from side to side on the fingernail or the toenail that may look like indentations or ridges on the nail plate. They are caused by temporary disruption in the growth of proximal nail matrix. Trauma is usually the initiating factor such as infections, severe medical illnesses, major surgery/anesthesia, medication side effects, and autoimmune disease.

HP:0041094.name: Complete tracheal ring
HP:0041094.definition: Continuous or nearly continuous configuration of the cartilaginous tracheal ring.

HP:0041095.name: Decreased middle cerebral artery pulsatility index
HP:0041095.definition: Abnormally reduced blood flow pulsatility in in the middle cerebral artery (MCA). The pulsatility index (PI) is calculated using the following equation PI = (peak systolic velocity-end-diastolic velocity)/mean velocity.

HP:3000031.definition: An abnormality of an anterior ethmoidal artery.

HP:3000035.definition: Abnormality of the plexus of the ventral rami of the first four cervical spinal nerves which are located from C1 to C4 cervical segment in the neck.

HP:3000036.name: Abnormal head blood vessel morphology
HP:3000036.definition: An abnormality of a blood vessel of the head, including branches of the arterial and venous systems of the head.

HP:3000037.name: Abnormal neck blood vessel morphology
HP:3000037.definition: An abnormality of a blood vessel of the neck, including branches of the arterial and venous systems of the neck.

HP:3000038.name: Abnormal cricoid cartilage morphology
HP:3000038.definition: Any structural abnormality of a cricoid cartilage, that is, of the ring-shaped cartilage of the larynx.

HP:3000039.name: Abnormality of dorsal nasal artery
HP:3000039.definition: An abnormality of a dorsal nasal artery.

HP:3000045.name: Abnormality of genioglossus muscle
HP:3000045.definition: An abnormality of a genioglossus muscle.

HP:3000046.name: Abnormal geniohyoid muscle morphology
HP:3000046.definition: An abnormality of a geniohyoid muscle.

HP:3000047.name: Abnormal glossopharyngeal nerve morphology
HP:3000047.definition: Any structural anomaly of the glossopharyngeal nerve, the ninth paired cranial nerve (CN IX).

HP:3000048.name: Abnormal great auricular nerve morphology
HP:3000048.definition: Any structural anomaly of a great auricular nerve.

HP:3000049.name: Abnormal greater palatine artery morphology
HP:3000049.definition: An abnormality of a greater palatine artery.

HP:3000050.name: Abnormal odontoid tissue morphology

HP:3000051.definition: An abnormality of a hyoglossus muscle.

HP:3000052.name: Abnormal hyoid bone morphology
HP:3000052.definition: Any structural abnormality of the hyoid bone (hyoid), a small U-shaped (horseshoe-shaped) solitary bone, situated in the midline of the neck anteriorly at the base of the mandible and posteriorly at the fourth cervical vertebra.

HP:3000053.name: Abnormal hypopharynx morphology
HP:3000053.definition: A structural anomaly of the hypopharyx, which is the most inferior portion of the pharynx. The hypopharynx continues from the oropharynx at the pharyngoepiglottic fold superiorly and extends inferiorly to the level of the inferior aspect of the cricoid cartilage, which marks the beginning of the cervical esophagus.

HP:3000054.definition: An abnormality of an inferior alveolar artery.

HP:3000058.name: Abnormality of inferior rectus extraocular muscle

HP:3000059.name: Abnormal inferior thyroid vein morphology

HP:3000061.name: Abnormality of infra-orbital nerve
HP:3000061.definition: A structural abnormality of an infra-orbital nerve. The infraorbital nerve arises from the maxillary branch of the trigeminal nerve and normally traverses the orbital floor in the infraorbital canal.

HP:3000062.definition: An abnormality of an internal carotid artery.

HP:3000066.name: Abnormal lacrimal sac morphology
HP:3000066.definition: An abnormality of a lacrimal sac.

HP:3000067.name: Abnormal lateral cricoarytenoid muscle morphology
HP:3000067.definition: Any structural abnormality of a lateral crico-arytenoid muscle, which extends from the lateral cricoid cartilage to the muscular process of the arytenoid cartilage, and can adduct the vocal cords, which closes the rima glottidis and thereby protects the airway.

HP:3000068.definition: An abnormality of a lateral pterygoid muscle.

HP:3000069.definition: An abnormality of a lateral rectus extra-ocular muscle.

HP:3000077.definition: An abnormality of a mandible condylar process.

HP:3000078.definition: An abnormality of a mandible coronoid process.

HP:3000079.definition: A structural abnormality of a mandibular symphysis.

HP:4000001.name: Abnormal cardiac magnetic resonance imaging finding
HP:4000001.definition: Abnormal finding by magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), which uses non-ionizing radiation via a strong magnetic field and radio frequency energy to generate three dimensional images. This term comprises findings that are specific to MRI. Findings such as ventricular spetum defect that can be detected by multiple modalities should be coded separately.

HP:4000003.name: Elevated myocardial native T2
HP:4000003.definition: Increased duration of myocardial T2 time without gadolinium contrast. Elevated T2, which can detect myocardial edema.

HP:4000004.name: Myocardial late gadolinium enhancement
HP:4000004.definition: Areas of high signal intensity in magnetic resonance imaging of the heart appearing 10 to 15 minutes after injection of the intercellular contrast agent gadolinium.

HP:4000005.name: Pericardial late gadolinium enhancement
HP:4000005.definition: Areas of high signal intensity in magnetic resonance imaging of the pericardium appearing around 10 minutes after injection of the intercellular contrast agent gadolinium.

HP:4000006.name: Elevated myocardial native T1
HP:4000006.definition: Increased duration of myocardial T1 time without gadolinium contrast. T1 mapping consists of quantifying the T1 relaxation time of a tissue by using analytical expressions of image-based signal intensities. A fundamental principle of MR imaging is that the signal intensity of pixels is based on the relaxation of hydrogen nuclei protons in a static magnetic field. The T1 relaxation times between two tissues vary substantially. Edema, fat infiltration, and fibrosis also cause differences in T1 relaxivity.

HP:4000007.name: Bronchoconstriction
HP:4000007.definition: Tightening of smooth muscle surrounding the bronchi and bronchioles with consequent wheezing and shortness of breath.

HP:4000008.name: Formation of multiple pronuclei during fertilization
HP:4000008.definition: Pronuclei formation is a critical process during fertilization. Normally, there are two pronuclei (2PN), including the paternal pronucleus and the maternal pronucleus, in the zygote after fertilization. It is generally accepted that multiple pronuclei (MPN) formation is due to the abnormal extrusion of the second polar body or to abnormal fertilization with multiple sperm. The MPN therefore can cause infertility and recurrent failure of IVF/ICSI.

HP:4000009.name: Kinesiophobia
HP:4000009.definition: An excessive, irrational, and debilitating fear of carrying out a physical movement due to a feeling of vulnerability to painful injury or reinjury.

HP:4000010.name: Impaired renal tubular reabsorption of bicarbonate
HP:4000010.definition: Decreased renal tubular reabsorption of bicarbonate.

HP:4000011.name: History of congenital HPV infection
HP:4000011.definition: A congenital human papillomavirus (HPV) infection of the newborn. Congential HPV infection can manifest as condyloma cuminata in the newborn.

HP:4000013.name: Anti-desmoglein-1 antibody positivity
HP:4000013.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoglein-1, a dermal cell adhesion molecule.

HP:4000014.name: Anti-desmoglein-3 antibody positivity
HP:4000014.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoglein-3, a dermal cell adhesion molecule.

HP:4000015.name: Anti-envoplakin antibody positivity
HP:4000015.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against envoplakin, a cytoskeletal linker protein that links intermediate filaments to cellular junctions.

HP:4000016.name: Anti-periplakin antibody positivity
HP:4000016.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against periplakin.

HP:4000017.name: Anti-desmoplakin I antibody positivity
HP:4000017.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoplakin-1.

HP:4000018.name: Anti-desmoplakin II antibody positivity
HP:4000018.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against desmoplakin-II.

HP:4000019.name: Anti-BP230 antibody positivity
HP:4000019.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against BP230.

HP:4000020.name: Anti-BP180 antibody positivity
HP:4000020.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against BP180.

HP:4000021.name: Anti-laminin 332 antibody positivity
HP:4000021.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin-332.

HP:4000022.name: Anti-laminin 6 antibody positivity
HP:4000022.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin-6.

HP:4000023.name: Anti-laminin gamma1 antibody positivity
HP:4000023.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against laminin gamma-1.

HP:4000024.name: Anti-laminin antibody positivity
HP:4000024.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a laminin. Laminins are major components of the basement membrane.

HP:4000025.name: Anti-integrin antibody positivity
HP:4000025.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against an integrin. Integrins are a family of cell adhesion molecules with 24 known integrin heterodimers. Integrins transduce mechanical and biochemical signals from fibrotic extracellular matrix into the cell, activate latent TGFbeta, and subsequently modulate fibroblast adhesion, migration, and growth.

HP:4000026.name: Anti-transglutaminase 6 antibody
HP:4000026.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against transglutaminase 6.

HP:4000027.name: Anti-LAD-1 antibody positivity
HP:4000027.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against LAD-1, which is the soluble 120 kDa ectodomain of BP180.

HP:4000028.name: Anti-LABD97 antibody positivity
HP:4000028.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against LABD97, which is structurally identical to a portion of the extracellular domain of BPAg2. BPAg2, a 180 kDa bullous pemphigoid antigen, is a transmembrane protein important for basement membrane cohesion.

HP:4000029.name: Antigliadin antibody positivity
HP:4000029.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against gliadin.

HP:4000030.name: Anti-reticulin antibody positivity
HP:4000030.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against reticulin.

HP:4000031.name: Anti-type VII collagen antibody
HP:4000031.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against collagen type VII.

HP:4000032.name: False perception of self-motion
HP:4000032.definition: A perception that one's body is moving or swaying despite lack of motion of the body.

HP:4000033.name: Non-spinning vertigo
HP:4000033.definition: A perception of unsteadiness of dizziness that is not characterized bythe spinning sensation of classic vertigo, but rather by an oscillatory perception (rocking, bobbing, or swaying despite the fact that the subject is not moving).

HP:4000035.name: Primary obstructive megaureter
HP:4000035.definition: Megaurater associated with obstruction or an adynamic ureteral segment in the ureterovesical junction.

HP:4000036.name: Encysted hydrocele of the cord
HP:4000036.definition: A type of hydrocele testis in which both the proximal and distal portions of processus vaginalis get obliterated while the central portion remains patent and fluid accumulates within it.

HP:4000037.name: Congenital hydrocele
HP:4000037.definition: Congenital hydrocele occurs when processus vaginalis is patent and communicates with the peritoneal cavity. This communication allows the movement of peritoneal fluid but is too small to allow the intra-abdominal contents to herniate through.

HP:4000038.name: Infantile hydrocele
HP:4000038.definition: Infantile Hydrocele is a type pf hydrocele in which the processus vaginalis gets obliterated at the level of the deep inguinal ring. However, the portion distal to it remains patent and allows fluid accumulation.

HP:4000039.name: Reduced mucosal-associated invariant T cell proportion
HP:4000039.definition: A decreased proportion of circulating mucosal-associated invariant T (MAIT) cells relative to total T cell count.

HP:4000040.name: Puerpural onset
HP:4000040.definition: Onset of a phenotypic abnormality or a disease during childbirth or in the period immediately following.

HP:4000041.name: AA amyloidosis
HP:4000041.definition: Extracellular tissue deposition of fibrils that are composed of fragments of and/or intact serum amyloid A protein, a hepatic acute phase reactant.

HP:4000042.name: Fracture type
HP:4000042.definition: Category of fracture. Terms from this subontology can be used together with terms in the subontology that descends from Bone fracture (HP:0020110).

HP:4000043.name: Greenstick fracture
HP:4000043.definition: A type of fracture in which the broken bone is not completely separated.

HP:4000044.name: Transverse fracture
HP:4000044.definition: A type of fracture in which the break is in a straight line across the bone.

HP:4000045.name: Spiral fracture
HP:4000045.definition: A type of fracture in which the break spirals around the bone.

HP:4000046.name: Oblique fracture
HP:4000046.definition: A type of fracture in which there is a diagonal break across the bone.

HP:4000047.name: Compression fracture
HP:4000047.definition: A type of fracture in which the bone is crushed, causing the broken bone to be wider or flatter in appearance.

HP:4000048.name: Comminuted fracture
HP:4000048.definition: A type of fracture in which the break is in three or more pieces and fragments are present at the fracture site.

HP:4000049.name: Segmental fracture
HP:4000049.definition: A type of fracture in which the same bone is fractured in two places, so there is a floating segment of bone.

HP:4000050.name: Open fracture
HP:4000050.definition: A type of fracture in which there is an open wound or break in the skin near the site of the broken bone.

HP:4000051.name: Closed fracture
HP:4000051.definition: A type of fracture in which the broken bone that does not penetrate the skin.

HP:4000052.name: Avulsion fracture
HP:4000052.definition: A type of fracture that is localied near to a a tendon or ligament and a small fragment of bone is separated from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

HP:4000053.name: Displaced fracture
HP:4000053.definition: A type of fracture in which the ends of the fractured bone are no longer aligned.

HP:4000055.name: Intestinal inflammation
HP:4000055.definition: A reaction characterizeds by capillary dilatation, leukocytic infiltration, redness, heat, pain, swelling localized to the in the intestinal tract.

HP:4000056.name: Abnormal apoptosis
HP:4000056.definition: Any abnormality of programmed cell death (apoptosis), which is defined as the orchestrated collapse of a cell characterized by membrane blebbing, cell shrinkage, condensation of chromatin, and fragmentation of DNA followed by rapid engulfment of the corpse by neighboring cells. Apoptosis is distinguished from death by necrosis by the absence of an associated inflammatory response.

HP:4000057.name: Decreased FasL-mediated apoptosis
HP:4000057.definition: A reduced amount of programmed cell death upon stimulation of the FAS receptor, which normally induces caspase-8 dependent apoptosis.

HP:4000058.name: Glomerular proteinuria
HP:4000058.definition: A type of proteinuria characterized by increased permeability of the glomerular capillary wall to macromolecules (particularly albumin), whereby protein excretion can reach 20 g/24 h and consists mainly of albumin.

HP:4000059.name: Abnormal lung development
HP:4000059.definition: A structural defect associated with abnormal development of the lung.

HP:4000061.name: Pancreatic alpha-cell hyperplasia
HP:4000061.definition: A diffuse and specific increase in the number of alpha-cells.

HP:4000062.name: 3-4 metacarpal synostosis
HP:4000062.definition: A congenital hand malformation characterized by the coalescence of the coalescence of third and fourth metacarpals (i.e., those corresponding to the middle and ring fingers).

HP:4000066.name: Abnormal iliac artery morphology
HP:4000066.definition: Any structural anomaly of the iliac artery.

HP:4000067.name: Iliac artery aneurysm
HP:4000067.definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the iliac artery.

HP:4000068.name: Abnormal interest
HP:4000068.definition: Any deviation from normal intensity or subject of a person's interests, which can be defined as a state of giving selective attention to something.

HP:4000069.name: Persistent preoccupation with parts of objects
HP:4000069.definition: A type of abnormal interest characterized by a persistent and intense focus on parts of a toy/object. For example, affected individuals may spin the wheels on a toy car rather than drive the toy car.

HP:4000070.name: Fixated interests
HP:4000070.definition: Highly restricted, fixated interests that are abnormal in intensity or focus (e.g., strong attachment to or preoccupation with unusual objects, excessively circumscribed or perseverative interests).

HP:4000072.name: Abnormal language feature
HP:4000072.definition: The presence of any atypical form of expressive language.

HP:4000073.name: Pronoun reversal
HP:4000073.definition: Atypical language features characterized by first vs. second or third person pronoun errors such as using 'you' or 'he/she' in place of 'I'.

HP:4000074.name: Involuntary vocalization
HP:4000074.definition: Production of sound done without will or conscious control. Involuntary vocalizations include tics, stereotypies vocalizations as part of dystonia or chorea, continuous vocalizing behaviors such as groaning or grunting, pathological laughter and crying, and others. These vocalizations are not recognized as socially or culturally appropriate.

HP:4000075.name: Reduced frequency of facial expressions
HP:4000075.definition: The number of times facial expressions are produced in a given period is lower than expected given the social and cultural context.

HP:4000076.name: Use of another person's body to communicate
HP:4000076.definition: Moving another person's hand, body part, or body to communicate a desire, e.g. pushing or pulling someone toward a desired object or placing someone's hand on something.

HP:4000077.name: Fixated interest with abnormal focus
HP:4000077.definition: A fixated interest in a specific topic that is atypical for the social context of the individual, such as topics of a non-social nature like fossils or vacuum cleaners.

HP:4000078.name: Fixated interest with abnormal intensity
HP:4000078.definition: An abnormally intense interest in a topic or object that is not atypical for the social context of the affected person.

HP:4000079.name: Sensory seeking
HP:4000079.definition: Unusual interest in sensory aspects of the environment.

HP:4000081.name: Reduced production of gestures
HP:4000081.definition: Diminished use of typical non-verbal conversational gestures such as shaking the head to indicate no or nodding the head to indicate yes.

HP:4000082.name: Reduced cooperative play
HP:4000082.definition: Impairment in a child's ability to be able to play in a way that involves peer collaboration. Collaborative play involves things such as verbal and non-verbal communication (e.g., self-initiated interactions), turn-taking, sharing, reciprocity, and collaborative problem-solving. It is often contrasted to parallel play, which involves a form of social play in which two children do similar activities near each other and often mimic each other. Typically developing children develop collaborative play between the ages of 4 and 5.

HP:4000083.name: Lack of interest in peers
HP:4000083.definition: Lack of interest in peers of comparable age and social groups is evident when an individual, such as a child, shows more interest in socializing with adults rather than children their own age.

HP:4000084.name: Reduced sharing of interests
HP:4000084.definition: An absence or abnormally low frequency of engaging with others to share personal interests or topics. Interest sharing includes offers of information about oneself as a form of social interaction.

HP:4000085.name: Reduced object sharing
HP:4000085.definition: An absence or reduction in object sharing. Object sharing is an early emerging social skill in which a child will share objects such as toys, balls, or books with parents or peers during object play.

HP:4000087.name: Abnormal communicative facial expressions
HP:4000087.definition: Abnormal expressions (movements or position of muscles of the face that convey the emotional state of an individual to observers during social interactions) comprising abnormalities of quantity, range, context-appropriateness, and quality.

HP:4000088.name: Facial expressions that do not match the context
HP:4000088.definition: Production of facial expressions that are misaligned with the social context.

HP:4000089.name: Abnormal quality of facial expression
HP:4000089.definition: Spontaneous production of communicative facial expressions that have poor quality or are exaggerated or muted.

HP:4000090.name: Abnormal gesture use
HP:4000090.definition: Abnormality in the use of gestures defined as hand, shoulder, and head movements that convey a shared meaning within a culture that replace or supplement verbal communication.

HP:4000092.name: Poor conversational reciprocity
HP:4000092.definition: Reduced use of reciprocal (back and forth) conversation, as compared to what would be expected for language level.

HP:4000093.name: Ectopic tooth eruption
HP:4000093.definition: A condition in which the permanent teeth, because of deficiency of growth in the jaw or segment of jaw, assume a path of eruption that intercepts a primary tooth, causes its premature loss and produces a consequent malposition of the permanent tooth.

HP:4000094.name: Corpus cavernosum hypoplasia
HP:4000094.definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by undergrowth of the corpus cavernosum.

HP:4000095.name: Elevated circulating thymine concentration
HP:4000095.definition: Concentration of the nucleobase thymine in the blood circulation above the normal range.

HP:4000100.name: Positive lactose hydrogen breath test
HP:4000100.definition: Elevated hydrogen gas level in exhaled breath following oral administration of lactose. In individuals with lactose intolerance, undigested lactose in the colon will be metabolized by colonic bacteria, releasing hydrogen gas.

HP:4000101.name: Triggered by exposure to medication
HP:4000101.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by administration of a medication.

HP:4000102.name: Triggered by allopurinol
HP:4000102.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to allopurinol.

HP:4000103.name: Ameliorated by oral zinc supplementation
HP:4000103.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by oral zinc supplementation.

HP:4000104.name: Curved dental root
HP:4000104.definition: A root of a tooth that is more rounded than normal.

HP:4000105.name: Abnormal four chamber view of the fetal heart
HP:4000105.definition: The four-chamber (4Ch) view of the fetal heart is the most widely used screening examination for the detection of structural cardiac abnormalities during routine fetal ultrasonography. In the healthy normal fetus, the apical 4Ch view demonstrates four well-developed chambers, a concordant atrioventricular (AV) connection, unobstructed AV valves (mitral and tricuspid valves), the foramen ovale flap opening into left atrium (LA), and an intact interventricular septum. Additionally, the pulmonary venous opening can be visualized at the LA wall. Any structural deviations from normal anatomy may lead to congenital heart disease that can be determined by the 4Ch view of the fetal heart's ultrasound imaging.

HP:4000106.name: Spleen hamartoma
HP:4000106.definition: A hamartomatous lesion (benign focal lesions composed of disorganized tissue elements) localized in the spleen.

HP:4000107.name: Positive lupus band test
HP:4000107.definition: Deposits of immunoglobulins and complement components along the dermoepidermal junction.

HP:4000108.name: Bone marrow erythroid vacuolization
HP:4000108.definition: Formation of vacuoles (a space within a cell that is empty of cytoplasm, lined with a membrane, and filled with fluid) in the cytoplasm of erythroid precursors in the bone marrow.

HP:4000109.name: Triggered by electromagnetic field
HP:4000109.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to an electromagnetic field.

HP:4000110.name: Exposure history
HP:4000110.definition: Information about current and past exposure to metals, dust, fibers, fumes, chemicals, biologic hazards, radiation, noise, and/or vibration at work or home.

HP:4000111.name: Asbestos exposure
HP:4000111.definition: History of exposure to asbestos, a fibrous mineral with physical and chemical properties that make it resistant to heat and degradation.

HP:4000112.name: Medication history
HP:4000112.definition: Information about current or past medications taken by an individual.

HP:4000113.name: Aminoglycoside exposure
HP:4000113.definition: History of having taken aminoglycoside antibiotics.

HP:4000114.name: Statin exposure
HP:4000114.definition: History of having taken statins, also known as HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors.

HP:4000115.name: Potassium-sparing diuretic exposure
HP:4000115.definition: History of having taken a potassium-sparing diuretic exposure such as amiloride, eplerenone, spironolactone, and triamterene.

HP:4000117.name: Valproate exposure
HP:4000117.definition: History of having taken valproate (valproic acid).

HP:4000119.name: Calcium channel blocker exposure
HP:4000119.definition: History of having taken a calcium channel blocker such as amlodipine, nicardipine, nifedipine, verapamil, or diltiazem.

HP:4000121.name: Triggered by poison ivy, poson oak, or sumac
HP:4000121.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure (cutaneous contact) to poison ivy, poison oak, and poison sumac. These three plants each contain urushiol. Contact with these plants is the most common causes of clinically diagnosed allergic contact dermatitis.

HP:4000122.name: History of exclusive breast feeding
HP:4000122.definition: A past medical history of having been fed exclusively by breast feeding.

HP:0200017.name: Cerebral white matter agenesis
HP:0200017.definition: Congenital defect with failure of the development of the cerebral white matter.

HP:0200018.name: Protanomaly
HP:0200018.definition: A type of anomalous trichromacy associated with defective long-wavelength-sensitive (L) cones, causing the sensitivity spectrum to be shifted toward medium wavelengths. This leads to difficulties especially in distinguishing red and green.

HP:0200020.name: Corneal erosion
HP:0200020.definition: An erosion or abrasion of the cornea's outermost layer of epithelial cells.

HP:0200022.name: Choroid plexus papilloma
HP:0200022.definition: Choroid plexus papilloma is a histologically benign neoplasm located in the ventricular system of the choroid plexus.

HP:0200023.name: Priapism
HP:0200023.definition: A painful and harmful medical condition in which the erect penis doesn't return to its flaccid state, despite the absence of both physical and psychological stimulation, within four hours.

HP:0200024.name: Premature chromatid separation
HP:0200024.definition: The presence of premature sister chromatid segregation.

HP:0200025.name: Mandibular pain
HP:0200025.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the mandible.

HP:0200026.name: Ocular pain
HP:0200026.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the eye.

HP:0200028.name: Pretibial myxedema
HP:0200028.definition: A diffuse, non-pitting edema and thickening of the skin usually on the anterior aspect of the lower legs spreading to the dorsum of the feet.

HP:0200029.name: Vasculitis in the skin
HP:0200029.definition: A type of vasculitis (inflammation of blood vessel walls) that affects skeletal muscle tissue.

HP:0200032.name: Kayser-Fleischer ring
HP:0200032.definition: Grey-green or brownish-pigmented ring in the deep epithelial layers at the outer border of the cornea.

HP:0200034.name: Papule
HP:0200034.definition: A circumscribed, solid elevation of skin with no visible fluid, varying in size from a pinhead to less than 10mm in diameter at the widest point.

HP:0200035.name: Skin plaque
HP:0200035.definition: A plaque is a solid, raised, plateau-like (flat-topped) lesion greater than 1 cm in diameter.

HP:0200036.name: Skin nodule
