HP:0034015.definition: Thick-walled abnormal gas-filled interstitial nodule within a lung.

HP:0034016.name: Anti-HLA antibody positivity
HP:0034016.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen (HLA).

HP:0034017.name: Anti-class I HLA antibody positivity
HP:0034017.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a class I human leukocyte antigen (HLA). Class I HLA corresponds to MHC class I (A, B, and C).

HP:0034018.name: Anti-class II HLA antibody positivity
HP:0034018.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a class II human leukocyte antigen (HLA). Class I HLA corresponds to MHC class II (DP, DM, DO, DQ, and DR).

HP:0034019.name: Anti-HLA-A antibody positivity
HP:0034019.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen-A (HLA-A).

HP:0034020.name: Anti-HLA-A IgG1 antibody positivity
HP:0034020.definition: The presence of IgG1 autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen-A (HLA-A).

HP:0034021.name: Anti-HLA-A IgG3 antibody positivity
HP:0034021.definition: The presence of IgG3 autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen-A (HLA-A).

HP:0034022.name: Anti-HLA-B antibody positivity
HP:0034022.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen-B (HLA-B).

HP:0034023.name: Anti-HLA-B IgG1 antibody positivity
HP:0034023.definition: The presence of IgG1 autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen-B (HLA-B).

HP:0034024.name: Anti-HLA-B IgG3 antibody positivity
HP:0034024.definition: The presence of IgG3 autoantibodies in the blood circulation that react against a human leukocyte antigen-B (HLA-B).

HP:0034025.name: Abnormal circulating GABA concentration
HP:0034025.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) in the blood circulation.

HP:0034026.name: Elevated circulating saccharopine concentration
HP:0034026.definition: An increased concentration of saccharopine in the blood circulation. L-saccharopine is the N(6)-(1,3-dicarboxypropan-1-yl) derivative of L-lysine.

HP:0034027.name: Abnormal urinary non-proteinogenic amino acid level
HP:0034027.definition: Any deviation from the normal amount in the urine of an alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

HP:0034028.name: Saccharopinuria
HP:0034028.definition: Presence of saccharopine in the urine.

HP:0034029.name: Hepatic foam cells
HP:0034029.definition: The presence of foam cells, a type of macrophage that localizes to fatty deposits on blood vessel walls, in the liver.

HP:0034031.name: Facial cyanosis
HP:0034031.definition: Bluish discoloration of one or more regions of the face.

HP:0034032.name: Central cyanosis
HP:0034032.definition: Generalized bluish discoloration of the body and the visible mucous membranes, which occurs due to inadequate oxygenation secondary to conditions that lead to an increase in deoxygenated hemoglobin or presence of abnormal hemoglobin.

HP:0034033.name: Peripheral cyanosis
HP:0034033.definition: Bluish discoloration of the distal extremities in the absence of cold temperature or stress. Peripheral cyanosis can involve hands, fingertips, or toes, and sometimes circumoral and periorbital areas. Mucous membranes are generally not involved.

HP:0034034.name: Differential cyanosis
HP:0034034.definition: Differential degree of bluish discoloration between the upper and lower extremities.

HP:0034035.name: Pharyngeal exudate
HP:0034035.definition: Fluid exuded from the posterior wall of the pharynx.

HP:0034036.name: Pseudo-chilblains on toes
HP:0034036.definition: Inflammatory chilblain-like nodules on the feet and/or toes.

HP:0034037.name: Pseudo-chilblains on fingers
HP:0034037.definition: Inflammatory chilblain-like nodules on the hands and/or fingers.

HP:0034038.name: Silent hypoxemia
HP:0034038.definition: Abnormally low blood oxygen level without the presence of dyspnea.

HP:0034039.name: Ventricular couplet
HP:0034039.definition: Two consecutive premature ventricular contractions (PVCs) with no intervening normal beats.

HP:0034040.name: Bidirectional ventricular tachycardia
HP:0034040.definition: Bidirectional ventricular tachycardia (BDVT) is a regular ventricular tachyarrhythmia (VT) with two different QRS morphologies alternating at a rate typically between 140 and 180 bpm.

HP:0034042.name: Dorsal hirsutism
HP:0034042.definition: Abnormally increased hair growth in the lskin of the back.

HP:0034043.name: Increased fecal bile acid
HP:0034043.definition: Elevated amount of bile acids in the feces.

HP:0034044.name: Trident pelvis
HP:0034044.definition: Spurs at the medial and lateral acetabular margin and in the center of the acetabulum gives rise to shape resembling a three-pronged spear known as trident.

HP:0034045.name: Angulated muscle fibers
HP:0034045.definition: Normal muscle fibers are polygonal-shaped in cross section, are multinucleated, and have minimal amounts of endomysial connective tissue. In contrast, angulated (also known as angular) muscle fibers have long and narrow vertices (corners) with sharp edges and a pointed tip.

HP:0034046.name: Mandibular osteolysis
HP:0034046.definition: Osteolysis (destruction of bone through bone resorption with removal or loss of calcium) localized to the mandible.

HP:0034047.name: Rib osteolysis
HP:0034047.definition: Osteolysis (destruction of bone through bone resorption with removal or loss of calcium) localized to a rib.

HP:0034048.name: Decreased circulating chenodeoxycholic acid concentration
HP:0034048.definition: A reduced concentration of chenodeoxycholic acid in the blood circulation.

HP:0034049.name: Elevated urinary prostaglandin E2 level
HP:0034049.definition: An increased amount of prostaglandin E2 in the urine.

HP:0034050.name: Elevated urinary prostaglandin E2 metabolite level
HP:0034050.definition: An increased amount of prostaglandin E2 metabolite (PGE-M) in the urine.

HP:0034051.name: Hypoplastic anterior limbs of the internal capsule
HP:0034051.definition: Underdevelopment of the frontal part (anterior crus or anterior limb) of the internal capsule.

HP:0034052.name: Impaired toe-walking ability
HP:0034052.definition: Difficulty or reduced ability to walk on toes. Toe-walking can be tested as a part of the neurological examination. Foot plantar flexion weakness leads to difficulties in walking on toes.

HP:0034054.name: Probst bundles
HP:0034054.definition: Probst bundles (also known as longitudinal callosal fascicles) are neuroanatomical homologues to the corpus callosum and can occur in association with callosal agenesis. Probst bundles are white matter fibers that normally cross the corpus callosum but (because of the agenesis of the corpus callosum) fail to cross the midline, such that when they reach the corticoseptal boundary, they turn and run parallel to the interhemispheric fissure within the septal leaves, indenting the medial walls of the lateral ventricles.

HP:0034055.name: Anti-side-chain cleavage enzyme antibody positivity
HP:0034055.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against cytochrome P450 cholesterol side-chain cleavage enzyme (P450scc), which is encoded by CYP11A1 cytochrome P450 family 11 subfamily A member 1 (Gene ID:1583).

HP:0034056.name: Increased fecal calprotectin level
HP:0034056.definition: An increased amount of calprotectin in the feces.

HP:0034057.name: Fetal anomaly
HP:0034057.definition: Structural or functional abnormalities of the fetus. Note that this section comprises terms that describe abnormalities that are specific to the fetus or differ from the corresponding general terms. A term from anywhere in the Human Phenotype Ontology can be applied to a fetus if appropriate.

HP:0034058.name: Abnormal fetal morphology
HP:0034058.definition: Any structural anomaly of the fetus.

HP:0034059.name: Abnormal fetal physiology
HP:0034059.definition: Any functional anomaly of the fetus.

HP:0034060.name: Triggered by fava bean ingestion
HP:0034060.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by eating fava beans.

HP:0034061.name: Anti-steroid 17alpha-hydroxylase antibody positivity
HP:0034061.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against steroid 17alpha-hydroxylase.

HP:0034062.name: Anti-insulin antibody positivity
HP:0034062.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against insulin.

HP:0034063.name: Anti-islet antigen-2 antibody positivity
HP:0034063.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against tyrosine phosphatase IA-2.

HP:0034064.name: Anti-salivary protein antibody positivity
HP:0034064.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against salivary protein.

HP:0034065.name: Anti-Zinc transporter 8 antibody positivity
HP:0034065.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against zinc transporter 8.

HP:0034066.name: Anti-carbonic anhydrase VI antibody positivity
HP:0034066.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against carbonic anhydrase VI.

HP:0034067.name: Tonofilament clumping
HP:0034067.definition: Formation of lumps of tonofilaments, which are bundles of keratin filaments. In some but not all epithelia, keratin filaments are conspicuously bundled as tonofilaments. Inside the cell they braid the nucleus, span through the cytoplasm and are attached to the cytoplasmic plaques of the typical epithelial cell-cell junctions, the desmosomes.

HP:0034068.name: Anti-plasminogen binding peptide antibody positivity
HP:0034068.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against plasminogen binding peptide.

HP:0034069.name: Anti-parotid secretory protein antibody positivity
HP:0034069.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against parotid secretory protein.

HP:0034070.name: Anti-enterocyte antibody positivity
HP:0034070.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against enterocytes.

HP:0034071.name: Anti-21-hydroxylase antibody positivity
HP:0034071.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against 21-hydroxylase.

HP:0034072.name: Abnormal fetal long-bone echogenicity
HP:0034072.definition: Any deviation from the normal appearing echogenicity of the fetal bone. Echogenicity refers to the ability of tissue to reflect ultrasound waves back toward the transducer and produce an echo. Whenever there is an interface of structures with different echogenicities, a visible difference in contrast will be apparent on the screen. The higher the echogenicity of tissues, the brighter they appear on ultrasound imaging.

HP:0034073.name: Reduced fetal long bone echogenicity
HP:0034073.definition: An abnormally decreased echogenicity of fetal long bones in a prenatal sonographic investigation. This finding is due to hypomineralization and can be seen in some disorders such as hypophosphatasia, osteogenesis imperfecta, and achondrogenesis.

HP:0034074.name: Increased fetal long bone echogenicity
HP:0034074.definition: An abnormally elevated echogenicity of fetal long bones in a prenatal sonographic investigation. This finding is due to hypermineralization.

HP:0034075.name: Decreased circulating apolipoprotein B concentration
HP:0034075.definition: Reduced circulating level of apolipoprotein B, which is the main apolipoprotein of chylomicrons and low density lipoproteins. It occurs in plasma as two main isoforms, apoB-48 and apoB-100.

HP:0034076.name: Anti-ribosome Po antibody positivity
HP:0034076.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ribosome Po.

HP:0034077.name: Anti-complement component C1q antibody positivity
HP:0034077.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against C1q.

HP:0034078.name: Anti-centromere protein A antibody positivity
HP:0034078.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against CENP-A.

HP:0034079.name: Anti-centromere protein B antibody positivity
HP:0034079.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against CENP-B.

HP:0034080.name: Anti-U3 RNP antibody positivity
HP:0034080.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against U3 RNP.

HP:0034081.name: Anti-Th/To antibody positivity
HP:0034081.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Th/To.

HP:0034082.name: Anti-bicaudal D2 antibody positivity
HP:0034082.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against bicaudal D2.

HP:0034083.name: Anti-nucleolus-organizing region antibody positivity
HP:0034083.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Nor90.

HP:0034084.name: Anti-phosphatidyl ethanolamine antibody positivity
HP:0034084.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phosphatidyl ethanolamine.

HP:0034085.name: Anti-PM-Scl100 antibody positivity
HP:0034085.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against PM-Scl100.

HP:0034086.name: Anti-PM-Scl75 antibody positivity
HP:0034086.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against PM-Scl75.

HP:0034087.name: Anti-U11/U12 RNP antibody positivity
HP:0034087.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against U11/U12 RNP.

HP:0034088.name: Anti-Ku antibody positivity
HP:0034088.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ku.

HP:0034089.name: Anti-B23 antibody positivity
HP:0034089.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against B23.

HP:0034090.name: Anti-RuvBL1/2 antibody positivity
HP:0034090.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against RuvBL1/2.

HP:0034091.name: Anti-platelet derived growth factor receptor
HP:0034091.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against platelet derived growth factor receptor.

HP:0034092.name: Anti-cyclic citrullinated peptide antibody positivity
HP:0034092.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against cyclic citrullinated peptide.

HP:0034093.name: Anti-Ro52/TRIM21 antibody positivity
HP:0034093.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ro52/TRIM21.

HP:0034094.name: Anti-angiotensin receptor type-1 antibody positivity
HP:0034094.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against angiotensin receptor type-1.

HP:0034095.name: Anti-endothelin-1 type A receptor antibody positivity
HP:0034095.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against endothelin-1 type A receptor.

HP:0034096.name: Anti-phosphatidic acid antibody positivity
HP:0034096.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phosphatidic acid.

HP:0034097.name: Anti-phosphatidyl choline antibody positivity
HP:0034097.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phosphatidyl choline.

HP:0034098.name: Anti-phosphatidyl glycerol antibody positivity
HP:0034098.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phosphatidyl glycerol.

HP:0034099.name: Anti-phosphatidyl inositol antibody positivity
HP:0034099.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phosphatidyl inositol.

HP:0034100.name: Anti-phosphatidyl serine antibody positivity
HP:0034100.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phosphatidyl serine.

HP:0034101.name: Anti-annexin-V antibody positivity
HP:0034101.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against annexin-V.

HP:0034102.name: Anti-sphingolipid antibody positivity
HP:0034102.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against sphingolipids.

HP:0034103.name: Anti-GM1 antibody positivity
HP:0034103.definition: Ganglioside-monosialic acid (GM1) is a type of glycosphingolipid with one sialic acid. GM1 is located on the outer layer of the plasma membrane, and plays a vital role in neurogenesis, nerve development, differentiation and repair after injury

HP:0034104.name: Anti-neutrophil elastase antibody positivity
HP:0034104.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against neutrophil elastase.

HP:0034105.name: Anti-transcription intermediary factor-1gamma antibody positivity
HP:0034105.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against transcription intermediary factor-1gamma.

HP:0034106.name: Anti-Su antigen/argonaute 2 antibody positivity
HP:0034106.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Su antigen/argonaute 2.

HP:0034107.name: Anti-p53 antibody positivity
HP:0034107.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against p53.

HP:0034108.name: Anti-Y-box protein-1 antibody positivity
HP:0034108.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Y-box protein-1.

HP:0034109.name: Anti-GW182 antibody positivity
HP:0034109.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against GW182.

HP:0034110.name: Anti-Gerbich phenotype 1 antibody positivity
HP:0034110.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ge-1.

HP:0034111.name: Anti-MIT3 antibody positivity
HP:0034111.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against MIT3.

HP:0034112.name: Anti-GM1 IgG antibody positivity
HP:0034112.definition: The presence of IgG autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against GM1.

HP:0034113.name: obsolete Anti-type I liver-kidney microsomal antibody positivity
HP:0034113.definition: The presence of type I liver-kidney microsomal autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation.

HP:0034114.name: Anti-hexokinase-1 antibody positivity
HP:0034114.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against hexokinase-1.

HP:0034115.name: Anti-Kelch like protein 12 antibody positivity
HP:0034115.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Kelch like protein 12.

HP:0034117.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against angiotensin-converting enzyme 2.

HP:0034118.name: Anti-GM1 IgM antibody positivity
HP:0034118.definition: The presence of IgM autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against GM1.

HP:0034119.name: Anti-GD1a IgG antibody positivity
HP:0034119.definition: The presence of IgG autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside D1a.

HP:0034120.name: Anti-GD1a IgM antibody positivity
HP:0034120.definition: The presence of IgM autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside D1a.

HP:0034121.name: Anti-GD1a antibody positivity
HP:0034121.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside D1a.

HP:0034122.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside Q1b.

HP:0034123.definition: The presence of IgM autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside Q1b.

HP:0034124.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against GD1b ganglioside.

HP:0034125.definition: The presence of IgM autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against GD1b ganglioside.

HP:0034126.definition: The presence of IgG autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against GD1b ganglioside.

HP:0034127.name: Anti-GQ1b IgG antibody positivity
HP:0034127.definition: The presence of IgG autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside Q1b.

HP:0034128.name: Anti-GT1a antibody positivity
HP:0034128.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against T1a ganglioside.

HP:0034129.definition: The presence of IgM autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against T1a ganglioside.

HP:0034130.definition: The presence of IgG autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against T1a ganglioside.

HP:0034131.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against T1b ganglioside.

HP:0034132.name: Anti-GM2 antibody positivity
HP:0034132.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside GM2.

HP:0034133.name: Anti-GM3 antibody positivity
HP:0034133.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside GM3.

HP:0034134.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against ganglioside GM4.

HP:0034135.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against NF155.

HP:0034136.name: Anti-neurofascin 186 antibody positivity
HP:0034136.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against NF186.

HP:0034137.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against CNTN1.

HP:0034138.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-contactin-associated protein 1.

HP:0034139.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against SAE.

HP:0034140.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against SAE 1.

HP:0034142.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against NXP-2.

HP:0034143.name: Anti-threonyl-tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034143.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against threonyl-tRNA synthetase.

HP:0034144.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ro60.

HP:0034145.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against alanyl-tRNA synthetase.

HP:0034146.name: Anti-glycyl tRNA-synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034146.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glycyl tRNA-synthetase.

HP:0034147.name: Anti-aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034147.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against a tRNA synthetase enzyme.

HP:0034148.name: Anti-isoleucyl tRNA-synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034148.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against isoleucyl tRNA-synthetase.

HP:0034149.name: Anti-phenylalanyl tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034149.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against phenylalanyl tRNA synthetase.

HP:0034150.name: Anti-tyrosyl-tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034150.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against tyrosyl-tRNA synthetase.

HP:0034151.name: Anti-asparaginyl-tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034151.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against asparaginyl-tRNA synthetase.

HP:0034152.name: Anti-histidyl tRNA synthetase antibody positivity
HP:0034152.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against histidyl tRNA synthetase.

HP:0034153.name: Anti-cytosolic-5-nucleotidase-1A antibody positivity
HP:0034153.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against cytosolic-5-nucleotidase-1A (cN1A).

HP:0034154.name: Anti-Ki antibody positivity
HP:0034154.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ki.

HP:0034155.name: Anti-sp100 antibody positivity
HP:0034155.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against sp100. Autoantibodies causing the MND pattern are directed against sp100, sp140, promyelocytic leukemia nuclear body proteins (PML) or ubiquitin-like modifier (SUMO) proteins, while in the punctate nuclear envelope pattern, the target antigens are gp210, nucleoporin-62 or laminin B receptor proteins.

HP:0034156.name: Anti-beta-2-Glycoprotein I IgG antibody positivity
HP:0034156.definition: Presence of IgG antibodies against beta 2 glycoprotein I in the circulation. Beta-2 glycoprotein I (beta2GPI) is the principal target of autoantibodies in the antiphospholipid syndrome.

HP:0034157.name: Anti-beta-2-Glycoprotein I IgM antibody positivity
HP:0034157.definition: Presence of IgM antibodies against beta 2 glycoprotein I in the circulation. Beta-2 glycoprotein I (beta2GPI) is the principal target of autoantibodies in the antiphospholipid syndrome.

HP:0034158.name: Anti-tyrosine phosphatase region of islet antigen-2 antibody positivity
HP:0034158.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against the tyrosine phossphatase region of islet antigen 2A (this region is a specific part of IA-2). Usually IA-2A are measured using the intracellular portion of IA-2 (IA-2ic) made up of the protein tyrosine phosphatase (PTP) and juxtamembrane (JM) regions.

HP:0034159.name: Paget disease of bone
HP:0034159.definition: A localized disorder of bone remodeling. Increased numbers of larger than normal osteoclasts initiate the process at affected skeletal sites, and the increase in bone resorption is followed by an increase in new bone formation, altering bone architecture.

HP:0034160.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 9 concentration
HP:0034160.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 9 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034161.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 9 concentration
HP:0034161.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 9 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034162.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 10 concentration
HP:0034162.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 10 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034163.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 10 concentration
HP:0034163.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 10 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034164.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 21 concentration
HP:0034164.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 21 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034165.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 21 concentration
HP:0034165.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 21 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034166.name: Increased circulating interleukin 21 concentration
HP:0034166.definition: An abnormally increased concentration of interleukin 21 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034167.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 22 concentration
HP:0034167.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 22 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034168.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 22 concentration
HP:0034168.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 22 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034169.name: Increased circulating interleukin 22 concentration
HP:0034169.definition: An abnormally increased concentration of interleukin 22 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034170.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 23 concentration
HP:0034170.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 23 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034171.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 23 concentration
HP:0034171.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 23 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034172.name: Increased circulating interleukin 23 concentration
HP:0034172.definition: An abnormally increased concentration of interleukin 23 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034173.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 27 concentration
HP:0034173.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 27 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034174.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 27 concentration
HP:0034174.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 27 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034175.name: Increased circulating interleukin 27 concentration
HP:0034175.definition: An abnormally increased concentration of interleukin 27 in the blood circulation.

HP:0034176.name: Abnormal circulating interleukin 17A concentration
HP:0034176.definition: Any deviation from the normal range of the concentration of interleukin 17A in the blood circulation.

HP:0034177.name: Reduced circulating interleukin 17A concentration
HP:0034177.definition: An abnormally decreased concentration of interleukin 17A in the blood circulation.

HP:0034178.name: Increased circulating interleukin 17A concentration
HP:0034178.definition: An abnormally increased concentration of interleukin 17A in the blood circulation.

HP:0034179.name: Vertebral artery aneurysm
HP:0034179.definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of the vertebral artery .

HP:0034180.name: Fusion of the caudate and putamen
HP:0034180.definition: Abnormal joined appearance of the caudate and putamen with an absence of the anterior limb of the internal capsule.

HP:0034181.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the liver
HP:0034181.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the liver.

HP:0034182.name: Segmental hypoplasia of liver
HP:0034182.definition: Anatomically the liver is divided into right and left lobes based on the attachment of its peritoneal ligaments. This term refers to a developmental anomaly characterzied by the underdevelopment of one of the lobes of the liver. This is a rare and usually asymptomatic anomaly that can be detected incidentally on cross sectional imaging with computed tomography or magnetic resonance imaging.

HP:0034183.name: Spastic triplegia
HP:0034183.definition: Spastic weakness found in both lower extremities and one upper extremity.

HP:0034184.name: Increased insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit concentration
HP:0034184.definition: An abnormally elevated concentration of insulin like growth factor binding protein acid labile subunit level in the blood circulation.

HP:0034185.name: Median pseudocleft lip
HP:0034185.definition: A type of mild median cleft lip in which the central tubercle of the upper lip is replaced by a mucosal cleft in the midline.

HP:0034186.name: Patella alta
HP:0034186.definition: Patella alta is a patella that rides abnormally high in relation to the femur, the femoral trochlea, or the tibia, with decreased bony stability requiring increased knee flexion angles to engage the trochlea.

HP:0034187.name: Clavicular pseudarthrosis
HP:0034187.definition: A developmental defect in a the clavicule leading to bending and pathologic fracture, with inability to form a normal bony callus with subsequent fibrous nonunion, leading to the pseudarthrosis (or false joint).

HP:0034188.name: Midline liver
HP:0034188.definition: Position of the liver across the middle of the body instead of being in its normal position to the right of the stomach.

HP:0034189.name: Anti-thyroid-stimulating hormone receptor antibody positivity
HP:0034189.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against thyroid-stimulating hormone.

HP:0034190.name: Abnormal fetal cardiovascular physiology
HP:0034190.definition: Abnormal functionality of the fetal cardiovascular system.

HP:0034191.name: Elevated fetal middle cerebral artery peak systolic velocity
HP:0034191.definition: Increased peak systolic velocity of the fetal middle cerebral artery (MCA) as evaluated by Doppler ultrasound.

HP:0034192.name: Pulmonary thromboembolism
HP:0034192.definition: Pulmonary embolism is caused by emboli, which have originated from venous thrombi, traveling to and occluding the arteries of the lung.

HP:0034193.name: Stratum basale cleavage
HP:0034193.definition: Cleavage within the epidermal keratinocytes, which is the innermost layer of the epidermis and consists of proliferating cells that give rise to the outer layers of the epidermis.

HP:0034194.name: Suprabasal cleavage
HP:0034194.definition: Cleavage within the suprabasal cell layer of the epidermis, which lies directly above the basal layer and is composed of five to ten layers of cells.

HP:0034195.name: Triggered by muscle relaxant
HP:0034195.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a muscle relaxant such as suxamethonium and mivacurium.

HP:0034196.name: Ductus venosus agenesis
HP:0034196.definition: A developmental defect characterized by lack of formation of the ductus venosus (a shunt that allows oxygenated blood in the umbilical vein to bypass the liver in the fetal circulation).

HP:0034197.name: Third trimester onset
HP:0034197.definition: This term refers to a phenotypic feature that was first observed prior to birth during the third trimester, which is defined as 28 weeks and zero days (28+0) of gestation and beyond.

HP:0034198.name: Second trimester onset
HP:0034198.definition: This term refers to a phenotypic feature that was first observed prior to birth during the second trimester, which comprises the range of gestational ages from 14 0/7 weeks to 27 6/7 (inclusive).

HP:0034199.name: Late first trimester onset
HP:0034199.definition: This term refers to a phenotypic feature that was first observed prior to birth in the first trimester during the early fetal period, which is defined as 11 0/7 to 13 6/7 weeks of gestation (inclusive).

HP:0034200.name: Abnormal CSF homovanillic acid concentration
HP:0034200.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of homovanillic acid (HVA) in the cerebrospinal fluid. HVA is a metabolite of dopamine.

HP:0034201.name: Increased CSF homovanillic acid concentration
HP:0034201.definition: Elevated concentration of homovanillic acid (HVA) in the cerebrospinal fluid. HVA is a metabolite of dopamine.

HP:0034203.name: Decreased iduronate sulfatase level
HP:0034203.definition: An decreased level of iduronate-2-sulfatase activity in the blood circulation.

HP:0034204.name: Decreased circulating C1-esterase inhibitor concentration
HP:0034204.definition: Decreased concentration of C1-esterase inhibitor (C1INH) in the blood circulation.

HP:0034205.name: Iniencephaly
HP:0034205.definition: Iniencephaly is a rare neural tube defect involving dysmorphic spine and abnormal fusion of the portion of the occipital skull with the back. It results in extreme fixed head retroflexion.

HP:0034206.name: Abnormal fetal central nervous system morphology
HP:0034206.definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal central nervous system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

HP:0034207.name: Abnormal fetal gastrointestinal system morphology
HP:0034207.definition: An anomalous structural finding of the fetal gastrointestinal system. Terms in this subhierarchy are restricted to findings that can only be observed in the prenatal period. Other HPO terms can also be used to describe fetal phenotypes.

HP:0034208.name: Fetal intracranial hemorrhage
HP:0034208.definition: Abnormal bleeding inside the skull (cranium) of a fetus.

HP:0034209.name: Fetal subependymal hemorrhage
HP:0034209.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage located in the subependymal germinal matrix below the frontal horns of the lateral ventricles in the caudothalamic notch.

HP:0034210.name: Fetal intraventricular hemorrhage
HP:0034210.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage with bleeding into the ventricular system of the brain.

HP:0034211.name: Fetal cerebral parenchymal hemorrhage
HP:0034211.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage with bleeding into the parenchyma (tissue) of the brain.

HP:0034212.name: Fetal extra-axial hemorrhage
HP:0034212.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage with bleeding that occurs within the skull but outside of the brain tissue itself (into the epidural, subdural, or arachnoid space).

HP:0034213.name: Fetal posterior fossa hemorrhage
HP:0034213.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage that occurs in the posterior cranial fossa, which is the part of the cranial cavity that is located between the foramen magnum and tentorium cerebelli and contains the brainstem and cerebellum.

HP:0034214.name: Fetal intraventricular hemorrhage without ventriculomegaly
HP:0034214.definition: A type of fetal intraventricular hemorrhage characterized by clear hemorrhage spillover to the ventricles filling less than 50% of the lateral ventricle and without ventriculomegaly of greater than 15 mm in the transverse diameter of the lateral ventricular atrium.

HP:0034215.name: Fetal cerebellar hemisphere hemorrhage
HP:0034215.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage that occurs in the hemisphere of the cerebellum.

HP:0034216.name: Fetal cerebellar vermis hemorrhage
HP:0034216.definition: A type of fetal intracranial hemorrhage that occurs in the vermis of the cerebellum.

HP:0034217.name: Sonographic non-visualized fetal bladder
HP:0034217.definition: Inability to visualize the fetal bladder on targeted prenatal sonography examination. The fetal bladder can be visualized with sonography as a midline, fluid-filled structure in the pelvis as early as 10-12 weeks of gestation. The normal fetus voids at least once an hour but never completely empties the urinary bladder. The fetal bladdder should be consistently imaged after 13 weeks of gestation.

HP:0034218.name: Fetal intraventricular hemorrhage with ventriculomegaly
HP:0034218.definition: A type of fetal intraventricular hemorrhage (IVH) characterized by spillover to ventricles with flooding of 50% or more of one or both lateral ventricles accrued accompanying ventriculomegaly, but with no apparent brain parenchymal injury. This type of IVH may be defined as a diameter exceeding 15 mm in the transverse diameter of the lateral ventricular atrium as visualiuzed by prenatal sonography.

HP:0034219.name: Fetal intraventricular hemorrhage with periventricular hemorrhage
HP:0034219.definition: A type of fetal intraventricular hemorrhage that additionally includes hemorrhage in a large part of the periventricular parenchyma.

HP:0034220.name: Temporal lobe megalencephaly
HP:0034220.definition: Expansion of the temporal lobes of the brain along all axes, including rostrocaudal, superoinferior, and mediolateral, resulting in a globular appearance of the brain.

HP:0034221.name: Abnormal temporal lobe morphology
HP:0034221.definition: An abnormal structural of the zone (lobe) of the cerebral cortex that is located inferior to the lateral fissure on other cerebral hemispheres.

HP:0034222.name: Temporal lobe dysplasia
HP:0034222.definition: A developmental defect of the temporal lobe of the cerebral cortex that is characterized by prominent sulcations and radially directed gyrations.

HP:0034223.name: Elevated umbilical artery pulsatility
HP:0034223.definition: Human umbilical artery (UA) blood flow pulsatility measured by Doppler ultrasound is a widely used biomarker for the detection of elevated placental vascular resistance. Elevated UA pulsatility, which in the most extreme cases manifests as absent or even reversed end-diastolic velocity, is associated with intrauterine growth restriction (IUGR) and still-birth.

HP:0034224.name: Absent end-diastolic umbilical artery flow
HP:0034224.definition: An anomaly that is visualized by umbilical artery Doppler velocimetry. Flow in the umbilical artery should be in the forward direction in normal circumstances. This anomaly is characterized by an absence of flow in the umbilical artery at the end of diastole.

HP:0034225.name: Reversed end-diastolic umbilical artery flow
HP:0034225.definition: An anomaly that is visualized by umbilical artery Doppler velocimetry. Flow in the umbilical artery should be in the forward direction in normal circumstances. This anomaly is characterized by an reversal of flow in the umbilical artery at the end of diastole (i.e., backwards flow).

HP:0034226.name: Champagne cork sign
HP:0034226.definition: Characteristic appearance of the chest and abdomen in the sagittal view on prenatal ultrasound when the chest is small and the abdomen protruding.

HP:0034227.name: Aortic isthmus hypoplasia
HP:0034227.definition: A type of aortic arch hypoplasia whereby the isthmus (arch between the left subclavian and insertion of the patent ductus arteriosus/ligamentum arteriosum) has a diameter of less than 40% of the diameter of the ascending aorta.

HP:0034228.name: Proximal aortic arch hypoplasia
HP:0034228.definition: A type of aortic arch hypoplasia whereby the proximal aortic arch (arch proximal to the origin of the left subclavian artery) has a diameter of less than 60% of the diameter of the ascending aorta.

HP:0034229.name: Distal aortic arch hypoplasia
HP:0034229.definition: A type of aortic arch hypoplasia whereby the distal aortic arch (arch distal to the ductus arteriosus) has a diameter of less than 60% of the diameter of the ascending aorta.

HP:0034230.name: Inferior crossed fused renal ectopia
HP:0034230.definition: A type of cross fused renal ectopia characterized by fusion between the upper pole of the cross-fused ectopic kidney (located more inferiorly relative to the other kidney) and the lower pole of the other orthotopic kidney (located in a more superior position).

HP:0034231.name: Sigmoid kidney
HP:0034231.definition: A type of cross fused renal ectopia where the normal side kidney is present superiorly and the direction of pelvic is medial, the kidney which crosses positioned inferiorly with direction of pelvic toward the lateral side. As kidneys fuse after complete rotation on the vertical axis, both renal pelves lie in correct orientation.

HP:0034232.name: Unilateral lump kidney
HP:0034232.definition: A type of cross fused renal ectopia where fusion occurs over a wide margin, both renal pelves anteriorly directed and placed more inferiorly.

HP:0034233.name: Disc kidney
HP:0034233.definition: A type of cross fused renal ectopia in which kidneys fuse along their medial borders.

HP:0034234.name: L-shaped kidney
HP:0034234.definition: A type of cross fused renal ectopia in which the crossed kidney lies inferiorly and transversely, fused with the lower pole of the normal kidney.

HP:0034235.name: Superior crossed-fused renal ectopia
HP:0034235.definition: A type of cross fused renal ectopia in which the ectopic kidney lies superiorly and its lower pole fuses with the upper pole of the normal kidney. The renal pelvis of both kidneys lies anteriorly.

HP:0034236.name: Apnea of prematurity
HP:0034236.definition: Recurrent episodes of apnea occurring in infants born less than 37 weeks of gestation, defined specifically as a pause of breathing for more than 15-20 s, or accompanied by oxygen desaturation (SpO2 not more than 80% for at least 4 s) and bradycardia (heart rate less than 2/3 of baseline for at least 4 s), in infants born less than 37 weeks of gestation.

HP:0034237.name: Open neural tube defect
HP:0034237.definition: A type of neural tube defect that is not covered by skin.

HP:0034238.name: Closed neural tube defect
HP:0034238.definition: A type of neural tube defect that is covered by skin.

HP:0034239.name: Renal vein thrombosis
HP:0034239.definition: The presence of a thrombus (blood clot) in the major renal veins or its tributaries, generally leading to passive congestion that develops causes the affected kidney to swell and become engorged, leading to degeneration of nephrons and causing symptoms of flank pain, hematuria, and decreased urine output.

HP:0034240.name: Fetal neck mass
HP:0034240.definition: An abnormal growth (lump) of tissue in the neck region of a fetus. Masses may be simple cystic,, cystic with a few simple septations (fewer than three septations and less than 3-mm thick), cystic with multiple or thick septations (greater than three septations or septations 3-mm-thick or more), a mass that is than is less than 50% solid, and a mass that is 50% solid or more.

HP:0034241.name: Prenatal death
HP:0034241.definition: Death of a fetus in the uterus.

HP:0500196.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of glutamine amino acids in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0500223.definition: Abnormally increased levels of phenylalanine in cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0500240.definition: Any deviation from the normal concentration of carnosine in the cerebrospinal fluid.

HP:0500258.name: Abnormal carbon dioxide level in cord blood
HP:0500258.definition: Abnormal amount of carbon dioxide in umbilical cord blood

HP:0500259.name: Abnormal oxygen level in cord blood
HP:0500259.definition: An abnormal level of blood oxygen in the cord blood.

HP:0500260.name: Triggered by head trauma
HP:0500260.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to a head trauma.

HP:0500261.name: Triggered by anesthetics
HP:0500261.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to anesthetics.

HP:0500262.name: Atrichia
HP:0500262.definition: The most dramatic and severe form of hair loss characterized by an absence of hair follicles.

HP:0500263.name: obsolete Abnormal helper T cell proportion

HP:0500264.name: obsolete Increased helper T cell proportion

HP:0500265.name: Increased CD8+ TEMRA T cell proportion
HP:0500265.definition: An increased proportion of CD8-positive effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

HP:0500266.name: Decreased CD8+ TEMRA T cell proportion
HP:0500266.definition: An decreased proportion of CD8-positive effector memory RA TEMRA T cells compared to the total number of T cells in the blood. These cells have the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

HP:0500267.name: obsolete Abnormal proportion of CD4-positive helper T cells
HP:0500267.definition: An abnormal proportion of circulating CD4-positive helper T cells relative to total T cell count.

HP:0500269.name: Abnormal gamma-delta T cell proportion
HP:0500269.definition: Abnormal increase or decrease of TCR gamma/delta positive T cells, measured as percentage of total CD3+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0500270.name: Increased gamma-delta T cell proportion
HP:0500270.definition: Abnormal increase of TCR gamma/delta positive T cells, measured as percentage of total CD3+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0500271.name: Decreased gamma-delta T cell proportion
HP:0500271.definition: Abnormal decrease of TCR gamma/delta positive T cells, measured as percentage of total CD3+ T cells in the blood, compared to a reference range for a given sex and age-group.

HP:0500272.name: Abnormal immature gamma-delta T cell proportion
HP:0500272.definition: Abnormal proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

HP:0500273.name: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
HP:0500273.definition: Increased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

HP:0500274.name: Decreased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells
HP:0500274.definition: Decreased proportion of immature gamma-delta T cells relative to the total number of T cells.

HP:0550003.name: Proximal scleroderma
HP:0550003.definition: Symmetrical thickening, tightening and induration of the skin of the fingers and the skin proximal to the metacarpophalangeal or metatarsophalangeal joints. These changes can involve the entire limb, face, neck and trunk.

HP:0550004.name: Verruca plana
HP:0550004.definition: Slightly raised wart 2-5 mm in diameter often associated with viral infections, commonly persistent in immunodeficient individuals.

HP:0550005.name: Bilateral basilar pulmonary fibrosis
HP:0550005.definition: It is a bilateral reticular pattern of linear or lineonodular densities that are most pronounced in basilar portions of the lungs on standard chest x-ray. It is the third minor criterion for scleroderma diagnosis.

HP:3000002.name: Abnormal inner ear epithelium morphology
HP:3000002.definition: Any structural anomaly of an inner ear epithelium.

HP:3000003.name: Abnormal mandibular ramus morphology
HP:3000003.definition: An abnormality of a mandibular ramus.

HP:3000004.name: Abnormal frontalis muscle physiology
HP:3000004.definition: Abnormal function of the frontalis muscle, which covers parts of the forehead and is responsible for raising the eyebrows.

HP:3000005.name: Abnormality of masseter muscle
HP:3000005.definition: An abnormality of a masseter muscle.

HP:3000006.name: Abnormality of medial pterygoid muscle
HP:3000006.definition: An abnormality of a medial pterygoid muscle.

HP:3000007.name: Abnormality of mentalis muscle
HP:3000007.definition: An abnormality of a mentalis muscle.

HP:3000008.name: Abnormality of mylohyoid muscle
HP:3000008.definition: An abnormality of a mylohyoid muscle.

HP:3000009.name: Abnormality of nasalis muscle
HP:3000009.definition: An abnormality of a nasalis muscle.

HP:3000010.name: Abnormality of orbicularis oris muscle
HP:3000010.definition: An abnormality of an orbicularis oris muscle.

HP:3000011.name: Abnormality of palatoglossus muscle
HP:3000011.definition: An abnormality of a palatoglossus muscle.

HP:3000012.name: Abnormality of palatopharyngeus muscle
HP:3000012.definition: An abnormality of a palatopharyngeus muscle.

HP:3000013.name: Abnormal platysma muscle morphology
HP:3000013.definition: An abnormality of the platysma muscle.

HP:3000015.name: Abnormality of risorius muscle
HP:3000015.definition: An abnormality of a risorius muscle.

HP:3000016.name: Abnormality of styloglossus muscle
HP:3000016.definition: An abnormality of the styloglossus muscle.

HP:3000017.name: Abnormality of temporalis muscle
HP:3000017.definition: An abnormality of a temporalis muscle.

HP:3000018.name: Abnormality of zygomaticus major muscle
HP:3000018.definition: An abnormality of a zygomaticus major muscle.

HP:3000019.name: Abnormal buccal mucosa morphology
HP:3000019.definition: An abnormality of a buccal mucosa.

HP:3000020.name: Abnormality of zygomaticus minor muscle
HP:3000020.definition: An abnormality of a zygomaticus minor muscle.

HP:0033646.name: Absent hippocampal commissure
HP:0033646.definition: Absence of the fibers that connect the contralateral hippocampi via the crura of the fornix and run beneath the posterior portion of the corpus callosum.

HP:0033647.name: Silhouette sign
HP:0033647.definition: The silhouette sign is the absence of depiction of an anatomic soft-tissue border. It is caused by consolidation and/or atelectasis of the adjacent lung, by a large mass, or by contiguous pleural fluid. The silhouette sign results from the juxtaposition of structures of similar radiographic attenuation. The sign actually refers to the absence of a silhouette.

HP:0033648.name: Pulmonary pseudocavity
HP:0033648.definition: A pseudocavity appears as an oval or round area of low attenuation in lung nodules, masses, or areas of consolidation that represent spared parenchyma, normal or ectatic bronchi, or focal emphysema rather than cavitation. These pseudocavities usually measure less than 1 cm in diameter. They have been described in patients with adenocarcinoma, bronchioloalveolar carcinoma, and benign conditions such as infectious pneumonia.

HP:0033649.name: Paraseptal emphysema
HP:0033649.definition: Paraseptal emphysema is characterized by predominant involvement of the distal alveoli and their ducts and sacs. It is characteristically bounded by any pleural surface and the interlobular septa. This emphysema is characterized by subpleural and peribronchovascular regions of low attenuation separated by intact interlobular septa, sometimes associated with bullae.

HP:4000123.name: Nutrition history
HP:4000123.definition: A part of the past medical history consisting of information about the typical food intake of an individual.

HP:4000124.name: High dietary oxalate intake
HP:4000124.definition: A history of ingestion of a relatively high amount of foods containing high levels of oxalate, such as green-leaf vegetables, tea, nuts, chocolate and rhubarb.

HP:4000125.name: Recent honey ingestion
HP:4000125.definition: A history of ingestion of honey in recent weeks.

HP:4000126.name: Raw egg-white ingestion
HP:4000126.definition: A history of eating raw egg whites.

HP:4000127.name: Exacerbated by sodium channel blocking agent exposure
HP:4000127.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of sodium channel blocking agents such as phenytoin, carbamazepine, oxcarbazepine, lamotrigine, topiramate, and zonisamide.

HP:4000128.name: Addictive nitrous oxide use
HP:4000128.definition: Addiction to inhaled nitrous oxide gas (N2O) is a growing concern.

HP:4000129.name: Recent blood transfusion
HP:4000129.definition: A past medical history of a recent blood transfusion.

HP:4000130.name: Ameliorated by colchicine
HP:4000130.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of colchizine.

HP:4000131.name: Ameliorated by vitamin D
HP:4000131.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by administration of vitamin D.

HP:4000132.name: Exacerbated by phenytoin exposure
HP:4000132.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by administration of phenytoin.

HP:4000133.name: Triggered by angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor
HP:4000133.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is provoked or brought about by exposure to anngiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor such as benazepril, captopril, enalapril, fosinopril, and lisinopril.

HP:4000134.name: Prostaglandin E1 exposure
HP:4000134.definition: History of having been treateed with prostaglandin E1.

HP:4000135.name: 5-fluorouracil exposure
HP:4000135.definition: History of having been treated with 5-fluorouracil.

HP:4000136.name: 6-mercaptopurine exposure
HP:4000136.definition: History of having been treateed with 6-mercaptopurine.

HP:4000137.name: Isoniazid exposure
HP:4000137.definition: History of having been treateed with isoniazid.

HP:4000138.name: Absent cavum septum pellucidum
HP:4000138.definition: The cavum septum pellucidum (CSP) is an important fetal midline forebrain landmark that is normally visible by prenatal sonography. This term refers to the lack of visibility of the CSP on prenatal sonography. The CSP normally can be visualized between 18 and 37 weeks of gestation. Lack of visualization of the CSP in this time period generally requires follow up and may indicate the presence of underlying malformations such as malformations of the corpus callosum. The lack of CSP before 18 weeks or after 37 weeks of gestation (or postnatally) is considered a normal finding.

HP:4000139.name: Fetal abdominal cyst
HP:4000139.definition: Fetal abdominal cysts are usually detected during the second trimester anomaly scan or discovered incidentally at later gestations. However, a definitive diagnosis is often not made until postnatal life. The most common etiologies of fetal abdominal cysts are: ovarian, gastrointestinal cystic duplication, liver and choledochal, meconium pseudocysts, mesenteric and adrenal. Following identification of a cyst, careful morphological assessment allows the prediction of their natural history and importantly, the likelihood of surgical intervention being required postnatally.

HP:4000140.name: Fetal bowel dilatation
HP:4000140.definition: Fetal bowel dilatation is characterized by fluid-filled intestinal loops which measure at least fifteen millimeters long or seven millimeters in diameter. Ultrasonographic image of dilated fetal bowel is a sign of intestinal mechanical or functional obstruction and its prevalence will depend on the underlying condition: bowel atresia or stenosis, malrotation with volvulus, meconium ileus, total colonic aganglionosis, and meconium plug syndrome. The etiology of fetal bowel dilatation is a difficult prenatal diagnosis since ultrasound has limited accuracy for bowel evaluation.

HP:4000141.name: Left ventricular dilatation
HP:4000141.definition: Enlargement of the chamber of the left heart ventricle.

HP:4000142.name: Fetal trigonocephaly
HP:4000142.definition: A fetal ultrasound finding defined by flattening of the occiput with pointing of the frontal bones and brachycephaly with an increased cephalic index. It is characterized by keel shaped deformity of forehead with midline ridge, bilateral fronto temporal constriction with compensatory biparietal expansion, supra orbital and lateral orbital retrusion and hypotelorism. This finding is said to resemble a strawberry.

HP:4000143.name: Abnormal fetal heart outflow tract
HP:4000143.definition: A prenatal anomaly of the outflow tract. Fetal ultrasound may not always be able to easily and accurately describe the outflow anomaly, but can detect abnormal anatomy. Often, follow up with a fetal echo is recommended, but fetal ultrasound is limited.

HP:4000144.name: Recent past medical history
HP:4000144.definition: History of events that precede the current presenting condition and are thought to be of potential relevance, having occurred in the hours, days, or weeks before the current condition.

HP:4000145.name: History of recent viral illness
HP:4000145.definition: Medical history of a viral illness in recent weeks.

HP:4000146.name: History of recent dental procedure
HP:4000146.definition: Medical history of a dental procedure in recent weeks.

HP:4000147.name: Abnormal hepatic artery morphology
HP:4000147.definition: Any structural anomaly of the hepatic artery or its branches.

HP:4000148.name: Hepatic artery hyperplasia
HP:4000148.definition: Abnormal increase in size of the hepatic arteries.

HP:4000149.name: Lymph node necrosis
HP:4000149.definition: Areas of necrotic tissue within a lymph node.

HP:4000150.name: Multinucleated neuron
HP:4000150.definition: Neurons that contain more than one nucleus.

HP:4000151.name: History of recent contralateral injury
HP:4000151.definition: A history of an injury that occurred several hours, days, or weeks before the current presenting complaint and is located on the other side of the body relative to the current presenting complaint.

HP:4000152.name: Alternating laterality
HP:4000152.definition: Occurring on the left and right in succession. This term can refer to alternating sides of the body (e.g., Alternating hemiplegia) or alternative sides of the visual field (e.g., some migraine auras).

HP:4000153.name: Cervical squamous cell papilloma
HP:4000153.definition: A benign tumor arising from the epithelial surface of the cervix and usually caused by Human Papillomavirus infection.

HP:4000154.name: Liver leiomyoma
HP:4000154.definition: A benign smooth muscle neoplasm that arises in the liver.

HP:4000158.name: Typified by high penetrance
HP:4000158.definition: Description of conditions in which only an incomplete but relatively high proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for incomplete, but high penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least 80 percent but less than 100 percent of individuals with the given genotype would manifest the disease with a full lifespan.

HP:4000159.name: Typified by moderate penetrance
HP:4000159.definition: Description of conditions in which only a moderate proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for moderate penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least 20 percent but less than 80 percent of individuals with the given genotype would manifest the disease with a full lifespan.

HP:4000160.name: Typified by low penetrance
HP:4000160.definition: Description of conditions in which only a low proportion of individuals with a given genotype exhibit the disease regardless of age assuming a full lifespan of 80 years. There is no commonly accepted definition for low penetrance, but we suggest that this term be applied if at least some but less than 20 percent of carriers would manifest the disease with a full lifespan.

HP:4000162.name: Decreased Succinyl-CoA 3-ketoacid CoA transferase activity
HP:4000162.definition: Decreased activity of the enzyme succinyl-CoA 3-ketoacid CoA transferase.

HP:4000163.name: Reduced phytanic acid oxidase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000163.definition: Activity of the enzyme phytanoyl-CoA hydroxylase (PhyH; EC 1.14.11.18) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts. PhyH plays a role in the catabolism of phytanic acid, a branched-chain fatty acid that is a normal constituent of the human diet.

HP:4000164.name: Reduced bifunctional protein activity
HP:4000164.definition: Diminished activity of hydroxysteroid 17-beta dehydrogenase 4 (HSD17B4), also known as D-bifunctional protein (DBP), a peroxisomal enzyme that catalyzes multiple steps of beta-oxidation of very long chain fatty acids.

HP:4000165.name: Decreased circulating plasmalogen concentration
HP:4000165.definition: Reduced plasmalogen concentration in the blood circulation.

HP:4000166.name: Post-vaccination varicella zoster virus infection
HP:4000166.definition: Infection with live, attenuated varicella-zoster virus following vaccination. This is an extremely rare event that may indicate immunocompromise.

HP:4000167.name: Recent steroid exposure
HP:4000167.definition: History of having been treated with corticosteroid medications in recent weeks.

HP:4000168.name: Shark teeth
HP:4000168.definition: Eruption of permanent teeth behind deciduous (baby) teeth before they have fallen out, resulting in a double row of teeth. This phenomen is typically observed between the ages of 5 to 7 years.

HP:4000169.name: Pontine T2 hypointensity
HP:4000169.definition: A darker than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the pons.

HP:4000170.name: Anti-platelet antigen antibody positivity
HP:4000170.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against antigens present on the surface of thrombocytes such as the glycoproteins GPIIb/IIIa, GPIb/IX, and GPIa/IIa.

HP:4000171.name: Anti-voltage-gated potassium channel antibody positivity
HP:4000171.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum that react against a voltage-gated potassium channel.

HP:4000172.name: Vegan diet
HP:4000172.definition: A history of following a vegan diet characterized by avoidance of food sourced from animals including meat, fish, and dairy products.

HP:4000173.name: History of previous pregnancy with hydrops fetalis
HP:4000173.definition: One or more previous pregnancies in which the fetus developed hydrops fetalis.

HP:4000174.name: Ameliorated by potassium supplements
HP:4000174.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingesting a potassium supplement.

HP:4000175.name: Ameliorated by niacin
HP:4000175.definition: Applies to a sign or symptom that is improved or made more bearable by ingesting niacin (vitamin B3).

HP:4000176.name: Aggravated by exposure to medication
HP:4000176.definition: Applied to a sign or symptom that is worsened by treatment with a medication.

HP:4000177.name: Bleeding ameliorated by vitamin K
HP:4000177.definition: Applies to bleeding that is significantly reduced by treatment with vitamin K.

HP:4000178.name: Anti-retroviral therapy exposure
HP:4000178.definition: History of having been treated with an antiretroviral agent.

HP:4000179.name: Potassium-wasting diuretic exposure
HP:4000179.definition: History of having been treated with a potassium-wasting diuretic such as thiazide (chlorothiazide, chlorthalidone, hydrochlorothiazide, indapamide, metolazone) and loop (bumetanide, ethacrynic acid, furosemide, torsemide) diuretics.

HP:4000180.name: Tricyclic antidepressant exposure
HP:4000180.definition: History of having been treated with a tricyclic antidepressant medication.

HP:4000181.name: Excessive dental attrition
HP:4000181.definition: A higher than expected amount of attrition of teeth, as menifested by loss of tooth characteristics including rounding or sharpening of incisal edges, loss of cusps, and fracturing of teeth, to an extent that is deemed more than would be expected at a given age.

HP:4000182.name: Positionally dependent pain
HP:4000182.definition: Pain improves or worsens with changes in body position.

HP:4000183.name: Abnormal erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
HP:4000183.definition: Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) outside of the normal range.

HP:4000184.name: Reduced erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
HP:4000184.definition: Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) below the lower limit of normal.

HP:4000186.name: Elevated erythrocyte adenosine triphosphate concentration
HP:4000186.definition: Concentration of adenosine triphosphate (ATP) in red blood cells (erythrocytes) above the upper limit of normal.

HP:4000187.name: Spermatogonial maturation arrest
HP:4000187.definition: A type of spermatogenesis maturation arrest in which the block of developmental occurs in the spermatogonial stage. Testicular histology shows seminiferous tubules with Sertoli cells and spermatogonial cells but no further differentiated cells like spermatocytes or round spermatids.

HP:4000189.name: Elevated circulating neuron-specific enolase concentration
HP:4000189.definition: Concentration of neuron-specific enolase above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:4000190.name: Reduced leukocyte alpha-mannosidase activity
HP:4000190.definition: Concentration or activity of an alpha-mannosidase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

HP:4000191.name: Increased circulating alpha-mannosidase activity
HP:4000191.definition: Concentration or activity of alpha mannosidase above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:4000192.name: Reduced leukocyte cathepsin D activity
HP:4000192.definition: Concentration or activity of cathepsin D as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal. The reduction in cathepsin D activity can also be measured in fibroblasts.

HP:4000193.name: Reduced leukocyte N-sulfoglucosamine sulfohydrolase activity
HP:4000193.definition: Concentration or activity of N-sulfoglucosamine sulfohydrolase as measured in leukocytes is below the limits of normal.

HP:4000194.name: Pseudohyperkalemia
HP:4000194.definition: Pseudohyperkalemia describes a falsely elevated potassium level upon measurement of the serum electrolyte concentration due to disruption of cells during the collection or processing of the sample.

HP:4000195.name: Abnormal enzyme activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000195.definition: Concentration or activity of an enzyme is above or below the limits of normal in cultured fibroblasts. Fibroblasts are easy to grow in culture and are the main cell type involved in producing extracellular matrix. They are used as a convenient model system for measuring enzyme activity for enzymes that are not expressed in blood cells. Usually, the test is done in fibroblasts for convenience rather than for the investigation of a pathophysiology specific to fibroblasts.

HP:4000196.name: Reduced heparan-alpha-glucosaminide N-acetyltransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000196.definition: Concentration or activity of N-sulfoglucosamine sulfohydrolase as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

HP:4000197.name: Reduced N-acetylgalactosamine-6-sulfatase in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000197.definition: Concentration or activity of N-acetylgalactosamine-6-sulfatase as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

HP:4000198.name: Reduced acetylglucosamine-6-sulfatase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000198.definition: Concentration or activity of N-acetylglucosamine-6-sulfatase (EC 3.1.6.14) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. N-acetylglucosamine-6-sulfatase hydrolyzes heparan sulfate and keratan sulfate.

HP:4000199.name: Reduced erythrocyte porphobilinogen deaminase activity
HP:4000199.definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of porphobilinogen deaminase (EC 4.3.1.8) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

HP:4000200.name: Reduced holocarboxylase synthetase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000200.definition: Concentration or activity of holocarboxylase synthetase (EC 6.3.4.10) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

HP:4000201.name: Abnormal circulating alpha mannosidase activity
HP:4000201.definition: Concentration or activity of alpha mannosidase outside of the limits of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:4000202.name: Reduced tissue alpha-N-acetylgalactosaminidase activity
HP:4000202.definition: Concentration or activity of alpha-N-acetylgalactosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.49) is below the limits of normal. The activity can be measured in multiple tissues including cultured fibroblasts.

HP:4000203.name: Reduced erythrocyte arginase activity
HP:4000203.definition: Activity or concentration of arginase (EC 3.5.3.1) in red blood cells below the lower limit of normal. Arginase catalyzes the last step of the urea cycle.

HP:4000204.name: Reduced mitochondrial acetyl-CoA acetyltransferase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000204.definition: Concentration or activity of mitochondrial acetyl-CoA acetyltransferase (EC 2.3.1.9) as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal.

HP:4000205.name: Reduced tissue beta-mannosidase activity
HP:4000205.definition: Concentration or activity of beta-mannosidase (EC 3.2.1.25) below the lower limit of normal. Beta-mannosidas enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

HP:4000206.name: Reduced 3-methylcrotonyl CoA carboxylase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000206.definition: Activity of 3-methylcrotonyl-CoA carboxylase (EC 6.4.1.4) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

HP:4000207.name: Reduced branched-chain alpha-keto acid dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000207.definition: Activity of branched-chain alpha-keto acid dehydrogenase complex (EC 1.2.4.4) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

HP:4000208.name: Reduced erythrocyte galactose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase activity
HP:4000208.definition: Activity or concentration of in the level of galactose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase (GALT; EC 2.7.7.12) in erythrocytes below the lower limit of normal.

HP:4000209.name: Abnormal erythrocyte adenosine deaminase activity
HP:4000209.definition: Activity of adenosine deaminase in red blood cells outside the limits of normal.

HP:4000210.name: Reduced isovaleryl CoA dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000210.definition: Activity of isovaleryl-CoA dehydrogenase (EC 1.3.99.10) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

HP:4000211.name: Reduced glycerol kinase activity in cultured fibroblasts
HP:4000211.definition: Activity of glycerol kinase (EC 2.7.1.30) below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.

HP:4000212.name: Increased circulating vitamin A concentration
HP:4000212.definition: Concentration of vitamin A above the upper limit of normal in the blood circulation.

HP:4000213.name: Elevated circulating hyaluronic acid concentration
HP:4000213.definition: Concentration of hyaluronic acid in the blood circulation above the upper limit of normal.

HP:4000214.name: Diminished breath sounds
HP:4000214.definition: A reduction in the intensity of the breath sound as ascertained by auscultation of the lung.

HP:5000000.name: Anti-AK5 antibody positivity
HP:5000000.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-adenylate kinase 5 (AK5).

HP:5000001.name: Anti-AMPAR antibody positivity
HP:5000001.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against anti-alpha-amino-3-hydroxy-5-methyl-4-isoxazolepropionic acid receptor (AMPAR).

HP:5000002.name: Anti-Amphiphysin antibody
HP:5000002.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Amphiphysin.

HP:5000003.name: Anti-ARHGAP26 antibody
HP:5000003.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Rho GTPase-activating protein 26 (ARHGAP26).

HP:5000004.name: Anti-CARP VIII antibody
HP:5000004.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Carbonic anhydrase-related protein VIII (CARPVIII).

HP:5000005.name: Anti-CASPR2
HP:5000005.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against contactin-associated protein-like 2 (CASPR2).

HP:5000006.name: Anti-CV2/CRMP5 antibody positivity
HP:5000006.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against CV2/CRMP5. Anti-CV2/CRMP5 autoantibody is the most commonly detected anti-neuronal autoantibody. Patients with typical paraneoplastic chorea show fully developed chorea in the course of weeks to months with acute inflammation in the striatum.

HP:5000007.name: Anti-DPPX antibody
HP:5000007.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against dipeptidyl-peptidase-like protein 6 (DPPX).

HP:5000008.name: Anti-FGFR3 antibody positivity
HP:5000008.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against FGFR3.

HP:5000009.name: Anti-GABA(A)R antibody
HP:5000009.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against gamma-aminobutyric acid A receptor, i.e., GABA(A)R.

HP:5000010.name: Anti-GABA(B)R antibody
HP:5000010.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against gamma-aminobutyric acid B receptor, i.e., GABA(B)R.

HP:5000011.name: Anti-GAD65 antibody
HP:5000011.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glutamic acid decarboxylase 65 (GAD65).

HP:5000012.name: Anti-Gephyrin antibody
HP:5000012.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Gephyrin.

HP:5000013.name: Anti-GFAP antibody
HP:5000013.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against glial fibrillary acidic protein (GFAP).

HP:5000014.name: Anti-GlyR antibody
HP:5000014.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Glycine receptor (GlyR).

HP:5000015.name: Anti-Homer-3 antibody
HP:5000015.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Homer-3.

HP:5000016.name: Anti-Hu antibody positivity
HP:5000016.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Hu.

HP:5000017.name: Anti-Iglon5 antibody
HP:5000017.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against immunoglobulin-like cell adhesion molecule 5 (IgLON5).

HP:5000018.name: Anti-ITPR1 antibody
HP:5000018.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate receptor 1 (ITPR1).

HP:5000019.name: Anti-Kelch like protein 11 antibody positivity
HP:5000019.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against kelch-like protein 11 (KLHL11).

HP:5000020.name: Anti-LGI1 antibody
HP:5000020.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against leucine-rich glioma-inactivated 1 (LGI1).

HP:5000021.name: Anti-Ma antibody positivity
HP:5000021.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma.

HP:5000022.name: Anti-Ma2 antibody positivity
HP:5000022.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma2.

HP:5000023.name: Anti-Ma1 antibody positivity
HP:5000023.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against Ma1.

HP:5000024.name: Anti-mGluR1 antibody
HP:5000024.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against metabotropic glutamate receptor 1 (mGluR1).

HP:5000025.name: Anti-mGluR5 antibody
HP:5000025.definition: The presence of autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the blood circulation that react against metabotropic glutamate receptor 5 (mGluR5).

HP:5000026.name: Anti-neurexin-3alpha antibody positivity
